If you are reading this, you probably already know that Polestar is an electric performance car brand. We work hard to create a unique experience for the customer, owner, and driver. The thrill of driving the car, the digital experience of buying, owning, and controlling a Polestar require us to push the limits of technology and software development. Sustainability has been there from the beginning and we have set a moonshot goal for climate-neutral cars in 2030. There is an ocean of opportunities in this for talented IT professionals who want to dive in and make a difference.
The Role
A Cloud Software Architect at Polestar helps the long-term vision of cloud and software architecture and acts as a decision-maker in high-level design choices and technical standards, such as platforms and coding standards. This role will be part of the Technical Standards team. Working in that group means, among other tasks, setting the guardrails for software development and architecture in the product teams, as well as helping domain- and solution architects to build the best possible software solutions. The Cloud Architect is both a visionary and hands-on practitioner in regard to cloud technology and its usage at Polestar. In short, you will:

Set the standards for software development and ensure that the guardrails are followed by close interactions with the different development teams.
Ensure guardrails include quality, security and privacy aspects in collaboration with the Information Security team.
Maintain close relationships with key cloud partners (including AWS, Microsoft, Google and Cloudflare) together with the technical lead of the cloud platform, to maximize the value of the cloud platforms over time.
Coach and help the development teams and other areas of the business to deliver the best possible software.
Who you are
In order to thrive as our new Cloud Software Architect, we believe that you are comfortable with full-stack development and modern programming principles, perhaps even in product-led digital organizations. You probably have great knowledge of software architecture frameworks and design patterns needed for developing effective code, as well as experience in microservices such as AWS stack and tooling. Knowledge in Software Lifecycle Management and QA practices is considered a great plus as well. Specifically, we believe your experience includes the following:

Hands-on cloud architecture experience, ideally with infrastructure-as-code tools such as Terraform, CloudFormation, CDK or similar. We use AWS most extensively, but also run workloads in Azure and Google Cloud Platform.
Experience with serverless technologies such as AWS Lambda, including thorough understanding of the benefits and drawbacks of such approaches.
Hands-on development experience with either native or web-to-native tooling and frameworks.
Experience with reactive JavaScript frameworks and libraries, such as React, Angular, etc.
Using a variety of API styles and messaging patterns in distributed systems, e.g., REST, gRPC, GraphQL, pub/sub, request/reply.
Diverse experience in relational and NoSQL database technologies, e.g., MySQL, MongoDB, etc.
Application monitoring and observability.
Test-driven development and domain-driven design.
Development in cross-functional agile teams, and ideally practical experience of team leadership.
Personal Qualities
Specific experience is all good and well, but it’s important to state that we’re looking for a colleague who can grow with the company, drive us forward and ultimately enjoy working together with our amazing team. Polestar is a fast-growing company, taking on the world with innovative ideas and new ways of thinking. To thrive, you shouldn’t be afraid to take space, work creatively and engage your colleagues by initiating new processes and practices. In short, you probably:

Possess strong communication skills with the ability to align the organization on complex technical decisions
Enjoy acting as a coach and mentor with the goal to grow and maximize your team’s potential
Are excited about trying new solutions outside standard approved practices
Embrace a culture of trust and complete transparency
Promote free thought and feel energized by ideas from others
Are brave and rebellious, willing to challenge the status quo
Are a learner and teacher, not stopping at what you know today and what you can teach others right now
People at Polestar
We know that a change is needed. We also know that each one of us can help bring about that change. Our commitment to becoming climate-neutral by 2040 is just as important to us as being inclusive, diverse, and innovative. Together, we are creating, collaborating and experimenting to usher in a new era of sustainable mobility.
We are an electric performance brand, determined to improve the society we live in.
Is this you? If you are interested in joining the Polestar family, don't wait with submitting your application. We apply a continuous selection process and the job post will be open until the position is filled.
Are you ready for the journey? Which is electric by the way...

column1: CloudBackend, Sveriges nästa tech-under, söker senior C++-utvecklare!
column4:
”Det här är en unik chans att vara med och bygga en global, revolutionerande tjänst. De tekniska utmaningar vi har löst anses allmänt vara omöjliga att lösa; men det är vad vi gör. Vi löser det omöjliga, varje dag. Vårt team står bakom två av cloud-marknadens mest kända varumärken och vi vet att CloudBackend kommer bli det tredje.” 
     
   
  
  
   
  
   Daniel Arthursson
  
  
  
    Senior C++-utvecklare med produktfokus 
    
  
  
   CloudBackend står i begrepp att lansera en revolutionerande ny databastjänst, en ”Edge Database Platform as a Service” (Edge dbPaaS). Tjänsten gör utvecklare signifikant mer produktiva, då alla utmaningar med att utveckla och hantera API:er för molndatabaser är lösta från start. Samtidigt är all data synkad med alla uppkopplade enheter och noder, för att därigenom ytterligare förenkla applikationsutvecklingen. Detta möjliggör för front-end-utvecklare att bygga en komplett applikationslösning och därigenom bli full-stack-utvecklare.
  
  
  
    Detta är en revolutionerande teknologi för utvecklare inom såväl web och mobil-applikationer som IoT-applikationer. Det är en nyckelteknologi för att möjliggöra decentralisering av data, edge-computing och teknikskiftet till databaser som en tjänst, istället för att manuellt installera och köra databaser på ett moln.
    
  
  
    Produktlanseringen är beräknad till slutet av Q2 2022, varför vi nu behöver fler duktiga utvecklare till vårt team. Vi har en väldigt ambitiös och spännande utvecklingsplan och vi räknar även med att få in omfattande feedback och önskemål från kunder och användare efter lanseringen.
  
  
  
    Vårt mål är att bygga en tjänst från Linköping som används av miljoner utvecklare över hela världen. Vi är övertygade om att det finns en möjlighet för vår dbPaaS att etableras på en marknad som idag domineras av bolag som AWS, Azure och Google Cloud – medan dessa bolag samtidigt är leverantörer till oss och presumtiva återförsäljare av vår tjänst. I och med skiftet till decentralisering och edge-computing finns det en möjlighet för nya aktörer som CloudBackend att komma med innovativa tjänster.
  
  
  
    DINA ARBETSUPPGIFTER
    
  
  
    Som senior C++ utvecklare på CloudBackend kommer du ingå i SCRUM-teamet och arbeta för att realisera bolagets product roadmap och driva utveckling av densamma. Det är ett innovativt arbete fokuserat på produktutveckling av företagets egna databastjänst. Du blir en viktig del av företaget och kommer vara en nyckeldel i utvecklingen av nya lösningar och arkitekturer.
  
  
  
    Tjänsten är en unik möjlighet att få vara en del av att skapa en ny svensk unicorn, varför vi erbjuder våra medarbetare möjlighet att köpa optioner i bolaget. Teamet bakom CloudBackend har tidigare uppfunnit, utvecklat och lanserat iCloud samt skapat varumärket MyCloud. Efter skapandet av två av världens mest kända moln-varumärken, är det nu dags att skapa ett tredje och vi söker efter medarbetare som vill vara med på den spännande resan.
  
  
  
    Ansvarsområden:
    
  
  
   Fokus kommer ligga på arkitektur och utveckling av de decentraliserade edge-noderna, inklusive utveckling av det decentraliserade datalagret.
   Programmering i C++ och vara en del av ett distribuerat SCRUM-team.
   Delaktighet i arkitekturfrågor och möjlighet att specificera tekniska lösningar
   Utveckla ”stateless micro services APIs” samt daemons.
   Utrullning av kod genom Docker och Kubernetes
   Hjälpa juniora medarbetare att utvecklas och agera mentor
  
  
  
    Ditt blivande team förväntas bestå av 20 kollegor innan årets slut. Nu har du chansen att vara med på starten av något som kommer göra skillnad!
  
  
  
    OM FÖRETAGET
    
  
  
    CloudBackends Database Platform as a Service är en decentraliserad, policy-driven databas som minskar svarstider genom att lagra data i molnet, i edgen och på enheter distribuerat. Tjänsten är helt unik och lanseras under 2022, med avsikt att nå miljontals användare världen över.
  
  
  
    Med CloudBackend kan en startup eller apputvecklare lansera en global tjänst med prestanda över hela världen som uppfyller alla lokala datalagringsdirektiv, utan att det krävs en enorm utvecklingsinsats. App- och webbutvecklare som normalt lägger mycket tid på datahantering mellan klienter och backend kan istället lägga tiden på att förbättra användarupplevelse och funktionalitet. CloudBackends kunder kan helt enkelt lansera bättre lösningar snabbare, med mindre resurser, där de slipper tråkig ”data plumbing”, synkning av data, eller drift av utspridda databaser i molnet.
  
  
  
    Teamet är virtuellt och fördelat över Sverige och Kanada.
  
  
  
    DIN PROFIL
    
  
  
    Vi söker utvecklare som vill bygga något unikt som kommer påverka och användas av miljoner människor över hela världen. Utvecklare som bryr sig om kvalitet och som känner yrkesstolthet över den kod och arkitektur de skapar. Vi söker helt enkelt medarbetare som vill ha ett jobb där de kan göra skillnad och som känner ansvar för att hitta den bästa lösningen. Du brinner för att skriva bra kod och att lösa programmeringsproblem.
    
  
  
    Det är meriterande med hobbyprojekt och egna projekt som du byggt.
    
  
  
    Tjänsten kräver säkerhetsprövning med bakgrundskontroll och säkerhetssamtal, då positionen kan komma att lyda under säkerhetsskyddslagen.
  
  
  
    Krav:
    
  
  
   Eftergymnasial utbildning inom programmering
   Flytande i Svenska samt Engelska (tal och skrift)
   Flerårig erfarenhet av C++
   Goda kunskaper om objektorientering
   Kunskap om GIT, SQL, REST eller SOAP API och Linux
   Svensk medborgare
  
  
  
    Meriterande:
    
  
  
   Kunskaper inom; SCRUM, JSON, XML, Docker, Kubernetes, Hadoop/MapR, Molnarkitektur, distribuerade nätverk, Python, Ruby, automatiserad testning, Shell script, ledarskap av utvecklare i grupp.
  
  
  
    OM FRAMTIDEN
    
  
  
    Framtiden arbetar med både bemanning och rekrytering, vi vill göra skillnad i människors liv. Skillnad gör vi genom att hjälpa människor att hitta rätt jobb och rätt kollega. Vi är specialister på att rekrytera rätt talanger till rätt företag. Framtiden finns på sju orter i Sverige samt i Oslo.
  
  
  
    Den här tjänsten är en direktrekrytering, du kommer bli anställd direkt av CloudBackend, Framtiden AB ansvarar för rekryteringen.
  
  
  
    VILLKOR
    
  
  
    Startdatum: Omgående, efter överenskommelse
    
  
  
    Placeringsort: Linköping (arbete på distans eller från kontoret)
    
  
  
    Arbetstider: 8 timmar per dag. Flex med tillgänglighet 10:00 – 16:00
    
  
  
    Omfattning: Heltid, Tillsvidare
  
 
  Bransch 
   
    IT/Teknik 
   
  Rekryterare 
   
    Robin Hermansson 
   
  E-post 
   
    robin.hermansson@framtiden.com 
   
  Postnummer 
   
    580 02 
   
  Län 
   
    Östergötland County 
   
  Land 
   
    Sweden 
   
  Stad 
   
    Linköping

Vilka är vi
ted&gustaf startades 2010 för att skapa en digital fullservicebyrå med fokus på kvalité, innovation och personlig utveckling. Medvetet har vi bibehållit en mindre bolagsstorlek för att prioritera lagkänsla och gemenskap i ett team där kvalitet går före kvantitet.
Vi hjälper företag att lyckas med digitala satsningar och det gör vi genom att vara experter på webbteknik, digital strategi, ux, design och analys.
Vi har startat en tillväxtresa och söker nu nya kollegor som vill vidareutveckla sig själva, tekniken och våra kunder. Vi har en snabbt förändrande och spännande tid framför oss och hoppas att du vill vara med.
Vad gör du som CMS-utvecklare
Som CMS-utvecklare hos ted&gustaf har du mycket frihet att skapa din egen roll och arbete. Det viktigaste är att vi tillsammans förverkligar våra kunders affärsidéer genom att på ett innovativt sätt undanröja tekniska hinder. Vi jobbar med alltifrån databaslagret ända fram till finjusteringar i SASS, så oavsett var i stacken du känner dig bekväm så finns det möjligheter att bidra och utvecklas.
Som en av våra CMS-utvecklare kommer du t.ex.:
Skriva en lättläst, testbar och välstrukturerad kod i Episerver
Skapa en förståelse för kundens behov tillsammans med dina teammedlemmar
Jobba brett med alltifrån utveckling och testning till infrastruktur och deployment
Bidra till teamet och organisationen genom kunskapsdelning och feedback
Aktivt ta till dig nya tekniker och arbetssätt
Vår techstack varierar sig beroende på vilken kund vi arbetar med men kan typiskt innehålla:
ASP.NET/.NET Core/Node.js
TypeScript/SASS/Webpack
React/Angular/Aurelia
Azure
SQL Server/Cosmos DB
Vem är du
Troligtvis har du några års erfarenhet inom webbutveckling i Episerver och har god förståelse för både frontend och backend. Du tycker om att driva ditt eget arbete och projekt framåt samtidigt som du förstår vikten av att vara lyhörd för kund och teammedlemmar. Du förstår vikten av att arbeta effektivt samt att hela tiden söka ny kunskap för att hitta nya kreativa lösningar.
Du har vana att arbeta med varierande uppgifter samt använda dig av:
ASP.NET/.NET Core - C
JavaScript (ECMAScript 6+)/TypeScript
HTML5/CSS3/SASS
Azure
Vad tänker du?
Ifall du vill vara en del av ett innovativt, ständigt utvecklandes team som ser kodande som ett hantverk snarare än bara ett jobb samt vill hjälpa till att förverkliga de kundprojekt andra byråer inte klarar av, skicka oss dina kontaktuppgifter genom knappen nedan så tar vi det därifrån!

Content designers at Facebook craft simple, straightforward and human experiences by leveraging our expertise in user experience design, design thinking, product strategy and writing. Come join our team to create and shape great, intuitive products and services used by billions of people around the world every day.You’ll be expected to design and deliver product flows, new features, in-product messaging, content frameworks, navigation, product naming and more for all platforms, including mobile, desktop, AR/VR, hardware and voice. The Facebook Content Design team is one of the largest and most established in the world, and includes people at various stages in their careers.


Content Designer Responsibilities:

Design, write, edit, test and improve content that makes our products easier to use. This includes product flows, interface language, education materials, product names, navigational nomenclature, terminology, taxonomies and other content across Facebook products and experiences.
Give and solicit feedback from your UX design peers in service of building the best products.
Contribute to projects in ways that enhance the clarity and usability of product experiences.
Identify problems you can help solve and deliver on them.
Edit and contribute to designs and content in Figma, Sketch or other design tools.
Collaborate daily with peers across disciplines, including engineering, design, research, marketing and data science.
Partner with our internationalization and localization teams to ensure product experiences are of the highest quality in every language.


Minimum Qualifications:

1+ years’ experience writing and designing content for web or mobile.
Adept at simplifying and communicating complex ideas to broad audiences.
Familiar with content tooling and/or front-end programming.
Proven systems thinking, with aptitude for learning our technical systems.
UX writing and communication experience.

column1: Continuous Integration Machine Developer for Baseband SW products
column4:

We are looking for a CI Machine Developer to evolve our CI tools and services towards Cloud Native world-class development environment. The CI machinery integrates base station functionality for the baseband products from thousands of baseband SW developers every day.

You will
Create stable and reliable BB SW CI Machinery using Ericsson standard Engineering Environment solutions and tools together with Open Source technologies.
Contribute to the journey of transformation from the legacy environment towards Cloud environment and methodology.

Work in a local team in Lund as well as with a global team around the world with highly skilled developers and architechts.

A Master of Science degree in Software Engineering, Computer Science, Electrical or Electronic Engineering, Applied Physics or equivalent.
Shown experience in working with Continuous Integration and Cloud tools, methods and environment.
Proficiency in Pearl, Bash, or Python as well as NodeJS or GoLang programming languages.
Good knowledge of Kubernetes, Docker and Microservices technologies.
A forward-thinking, hardworking and creative personality. You are an outstanding teammate who enjoys a fast-paced work environment and embraces challenges.
Love for multicultural environment and appetite for cutting-edge technology.
In addition, we value knowledge and experience in frontend development for web pages and web services using REACT and other similar technologies.

Why join Ericsson?
At Ericsson, you´ll have an outstanding opportunity. The chance to use your skills and imagination to push the boundaries of what´s possible. To build never seen before solutions to some of the world’s toughest problems. You´ll be challenged, but you won’t be alone. You´ll be joining a team of diverse innovators, all driven to go beyond the status quo to craft what comes next

Click Here to find all you need to know about what our typical hiring process looks like.
Encouraging a diverse and inclusive organization is core to our values at Ericsson, that's why we nurture it in everything we do. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and realize their full potential as part of our Ericsson team.

column1: Create sports at the forefront as a Frontend Developer
column4:
The Nice Little Betting Company was founded in 2020 with a distinct intention, to create something that makes the fun funnier with a clear focus on sustainable gambling. By developing products that increase the entertainment and decrease the risk we contribute to change in an industry that we believe has partly gone into a negative spiral.
We’re passionate about sports, but we know that not every game offers Champions League standards. We want to create fun experiences for our participants throughout all games, regardless of quality, by combining the excitement of betting and making the sport even more fun.
We believe that our product is just right for those who love sports.
Frontend Developer on TNLBC
Our product requires you as a Frontend developer to build an app that guarantees an appealing design and a good user experience. You will work in a team with three other developers (at the time of writing) but an expansion of the team is imminent in connection to the product launch.
We’re agile (obviously) and work according to DevOps principles, to be successful in the role you need to have a good understanding concerning the development of apps, from idea to finished product.
We need to strengthen both ability and accessibility with people who recognize themselves in:

Experience in working with services based on AWS.

Knowledge of work with multi-platform development, for example, React Native and/or Flutter.

Experience in developing mobile applications for iOS and Android.

For our customer- 70Agency- international brand and business design agency using tech, creativity, and market understanding to help businesses unlock sustainable growth we are looking for creative FrontEnd or FullStack Developer.
The team is a beautiful mismatch of over 50 brilliant misfits from every corner of the world – joined together in a culture where strategists, designers, analysts, film makers, producers, copywriters, and art directors unite to create brands and experiences with the ability to power forward and empower growth.
WHO YOU ARE
You are passionate about technology and trends, and you know the answer to “What’s next?” for digital storytelling and immersive experiences.
In this role, you will champion our commitment to creating exceptional digital experiences and execution for client campaigns in a variety of environments that solve business needs and push the envelope of traditional digital campaigns. You are not afraid to dig deep together with our creatives and strategists in order grow a kernel of an idea into a fully formed pitch or prototype. At the same time, you are capable of taking a step back to brainstorm the big picture together with our C-Suite level clients. You approach everyone with an open mind and not only welcome but look to be inspired by other perspectives and opinions.
The role is very entrepreneurial in nature and will span a variety of existing client initiatives as well as pitch work and new business development. Excellent communication skills, leadership and a history of successful client relationships are a must.
RESPONSIBILITIES

Working collaboratively with project teams on rapidly prototyping, scoping and delivering innovative and complex creative technology solutions, and provide detailed supporting documentation for pitches and proposals
Champion internal innovation using new and emerging technology in the space, raise the bar for understanding immersive technologies in-house, host workshops and seminars and inspire the wider team with how technology can be applied to existing or potential projects
Drive partnerships, processes and innovation across internal and client teams in experience projects and initiatives. Evaluate internal and external solutions and associated risks and opportunities
Test, document, and share learnings to enable organizational maturity and shared growth

REQUIREMENTS

Familiarity with current and future looking technologies and trends, both first party and third party. Strong understanding of performance considerations in development of immersive experiences
Experience as a Front-End or Full-Stack developer, understanding of CRM and CMS platforms, Javascript and interactive technologies such as React would be a huge plus
Experience with at least one non-web-based programming language or development platform for creative purposes, e.g. Unity, Unreal, Touch Designer, C, C, Python, Arduino etc
Knowledge and experience in creative tools such as the adobe suite and Figma. Knowledge in 3D software such as Cinema 4D, Blender or Modo is considered a bonus
Exposure to social media networks, such as Instagram, Twitter, TikTok, Facebook and Snapchat, and their interactive features
A curious mindset, always searching for what’s next and how it could be used in a meaningful way to meet clients’ business objectives. An interest in moving between disciplines, remixing ideas and appropriate techniques into new contexts
The ability to problem-solve with the confidence, to flag concerns and challenge assumptions on a regular basis and an eye for detail
Excellent communication skills and ability to explain technical solutions effectively to less technical colleagues or clients, and a commitment to be part of a successful team

Seventy Agency is keen to fill this role asap, so if it feels like a match, please don't hesitate to apply. We look forward to speaking with you.

WHO WE ARE Seventy Agency is an international brand design agency using tech, creativity, and market understanding to unlock sustainable growth and build brands for a better future. Our team is a beautiful mismatch of over 50 brilliant misfits from every corner of the world – joined together in a culture where strategists, designers, analysts, film makers, producers, copywriters, and art directors unite to create brands and experiences with the ability to power forward and empower growth. 
  What that means? Well, let's have a quick look into what we've been up to lately: 
  
   We've helped tech entrepreneur Carl Pei create his own venture, bringing Nothing out into the world.
    We've created the world's first smartphone AR launch for OnePlus Nord during the height of the pandemic.
    We're moving Tietoevry, one of Nordics biggest tech companies, towards a future where 24.000 people will work each day to create purposeful technology that reinvents the world for good.
    We've helped the country of Sweden to create stories that brings the brand of Sweden across the globe.
   
  Needless to say, we're keeping ourselves busy and actively pushing the boundaries of immersive experiences together with our clients. But in order to push them even further we need someone like you.
   
  WHO YOU ARE You are passionate about technology and trends, and you know the answer to “What's next?” for digital storytelling and immersive experiences. 
  In this role, you will champion our commitment to creating exceptional digital experiences and execution for client campaigns in a variety of environments that solve business needs and push the envelope of traditional digital campaigns. You have 7+ years of front-end (or full-stack) development experience and you are not afraid to dig deep together with our creatives and strategists in order grow a kernel of an idea into a fully formed pitch or prototype. At the same time, you are capable of taking a step back to brainstorm the big picture together with our C-Suite level clients. You approach everyone with an open mind and not only welcome but look to be inspired by other perspectives and opinions. 
  The role is very entrepreneurial in nature and will span a variety of existing client initiatives as well as pitch work and new business development. Excellent communication skills, leadership and a history of successful client relationships are a must. 
  RESPONSIBILITIES 
  
   Working collaboratively with project teams on rapidly prototyping, scoping and delivering innovative and complex creative technology solutions, and provide detailed supporting documentation for pitches and proposals
    Champion internal innovation using new and emerging technology in the space, raise the bar for understanding immersive technologies in-house, host workshops and seminars and inspire the wider team with how technology can be applied to existing or potential projects
    Drive partnerships, processes and innovation across internal and client teams in experience projects and initiatives. Evaluate internal and external solutions and associated risks and opportunities
    Test, document, and share learnings to enable organizational maturity and shared growth
   
  REQUIREMENTS 
  
   Familiarity with current and future looking technologies and trends, both first party and third party. Strong understanding of performance considerations in development of immersive experiences
    7+ years experience as a Front-End or Full-Stack developer, understanding of CRM and CMS platforms, Javascript and interactive technologies such as React
    Experience with at least one non-web-based programming language or development platform for creative purposes, e.g. Unity, Unreal, Touch Designer, C#, C, Python, Arduino etc
    A solid understanding of Web3 principles, blockchain technology and NFTs
    Knowledge and experience in creative tools such as the adobe suite and Figma. Knowledge in 3D software such as Cinema 4D, Blender or Modo is considered a bonus
    Exposure to social media networks, such as Instagram, Twitter, TikTok, Facebook and Snapchat, and their interactive features
    A curious mindset, always searching for what's next and how it could be used in a meaningful way to meet clients' business objectives. An interest in moving between disciplines, remixing ideas and appropriate techniques into new contexts
    The ability to problem-solve with the confidence, to flag concerns and challenge assumptions on a regular basis and an eye for detail
    Excellent communication skills and ability to explain technical solutions effectively to less technical colleagues or clients, and a commitment to be part of a successful team
   
  
  Seventy Agency is keen to fill this role asap, so if it feels like a match, please get in touch with some examples of your work. We look forward to speaking with you. 
  For more information about Seventy Agency please visit: seventyagency.com (http://seventyagency.com) or follow us on LinkedIn or Instagram.

About Humly
   Humly is a digital marketplace for teachers to match exciting job opportunities within schools and nurseries. Humly’s teachers have delivered more than two hundred thousand teaching days to date. But we haven’t finished yet. We are continuously improving and developing our marketplace and expanding our offer into new international markets.
   Humly has 60 employees working at our offices in Gothenburg in Sweden and Fareham, Milton Keynes, Manchester and Birmingham in the UK. We have over 3,000 registered teachers and agreements with over 4,000 schools in Sweden and the UK.
   Humly has financially strong and active owners, Viking Ventures, and have raised 10 MEUR. We see great potential for the company and have a high ambition.  The Humly platform consists of multiple web clients written in React.js and mobile apps for iOS and Android written in React Native that connect to Ruby on Rails API. Data is permanently stored in the MongoDB database and temporarily cached in Redis.  The infrastructure is run on Amazon Web Services with Infrastructure As Code approach (Terraform).
  
   About the role
   Our user base and business is growing quickly. Our marketplace is becoming more and more demanding to maintain and develop. With the extensive need for our platform and exciting opportunities, we need a well-working development team and technical infrastructure to help us scale our platform and reach our goals and ambitions.  We are looking for someone in our management team who owns the platform's technical aspects and builds a development organization that can further maintain, scale and develop the marketplace.
   As a CTO, you will own the budget and investment plan for the engineering team. You will work closely with the company CPO to develop a scalable and loved digital marketplace. It is your responsibility to align the technical strategy with the company strategy. We expect you to be a proactive and solution-oriented member of the management team.
   We will need an excellent team to help us, so you must enjoy building and forming a development team. Being a good leader who aligns with our values is more important than having the perfect technical skillset.
   Humly is right now having a development team of seven people in Poland. They are not employed by Humly but work full-time for Humly. We have cooperated with them since 2017, and it works very well. The product management team consists of a CPO, a UX designer, two UI designers and a data scientist located at the Humly headquarters in Gothenburg, Sweden. With the great potential ahead of us, the next step in our company development is to build an internal engineering team. We are looking for a CTO to take full responsibility for building and developing a team of high performers that are fun to work with.
   The current development organization works data-driven and agile. We don’t follow any exact agile process model but have designed our own with similar principles. You must prefer being outcome-driven, running small sprints and deploying often.
  
   What can Humly offer you?
   At Humly, we help and motivate each other. The team always comes first, and we like to work together. Seeing and working for the whole is essential, as is having fun, setting high goals, and constantly working for improvement. We have high ambitions for both the individual and the company’s development, but at the same time care about being a friendly workplace where everyone has a place.  In addition to a competitive basic salary, Humly also offers:
  
    Annual bonus. 
   Pension scheme. 
   Flexible and modern workstyle. 
   Share option scheme. 
   Six weeks annual paid leave. 
   A well-working agile team with lots of real user needs to solve.
    A Viking venture community of 20+ other companies to learn and share knowledge with. 
   A globally important and exciting solution that creates a lot of good values for our users and all the children and students they meet every day.
  
  
   Qualifications:
  
   5+ years CTO experience.
   Speaking Swedish is a plus but not required. The team communicates in English.
   Experience from scaling a multi-national platform.
   Well documented experience as a leader.
    Experience in team management and cross-functional team coordination.
  
   We also value your personality highly and think it’s important that it aligns with our values and culture at Humly. We believe that you will like working with us if you are communicative, have high integrity, like to laugh and are willing to walk the extra mile to achieve our goals together.
  
   Location
   Humly is a hybrid organisation with a team spread over many locations in Sweden, England and Poland. We harness the power of remote work and have a structure to build a solid collaborative culture without meeting every day. For this role, it will be preferable if the candidate is situated in Sweden or the UK where we currently have team members. You don't have to be living in a city where we have offices.

Microsoft Industry Solutions (IS) is a global organization of over 13,000 strategic sellers, industry experts, elite engineers, world-class architects, consultants, and delivery experts who work together to bring Microsoft’s mission of empowerment to life for the world’s most influential customers. We are on the front lines of innovation, working side-by-side with customers to drive value across the entirety of their digital transformation journey. Our cutting-edge technology allows us to accelerate life-changing innovations for customers that impact billions around the world!
    
    
    
      The Customer Transformation (CT) team leads and orchestrates pre-sales capabilities to enable the ‘consultative front end’ of the broader Industry Solutions organization. Our core goals are to discover relevant and transformative digital solutions to increase business value for our customers while also meeting internal business goals - to increase Microsoft cloud consumption and innovate with Microsoft products and services through industry-specific lenses.
    
    
    
      Inside of CT, the Digital Strategy & Enablement team sets strategy and manages overall operational effectiveness while also developing methodologies, solutions, offerings, and tools to enable the success of this 700+ person pre-sales organization. Our team prides itself on embracing a growth mindset, inspiring excellence, and encouraging everyone to share their unique viewpoints and be their authentic selves.
    
    
      
    
    
     The Strategist, Customer Value Acceleration role will fulfill two primary functions:
    
    
      Work closely with multi-disciplinary pre-sales specialists including our Prototyping/Innovation Team, Digital Advisors, UX/UI/Mixed Reality designers, Data Scientists, Value Engineering, SW/HW Engineering and Solution Architects along with leadership from our customers to drive alignment on transformation and innovation topics that should be explored at the most senior levels. These customer engagements should focus on differentiated experiences and new capability scenarios or business models. This role will actively collaborate across Product Marketing, Engineering, R&D, Industry & Sales to build the right stakeholder team and orchestrate and craft the relevant customer conversations. They will drive the upfront workshop planning and ideation process(es), development of the transformation vision, strategy, business case, solution architecture and implementation plan for broader scale-out, and management of those stakeholders to ensure the areas of focus are realized at an accelerated pace. 
     Apply lessons from real-time customer experiences to develop, inform and evolve business/GTM strategy, methodology, operations, and best practices for CT team members worldwide. This team will need to work closely with internal People & Readiness teams to support the development of capabilities, operations team to streamline business processes, and develop assets/IP that can scale out to the broader community of practitioners across the various disciplines.
    
   
    
    
   
    Responsibilities 
    
     
      Responsibilities
     
     
       
     
     
      Lead customer engagements and model desired capabilities/behaviors that can scale across the organization
       Engage directly with C-level LOB and IT stakeholders within top-tiered customers to learn and understand the business outcomes the customer is trying to drive; then synthesize this into the primary areas we should explore envisioning and ideation
       Responsible for executing Microsoft’s Business Value Selling process, which includes workshop prep, envisioning planning, strategy for scenario validation, and narrative for business case
       Orchestrate capabilities across CT during engagements such as UX/UI, data science, SW/HW engineering, value engineering, etc. with senior customer executives and/or partners
       Define with key stakeholders the right execution and progression path post envisioning, including but not limited to, business value assessment and business casing, market and organizational assessments, technical assessments, solutioning and deal crafting to accelerate realization of customer outcomes and value
       Capture field learnings and experiences to apply back to CT strategy, value propositions, methodologies, tools, practices, and engagement patterns
       Drive learnings and content from these high touch executive briefings and envisioning workshops to inform our customer-centered strategy and industry perspective
     
     
   
   
    Qualifications 
    
     
      Qualifications and Experience
     
     
     
       Proven experience working in top-tier management consulting or consulting design firms
       Experience engaging with senior executive-level customers through a consultative/value/experience design-led pre-sales motion.
       Experience in future studies, ethnographic studies or qualitative/quantitative research, product, business or industrial design, design thinking methods, rapid prototyping, facilitation and participant energy management, storytelling, persona development, journey map and service blueprints

       Experience building and leading programs that require cross-org collaboration, multi-discipline teams, and support from senior leadership

       Learn it All – embrace and practice this philosophy every day and in every engagement
       Passion for technology’s potential to drive transformational change

       A proven ability to understand the CEO’s agenda with curiosity and empathy for customer challenges and a passion for resolving them

column1: Data & Software Engineer to ADB Safegate
column4:
job description.
 Are you an experienced software developer? Ready for your next journey? ADB Safegate is now opening up for a new position located in Malmö who will take responsibility for our gate solution’s technical development and implementation!
qualifications.
We see that you have a Master’s or Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in IT or Computer Science related subject.

We think that you are an experienced software developer with good knowledge in container and server deployments. You are also well known in visualization tools and scalable distributed systems architecture. This role also requries you to be experienced in building business intelligence reporting from disparate data sources and have expertise in data warehousing.


Technical requirements:
Experience in at least two of the Programming Languages: Java, Scala, Python, TypeScript, C++, SQL
Message Queues, SQL and non SQL Databases
Data streaming platforms, e.g., Kafka
Container and Server deployments
Experience in DevOps, Continues Integration & Delivery
Experience in function testing
Nice to have
JavaScript Frameworks: Angular, Nest
Azure & AWS, infrastructure as code (AWS CloudFormation)
Experience working with collaboration software (e.g., Jira, Confluence, Git)
Personal Competences

 You have an international, intercultural mindset and experience and love working with, and learning from, colleagues and clients around the globe.


Aviation is a fast-paced and challenging industry, but you know how to deal with that. You have great time management and organizational skills that allow you to meet customer commitments for large scale projects.


You have a strong customer focus and are skilled in communicating and effortlessly conveying complex information in an understandable manner. In turn, you are able to read between the lines and understand the needs of the customer.
responsibilities.
 ADB Safegate leads the world in smart solutions that help airports handle more aircraft, safely and efficiently, from approach to departure. Our products and services include runway and taxiway lighting; to tower-based traffic control systems; to intelligent gate and docking automation.


We are looking for talented and enthusiastic people with the passion to support our vision and help to change the future of our GATE Business. We are now offering a fascinating position as Data & Software Engineer to join our team.


GATE solutions help to position the aircraft safely and efficiently at the gate. GATE solutions base on elaborated sensor technology as well as a comprehensive software suite. As our data & software engineer you are responsible for the solution’s technical development and implementation. Your responsibilities involve developing and implementing the system architecture of a new solution, ensuring adequate data/IT architecture is in place (or is being set up) to support the new solution, designing and developing adequate UX for the new solution. Depending on the business unit needs and your background the emphasis will be on back-end, back-end to front-end (BFF) or front end.


What will you do?
Design, specify and select information system solutions while considering functionality, data, security, integration, infrastructure and performance
Develop, maintain and improve the overall data architecture
Assess current systems and determine their viability in terms of data architecture
Evaluate the solutions that will be developed to ensure their coherence with the data architecture standards
Leverage the agile methodology to ensure product delivery with POC and MVP, sprints, etc.
application.
 You are welcome to submit your application in both Swedish and English.

We encourage you to send your application as soon as possible, since interviews and candidate selection are done continuously!

If you want to know more about the role, please send an email to Claudia Baronescu to claudia.baronescu@randstad.se
about ADB Safegate Sweden AB.
 At ADB SAFEGATE, our diverse team, spanning 45+ nationalities across 37 offices, shares one purpose: helping airports achieve new levels of safety, sustainability and efficiency in airside operations. If you are people-centric, and a team player who’s driven and passionate about developing and delivering products, solutions and projects that improve apron operations and make air travel safer and better, come join our crew.
https://www.adbsafegate.com

Lund University was founded in 1666 and is repeatedly ranked among the world’s top 100 universities. The University has around 44 000 students and more than 8 000 staff based in Lund, Helsingborg and Malmö. We are united in our efforts to understand, explain and improve our world and the human condition.

Lund University welcomes applicants with diverse backgrounds and experiences. We regard gender equality and diversity as a strength and an asset.
MAX IV is a Swedish national large-scale research laboratory hosted by Lund University. It provides scientists from Sweden as well as internationally, with state-of-the-art instrumentation for research in areas such as engineering, physics, structural biology, chemistry and nanotechnology. Fully developed it will receive more than 2 000 scientists annually, conducting ground-breaking experiments in materials and life sciences using the brilliant X-ray light.
KITS Software Team
Are you our new software developer that will boost research for the scientists? Apply your software development skills to help explore the full capabilities of Sweden's new ﬂagship laboratory. You will have the chance to face new challenges of the synchrotron domain in a very diverse and interesting environment.
The KITS-SW group provides MAX IV with a wide range of software solutions for the facility scientific endeavors. Among others we provide control system solutions following international standards in synchrotrons such as web-based user interfaces, distributed hardware control, scanning tools for running experiments, acquiring and saving data and metadata, etc. As a very important part of MAX IV, the functionality and the reliability of the control and acquisition system software is continuously developed to meet the research requirements.
In our team you will meet open minded people from different perspectives. Being part the KITS group, you will be in close collaboration with scientists as well as network, system, software and hardware engineers and scientiﬁc software experts. We promote a DevOps style cross functional team and collaboration between all people.
MAX IV is looking for a Computer or Physics Scientist who will…
be involved in the software developments of the data acquisition and the experiment control framework from a variety of detectors and their integration into the experimental stations. You will join a trust-oriented and open team where continuous improvement and mentorship is part of our culture. As an experienced professional we expect you to bridge science and state of the art software development.
You will be expected to participate in different international collaborations about control and data acquisition, as well as to contribute to international conferences.

You will also be able to learn and to increase your skills, competence, and experience.
Your main work tasks will be
Developing software projects for scientific experimentation at MAX IV.
Supporting the MAX IV staff in using the data acquisition and the experiment control framework
Increasing the functionality and the reliability of the data acquisition, experiment control and visualization system to realize its scientiﬁc potential of the whole facility.
Improving the “User eXperience” for troubleshooting and ﬁnding simple user-friendly solutions to complex problems.
Participating to the team planning and resource estimation as well as improving the group infrastructure.
To be successful in this role you need to have the following qualifications
An advanced university degree.
A professional experience with Python 3 programming.
An understanding of measurement and data collection for experiments.
An understanding of common Software Architecture: Functional, OOP, Reactive ...
An understanding of Performance and Distribution of systems: TCP/IP, ZMQ, …
Experience with Agile team environment and familiar with peer programming, review, unit tests, continuous integration, and continuous delivery.
An open source spirit.
Below are seen as merits
Experience in Data Collection and Control System development.
Experience in Tango and/or Sardana development.
Scientific domain knowledge about a related discipline (e.g. spectroscopy, microscopy, particle accelerators...).
The ability to work in a Linux operating system environment.
Other Software programming languages: JavaScript, C, C++, Go, Rust …
Software development for scientific environment.
Web development: Microframework, HTTP, React…
Showing evidence of an Open Source community collaboration.
Working in an international research-oriented environment.
As a person you are …
In addition to the above it is regarded as highly important to supply evidence that you are a team player and can demonstrate your communication and collaborative skills. You should also be committed to quality work and able to understand requirements for scientific related developments.
Probationary period may apply.
On call services may apply in the future.

MAX IV is a Swedish national large-scale research laboratory hosted by Lund University. It provides scientists from Sweden as well as internationally, with state-of-the-art instrumentation for research in areas such as engineering, physics, structural biology, chemistry and nanotechnology. Fully developed it will receive more than 2 000 scientists annually, conducting ground-breaking experiments in materials and life sciences using the brilliant X-ray light.
The MAX IV Controls and IT team (KITS) deliver solutions to the whole MAX IV organisation in the areas of control system hardware, controls software applications, infrastructure and networking, information management and scientific software. This is a dynamic and highly challenging environment and requires close collaboration with the staff in order to understand the needs and be effective in forming solutions. We are around 50 people in total who work in 5 domains in a well organised and agile way. We hold values of lean management, knowledge spread, user autonomy, continuous improvement and flexibility as guiding principles for our work.
We kindly decline all sales and marketing contacts.

Job Description
   The Ubisoft Connect team at Massive is looking for a skillful, hard-working and perceptive data analyst to join us in pursuit of making Ubisoft Connect the natural first pick as a gaming platform. As an analyst on our team, you will play a significant role in developing and enhancing the PC gaming experience for millions of people together with a team that is dedicated to delivering best services for gamers and game development teams across the globe.
   As a part of the Ubisoft Connect team at Massive, you will be part of a highly creative and focused team where many different disciplines work closely on a daily basis.
   This is a permanent position based in Malmö Sweden, with the opportunity to work partially from home according to our Flexible Workplace Policy. Please apply in English (our company language), and we’ll check your application asap!
  
   Responsibilities
  
    Analyze platform data and transform it into automated reporting, focusing on various user behaviours, including but not limited to user acquisition, engagement and retention.
    Maintain and develop standard and event-specific reports to help the team understand how users interact with our platform and react to changes in different user flows.
    Design telemetry tracking events for new platform features, accounting for both production and business needs.
    Build data pipelines and maintain data warehouses in cooperation with BI development to ensure the quality of the data.
    Support operations and developers with platform insights based on telemetry data.
    Perform ad-hoc analyses to support the development of the new features, explain anomalies in the data, help team understand our users better etc.
  
   You as a person You are eager to learn new things and appreciate every opportunity to grow your expertise. You have an excellent analytical mind with an interest in big data and the gaming industry. At the Ubisoft Connect team we value focus on being thorough, team-spirited and result-oriented, while we aim to develop our platform and enhance the life of millions of PC gamers around the world. You’ll be joining a dynamic environment, where you will be presented with opportunities to grow and interesting challenges to overcome on a daily basis. Therefore, it is great if you know how to prioritize work, as well as ask for help when needed.
 
  Qualifications
   
  
    Relevant university degree with focus on data analytics/data science (Computer Science, Economics, Statistics, or any other quantitative field), ideally combined with computer science or game development or an interest in data in a game development environment
    Good knowledge of SQL-based languages (MySQL, T-SQL, SQL in Hive/Impala/Snowflake)
    Experienced in (analytics) scripting languages, such as R or Python
    Familiarity with dashboard/reporting solutions like Tableau, Power BI, Microstrategy, Grafana or similar
    Knowledge of non-relational DBMS technologies (Key-value stores, object databases, etc.) is a plus
    Knowledge of Spark and pySpark is a plus
    Drive, enthusiasm and insight into gaming and software development to be able to push our platform to the next level, by utilizing their analytical mind-set in collaboration with gaming experience
    Experience from working close to business/marketing is a plus
    You know some of the troubles of online gaming platforms or digital distribution
    Excellent English and communication skills
  
   Additional Information
   Massive Entertainment is a world-leading AAA studio located in Malmö, Sweden and part of the Ubisoft family. We’re a multinational team of more than 650 passionate and highly skilled people from 50+ different countries. Our studio’s goal has always been – and still is – to craft the finest gaming experiences for all players.
   At Massive, you get to do what you love most while bringing your own experience to our ongoing projects, like Tom Clancy’s The Division 2, Avatar: Frontiers of Pandora, and The Star Wars Project. We're also developing new tech here, such as our in-house engine Snowdrop, and Ubisoft Connect - Ubisoft's digital ecosystem and distribution platform.
   All your application information will be kept confidential according to EEO & GDPR guidelines.

column1: Data Analytics Sales Specialist, Google Cloud
column4:
Note: By applying to this position you will have an opportunity to share your preferred working location from the following: Oslo, Norway; Helsinki, Finland; Stockholm, Sweden.
Minimum qualifications:

Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience.
Experience promoting data analytics software or solutions.
Preferred qualifications:

Experience working with market leading Business Intelligence Front-End, Data Analytics Middleware, or Back-End Data Warehouse technologies.
Understanding of cloud Data Analytics stack (e.g., Hadoop/Spark Data lakes, SQL Data Warehouses, Data Streaming, ETL, Data governance, Business Intelligence, Predictive Analytics, OLAP, Data science framework, BigQuery, Looker etc.).
Ability to translate business insights into technology at C-level and act as a thought leader in data analytics topics.
Ability to build influential relationships and deliver results in a cross-functional, matrixed environment.
Ability to plan, pitch, and execute a business strategy.
Excellent written and verbal communication and presentation skills.
About the job
As a member of the Google Cloud team, you inspire leading companies, schools, and government agencies to work smarter with Google tools like Google Workspace, Search, and Chrome. You advocate the innovative power of our products to make organizations more productive, collaborative, and mobile. Your guiding light is doing what’s right for the customer, you will meet customers exactly where they are at and provide them the best solutions for innovation. Using your passion for Google products, you help spread the magic of Google to organizations around the world.

Our team of engineers, product managers, business, and marketing professionals work with partners and customers to advance the company's mission to organize the world's information to make it universally accessible and useful. You will create and execute the Data Analytics business strategy.
As a member of the Google Cloud team, your focus is on customers and prospects who have an opportunity to run Data Analytics workloads on Google Cloud Platform. You will advocate for the innovative power of our data products to make organizations more productive, collaborative, and mobile.
Google Cloud accelerates organizations’ ability to digitally transform their business with the best infrastructure, platform, industry solutions and expertise. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s cutting-edge technology – all on the cleanest cloud in the industry. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.
Responsibilities
Generate a plan to ensure Data Analytics development within Google Cloud accounts.
Manage Data Analytics workloads in existing Google Cloud accounts and accelerate consumption for key accounts with ramping.
Build and maintain executive relationships with customers as the Data Analytics subject matter expert, influence long-term strategic direction, and act as a trusted advisor.
Develop business strategies to be successful at accelerating agreement cycles.
Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to grow the business with Data Analytics customers and workloads.
Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form.

Data Engineer for GlobalConnect 
   GlobalConnect is a leading technology and telecommunications company in Northern Europe. The group delivers comprehensive communications solutions from the ground to the cloud. The solutions are based on our own infrastructure consisting of a 100,000 kilometre fibre network and 30,000 square metres of data centre. GlobalConnect has 30,000 enterprise customers covering all sectors from SMEs to the public sector and multinational companies. In the B2C segment, GlobalConnect has 420,000 customers across the Nordic region. With EQT Infrastructure as owner, GlobalConnect has launched an ambitious growth strategy, which includes investments in new infrastructure, storage and outsourcing, collaboration solutions, intelligent automation and security solutions. GlobalConnect has over 1,700 employees and a turnover of approximately SEK 6 billion in 2020, with headquarters in Stockholm, Oslo and Copenhagen. 
   We at GlobalConnect can offer you a flexible as well as stimulating job, where you will have great freedom to shape your own daily life and develop your skills in an inspiring and fast-paced environment. 
   The team 
   You now have the opportunity to become part of our fantastic and fast-growing Analytics team, which currently consists of 10 people spread between Uppsala, Stockholm and Oslo. The team is responsible for the group's data platform and possesses expertise in Python, SQL, Qlik Sense, Power BI, JavaScript, GO and Azure Cloud etc. You will work with incredibly dedicated colleagues who are eager to share their knowledge and who are passionate about making GlobalConnect data-driven. 
   You can choose to work at our office in Uppsala or Stockholm and some time remotely. 
   About the role 
   In the role of Data Engineer, you will develop and manage our data platform VERUM. As we have built three different in-house applications for our platform here at GlobalConnect, this position will also involve system development. You will bring in new data, handle our CI/CD flows and watch over our running procedures. Furthermore, you will keep track of the data pipeline. A usual week includes both maintenance and the development of new features for our applications. 
   Technology stacks 
   Our platform is based in Azure Cloud where we have chosen Snowflake as our data warehouse. We have Power BI as our primary front-end tool for future development, but also manage a large Qlik Sense environment. The Data & Metrics team within the Financial Engineering mission builds data products and platforms that influence the future path of the Finance organization and Spotify as a company. You'll be working on a vast data ecosystem that drives Spotify’s revenue recognition from subscriptions and ads, forecasting algorithms and financial performance measurement and analysis. You will have a direct impact on the future of Spotify’s global business and product decisions!

As a data engineer within Data & Metrics, you will be involved in building data platforms at scale to tackle business and technical use cases, leading epics and work-streams along the way. We use the Google Cloud Platform and technologies such as Big Query, Scala, Scio and Docker. You will work with the data science, product and analytics community to build various insights around financial performance analysis, key metrics creation and monitoring, and forecasting workstreams.

Teams in Data & Metrics
Adventure: In Adventure you will be responsible for providing the data products and technical foundation for our partners in the ads supported business domain. We work closely with the business teams to model data and enable them to create insights and forecasts in a complex and constantly changing domain.
The Keys: In the Keys you will join our mission in building the technical platform which supports our key company decisions, royalty calculations and our ability to scale into new markets and products. Our day to day work is to handle some of the largest and most important datasets at Spotify.
Overtone: In Overtone you will curate high-quality canonical financial datasets describing transactions, revenue, costs, and support business initiatives such as Customer Lifetime Value (LTV), Forecasting, Financial Reporting, and Strategic Planning.
What you will do
Closely work with product managers and business partners to come up with innovative ideas and engineering solutions to solve complex financial workflows.
Define data models that tie together fragmented data across the entire organization
Design and implement a large scale data ecosystem for all Financial stakeholders using Spotify best practices.
May come across a need to design, implement and maintain ETL pipelines.
Who you are
Have a degree in Computer Science or a similar field.
3+ years of professional software engineering and programming experience (SQL, Java, C++, Scala, Python)
3+ years of architecture and design (patterns, reliability, scalability, quality) of complex systems
Strong analytical and problem-solving ability with advanced written and verbal communication skills
Advanced coding skills, experience in distributed systems, functional principles & performance optimization
T-Shaped. Your primary area is data engineering but you are comfortable with second areas such as data presentation, backend engineering or front-end development
Professional experience working in an agile environment
Comfortable with tackling very loosely defined problems, especially when working on a team that has autonomy in their day to day decision
Have performed an analysis of large datasets in a cloud based-environment, preferably with an understanding of Google’s Cloud Platform
Experience with Google Cloud Platform is beneficial
Experience in mentoring and leading junior engineers is a plus
Where you'll be
We are a distributed workforce enabling our band members to find a work mode that is best for them!
Where in the world? For this role, it can be within the Europe region in which we have a work location
Prefer an office to work from home instead? Not a problem! We have plenty of options for your working preferences.
Working hours? We operate within the Central European Time zone for collaboration
Our global benefits
Extensive learning opportunities, through our dedicated team, GreenHouse.
Flexible share incentives letting you choose how you share in our success.
Global parental leave, six months off - fully paid - for all new parents.
All The Feels, our employee assistance program and self-care hub.
Flexible public holidays, swap days off according to your values and beliefs.
Spotify On Tour, join your colleagues on trips to industry festivals and events.
Learn about life at Spotify
Spotify is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome at Spotify for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what’s playing in your headphones. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all thrive, contribute, and be forward-thinking! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our differences that we will find the power to keep revolutionizing the way the world listens.
Spotify transformed music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the chance to enjoy and be passionate about these creators. Everything we do is driven by our love for music and podcasting. Today, we are the world’s most popular audio streaming subscription service.

Introduction
    Data Scientists / Engineers are part of a cross-functional team that delivers a unique client co-creation experience to accelerate client transformation
    
   
    Acts as a key contributor to a pre-sales Client Engineering team, partnering with clients to understand business problems and propose solutions
    Contributes to co-creation of rapid proofs of concept and Minimal Viable Solutions that demonstrate business value, leading to client investment in strategic solutions
    Translates business problems into leading-edge analytics solutions using consulting skills, industry expertise and technical knowledge
    Delivers meaningful insights and predicts emerging trends to inform business solutions that optimize client value
    Familiar with Data Engineering techniques to gather, prepare, cleanse, and transform client data for analysis and AI automation
   
    What role specific skills should you have?
    
    Data Scientist requires deep understanding of machine learning (ML) algorithms and statistical methods to prepare data for predictive and prescriptive modeling to solve a specific business problem. They need to collaborate with data engineers in architecting and optimizing data pipelines for production-ready models. Experience/skills:
    
   
    Experience with statistical SW and programming languages (R, Python, SPSS) and database languages (SQL)
    Ability to research, explore, examine and find patterns in data to answer industry and business questions
    Ability to evaluate and improve the data sets quality
    Ability to prototype and build data pipelines iteratively to provide insights at scale
   
    
    Your Role and Responsibilities
    Technical Expertise
   
     Possesses deep technical expertise and business domain knowledge in their select specialty areas, including Data Science, Site Reliability, Cloud, Data, Automation, DevOps, and Security demonstrated by advanced degrees, certifications and relevant work experience
     Learns and applies relevant industry experience to establish credibility with the client
     Demonstrates a growth mindset and continuous learning; stays current on IBM strategy and offerings with understanding of technical principles of Docker and Kubernetes
   
    Solution Co-Creation
   
     During the pre-sales process, partners with the client and members of the Client Engineering team to co-create solutions that leverage IBM offerings to solve the client’s business challenges
     Iterates on the solution, in Agile fashion, to react to client feedback and demonstrate rapid progress
     Uses Design Thinking and Garage methods to to document pain points and opportunities; illustrate new process designs and journey maps and visualize transformation outcomes
   
    Strategic Innovation
   
     In a dynamic, fast-paced pre-sales environment, designs and implements innovative solutions, ensuring that interdependencies with other functions are addressed
     Collaborates with others to validate new analytical approaches, share and learn from best practices
     Demonstrates growth mindset by being eager to understand clients’ business processes, their potential for transformation, and learn new technologies and methods continuously
   
    
    Required Technical and Professional Expertise
    
   
    At least 4 years as a Data Scientist with a deep understanding of Statistics, Machine Learning, NLP/NLU
    At least 4 years of experience with identifying data sources, transforming data, and the use of Frameworks (e.g., MXNet, TensorFlow, PyTorch, SparkML, scikit-learn) to help our customers build ML models
    Creative mind and out of the box thinking and you write code with Python, R, Scala, Java, C++ & G0
    Demonstrates strong business acumen and ability to understand business problems, formulate hypotheses and test conclusions to influence solution design.
    Can leverage a variety of structured and unstructured data sources, analytics, AI tools and programming languages to derive meaningful data insights (e.g., Python, Spark, TensorFlow, Jupyter etc.).
    Fluent English
   
    
    Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise
    
   
    Masters or PhD in a highly quantitative field (Data Science, Computer Science, Machine Learning, Operational Research, Statistics, Mathematics, etc.)
    Experience Consulting with client and taking on and solving complex business problems related to data, Ability to thrive in a startup environment and deliver on the end goals
    Demonstrable track record of dealing well with ambiguity, prioritizing needs, and delivering results in a dynamic environment
    Experience and Ability to work across multi clouds (IBM, AWS, GCP and Azure)
   
  
  
   
     
     About Business Unit
    IBM has a global presence, operating in more than 175 countries with a broad-based geographic distribution of revenue. The company’s Global Markets organization is a strategic sales business unit that manages IBM’s global footprint, working closely with dedicated country-based operating units to serve clients locally. These country teams have client relationship managers who lead integrated teams of consultants, solution specialists and delivery professionals to enable clients’ growth and innovation. By complementing local expertise with global experience and digital capabilities, IBM builds deep and broad-based client relationships. This local management focus fosters speed in supporting clients, addressing new markets and making investments in emerging opportunities. Additionally, the Global Markets organization serves clients with expertise in their industry as well as through the products and services that IBM and partners supply. IBM is also expanding its reach to new and existing clients through digital marketplaces.
  
  
   
     
     Your Life @ IBM
    Are you craving to learn more? Prepared to solve some of the world's most unique challenges? And ready to shape the future for millions of people? If so, then it's time to join us, express your individuality, unleash your curiosity and discover new possibilities.
    
    Every IBMer, and potential ones like yourself, has a voice, carves their own path, and uses their expertise to help co-create and add to our story. Together, we have the power to make meaningful change – to alter the fabric of our clients, of society and IBM itself, to create a truly positive impact and make the world work better for everyone.
    
    It's time to define your career.
  
  
   
     
     About IBM
    IBM’s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that through the application of intelligence, reason and science, we can improve business, society and the human condition, bringing the power of an open hybrid cloud and AI strategy to life for our clients and partners around the world.
    
    Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are not only one of the largest corporate organizations in the world, we’re also one of the biggest technology and consulting employers, with many of the Fortune 50 companies relying on the IBM Cloud to run their business. 
    
    At IBM, we pride ourselves on being an early adopter of artificial intelligence, quantum computing and blockchain. Now it’s time for you to join us on our journey to being a responsible technology innovator and a force for good in the world.
  
  
   
     
     Location Statement
    IBM wants you to bring your whole self to work and for you this might mean the ability to work flexibly. If you are interested in a flexible working pattern, please talk to our recruitment team to find out if this is possible in the current working environment.
  
  
   
     
     Being You @ IBM
    IBM is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, pregnancy, disability, age, veteran status, or other characteristics. IBM is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status.

Vi erbjuder
Du blir del av en mycket god arbetsmiljö! Medarbetarna är det viktigaste vi har och det är de som gör att vi lyckas. Vi tror på frihet under ansvar vilket gör att du har stor möjlighet att själv påverka. Det är viktigt att vi har kul på jobbet och vi arbetar i roliga projekt. Vi har högt i tak och ställer upp för varandra!

Vi tror på ett samhälle format av framgångsrika företag där entreprenörskap och samhällsnytta går hand i hand. Att vara en del av Fortnox är att vara en del av en ständig förändring - en förändring där du själv bestämmer hur långt du vill nå. Vårt största fokus är att ge dig rätt förutsättningar att få leva din passion tillsammans med oss. Var du kommer ifrån är inte relevant - det är vart du är på väg som är intressant för oss. Precis som vi igår inte kunde drömma om det Fortnox som finns idag, så kan du vara med och forma vilka vi är imorgon.
   Pirrar det i magen på dig med?
   Om tjänsten Som Developer på Fortnox arbetar du med andra Developers, Product Owners och Test Engineers som brinner för att utveckla innovativa lösningar. I rollen ingår du i ett mindre team som tar stort ansvar för lösningens utformning och du har möjlighet att utveckla i hela stacken. Vi jobbar agilt och vi tror på självorganiserande team.
   Vi arbetar med moderna tekniker, allt från React i frontend till RxJava i backend. Vår mikrotjänstarkitektur bygger på Docker och Kubernetes. Du utgår från vårt kontor i Linköping men kommer ha ett nära samarbete med dina kollegor i Växjö.
   Om dig Du har ett par års erfarenhet av utveckling i Java, Javascript, TypeScript, Kotlin och kanske några andra språk. Har du intresse av och har testat på funktionell programmering och reactive extensions kommer du att gilla vår Javastack som är light weight och använder moderna ramverk som t ex RxJava. Vi ser även att du har erfarenhet av SQL och att arbeta med och utveckla REST - API:er.  Då du kommer att arbeta tillsammans med andra i ett mindre team, men som en del av hela Fortnox, så krävs en förmåga att kommunicera väl med olika människor. Vi tror även att du har viljan att lära nytt och att sprida din egen kunskap vidare till dina kollegor. Är du kreativ i arbetet och gärna tar egna initiativ till lösningar står vi bakom dig hela vägen.
   Om Fortnox Fortnox AB (publ) är en företagsplattform som knyter samman människor, företag och organisationer. Vi hjälper företag starta, växa och utvecklas. Med smarta tekniska produkter, lösningar och tjänster, och möjlighet att koppla ihop dem med hundratals externa parter, är vi ett nav för företagande i Sverige. Vår vision är att skapa ett välmående samhälle format av framgångsrika företag. Fortnox grundades 2001 och har huvudkontor i Växjö samt kontor i Malmö, Linköping och Stockholm. Aktien är noterad på Nasdaq Stockholm. För ytterligare information se www.fortnox.se.
   Bra att veta Tillträde: Snarast eller enligt överenskommelse Arbetstid: Heltid Arbetsort: Linköping Sista ansökningsdatum: Urval och intervjuer sker löpande.
   För frågor om tjänsten, kontakta Erik Stenberg, erik.stenberg@fortnox.se
   Välkommen med din ansökan!

At Tele2 you and your team develop digital products that effects millions of people. To continue to do so we are looking for talented and skilled developers in multiple areas. Our teams are autonomous and you will join a team that is responsible for the full product life-cycle and the development of new features that continuously bring value to our customers. We are using the latest technologies and methodologies and our microservices are running on Kubernetes over Azure. We breath Agile, believe in DevOps principles and own what we build.

The Telecom Industry is going through an exciting transformation and taking big leaps towards the future of Telecom, Tele2 want to lead the way and work hard to challenge the industry and be the number one provider.

We are looking for
Fullstack Developers (Java, React)Front-end Developers (React)
Back-end Developers (C#/.Net, Java, PL/SQL Oracle)

Tele2 offers you to work in a creative and flexible work environment. You will be part of a culture where teamwork, diversity and inclusion are leading the way forward. Every employee is important for the company’s success and you will always have an impact with your work. We provide you with the opportunity to grow and develop through internal paths within the organization.

The position is located in our headquarter in Kista, Stockholm.

Does Tele2 sound like the right place for you? Don’t hesitate, send your application now!

Please note that this is a general job ad for developers, therefore you will only be contacted should your profile match with one of our open positions.
