Are you ready to work at Sweden's outstanding digital product & service company?
   Why not join a workplace that gives you freedom, inspiration, incredible colleagues and a chance to work the way you want with projects you'll love.
   Maybe you saw this article on Medium and thought it sounded exactly like the place you'd like to spend your days?
   What we're looking for:
   We're looking for an experienced developer to join our team in Gothenburg. It doesn’t matter that much if you call yourself front-end, back-end or full stack. The most important thing is that you’re good at programming and web development in general, and that you love developing great experiences and building what’s needed.
   Together with the team, you will work closely with current and new clients to create digital products and services. Your main focus is the Javascript stack, and you should have good experience with both Node.js and React.
   Our way of working
   Our work is naturally driven by UX and service design. We extend this notion when it comes to architecture and technical solutions by also being informed by domain-driven design meaning that our software should reflect the client’s business, not be just a technical-jargon construct. We prefer microservices rather than monoliths and love the cloud and the possibilities that it gives for creating performant, reliable and secure applications that can scale over time.
   What we would expect from you:
   
   You love working with Javascript and Typescript. 
   You're experienced in React and/or other frameworks like Angular, Vue etc. 
   You communicate via API:s, preferably Node.js and GraphQL 
   You're interested in technologies like Serverless architecture, Headless CMS etc. 
   You enjoy collaborating with a multi-disciplinary, multi-cultural team. 
   You experiment with new technologies. 
   You spread energy and inspire your team members. 
  
  You are as important as your skills
   We employ people as much for their human traits as their competence and skill sets. We like good humans around us. We work in a collaborative environment (design sprints, development sprints, workshops with clients etc) and therefore we employ people who are empathetic, kind, patient and gracious. We are Humblebee.

Vill du vara med och bygga nästa generations e-handelsupplevelse baserad på headless arkitektur? Vill du jobba med de senaste teknikerna som t.ex. React, .NET Core, Containrar och Serverless? Vi letar efter dig som förstår hur viktigt det är med bra skriven kod och en god arkitektur och som vill bygga något att vara stolt över.
   Nordic Nest växer så det knakar och vi börjar nu arbetet med att bygga vår nya plattform som ska klara av framtida tillväxt. Här blir du en del av teamet som levererar applikationer som miljontals besökare ser och verktygen som hundratals anställda använder i sitt dagliga arbete. Du bygger tjänster som kommer användas utav människor över hela världen (förra året skickade vi paket till 70 länder), därför lägger vi stor vikt på prestanda och skalbarhet.
   I ditt dagliga arbete kommer du vara med i hela processen från design, utveckling och driftsättning. Du deltar i sprintplanering och retrospectives. Du kommer bl.a. arbeta med integrationer mot t.ex. ERP, betalväxlar, WMS, CRM och andra system. Vi vill alltid bli bättre och en viktig del i det är code reviews som görs löpande, här är vi prestigelösa och uppskattar när vi lär oss något nytt och vill gärna dela med oss av vår kunskap. Vi gillar förändring, öppenhet och vill alltid leverera bra resultat.
  
   Vi tror att du
   
    Har minst 3 års erfarenhet med utveckling av affärskritiska applikationer 
   Har gedigen kunskap inom C eller annat liknande språk 
   Har vana av SQL (MS SQL, PostgreSQL eller MySQL) 
   Har arbetat med Javascript och något ramverk (t.ex. React, Angular, Vue) 
   Är van vid CSS och någon pre-processor som t.ex. LESS eller SASS 
   Använder Git och Gitflow
  
  
   Har du dessutom erfarenhet utav något av följande är det meriterande
   
    E-handel 
   Arbete i Azure, AWS eller GCP 
   Serverless tjänster som Azure Functions eller AWS Lambda 
   Docker och Container-lösningar 
   GraphQL 
   CI/CD
  
  
   Vi erbjuder dig en fantastisk rolig tjänst med ett team av kollegor som engagerat kämpar för att utveckla verksamheten. Du kommer att vara en del i ett bolag där kunden alltid kommer i första hand, allt vi gör ska bidra till att skapa nöjdare kunder. Vi är ett bolag i en stark tillväxtfas där du kommer ha en direkt påverkan på vårt gemensamma resultat. Du kommer få arbeta med kollegor som har ett stark driv och ett resultatfokus, vilket gör att vi i perioder jobbar extra hårt och intensivt för att nå våra mål. Det är viktigt att du trivs i en kultur som präglas av ett högt tempo, där vi firar framgångar och jobbar hårt för att skapa dessa.
  
   Välkommen hem! Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning på heltid.
   Vi tror att talang och personliga egenskaper säger mer om din framtida prestation än vad din dokumenterade erfarenhet gör, därför använder vi personlighetstester i ett tidigt skede i rekryteringsprocessen. Sök senast den 1 maj! 
  Vi kommer gå igenom ansökningarna löpande, så vänta inte med din ansökan. Varmt välkommen med din ansökan!
   För frågor kring tjänsten kontakta CTO Jacob Rastad på jacob.rastad@nordicnest.com .

Ansök nu
Har du kommit en bit i din karriär som systemutvecklare och är redo att axla rollen som Tech Lead? Som Tech Lead på Sogeti kommer du inspirera och leda ett team av engagerade och duktiga systemutvecklare där deras utveckling ligger i fokus. Du kommer arbeta hands-on med utveckling dela på ägandeskap och ansvar för leverans med övriga teamet. Hos oss på Sogeti får du vara med och skapa morgondagens lösningar, idag.
Våra kunder finns över flera branscher vilket ger dig möjligheten att arbeta med varierande uppdrag och tekniker. Gillar du snabbheten hos Start-ups? Vill du vara med och bygga framtidens system för samhället via publika sektorn? Drivs du av bank- och finansbranschens utmanade krav på stabilitet och snabbrörlighet? Tillsammans med din teamchef kommer du sätta upp en plan för att bygga vidare på din karriär som du vill och utvecklas åt det håll du önskar.Vi tror att du som söker har arbetat med utveckling i minst fem år men vi vet av erfarenhet att dina tech och people skills är viktigast så om du känner att du är redo för det här steget så uppmuntrar vi dig att söka ändå. Du är en person som vågar delegera, som har förmågan att inspirera andra och skapa förtroende och ta ägandeskap i såväl kundsammanhang som för tekniken.
Många av våra uppdrag innehåller tekniker som:
Kodning i C#/.NET, Java EE och JavaScript
Ramverk såsom Node, Angular, React eller dylikt
Cloud-tjänster (App Services, API Services, Micro Services, Data Bricks) och migrering till publika moln (Azure, AWS, Google Cloud).

Då flera av våra uppdrag kräver svenskakunskaper ser vi det som meriterande om du pratar och skriver svenska obehindrat.

För dig som vill lite mer, sök tjänsten som Tech Lead och ta nästa steg i din karriär!

På Ropo Capital är medarbetaren den viktigaste framgångsfaktorn och vi ser nu fram emot att få välkomna en ny kollega till vårt team. Trivs du likt oss i en växlande miljö där arbetsglädje och engagemang står i fokus? Då tror vi att du kommer trivas hos oss!
Ropo Capital erbjuder vad vi kallar för Invoice Life Cycle-tjänster för fakturahantering, dvs, allt från distribution och reskontrahantering till påminnelser och inkasso. Vårt fundament bygger på egenutvecklad teknik och vi brinner för att skapa extraordinära kundupplevelser med hjälp av data och en oslagbar fakturahanteringsprocess. Genom att vi vågar tänka nytt och sätta nya normer skapas värde för våra klienter och deras kunder i form av stärkta kundrelationer och bättre finansiella resultat.
Ropo Capital är marknadsledande inom fakturahantering i Finland och har genom förvärv de senaste åren expanderat till den nordiska marknaden. Idag har vi ca 400 anställda specialister i Finland, Sverige och Norge och mer än 10 000 kunder. Vårt mål är att år 2023 vara den ledande leverantören i Norden av tjänster inom fakturans livscykel.
Vad erbjuder vi?
Du får möjligheten att vara en del av ett spännande företag i tillväxtfas med goda personliga utvecklingsmöjligheter i en bred utvecklarroll. Du kommer att få arbeta med olika tekniker och möjlighet att både bevara och förbättra nuvarande system samtidigt som vi tillsammans tänker nytt.
Vi är ett modernt företag som erbjuder dig en stimulerande arbetsmiljö i fina lokaler mitt i centrala Göteborg. Vi arbetar flexibelt och tror på frihet under ansvar. Som medarbetare hos oss blir du en del av vår starka företagskultur som präglas av drivkraft och passion. Vi tänker stort och utmanar oss själva varje dag för att utvecklas både personligt och tillsammans.
Vad kommer du göra i rollen?
Vi söker nu dig som vill vara en del av vårt team som arbetar med design, utveckling och drift av våra inkasso- och dokumentsändningsprodukter på våra plattformar. Arbetet bedrivs till störst del mot Back-End, men har du kunskap och intresse kommer du även få arbeta mot Front-End.
Dina primära arbetssysslor är utveckling, underhåll och att agera som 3rd line support. Dina arbetsuppgifter kommer att variera och du har mandat att, tillsammans med plattformsägaren, prioritera i det dagliga arbetet. Du kommer att arbeta med kontinuerliga förbättringar och kvalitetssäkra förändringar i produktionen för att säkerställa en stabil miljö. I din roll kommer du vara ansvarig för utveckling och produktionssättning av skalbara, flexibla lösningar i våra mjukvaruprogram.
Vårt utvecklingsteam utgår från Göteborg och Stockholm och du kommer ingå i ett engagerat team där vi hjälper varandra till att utvecklas dagligen.
Vi söker dig som har följande egenskaper och kunskaper
Kundorienterad. Du förstår slutkunden och jobbar utifrån att skapa mervärde och positiva kundupplevelser.
Problemlösare. Du identifierar och löser problem på ett effektivt och genomtänkt sätt.
Initiativtagande. Du tar initiativ till löpande förbättringar som behöver genomföras och tar ansvar över att planera och genomföra ditt arbete.
Nyfiken. Du trivs i en föränderlig miljö och är öppen för att utvecklas och lära dig tillsammans med bolaget. Vi tror att du trivs allra bäst om du likt oss är driven och bidrar till teamets positiva energi.
Vi tror att du som sökerHar flerårig erfarenhet av mjukvaruutveckling och kvalitetssäkring.Har goda kunskaper inom relevanta programmeringsspråk, främst inom C++. Med fördel har du även erfarenhet av:

MS SQL / T-SQL
.NET (C) and ASP.NET stack
React - TypeScript – JavaScript
Azure Cloud & DevOps platform

- Har en akademisk- eller högre yrkesexamen inom IT, alternativt motsvarande arbetserfarenhet.
Behärskar flytande svenska och/eller engelska.
ÖVRIG INFORMATION
Start: 1 september 2022.
Plats: Göteborg.
Anställningsform: Detta uppdrag är en rekrytering och anställningen sker direkt hos vår kund. Lön, villkor och dylikt diskuteras separat.
Rekryteringsprocessen hanteras av A-hub. Ropo Capitals önskemål är därför att alla frågor rörande tjänsten hanteras av A-Hub. Varmt välkommen att kontakta ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Agnes Stolt vid frågor om tjänsten via agnes@a-hub.se.

column1: Developer who loves to make magic with code
column4:
Prisjakt helps thousands of consumers safely navigate and make better decisions in the e-commerce world every single day. We want to help them so they never have to feel that they regret buying something, or discovering they could have gotten it cheaper or faster from some other shop. To make this even more of a reality for our users we are looking for curious and skilled developers to join our journey for better decisions!
Teams
When working as a developer at Prisjakt you will find yourself in one of our domain teams. That means that you are part of an agile cross-functional team that is dedicated to a specific area of Prisjakt. The team will consist of the skills needed for the current mission, and that can mean that you can find yourself in a team with other skilled frontends, backend, and native developers, UX designers, and architects, DevOps, or marketing specialists. The teams are the experts of their domain and with common sense and great cooperation, you’ll be able to find the paths you want to take towards our goals.
Where will you find yourself in this setup? Well, it depends on you! Based on what areas you prefer whether it’s the backend, frontend, or a bit of both - we’ll find the team you fit in and where you can grow even more.
Experimenting/data
With lots of data and many people that use our product, we have both challenges and opportunities. We navigate through these by constantly trying new things and seeing what sticks through experimentation and A/B testing. Together with your peers you’ll learn from what didn’t succeed and try again, and celebrate when you do succeed. What we’ll end up with is epic functionality that our users love.
Your vibe and tribe

You’re a developer with experience and expertise, who understands that the playing field around you is constantly changing and evolving. You are curious and don’t sit around and wait for work to come to you - you are a doer and drive initiatives like it’s all you’ve ever done. And if you run into any obstacles along the way you adapt, find a solution and keep going. This combined with the fact that you’re very results driven and love to learn things, which makes you pop new ideas like microwave popcorn.
What you bring
Proven experience of JavaScript / React / TypeScript / Node.js
No stranger to continuous releases
An agile mindset and a big amount of curiosity
Bonus points
ElasticSearch
GraphQL
Python
MySQL
Microservice thinking
Cloud services, like GCP, AWS etc
Where: You will be located at our beautiful Malmö or Ängelholm studio but great news, we are a hybrid working company which means that you have the flexibility to sometimes work from home as well.
When: We would like you to start tomorrow but we understand that you have obligations today and those need to be handed over first.
We want you to start loving Mondays
At Prisjakt, you don’t need a work persona. Our dearest principle is that you’re welcome just as you are. We’ve made it our mission to make you feel excited about Mondays and also make it easier for you to manage the hassle of everyday life. We are proud of our relaxed and familiar atmosphere. In addition to working, you will also be able to fix your torn jeans in our creative workshop or learn how to make a proper espresso. With our epic printer Printz Charming, we dress our walls with whatever art we like, and our scooter swiftly gets you to your lunch date. Kids are always welcome, and you are free to borrow tools from the workshop for your home improvement projects. You can read more about us in the Prisjakt Culture book. If you like it - you’ll definitely like us.

Annevo is expanding to Stockholm and we're looking for visionaries to work with. Frontend, backend and fullstack developers, UX designers. Get in contact with us!

About us
   Founded in 2011, Billhop is a technology company on a mission to continuously develop great products.  We are active in the exciting intersection of card payments, banking infrastructure and a lot of API’s. With a proven demand for the product, we are now in an expansive phase and are growing our tech department.  Read more about our recent investment by EQT Ventures here. This is your chance to join Billhop’s software engineering team, winners of the Deloitte Digital “Most Disruptive Innovation Award” 2020.  The role
   As a Development Team Lead at Billhop, you will be leading a team of software engineers that are developing new features and applications as well as improving and maintaining our current platform. 
  In addition to managing the team and their deliverables – you will also be coding a lot, which we hope makes you feel excited and happy!
   Our infrastructure is based on a Kubernetes cluster with a Pub/Sub running through a dozen of Node-based micro services talking REST. Our frontend applications are written in React and everything is hosted on GCP. We are happy with our setup, but never content and never finished. As team lead, you will have a key role in identifying new technologies to implement and better ways to overcome our challenges.  What you bring:
   
  
  We hope that you are as passionate about software and solving interesting problems as we are. You simply can't wait to start coding and to contribute to a great product that not only works, but also makes you proud. It is important that you are comfortable with discussing complex technical problems with your team. You are also confident in leading a team and have experience from working in an agile environment with multiple scrum teams.   To succeed in this role, we also think you need:
   
   BS degree in Computer Science or related technical field, or equivalent practical experience 
   Strong experience from professional development, primarily using Node/React 
   Experience from development of production grade scalable applications 
   Preferably, you also know a little about databases, Docker and Kubernetes.  What we offer 
   Work in a friendly environment, with approachable colleagues and stimulating challenges 
   An organization with a flat hierarchy and possibility to impact the business and processes from day one 
   Career development in a fast-growing company 
   Competitive remuneration and perks  
  
  We have high ambitions and people that are passionate about what they do. Everyone digs in and makes the most of every day. We discuss, share and learn from each other. Does this sound like you? We would love for you to join our team!

Why is this job for you?
Because you like the idea of working as a product company and want the diversity of projects that comes from being a consultant. It's all about delivering products and services as a team. The core of the everyday business is knowledge sharing. All code is reviewed, fast decision paths and great freedom allow you to develop your skills.
The team is self-managed, so how the problem is solved is up to you. You and your team will pick the technologies needed to solve the task, not the other way around.
What it all boils down to is that we want you to give you the possibility to only focus on what you love the most, solving technical problems.
Build a career that you can be proud of
All projects, whether it is regarding self-driving vehicles, a medical technology solution to fight cancer, or a streaming service, have one thing in common, they are all cloud solutions/products.
Mob programming, code review, tech talks, hackathons, and certifications are some of the ways we can get even better together. That's what it's about, achieving things together.
You are surrounded by people that care. Not just about the project and technology, but about each other. We do it as a team, that's the way forward.
Skills needed
You are experienced as a DevOps Engineer and have for some years been working with cloud products or services.
You feel comfortable working in our tech stack, which consists of (but not exclusively):
Languages and frameworks - Java, C#, NodeJS, React, JavaScript, TypeScript.
Cloud technologies - AWS, Azure.
Orchestration – Serverless, Docker, Kubernetes
Experience in writing scripts for infrastructure using Terraform is meritorious but not a requirement. You need to be fluent in Swedish and English.
One Knightec
Knightec is a new breed in the art of engineering with over 800 colleagues in locations around Sweden. We are consultants with our soul in digitalization who strive forward together.

Company Description
   Are you passionate about digital marketing and advertising technology, and the ever-changing customer acquisition trends? Are you an experienced Azure DevOps Engineer and eager to work with one of the fashion industry’s biggest tech transformations? Do you want to create state of the art solutions to make an impact on a global scale? If you have the passion to build the most innovative online marketing solutions on one of the world’s largest fashion platforms, then this is the opportunity for you to join the Customer Attraction team at H&M Group.
   You will work within the Customer Attraction area, a product area responsible for all digital marketing capabilities across the H&M group. Our mission is to attract new and existing customers into our stores, both digital and physical, across all 8 brands and 74+ markets. Our vision is to lead the H&M Group into the future of retail tech, with our marketing tech capabilities. In Specific, you will be part of the Social Media product team, supporting the H&M Group to become the most loved group of brands on social media, by innovation and by developing our tech foundation.
 
  Job Description
   You will be a part of a global cross functional agile product team, working with a range of end-to-end solutions, focusing on Azure development and cloud engineering. You will play a leading role in technical development and architecture - helping the team with software quality and take personal ownership of the product you ship. Actively seeking ways to shift its design into a cloud enabling microservices architecture. Establishing a holistic view of how the solution adds value to the business.
   We are looking for an all-rounder Azure Developer, aim to work as full stack and cross-functional in the team as possible. You also have experience from true agile ways of working; in this small product team, you will have a great personal responsibility to make things happen.
   Work tasks includes but are not limited to:
  
    DevOps backend development on Azure Cloud.
    Building and setting up new development tools and infrastructure.
    Defining and setting development, test, release, update and support processes for DevOps operations.
    Working on ways to automate and improve development and release processes.
    Building and improving CI/CD pipelines.
    Ensuring that systems and architecture is safe and secure against cybersecurity threats. Performing vulnerability assessment and risk management.
    Working with containerization and releases of microservices
  
 
  Qualifications
   We believe you are communicative, have a "You build it you run it" mindset and able to work in an environment that is not yet formalized. More specifically you need to have/are:
  
    Experience on the Azure platform and resources - Service bus, Data Lake, API Management, Data lake, Logic app, App Service, Azure Function, Azure Event hub, Pipelines, SQL Server etc.
    Working according to enterprise architecture frameworks; principles, policies, standards, patterns, roadmaps.
    Good understanding of the overall Azure infrastructure.
    Knowledge of Git, Jira, Confluence, Splunk, DevOps etc·
    Previous experience working with delivering of technical features.
    Experience of working closely with functional developers and technical teams.
    Good understanding of the different solution layers from front-end/APP to cloud setup.
    Good knowledge with API integration (REST API, Web API) and online marketing platform integration such as facebook, Instagram, snapchat, tiktok etc.
    Experience of working in agile development organizations.
  
   Additional Information
   Besides the obvious perks such as staff discount card, flexible work life, learning communities, wellness benefits, parental benefits etc. You are joining a unique value driven culture, a large tech network and community where you can be yourself.
   At H&M Group we have a strong, value-driven culture characterized by believing in people, teamwork and an entrepreneurial spirit. Here you can be yourself and develop. You will be part of an important project at H&M Group with significant opportunities to influence and make a difference. With the right mindset and ambition, you will find plenty of room to grow. We welcome your application regardless of gender, age, gender expressions, sexual orientation, disabilities, religious beliefs, origin or background.
   If this sounds exciting to you, come join the journey and build the future with us!
   This is a full-time position. Please apply with your CV and Personal letter as soon as possible, no later than the 30th April 2022. If you have any questions about the role, please contact Talent Acquisition Partner Dia Gangwani at dia.gangwani@hm.com

This includes the assessment of user-level data and integration with real-time technologies; formulating testing mechanisms to measure and optimize media performance; and overseeing the execution of recommendations for optimal performance across the wide base of paid and unpaid, online and offline media channels our clients leverage. 
   Responsibilities include: 
   Client Facing 
   
   Hands on implementation of clients' analytics accounts including properties, user management, dashboards, and reporting

   Architect client-side "source of truth" such as a Site Analytics and Marketing Intelligence platform or dashboard

   Project manage account analytics efforts setting company-wide best practices and processes

   Work with the Product team to translate business requirements into new products; Work with Sales team to translate products into outbound opportunities; work with Account Management team to R&D and Commercialize products 
   Educate Accounts, Sales, and Engineering teams on various analytics software to support fulfillment; train employees and offer platform expertise; define roadmap for long-term Customer Analytics needs 
  
  What you bring to it: 
  
   3+ years hands-on experience with Google Analytics 360 and Google Tag Manager 
   Fluent English is required

   Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Management of Information Systems, Math, or Statistics/Economics 
   Excellent analytic, quantitative and problem solving skills with proven ability to deliver actionable insights 
   Proficient in computer applications used to manipulate large datasets to analyze, test, validate and report public web usage data 
   Able to relay technical requirements to engineers for execution of custom code 
   Experience reading API documentation and understanding the technical requirements for implementation with other platforms 
   Experience in tag architecture analysis and using tagging platform(s) to execute proper data flow

Arbetsort:

Som Lead Developer på Factoringgruppen driver du ett litet och sammansvetsat utvecklingsteam i att skapa produkter och lösningar i världsklass. Vårt utvecklingsteam har under en lång tid byggt smarta verktyg och skalbara lösningar för bolaget, vilket är det arbete du kommer delta i och fortsatt leda framåt. Teamet äger och förvaltar de produkter som tas fram och vi värdesätter alltid utrymme till att testa, förbättra och finputsa för att skapa optimerade och välutvecklade lösningar.

Vem är du?

Vi söker dig som har erfarenhet av och förståelse för systemutvecklingens stora betydelse för en digital verksamhet. Du mångsidig och duktig på att sätta dig in i behov hos såväl kollegor som bolagets kunder. Du är inte rädd för att testa nya metoder eller utmana gamla arbetssätt. Framför allt är ditt ledarskap, din sociala förmåga och ditt stora driv för att hitta lösningar där andra ser hinder det som gör att just du passar perfekt för denna roll.

I korthet letar vi efter dig som:
Har gedigen erfarenhet av att utveckla i .Net, C# och React
Har erfarenhet av att jobba med Microsoft Azure, Elasticsearch och Kubernetes
Är duktig på att förstå, bygga och utveckla API:er
Kan omvandla idéer till teknisk implementation
Är mångsidig på så sätt att du både kan programmera, hålla en backlog uppdaterad och samtidigt leda och motivera ett starkt team
Varför Factoringgruppen?

Hos oss får du möjligheten att växa och utvecklas tillsammans med en branschledande aktör. Du får arbeta med den allra senaste tekniken och leda ett skarpt och nyfiket team i spännande utvecklingsprocesser. Framför allt kommer du att vara stolt i slutet av varje arbetsvecka, då du och ditt team återigen förenklat vardagen för såväl våra kunder som dina kollegor genom smarta digitala lösningar.

Omfattning och placering

Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning på heltid med placering på vårt huvudkontor i Göteborg. Här sitter vi centralt i vacker miljö, precis intill Näckrosdammen, med endast fem minuters promenad till Avenyn.

Är du den vi söker?

Då är du varmt välkommen med din ansökan! Du behöver inte ha ett flott CV och ett långt, välformulerat personligt brev. Vi vet av tidigare erfarenhet att personlighet, inställning och motivation är det som krävs för att du ska lyckas hos oss. Bifoga ditt CV och några korta rader om varför just du är rätt person för denna tjänst.

We are looking for a developer who has extensive experience of Drupal development and integration work, with good knowledge of Drupal 8/9. You will work in a collaborative enviroment as part of a scrum team that includes other developers and a project manager.
Together you will build websites and applications for some of Sweden's most well known companies, unions and non profit organizations. Your role is to see and realize solutions, to understand the interaction between system components, to identify and manage risks and to be a strong team player in a Scrum team.
About us
Digitalist is an international digital agency with a balanced focus on business value, customer experience, and employee experience. As a large agency with offices in several countries, there will be plenty of development opportunities. Within the company we have a strong team spirit. We want to be a fun place to work, but more than that, we want for all of our employees to feel valued. We are a conscientious agency that takes the developer experience seriously. We realise that creating a workplace in which our teams thrive is a holistic exercise that involves listening to our teams and adapting. We believe in diversity and know that different backgrounds and areas of expertise make us stronger. Co-creation is our watchword. We enjoy helping, advising and developing each other. Our highest priority is our people.
We build and improve digital products. We mainly work with public sector, NGO:s and unions.
About you
You are humble, thorough and analytical. You keep track of security issues and stay up to date on the latest developments both within the Drupal community as well as in new technologies and methods. We see that you are consultative, communicative and service-oriented. The work involves both working with the customer to develop new functions and work with changes to previously built functionality. You are

a team player
not afraid of raising risks and coming with suggestions for improvements
used to working in agile processes according to scrum
a Senior front-end / fullstack developer
an Open Source enthusiast

Knowledge requirements

You have several years of experience as a Drupal developer and know Drupal 8/9.
You understand the Drupal module ecosystem.
You see details in requirements but can also look up.
You have worked with integration.
You have worked with Scrum before and feel comfortable adopting it’s principals.
You can produce estimates for development activities.
You have worked with automatic tests.
You understand Package managers like Composer and npm.
You have used Git and Gitflow for version control in past professional roles.
Familiarity with terminal development tools like Drush.
Worked before with large teams (+4 people) and large & complex projects.
Experience with some JavaScript framework, preferible VueJS.
Some Employee Benefits

Compliance to a collective agreement
Individual training budget
A generous wellness allowance

Are you a skilled and passionate CAD Engineer? Are you also "Professional, Flexible & Engaging"? Then you are the right person for us!
  
   Assignment description
   We are hiring an CAD Engineer to work at one of our clients within the Automotive industry.
   As a design engineer in Hood & Fender Systems, you play an important role in developing front-end systems. The product team is responsible for developing pedestrian protection system, hood locking system, hood, fender and structural parts that ensures stability in the front end of the car. The team collaborates with a wide variety of stakeholders to find the best solutions and you will work closely with CAE and test engineers as simulation and verification are vital tools in our development process. We work in flexible, cross-functional, product teams tailored to development tasks and in this position, there are always open possibilities for personal development, depending on your interest, self-drive and your initiative. We will support you to reach your full potential.  What you’ll do You will be part of a product team in Hood & Fender Systems that are developing technical solutions according to agile principles and SAFe/VCAF. The work is conducted in an international environment in close co-operation with design, CAE/testing, manufacturing, our factories and external suppliers. You will focus on product development in programs but also be open to contribute to our advanced engineering projects or concept investigations to support our development of new technology introductions.
  
   Requirements
   You enjoy working in a changing environment, which challenges you in a positive way. You understand business value and you got the ability to analyse information and prioritize your tasks accordingly. You take responsibility for the team's and your commitments. Communication, collaboration and personal drive to initiate and drive tasks towards target are key skills for your success.
   Software & IT skills
  
   B.Sc. or M.Sc. in Mechanical Engineering or other equivalent education
   Experience from design engineering using Catia v5 is required
   Experience from sheet metal design and manufacturing is required
   Experience from casted and extruded metal design and manufacturing is required
   Experience from kinematic system design and manufacturing is meritorious
   Experience from Agile, Scrum and SAFe/VCAF is meritorious
  
   Personal attributes
  
   Communicative
   Decisional
   High degree of personal order and drive to targets
   Good people skills
  
   Other information
   Open to Sub-contract and permanent candidates Location of work: Gothenburg Start day: ASAP Extent: Full time starting with a six month probation period
    For more information contact: Bhushan Moghe Email: bhushan.moghe@globallogic.com Tel: 00 46 (0)703775925
  
   About GlobalLogic
   GlobalLogic is a full-lifecycle product development services leader that combines chip-to-cloud software engineering expertise and vertical industry experience to help our customers design, build, and deliver their next-generation products and digital experiences. We expertly integrate design, complex engineering, and agile delivery capabilities to deliver superior business outcomes for global brands in telecom, automotive, healthcare, technology, media and entertainment, manufacturing, and semiconductor industries.
   Headquartered in Silicon Valley, GlobalLogic employs over 11,000 designers and engineers across the globe. Analysts like NASSCOM and Zinnov have recognized us for being a top company in our field, and we are consistently nominated as a preferred employer by both global HR consultative firms and local job boards. By creating a work environment that is exciting and flexible, and by fostering growth through ongoing learning and development programs, we empower our employees to achieve both their professional and personal goals.
   At GlobalLogic, we make amazing products — and careers.

column1: Engineer Lead - Build, Coach and Develop an amazing Tech...
column4:
If you love to work helping engineering teams to grow and face great challenges, at Streamloots you will be building a team of dreamers who know how to also be relentless doers.
You will have the possibility to work 100% remote, working in an international and fast-growth startup where all the team members would like to have a positive impact helping the creators to turn their passions into livelihoods.
Please check our mission statement and values, which are two fundamental components of our culture and daily routine.
Your mission is to inspire and lead engineers from product squads, nourishing them with new and interesting challenges while ensuring the quality of its technical deliverables. Technical leadership and people management is your daily basis.
In this position, you will be able to have a wonderful contribution and impact in different areas:
As Engineer Manager
Work closely with the Product Manager on your team to drive team strategy and direction.
Work with other Engineers Leads across the department to improve our processes and systems.
Support, coach, mentor, and further develop your direct reports through continuous feedback, regular 1:1s and performance reviews.
Manage Strategically: You will track team performance metrics because as you know, what is not measured cannot be improved, and as a manager, this is your opportunity to give feedback and make decisions to ensure the alignment of the team with the agreed strategy.
Own the growth of the team: You will be the one identifying and making decisions on what profiles are needed to build a highly engaged distributed and diverse tech team, leading the recruitment and the onboarding.
As Tech Lead
Lead with your best practices: You will be a leader focused on educating, promoting, bringing & evangelizing about best practices, to help the team members to enjoy more and more of their daily work, feeling safe and experts, raising the quality of the execution and being proud of our deliveries and creations.
Your voice is important: With the CTO and the rest of the team, your voice will be a key opinion to decide on our technology architecture.
Become a reference: We will help you to become an external reference in the field, adding value to tech talent networks to attract the best people in our team.
As part of the team
Understand the operative: We believe in internal development and promotion, and also in the expertise that we have accumulated with the current team, for this reason, you will contribute to producing code and developing our core technology in 50% of the time during the first 3 months.
Lead by example: After this time you will know perfectly the current processes and architectures, and also you will be able to win the credibility of the team as an engineer and role model. Then you will work in this area 30% of the time.

Long story, short: How will be your first days in Streamloots?
First month: For the first few weeks we will make sure you know your impact on the team and the business, learning about the team, the business and processes. You will meet every contributor on your team and understand what their areas of expertise are. Little by little, you will begin to have one-on-one meetings with the CTO who will take care of your professional and personal development. An, also, you will be a participant in the meetings and processes that after you will lead, we don’t expect you to lead from the beginning, take your time to land your own conclusions.
First Quarter: within the first three months, you will start impacting by leading your own team. You will work with product and design to prioritize the roadmap and drive the iteration planning process, working with engineers, product manager and design. Work with engineers on your team to understand their short-term and long-term goals and help them with their career planning and progression. And engaging with your peer engineer leads around improving our engineering processes to help us operate more efficiently.
To the moon: After this process, you will become a role model, inspiring the rest in their development and helping them to achieve their career goals. Streamloots will challenge you to grow in your impact on the company, as you will do with the teams, we will work to help you enjoy yourself at work. We expect you to train and share your knowledge with others, and change Streamers Lives! :D

Job requirements. You’ll be successful in your mission if:
5+ years working in software development, preferably for a product company handling high levels of traffic. You don’t have to be a full expert in our stack, but it is important you can learn, understand and develop great practices aligned with our technical challenges. Our main stack is in JavaScript / TypeScript (React + Redux client-side application; API with Node.js, MongoDB and Redis) deployed in Docker containers running in AWS infrastructure.
3+ years managing at least one cross-functional, diverse team in an agile startup environment (4 to 8 engineers). We are going to face great challenges that will demand a lot of us, and we are searching for someone who walks the talk with a clear leadership mindset and organizational abilities. Interested in personal development, values and principles.
Experience working cross functionally to build prioritized roadmaps for your teams. Strategic thinking and ability to prioritize and plan iterative developments, avoiding over-engineering without impacting product quality and customer needs, and relying on business data and metrics to guide the workload.
Knowledge about good practices in development and its implementation, providing technical leadership to the team and working with engineers to help guide them into important technical decisions, and also making improvements in team structure, processes, and delivery.
Experience working with engineers of all levels and have coached them in their career development. Mentoring in an open, respectful, flexible, empathetic manner. Fostering a culture of mentoring across the team by seeking out mentoring opportunities for themselves and others, and supporting others in their growth.
Outstanding ability to communicate (verbal, written and presentation) up and down the organization, from individuals and departments leads to C-Suite.
Native or fluent English. In the product team, marketing and every day more areas are people who are English Native. Also, it would be helpful if you also know Spanish.

What we offer:
Remote Company: That means that team members will be able to work from wherever they want. Also means that all processes need to be thought of as if we had no office and everyone is working remotely. No one will feel an outsider, since all conversation will have to happen on slack or zoom/hangouts.
The annual meetups: Once per year, we will all gather to work altogether. We will try to make it for the week of the Company & Team KR's definition.
Disrupt an industry with tech and data-oriented solutions. We started 4 years ago, and now, over 50,000 streamers in more than 20 different countries have increased their revenue interacting with their fans on Streamloots. We're funded by leading global tech investors, including Bessemer.
Competitive salary and stock option plan. We are working to align our budgets with the market, and we believe that our salary packages are deeply competitive.

If you are excited with the things that you just read, please don't hesitate to apply for the job position.

This exclusive role is only available through Jefferson Frank, an international agency that has grown to be one of the trusted recruitment partners to businesses across Sweden in different industries and domains. To learn more about this opportunity, reach out to George Paxton on LinkedIn who is responsible for this advert. You can also reach him at g.paxton@jeffersonfrank.com.


The Company:

Jefferson Frank are working in partnership with an agile and forward thinking Fintech company that are based in Stockholm. Originally focusing on personal services to the regular worker, they made the decision to switch to the corporate market which has catapulted the company to being one of the most successful of it's type. Their service allows customers to pay ANY invoice with a credit card, making it an efficient operation for all parties. Furthermore, they charge around 3% for their services making them cheaper than factoring or loaning from a bank. In addition to this customers earn points which can offer a range of benefits in return.

As stated, the switch in markets has been hugely beneficial to this client and so they have experienced rapid growth as a result of this. They've achieved €5 million in turnover, grown 1100% in 3 years and have acquired €15 million in funding since the beginning of 2021. Now entering a scaling up phase they are aggressively hiring in 2022 to ensure they keep up with the demand they're experiencing for their services. This initially comes in the form of hiring for multiple Engineering Lead (s) to lead separate applications following a team re-structuring that is setting the company up for the future.


The Role:

As mentioned teams are currently being restructured and split into 2 separate applications which will allow them to deliver a premium service to their customers. The end goal here is to create 2 autonomous, self-sufficient teams which work independently from each other including an Engineering Lead, Product Manager, Quality Assurance and Developers. Both applications are build using the same infrastructure; Node.JS, React, Microservices and GCP. You'll be required to show your experience with full-stack development and a strong competence with all of these technologies. Preferably from a senior/similar role in the past.


This is a hands on position where you'll be immersed in a technical environment, much of your time will be spent coding full-stack. You'll be responsible for building and overseeing your team building API's, troubleshooting and fixing performance related issues and developing scalable solutions. Your core responsibility will be managing the entire application from an architectural standpoint to maintain performance and efficiency.

Both teams will work in an agile methodology and so you'll be managing the scrum. You will be working alongside the product manager, translating business needs into tech stories for developers whilst assurance due diligence is completed with quality assurance through code reviews. In addition to this, you'll be responsible for training and mentoring the more junior members of the development team.


Requirements:

Previous experience as an Engineering Lead or a similar, technical roleStrong full-stack experience with Node.JS & React (minimum 3 years) having built API's and/or microservices from scratch to be added to an already existing infrastructureCloud experience (preferably with GCP) used for deployment and hosting servicesExperience managing a microservices architecture
Preferable Requirements:

Previous experience as a software architect or having strong architectural responsibilities within a similar position in the pastStrong interest or previous experience with Fintech projects

In return, you'll be joining a rapidly expanding company that has unlimited potential with what is possible in the coming years. Now in significant growth phase, their product is growing in popularity and as a result they're investing heavily in this and marketing to capitalise in the lack of activity within their domain. You'll be joining a company that operates on a flat hierarchy meaning that every employee has the opportunity to add value and their voice can be heard. Furthermore, openness is one of their core values which is reflected in their practices. Alongside your salary, you'll receive a range of benefits including the ITP1 pension, wellness allowance, health insurance and 30 days holiday.

To apply for this position, send your CV via this portal or email it to g.paxton@jeffersonfrank.com. Alternatively, you can reach out to George Paxton on LinkedIn to learn more regarding this position or others which are available at Jefferson Frank.

WELCOME TO UTOPIA
Music is incredible. It can excite hundreds, and unite thousands. But as an industry, it has been slow, complicated, and disparate. While the tech world has moved into the future, the music industry continues to be shaped by inefficient systems of the past. At Utopia we believe there is a better way. Which is why today we are setting out to transform the entire industry; creating new revenue streams, consolidating the data and decluttering the admin. Unlocking the industry’s full potential by unifying it all in one truly holistic space. Some might call that a Utopia.
Funnily enough, so do we. Welcome to Utopia. Where music lives.
WHAT UTOPIANS DO
The open secret is that the music industry is struggling with the very basics of music accounting: What was played, when and where? Who should get paid and how much?
Utopia Music is bridging the data gap by connecting global consumption, accurate metadata, and fast payments to an industry-wide trust platform. Our goal is to unlock creative value and enable Fair Pay For Every Play to make a better world for Music. The solutions we offer do not threaten to usurp the role of industry incumbents - it is about bringing transparency in the industry and supporting efficient royalty collection for all.
THE ROLE
You will lead one of our engineering teams in Stockholm enhancing the outcomes, quality of tech and the people you manage. We believe in the modern approach to build tech products with cross-functional teams including software engineering, product management, data and design. You will inspire your team to innovate and create revolutionary products that change the music industry for better. Starting with a small team which you’ll grow over time to multiple teams. You will hire other managers to support the growing organization; working closely with other leaders to keep our engineering culture strong. We believe that the short feedback loop between operations and development is critical across all the engineering teams: “you build it, you run it”. We champion small and agile teams. You’ll be working on Utopia products built on the Utopia big data platform. We work full-stack including the product infrastructure and user experience. We take a holistic approach to product creation from data to robust backend and customer experience.
REQUIREMENTS
We expect you to understand the tech, care about people and be passionate about building great products. For us, years of experience are just a guidance - what counts is what you have achieved and how.
3+ years of experience managing software engineering teams as a people manager.
3+ years of experience building software powered products preferably operated as SaaS.
Finesse in managing complex cross-functional software projects.
Good knowledge of modern cloud infra and technologies.
History of building software engineering teams from one to multiple teams.
Experience building and leading larger teams and managing through managers.
Understanding of relevant regulation, especially GDPR, and its effect on SaaS services.
Experience working with React, Node.js and Golang.
Passionate about user experience and operational excellence, optimist by heart, paranoid by nature.
Excellent communication skills, fluent in English.
WHAT WE OFFER
Great atmosphere - we live, love & breathe music & tech!
Working in an impact oriented team and inclusive company culture.
An experienced team to learn from, with proven track records in multiple startups and big tech companies.
Our flexible remote policy provides Utopians the freedom to work either from one of our inspiring offices or from home.
We celebrate being an international and multicultural company.
Competitive benefits; packages depend on location. You’ll be given more details on this during the interview process.
We are supporting work permits for employees that moved here from countries outside the EU
THE HIRING PROCESS
You send us your CV in English
We invite you for an introductory video call with the Talent Acquisition team to get to know you better and share more about us
Engineering Manager fit interview covering people- and project management
You meet the hiring manager for the culture fit interview
Meeting the team
UTOPIANS
As we want to bring transparency, trust, and clarity to the music industry we serve, we know a change comes from within. Utopia is a transparent, trust-based organization striving to have clarity in thinking and doing what we set out to do.
We execute urgently and innovate to grow faster. We ship things that make a difference today, so we can make them better tomorrow. We embrace fairness and are all accountable.
Strictly diverse and inclusive. We are an equal opportunity employer.
We celebrate our diverse backgrounds and we welcome everyone who identifies with the above to apply. Welcome to Utopia - Where Music Lives!

We’re eager to meet You! :)

Role

As an Engineering Manager at Kambi, you manage two to three development teams.We believe that to succeed in this role you are a leader with strong ability in empowering individuals and teams and want to be part of a successful and fast-growing company.

You will work proactively with competence development and growth, ensuring that the right skills are within the teams you manage. Ensure team goals by removing blockers and impediments and be a point of contact in escalation. You will support your teams in cross-team communications and foster an open and collaborative culture between teams.

You should have a curious and energetic approach which inspires and engages colleagues and collaborators to achieve, deliver and own their work.

Kambi is in the early phase of a DevOps transformation journey, so if you have some experience of this or are looking for new ways of working in an ever-changing tech organization, this is the right time to join us!

Aside from working with your teams you will also have a responsibility of continuously improve work throughout the Engineering organization. You will together with other Engineering Managers, be a driving force in evolving Kambis development organization to grow in parallel with Kambi global strategy.

At Kambi we believe in the importance of work-life-balance and making that culture part of our day-to-day. We believe that you as well as Kambi benefit from having happy, healthy colleagues.

You will be based in our Stockholm office, working in a team together with other Engineering Managers, reporting to Head of Development. As we are an international and multinational company, our main language is English.

Describes in the cover letter yours way of leading people and why that is successful.

We think the successful candidate:

Has worked as a manager for at least 2 years with development teams in agile environments
Has been involved in a DevOps transformation or worked in a DevOps organization

What’s in it for you?

An opportunity to work in a successful and fast-growing, international company. We are an organization in change, with an ongoing AWS cloud journey and we can offer an exciting environment where you will grow and learn new thing.
You will be able to directly influence the work environment and processes. We also believe in an encouraging environment, and we embrace diversity.

We are curious about your story. If you are interested in meeting us, please apply with a cover letter and your CV.

About Kambi

Kambi Group plc is a leading B2B provider of premium sports betting services to licensed gaming operators. Our services provide an end-to-end solution for operators wanting to launch a standalone Sportsbook or bolster their existing offering with an innovative sports betting product. From front-end user interface to customer intelligence, risk management and odds compiling, all built on our in-house developed software, we strive to deliver the ultimate service and solution to our partners.

Our vision is to create the world’s leading sports betting experiences, together with our partners.

With offices in Malta (HQ), Bucharest, London, Manila, Sydney, Uppsala and Stockholm and together with over 1000 passionate and highly skilled people; Kambi live and breathe sports betting. It is in everything we do. From delivering a premium service to our operators, to creating an entertaining experience for the end user; we are unwavering in our mission to create the worlds’ leading sports betting experience.

On our path to becoming the world's favorite way to shop, we’re assembling an unparalleled global talent network, accelerating individual careers, and disrupting entire industries. We are on a mission to liberate humanity from all the meaningless time spent managing their purchases and finances, so they can do more of what they love. We’re in search of global talent eager to embrace a hypergrowth atmosphere and defy their own expectations.
Engineering at Klarna is an inspired, customer focused community, dedicated to crafting solutions that redefine our industry. Working in small, highly collaborative Agile teams, you and your team will have a clear mission and ownership of an important outcome that supports Klarna and our customers. At Klarna we optimise for quality, flow, fast feedback, focussing on end-to-end ownership, continuous improvement, testing, monitoring and experimentation. We aim for teams that are inclusive, helpful, and have a strong sense of ownership for the things they build.
Our engineers make some of the most significant decisions for the company and we are looking for bold, open and curious developers. As a Klarnaut, you’ll be inspired to contribute to the growth of Europe’s most highly valued fintech and your work will reach millions of users.
Want to be part of the change? We're expanding several of our engineering teams; teams working on our core checkout product, payment services and app, focusing on areas such as infrastructure, UX design or security to name a few.
What you'll get to do:
Inspire, lead, shape and grow a software engineering organization consisting of 3-8 team members.
Manage and drive procurement for third party products that your team depends on.
Drive continuous improvement focusing on quality in your own team and cross teams.
Scope and own a problem space, articulate and develop fact based argumentation and present it to senior management or CXOs, develop vision and mission statement.
Prioritise and optimise for highest speed in execution.
Take calculated risks, anchor with different stakeholders and articulate short and long term consequences.
Continuously develop relationships between product, engineering and key stakeholders across all domains.
Influence and drive software design discussions.
Translate business needs into capability build up and hiring plans in own team.
Play a key role in helping us continue attracting, developing and retaining great engineering talent.
Act swiftly to change of direction, re-evaluate priorities and steer the team accordingly.
Manage the budget for the team and dependencies.
You’ll need to have:
A strong coding ability in JavaScript.
Experience leading cross functional software engineering teams in a fast paced, delivery focused environment.
A track record of delivering influential software, preferably in complex business models and high transaction environments.
Strong people management skills.
Some of the technologies we work with:
Javascript
React and React Native
Redux
Node.js and Express.js.
AWS, Splunk, Ansible, Terraform, Jenkins, Docker and Kubernetes.
What we can offer you
Culture - You'll have an opportunity to work with talented people from 90+ different countries in our offices in Stockholm city center.
Learning - We have a learning and development focused environment with an emphasis on knowledge sharing, training, and regular internal technical talks.
Compensation - You’ll receive an attractive salary, pension, and insurance plans, plus we offer all of our employees an opportunity to invest in a RSU program and own a stake of the company. You’ll also receive 30 days annual leave and since we recognise that life is about more than work, we also offer benefits for gym memberships, marathons, and all sorts of activities that promote physical health. We also have generous parental leave (for men and women).
Relocation - We can offer relocation support to Stockholm.
We also believe in contributing back to the open source community. You can find some of our work here https://github.com/klarna.
How to apply: please send us your CV or LinkedIn profile in English
What we offer:
Diversity & Community
With our diversity of skills, perspectives and backgrounds, we can create, innovate, and disrupt like no other. Diversity is part of who we are, and essential to our success.
Ownership & Impact
Here, every voice matters. We’re organized into hundreds of small teams, each run like a start-up, focused on their own problem-space.

Trust & Collaboration
Successes and failures are won together at Klarna in a melting pot of teams. Win, lose, and learn, we’re on this path together.
The Klarna Work Policy is designed to make sure we foster team collaboration while also ensuring a productive and flexible work environment. We work 2 days per week in the office on agreed days, and then 3 flexible days. We’re also providing each Klarnaut with an annual financial contribution to improve their flexible work life whether they use it to upgrade their work accessories, or their home office space!
Challenges & Rewards
We take a very Swedish approach to benefits. Support for parents, health and wellness perks—we’ve got you covered.

About Klarna
Since 2005 Klarna has been on a mission to revolutionize the retail banking industry. With over 90 million global active users and 2 million transactions per day, Klarna is meeting the changing demands of consumers by helping them save time and money while better managing their cashflow and making informed decisions. Over 250,000 global retail partners, including H&M, Saks, Sephora, Macys, IKEA, Expedia Group, and Nike have integrated Klarna's innovative technology to deliver a seamless shopping experience online and in-store. With over 5,000 employees, Klarna is active in 20 markets and is one of the most highly-valued private fintechs globally, with a valuation of $45.6 billion. For more information, visit Klarna.com
It is our commitment that every qualified person will be evaluated according to skills regardless of age, gender, identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability status or religion. Please refrain from including your picture and age with the application.

Engineering Manager to Alva Labs
A woman has to send in 30% more applications to get a job. For a person of color, that number goes up to 50%. At the same time, only 19% of all hires made are deemed to be a complete success. Some candidates never get a fair chance, while others are getting flooded with requests. Simply based on a few lines on a CV or on Linkedin.
There is something seriously wrong with the hiring market. We want to change that. Don’t you?
Alva Labs is looking to add another lead engineer to drive one of our squads, and together with a product manager and a designer, own a surface of our product.
The company
Alva Labs is a Stockholm-based SaaS company that offers a solution that is helping global companies grow their team in a scientific way. Alva has created a unique candidate assessment platform that helps companies build their organizations with the right people in the right place. By combining state-of-the-art psychometrics, data science, and an obsession with candidate experience, provides the needed tool for data-driven talent acquisition.
We are growing 2-3x per year and are in the exciting phase to launch Alva in new markets. The current focus is on building a great product, enabling Product-Lead-Growth, and releasing our next big bets.

The role
The team is currently divided into three different squads, At the end of the year, we are looking at six to seven squads. Each focuses on one product surface. In the role of engineer manager, you will manage and drive your own squad. In close collaboration with other experienced engineers as well as designers, and product managers, you will make sure we make a difference for candidates and recruiters, worldwide.
Within 1 month you will:
Get the support you need from your squad in order to get a good start at Alva.
Contribute to your squad’s delivery by writing code.
Manage your squad’s processes and ways of working.

Within 3 months you will:
Have a good understanding of both the existing system and Alva’s architectural vision.
Be managing the planning and discovery of new features and functionality.

Within 6 months you will:
Assume full accountability for the technical aspects of the functionality that your squad is working on.
Be responsible for the performance development of your squad members.
Collaborate daily with the squad’s product manager, together you will build features that help our customers to take their recruitment to the next level.
Be an important part of growing the engineering team at Alva to the next level.

Our tech stack:
Python
React, JavaScript/TypeScript
Google Cloud Platform
Pub/Sub
PostgreSQL, Firestore
Kubernetes, Cloud Run
GraphQL
Protocol buffers
Event-driven microservices
Curious to know more? The tech stack is described in more detail HERE.
You
We believe you have worked a couple of years as a software engineer, ideally you have led technical discovery work and driven projects before. Except that, you are:


A humble leader.
A master of turning complex problems into solutions that breathe simplicity.
Ambitious and goal striving.
A prestigeless team player.
You enjoy sharing your knowledge to help other members of the team improve their engineering skills.
Our internal language is English, so no need to speak Swedish.


What we offer
7 weeks of vacation!
On-market salary and stock options.
Flexible work hours and a hybrid model (you decide if you are at the office or remote).
Opportunities to grow both your technical and leadership skills.
A well-used and appreciated system to work on (with limited technical debt and legacy).
A company that actually puts the product first.
60+ coworkers from 16+ nationalities (If you want to creep on the team, fire away!).
A value- & purpose-driven organization that has the opportunity to change the world of hiring, and impact lives (read about our company values HERE).
You can read more about our benefits HERE.

The hiring process
Given that we claim to be experts in hiring, you probably wonder what we have in store for you.

Objective screening with Alva’s own tests
First interview (focusing on who you are)
Case
Technical interview with pair-programming
Final interview with Head of Engineering
Done deal!

Come help us impact peoples’ lives!
Welcome to Alva!

We are growing fast and looking to find experienced developers to join our great team at our amazing new office!
Whether you are passionate about tech, esports or both we can offer a unique opportunity to build state of the art data- manipulation and visualisation applications and user dashboards in a fast-moving business. We're looking for someone that wants to be challenged and want to challenge us, someone passionate about technology and motivated to see both yourself and the team as a whole grow and excel!

Role description
For us, a frontend engineer is someone who has an equal passion for design and the user experience as for the structure, scalability, abstraction and quality of the codebase. We are looking for someone who finds excitement in creating both functional designs and workflows to solve everyday tasks, and in producing engaging data visualisations on the web.
It is also important that you are open to new challenges and have a willingness to learn from colleagues as well as research new topics as needed.
Some of the technologies you will work with are:
React & nextjs
Typescript
Styled components and storybook
Data visualisations
CI/CD pipelines
Some applications you will work with are:
Widgets
Widgets are ‘ready made’ front end content for customers who don't have the time or resources to build esports content from scratch. These widgets consist of a number of ‘content components’ that the customers can combine as they see fit, and then style according to their brand guidelines. This is a challenge in developing components captivating data visualisations and internet-scale performance. See more here and here.

Website
Our website is our main way to interact with potential customers and industry colleagues. The site is continuously evolving and a great place to be able to try out new design patterns and develop interactive demo products.

Customer Dashboard
In addition to our public website and documentation, we offer all our customers a dashboard where they can administer their accounts. The dashboard allows customers to see logs and graphs of their request patterns towards our APIs, read their error logs as well as administer their payment details and download receipts. All to keep the Abios user experience smooth.

Admin CMS
To edit and check all of our data for the development, sales and editorial teams, we have a custom CMS system built from scratch to suit our needs. The system allows engineers and editors to enter and alter data, and respond to events and alarms from services in our platform.

column1: Erfaren backendutvecklare med intresse för systemarkitektur
column4:
Skicka ansökan 
   
  
  
  
   
    Om oss Vi är ett produktbolag som erbjuder högkvalitativa, webbaserade produkter inom fastighets- och mäklarbranschen. Produkterna är integrerade med varandra och de olika affärssystem som finns för fastighetsmäklare, samt andra verktyg som våra samarbetspartners använder.
     SE360 ingår i en koncern med andra bolag inom fastighets- och mäklarbranchen. Utvecklingsbolaget står på egna ben inom koncernen och arbetar även mot SE360’s systerbolag Zentuvo Finland samt bostadsregistret.se. 
     Vi är just nu åtta personer på utvecklingsavdelningen och har ambitionen att växa med två till under 2021.
    
     Arbetsuppgifter
     I rollen som Backendutvecklare kommer du att utveckla både befintliga och nya produkter. Du kommer att ingå i ett litet, tajt team som jobbar i en agil utvecklingsmiljö. Våra team arbetar full stack och har ett helhetsansvar över de produkter de utvecklar. Tillsammans sköter vi allt från planering, UX, utveckling och underhåll till test, drift och devops. Eftersom vi är ett litet team och alla är delaktiga från idé till färdig funktion gör det arbetsuppgifterna väldigt varierande.
     Din profil
     Du tycker att det är viktigt med välskriven och strukturerad kod av hög kvalitet och har vana av, eller en önskan om, att jobba testdrivet. Som backendutvecklare lockas du av att driva utvecklingen av vår produktsvit framåt på ett strukturerat och skalbart sätt. Är du dessutom intresserad av arkitektur (i både stort och smått), säkerhet eller integrationer, är det meriterande. Som person är du är initiativrik och samarbetsvillig och gillar att jobba i team, med varierande arbetsuppgifter på ett litet produktbolag.
     Vi tror att du:
     
      Har en relevant utbildning eller 3-5 års motsvarande erfarenhet som kan bedömas som likvärdig 
     Har god erfarenhet av .Net samt Microsoft Azure 
     Har erfarenhet och intresse av infrastruktur och systemarkitektur 
     Bor i Sverige och pratar svenska, eller har ambitionen att lära dig. 
    
     Vår Tech stack
     
     Backend i .NET, C# 
     Frontend i React + Typescript 
     Allt driftas i Microsoft Azure, framför allt med Docker och Kubernetes 
     UX baerat på Material Design med ett gemensamt komponentbibliotek 
     MSSQL, MongoDb 
    
     Vi erbjuder 
    Möjligheten att påverka hur både teamet och produkterna utvecklas framåt inom en spännande bransch, samt vilka tekniker vi ska använda. Vi jobbar kontinuerligt med kompetensutveckling där varje utvecklare tilldelas en pott att spendera efter eget val. Du får frihet att vara kreativ. Vi har kontinuerliga lab-dagar och varvar kontorsjobb med stor frihet att jobba på distans.
     Kontakt
     För frågor om tjänsten kontakta vår Utvecklingschef Jonathan Ljungblad, på jonathan@se360.se.

      Roll
      
     
      Backendutvecklare

      Göteborg 
     
     
      Distansarbete
      
     
      Hybrid 
     
    
   
  
  
   
    
     
      Göteborg 
      
       Gamlestadsvägen 18A 
       415 02 Göteborg Vägbeskrivning info@se360.se 031-68 10 66 Se sida 
      
     
    
   
  
  
  
   
    
     Om SE360 
     
      Sveriges första rikstäckande leverantör av fototjänster till fastighetsbranschen. Vi skräddarsyr helhetslösningar utifrån kundens och marknadens behov. Hos oss finns alla kompetenser som krävs för proffsiga bilder, effektivt säljmaterial, imagebyggande projekthemsidor och snygga planritningar.
