column1: Front End Developer - Data Visualization - Malmo
column4:
From our technology to our team members, Neo4j is built on relationships.
   
   
   
     As part of Neo4j product engineering, you will work together with a diverse team of talented colleagues from around the world. Our culture encourages engineers who want to become deep experts in a particular field – or to build broad expertise across several technologies. Our engineers regularly work with peers in field engineering and experience the full lifecycle of the systems they build.
   
   
   
     We build technology that helps cure cancers, addresses diabetes, and gets humans to Mars. We're proud to fight fraud, crush pandemics, and even help journalists uncover the truth. Neo4j’s engineering teams are located in Malmö, Sweden and London, UK.
   
   
   
     Please submit your CV and cover letter in English.
   
   
   
     The Role: 
   
   
    Our team makes 
    Neo4j Bloom, the graph visualisation product from Neo4j. It allows non-technical business users to search and explore connected data. It features a high-performance GPU-accelerated graph visualisation engine, and an innovative natural-language search system. We have a roadmap of additional powerful features and we are growing the team to build them.
     
   
   
    
   
    This is an exciting time to join the Neo4j Bloom team.
   
   
  
   
    What You'll get to do: 
    
     Work on brand-new innovative features Build things that you won’t find in a normal web application Make software that people use to get their daily job done
    
   
   
  
   
    What You'll Bring:
    
      Knowledge of and experience with a graph database, such as Neo4j Proficiency with data visualization libraries like d3.js Understanding of ETL concepts such as data modelling and transformation Experience doing UI/Front-end development with a solid knowledge of modern JavaScript, HTML5, and CSS3 At least bachelor degree in relevant computer science Exceptional proven communication skills excellent stakeholder management Experience with client-side frameworks and libraries such as React, Redux, Angular.js, Vue.js and CycleJS Experience with BDD, TDD, and JavaScript testing frameworks (Jasmine, Mocha/Chai, Selenium) Experience with build tools such as Grunt, Gulp or Webpack Comfortable working in a distributed team and ability to work autonomously and with initiative when necessary User-first design thinking
    
   
   
  
   
    Country
    
      SE
    
   
  
  
  
   
     Neo4j Values:
   
   
     Our work in Neo4j Engineering is guided by our company values:
   
   
   
     (we)-[:VALUE]->(relationships)
   
   
     (we)-[:FOCUS_ON]->(:UserSuccess)
   
   
     (we)-[:THRIVE_IN]->(:Culture {type: [‘Open’, ‘Inclusive’})
   
   
     (we)-[:ASSUME]->(:Intent {direction:’Positive’})
   
   
     (we)-[:WELCOME]->(:Discussions {nature: ‘IntellectuallyHonest’})
   
   
     (we)-[:DELIVER_ON]->(ourCommitments)
   
   
   
     Why Join Neo4j?
   
   
     Neo4j is one of the 20 most popular databases in the world, and the leader in the rapidly emerging Graph Database category. We’re building the technology that enables connected data to solve the world’s most pressing problems. You’ll work on unique engineering projects that challenge what’s possible.
   
   
   
     We have customers in every industry across the globe, and our products a proven product/market fit. Joining our team is an opportunity to shape the future of data and analytics.
   
   
   
     We pride ourselves on being a welcoming team. Most of us would agree that one of the best parts of working at Neo4j is the people we get to work with.
   
   
   
     We encourage you to apply even if you don’t 100% fit the qualifications above. Why? Because we are committed to building an environment that fosters belonging, which means valuing intellectually honest discussions and being receptive to new ideas and perspectives.
   
   
   
     One of our central objectives is to provide an inclusive, diverse, and equitable workplace for everyone to develop their potential and have a positive, career-defining experience.
   
   
   
     About Neo4j:
   
   
     Neo4j is the leader in graph database technology. As the world’s most widely deployed graph database, we help organizations – including NASA, UBS and Volvo Cars – to reveal and predict how people, processes and systems interrelate. Using this relationships-first approach, applications built using Neo4j tackle connected data challenges such as analytics and artificial intelligence, fraud detection, real-time recommendations and knowledge graphs.
   
   
   
     Neo4j is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. Please read the privacy notice regarding Neo4j's recruitment process to understand how we will handle the personal data that you provide.
   
   
     More information at www.neo4j.com.

Paf skiljer sig från andra spelbolag. Bolaget grundades av Folkhälsan på Åland, Röda Korset, Rädda Barnen och dåtida Stiftelsen Dagens Barn. Paf strävar efter en långsiktigt hållbar verksamhet och bryr sig om deras anställda, kunder och samhället i stort. Ansvarsfullt spelande är en viktig byggsten i verksamheten. All vinst går till samhällsnyttiga ändamål
   Vill du vara med och jobba med teknik i framkant? Vill du dessutom ha en stor flexibilitet med remote-arbete samt flexibla arbetstider? Paf expanderar och utökar med vassa Front End Developers! Vi söker både dig som är erfaren men också dig som är i början på din karriär. 
  Om tjänsten Som Front End Developer på Paf kommer du vara med och utveckla användargränssnittet i Paf:s olika system. Det finns en tydlig arbetsfördelning där alla vet vad som förväntas av dem. Du kommer att arbeta i en snabbfotad miljö där arbetat inkluderar att ständigt ligga i framkant där du förvaltar och vidareutvecklar företagets system. Tjänsten passar därmed dig som älskar programmering och vill arbeta i ett bolag som värnar om sin personal och deras personliga utveckling.
   Teamen idag präglas av en arbetsmiljö med högt i tak där alla är välkomna. Tjänsten är placerad i Norrköping men det är möjligt att arbeta på distans om du bor på annan ort. 
  
   Det här, och mycket mer får du som utvecklare på Paf: 
    
   
    Flexibla arbetstider för att jobbet ska gå ihop med din fritid 
    Generösa villkor vad gäller pension, friskvård, fri sjukvård etc 
    Paf undviker övertid. Att du är kvar på bolaget om 10 år är viktigare än kortsiktiga affärsmål 
   
  
  Kolla gärna in Paf:s tech-radar här för att se vilka tekniker du får jobba med
   Arbetsuppgifter Som Front End Developer är du delaktig i hela utvecklingsprocessen och arbetar därför bl.a. med; kravspecifikationer, feedback på mockups, skapande av stories, estimeringar, sprintplanering, utveckling/programmering, testning och release.
   Vi söker dig som  Vi söker duktiga Front End Developers som är tekniskt nyfikna och brinner för programmering. Det viktiga är inte att du har gått en specifik utbildning, utan att du är en duktig programmerare. Vi söker både dig som är erfaren men också dig som är i starten på din karriär.  Vi ser att du har förvärvat kunskaper och erfarenhet inom något eller några av följande tekniker, antingen genom utbildning, arbete, eller på annat sätt: 
  
   React 
   TypeScript 
   GraphQL 
  
  
   Du bör även stämma in på följande: 
    
   
    God kommunikationsförmåga i svenska 
    Prestigelös 
    Driven 
    Brinner för programmering 
    Samarbetsförmåga 
    Självgående 
    Ansvarstagande 
   
    
   Information om företaget
    Paf är ett nordiskt spelbolag som grundades 1966 på Åland för att generera vinst till samhällsnyttiga ändamål. Vi blev ett av de första spelbolagen online när vi 1999 tog verksamheten till nätet. Många av Paf.coms spel har skapats av vår egen Games Studio och finns därmed bara hos oss. Vi är prisbelönta och branschledande inom ansvarsfullt spelande. Paf bedriver också fysisk spelverksamhet ombord på över 30 kryssningsfartyg på Östersjön och Nordsjön. 
  
  Paf har cirka 400 anställda från över 30 olika länder och vi har kontor på Åland samt i Helsingfors, Stockholm, Riga, Tallinn, Oslo, Norrköping och Madrid och Gzira. Paf (Ålands Penningautomatförening) licensieras och kontrolleras av Ålands landskapsregering. 
  Under 2019 omsatte Paf-koncernen sammanlagt 114,2 miljoner euro och gjorde en vinst på 25,6 miljoner euro. Mer information finns på aboutpaf.com
   Startdatum och omfattning: Omgående med hänsyn till uppsägningstid. Heltid, med flexibla arbetstider
   Övrig information 
  
   I rekryteringsprocessen kommer det ingå ett programmeringstest. Om du vill visa upp projekt som du gjort i tidigare arbeten eller på fritiden välkomnas även detta i din ansökan. 
   Placering: Paf har kontor i Norrköping och Stockholm, men är flexibla vad gäller placeringsort. Bor du hellre kvar på annan plats i Sverige så går det att ordna också. 
   Tjänsten är en direktrekrytering vilket innebär att rekryteringsprocessen sker genom Tech Talents, men du kommer att anställas direkt hos Paf. Paf:s önskemål är att alla frågor kring tjänsten går till Tech Talents och ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Martin Rehn. martin.rehn@techtalents.se eller 0738445206 
   Vi går igenom urvalet löpande och annonsen kan stängas ner innan tjänsten är tillsatt. Sök därför tjänsten så snart du kan! 
  
  
   
   
  Tech Talents är ett dotterbolag till Vinnergi AB och ingår i en större koncern. Huvudägare är Sobro AB, en engagerad och långsiktig ägarpartner. Genom affärsglädje, fokus på företagskultur och medarbetare samt tydliga målsättningar är de med och bygger våra lönsamma företag med god tillväxt och bestående värden. 
  Läs gärna mer om oss här!

column1: Front End Developer to tech startup
column4:
Our client, an exiting tech startup from the real estate industry, is looking for FullStack/ BackEnd (link to job ad here) and FrontEnd Wizards!
Since their launch in 2018 they are growing really rapidly, so as their needs. To make sure they succeed in their journey we are looking for a highly motivated individual with a passion for tech and data to deliver the best quality code.
Who are we looking for?
To succeed in the role, you have at least 2 years of experience in front-end development. You are a positive and self-driven person who takes responsibility, initiative and can see the bigger picture. You also have the following skill set:

Deep knowledge in developing reactive web applications using Vue.js and TypeScript
Translate our brand identity to responsive and user-friendly layout with CSS and Sass
Understand how to send and retrieve data using REST APIs and fetch
Experience, knowledge, and interest in UI/UX best practices
Maintain local browser storage according to GDPR
Ability to write and maintain unit tests to reduce defects and increase code maintainability
Other nice to haves: Vuex, Vue Router, Webpack 5, Babel, Bootstrap, SignalR

What will be your responsibilities?
You will play the key-role in the process of building new features, maintaining current features and forming the user experience for our users. As a work model, you will work closely with our Tech Team leader.

Build the front-end of our web application, from concept to release with a mission to deliver an enterprise level product experience
Suggest and be part of decision-making regarding designing the user experience
Strive for technical excellence, great design and best practices implementation
Keep updated with modern browser capabilities and use this to create a better user experience

What can we offer you?

An exciting journey in one of Europe’s hottest PropTech startups
A thriving and mission driven work environment
Competitive compensation package

SELLPY WHO?
   At Sellpy we develop an international, climate-positive selling service and e-commerce for second hand. Our idea is to make circular living as convenient as traditional online shopping but without harm to our planet. Since launching, we’ve given new life to more than 10 million pre-owned items, saving almost 16 billion liters of water.
   Building a scalable, high-pace, and transaction intense e-commerce platform has its challenges. We thrive on finding elegant solutions to those challenges and realizing them through clean and simple code.
   With a user-centric approach, we build the Sellpy platform by understanding our users wants and needs. As a part of the team, you will always get your voice heard, and together we aim to deliver results that we are proud of.
   ABOUT YOU
   Like us, you are dedicated to solving challenges through simple solutions that come from an understanding of the core of the challenge and a deep knowledge of the tech at your disposal.
   You take responsibility for the tasks that you take on and make sure that what we build is right for the customer, integrates well with the current architecture and runs well once it is deployed.
   You are communicative and helpful to your colleagues and share your knowledge in a prestige less and humble fashion. You are a team player who is as open to learning from teammates as you are sharing your knowledge with them.
   THE ROLE
   What you will do:
   
    Build user-centric, next generation web applications 
   Work with JavaScript and the React/React Native framework 
   Develop features from start to finish across the stack and take responsibility for your own code 
   Continuously improve and simplify Sellpys’ clients to maintain low complexity 
   Drive the technical development of Sellpys’ clients forward 
  
   Your qualifications:
   
    B.S. or M.S. degree in Computer Science, or a related technical field (3 or 5 years) or a shorter education but a couple of years work experience. 
   Very good knowledge of JavaScript 
   Speaks and writes fluently in English 
  
   We are impressed if you have:
   
    Proven ability with a couple of years experience as a front end engineer/developer 
   Worked in a team with responsibility for both technology and colleagues 
   Worked in a fast-growing, product-focused startup environment 
   Knowledge of React, React Native, Angular 2+, Vue, Ember, Web Components, Continuous Integration, Continuous Deployment, Logging and monitoring 
   Languages such as Swedish and/or German 
  
   How to apply: Upload your CV/links/LinkedIn and motivate why this seems like the perfect role for you! We work with ongoing selection.
   Location: Stockholm, Frihamnen
   Time type: Full-time
   Start: As agreed upon
   At Sellpy you will have the opportunity for a great environmental as well as social impact by changing the shopping behavior of Sweden, Europe, and beyond.

Job Title: Front End Software Developer  Location: Uppsala, Sweden Reference: 203073BR  Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc. is the world leader in serving science, with annual revenue of approximately $40 billion. Our Mission is to enable our customers to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer. Whether our customers are accelerating life sciences research, solving complex analytical challenges, increasing productivity in their laboratories, improving patient health through diagnostics or the development and manufacture of life-changing therapies, we are here to support them. Our global team of more than 100,000 colleagues delivers an unrivaled combination of innovative technologies, purchasing convenience and pharmaceutical services through our industry-leading brands, including Thermo Scientific, Applied Biosystems, Invitrogen, Fisher Scientific, Unity Lab Services, Patheon and PPD.  Thermo Fisher Scientific Sweden has an exciting opportunity for a Front End Software Developer. This position is based in Uppsala, where Thermo Fisher develops, manufactures, and markets complete blood test systems to support the clinical diagnosis and monitoring of allergy, asthma and autoimmune diseases. With 1,900 employees worldwide working with these products, and 1,000 in Sweden, we are the global leader in in-vitro allergy testing and the European leader in autoimmunity diagnostics.  Read how our R&D professionals in Sweden are enjoying our innovative work atmosphere and the role they are playing in helping humankind: https://www.youtube  How will you make an impact?   Are you looking for a meaningful job in an international company that has strong values? Would you like to use your knowledge as a senior software engineer and have a possibility to help our customers how they work with and diagnose allergy tests and autoimmune diseases around the world?  You are an enthusiastic person who wants to work with the development of the application software, instrument software or similar products in the life science area. We can offer you an interesting and rewarding career where you will get a great opportunity to develop your technical skills as well as professionally in one of the world's largest life science companies. Why not come and work in an exciting role where you can really make a difference in people's lives?  What will you do?   As a Front-End Software Developer you will work with design and development of software with main focus on the application software for controlling our Phadia Instruments. You will have strong focus on development of web interfaces. The software team is responsible for several PC and Webb software products, which are used for running Phadia Systems and for the world-wide support of instruments. In this role you would mainly work in a combined C#/.NET and HTML 5 environment using Microsoft's latest development environments and tools.  You will be working with specifications, design and testing of software and instrument functions, through the entire product life cycle from new products to support and improvement of existing products.  Duties:
  
    Development of specifications based on customer requirements
    Design work in close collaboration with UX Designers
    Design, implement and test software, mainly web interfaces
    Participate in the verification work
    Participate in design reviews and change management
    Participate in and drive new ways of working, including introducing new technologies
    Working with risk management and handling of complaints in accordance with our quality management system
    Be responsible for writing and updating technical documentation
    Participate in product maintenance and 3rd line support to our customers worldwide
  
   Skills:
  
    We are looking for a person with a higher education degree or Master of Science in computer engineering, electrical engineering, engineering physics or similar, with at least 1-2 years of work experience in the development of instruments and software.
    We develop software for diagnostic systems under regulatory requirements, so you need to have solid personal integrity and awareness of the importance of documentation, rules and procedures that need to be addressed.
    As an experienced web engineer (HTML5) you would have experience in some web framework like Angular, React, Razor or similar. Experience in C#, .NET would be a very strong merit as we will work with new technologies such as Blazor and Kestrel. 
   Experience in UI/UX would also be a strong merit, as work will be done closely together with our usability team. Experience of mobile app development is a plus as well. 
   Thermo Fisher Scientific is a global company, so it is important that you feel comfortable in an international and changing work environment. Fluent English skills are a requirement for this position. 
  
  APPLICATION DEADLINE:  If you have questions then please contact Thomas Larnhed: +46 70-747 09 80, Manager Software, System R&D.   Please send in your application, including a cover letter, CV (in one document) in English, apply via http://jobs.thermofisher.com Ref 203073BR Please apply as soon as possible, the position will be filled as soon as suitable candidate is found.  Apply today! http://jobs.thermofisher.com  Our global team of more than 100,000 colleagues delivers an unrivaled combination of innovative technologies, purchasing convenience and pharmaceutical services through our industry-leading brands, including Thermo Scientific, Applied Biosystems, Invitrogen, Fisher Scientific

Needefy är ett svenskt konsultbolag med betydande kompetens och erfarenhet inom telekom, IT och industri-branschen. Vi erbjuder en arbetsplats med utvecklingsmöjligheter och chansen att vara med på en tillväxtresa i ett bolag som jobbar i branscher med spännande framtid. Vår prioritet är våra medarbetare, gemenskap och work life balance.
Just nu söker vi Front end utvecklare med 2-4 års arbetslivserfarenhet av mjukvaruutveckling till spännande uppdrag inom Stockholmsområdet. De tekniker, ramverk och programmeringsspråk vi använder varierar från uppdrag till uppdrag, så oavsett vilka nedan du bemästrar, är sannolikheten stor att vi har ett projekt som passar dig.

React.js
JavaScript
Vue.js
Angular
TypeScript
HTML5/CSS3
SaaS
jQuery
Agila utvecklingsmetoder, eller andra moderna standarsutvecklingsmetoder som CI/CD, TDD eller Scrum

Personliga egenskaper
Vi önskar att du som person är du problemlösande, engagerad och har en stor nyfikenhet. Vi värdesätter lagspelare som har fokus på att teamet lyckas och att vi som företag förknippas med kvalité genom våra konsulters goda arbete och leverans. Du är kommunikativ och uttrycker dig obehindrat på svenska och engelska i tal och skrift.
Övrigt
Start: Enligt överenskommelse
Placering: Stockholms län
Kontakt

Vid frågor eller ytterligare information, vänligen kontakta rekryteringsansvarig Anneli Westermark - anneli.westermark@needefy.se
Vi tar emot ansökningar löpande, så tveka inte att skicka in din ansökan redan idag.
Varmt välkommen med din ansökan!

Position Description:
Efterfrågan är fortsatt stor från våra kunder inom området och därför söker vi nu dig som är
Front End-utvecklare för att förstärka och utöka vårt webbteam i Kalmar!

Vad vi erbjuder
Som frontendare hos oss i Kalmar kommer du att få arbeta med sköna kollegor i allt från små, korta webbprojekt på några månader till stora, långa åtaganden. Vi deltar i och driver projekt och åtaganden främst från vårt lokala kontor. Vi arbetar såväl enskilt som tillsammans med andra kollegor i våra uppdrag. Våra uppdrag genomförs med stöd av etablerade metoder och modeller som baseras på branschstandarder. Vi har alltid användaren och tillgängligheten i fokus och hjälper våra kunder att ta tillvara på den digitala världens möjligheter. Du kommer få möjlighet att arbeta med kunder som verkar i både privat och offentliga sektor.
Your future duties and responsibilities:
I rollen som Front End-utvecklare kommer du arbeta tillsammans med ett tema av back-end utvecklare och UX designers. Du anpassar och förbättrar befintliga lösningar och befintlig kod likväl som arbetar med nyutvecklingsprojekt och bygger från grunden.
Som Front End-utvecklare arbetar du nära vårt UX-team som består av designers och användarbarhetsexperter. I den här rollen får du möjlighet att arbeta såväl självständigt som i team och du får arbeta med både projekt- och förvaltningsuppdrag
Required qualifications to be successful in this role:
Vi söker dig som är en driven och skarp webbutvecklare med fokus på front-end och design, och vi tror att du har c:a 2-5 års erfarenhet inom webbutveckling för mobil och desktop mot kund.

Då du har några års erfarenhet ser vi att du bl.a:
Har erfarenhet av att jobba med Typescript och React.Har grunderna och god kunskap i HTML5, CSS3, Javascript och jQuery.Gillar snyggt skriven kod och god praxis inom webbstandarder, erfarenhet av att arbeta med responsiv webbdesign
Har erfarenhet av att arbeta med tillgänglig användarcentrerad webbdesign enligt WCAG.Goda kunskaper i Photoshop men även erfarenhet av andra verktyg som Figma, Sketch, InVision Studio eller andra verktyg.Meriterande med erfarenhet av CMS så som EPiServer, SiteVision och WordPress.Önskvärt med kunskaper om andra javascriptramverk som Angular och Vue.Önskvärt med erfarenhet av tekniker som SASS/SCSS/LESS, Node.js, Grunt.js, Webpack.Erfaren inom att jobba med versionshantering.Är uppdaterad på ny teknik och hungrig på att lära sig nya saker.Starkt intresse för bra design, UX och användarupplevelse.Detaljorienterad och förstår värdet av pixel-perfect.Har relevant eftergymnasial utbildning inom webbområdet eller en IT-inriktad akademisk examen med motsvarande kunskap erhållen genom arbetslivserfarenhet.
Vad kan vi på CGI erbjuda dig?
CGIs kombination av global och lokal närvaro, med kontor på 30 orter i Sverige, ger nöjda kunder men innebär även att du som anställd alltid har ett kontor nära dig. Detta i kombination med flexibla arbetstider ger dig möjlighet till balans mellan privatliv och arbete, oavsett var i livet just du befinner dig.

På CGI finns även stora möjligheter till interna karriärvägar där du kan välja att bli specialist inom ditt område, bredda dig inom nya områden eller ta en ledande befattning. Via våra interna nätverk, projekt och åtaganden i globala och nationella industrier, erbjuder vi dig kompetensutveckling och engagerade ledare som stöttar just dig i din utveckling.

Mer information om våra förmåner:
Aktieprogram och delägarskap: Som delägare har du möjlighet att påverka och i vårt aktieprogram matchar CGI ditt bidrag, krona för krona upp till 3% av din månadslön.Friskvårdsbidrag: Vi erbjuder ett årligt friskvårdsbidrag på 3 000 kr.Föräldralön: Vi betalar upp till cirka 90% av din lön under den första tiden hemma.Trygg anställning: Våra konsulter anställs med kollektivavtal och försäkringar.Pensionslösningar: Vi erbjuder attraktiva och förmånliga pensionslösningar.Personalbil: Personalbilen används som en privatbil men leasas av CGI.
Vill du veta mer?
Vi ser fram emot att höra från dig! Om det finns något du undrar över, skicka gärna dina funderingar till mats-ola.svensson@cgi.com

Skicka in din ansökan redan idag, vi hanterar ansökningarna löpande!
Resor ingår i rollen. Personliga säkerhetskrav kommer att krävas om rollen kräver det.

#LI-HW1
What you can expect from us:
Utveckla din karriär hos oss.

Det är en extraordinär tid i vår bransch. Den digitala transformationen accelererar och CGI är i centrum för förändringarna – som hjälp för våra kunders digitala resor och med spännande karriärmöjligheter för våra medarbetare.

På CGI når vi framgång genom våra medarbetares talang och engagemang. Som ett team delar vi de utmaningar och belöningar som kommer genom att vi skapar ett växande företag, vilket stärker vår ägarskapskultur. Alla våra medarbetare drar nytta av det värde vi gemensamt skapar.

Var med och bygg ett av världens största oberoende tjänsteföretag inom IT och affärsprocesser.

Kort om tjänsten
   Vi söker en nyfiken och driven Front End-utvecklare med ett brinnande intresse för skapa snygga, snabba och moderna digitala produkter. Ditt primära fokus kommer att vara på att leverera webbprojekt i toppklass tillsammans med ditt team. Du förstår vikten av att vara noggrann och kommunikativ i ditt arbete för att hålla hög kvalitet i dina leveranser. Vi nöjer oss aldrig förrän våra kunders högt ställda förväntningar infriats och vi tror att du är likadan.
   
  
   
  Om Roy
   Vi är en snabbt växande digitalbyrå som ingår i mediekoncernen Another Media Group. Tillsammans med våra syskonbolag omsätter vi årligen cirka 100 miljoner kronor och finns representerade med kontor i Stockholm, Malmö och Halmstad.
   
  Sedan starten 2015 har Roy vuxit i takt med våra uppdragsgivares behov. Idag kan vi knappt själva sätta en etikett på vad vi är. Man skulle kunna säga att vi är en webbyrå, contentbyrå och designbyrå i ett. Många av våra kunder uppskattar att vi kan hjälpa dem med allt och kallar oss för en fullservicebyrå. Nu växlar vi upp vårt digitala erbjudande och söker dig som vill vara med och kombinera strategi, design och teknik för att skapa snygga, snabba och moderna produkter som hjälper våra kunder att förverkliga sina digitala ambitioner.
   
  
   
  Vad du kommer att få göra:
  
   Bygga allt från mindre kampanjsidor till större hemsidor, nyhetssidor och digitala produkter med varierande krav på funktionalitet och teknik.
    Vidareutveckla och bygga webbappar, system, medlemsplattformar el. liknande (om du vill).
   Vara med och påverka i designprocesser för att säkerställa att vi skapar produkter som inte bara ser bra ut men också är funktionella, lätta att använda och håller länge.
  
  
   För att lyckas i rollen tror vi att du har:
   - 2 - 5 års erfarenhet som front end-utvecklare (frilans eller på byrå).
  
   En ständig vilja att vässa dina kunskaper och utforska morgondagens tekniker för att utvecklas i din roll.
   Goda kunskaper inom JavaScript och förståelse för moderna ramverk som React och Node.js
   Förmåga att förstå och översätta användarkrav och affärskrav till funktionell front end.
   Erfarenhet av vanliga front end-utvecklingsverktyg som t.ex. Babel, Webpack och NPM.
   Bra förståelse för hur man bygger webb som är både responsiv och har bra prestanda.
  
  
   Tekniker du kommer att jobba med:
  
   HTML5
   CSS / SASS, Styled Components
   PHP
   React
   Next.js
    State-hantering som t.ex. Redux
   REST och GraphQL Apier
   GraphQL
   Git & versionshantering
  
  
   Det är en bonus om du även har kunskaper inom:
  
   Design (i Sketch / Figma / Framer el. liknande)

Vi utmanar de traditionella konsultbolagen och vi kan med stolthet säga att Castra är konsultbranschens mest utvecklande arbetsplats där allt är möjligt. Känns det här som företaget för dig så läs gärna vidare.
Är du eller någon du känner sugen på en ny utmaning? Castra är IT bolaget för dig som vill ta nästa steg. Hos oss får du både intressanta uppdrag, och stor möjlighet att påverka det som betyder mest för dig. Det kan vara arbetstid, arbetsuppgifter, lön, utbildning, delägarskap och mycket mer.
Vem är du?
Du älskar att koda och JavaScript sitter i ryggmärgen. Du manipulerar DOM:en utan jQuery och att jobba med moderna byggverktyg känns självklart för dig. Dessutom har du naturligtvis koll på HTML/CSS, webbstandards, mobil utveckling och ditt defaultläge är att jobba agilt. Du bör vara intresserad av det som trendar just nu (exempelvis React, Vue.js, Angular, Node.js, TypeScript, Cloud-plattformar och Continuous Delivery).
Vi ser gärna att du har en längre arbetslivserfarenhet efter dina studier från något tekniskt universitet. Sannolikt är du systemvetare eller ingenjör. Viktigast är dock att du är en relationsbyggande person som trivs i konsultrollen.
Varför ska du välja oss?
Här tror vi på frihet, möjligheter och medbestämmande. Att du som medarbetare ska ha möjlighet att utvecklas och forma ditt arbete utefter dina intressen och prioriteringar i livet. Att alla får vara med och forma och påverka bolaget genom delägarskap, advisory board och projektgrupper. Att det är viktigt att ha ett sammanhang, känna tillhörighet och att man har kollegor som stöttar, utvecklar och tror på en.
Om Castra
Castra är en entreprenörsdriven konsultgrupp inom IT, management och systemutveckling. Bolaget ägs gemensamt av medarbetarna och tillsammans bygger vi det företag vi själva vill jobba på.
Vår vision är att vi ska vara Sveriges bästa arbetsgivare för konsulter. Att vi blivit certifierade av Great Place to Work fem år i rad är ett bevis på våra höga mål kring företagskultur. Våra tankar om delaktighet, påverkansmöjligheter och respekt för individens egna val och möjligheter fungerar.
Företaget har kontor i Göteborg, Stockholm, Helsingborg, Malmö, Linköping, Norrköping, Örebro och Jönköping. Mer information om Castra-koncernen hittar du på vår hemsida www.castra.se.
Har vi lyckats väcka din nyfikenhet? Sök direkt via länken eller kontakta thomas.florentin@castra.se Tfn: 070-5788391

About Debricked
At Debricked, we are all about open source. Our main goal is to make it easy for developers to use open source in a better way and remove any associated risks. As our nimble start-up just got acquired by Micro Focus, we are now accelerating our growth and looking for a Front-End developer to join our team in Sweden or remotely in Europe (+3/-3h GMT+1). If you want to work alongside a crew of fun, driven, and supportive colleagues while getting the opportunity to influence and impact the journey ahead, Debricked is the place for you!
The role
We are looking for a front-end developer to join our scrum team of nine, working on our SaaS tool.
You will be working alongside a mixed group of designers, front-end, full-stack and back-end developers. We collaborate closely, reviewing and helping each other throughout the development process, and implement modern best practises, e.g. test-driven development, consistent code-style etc.
We are looking for someone to help us continue to develop our existing tool, adding new features and improving existing ones. We try to use up-to-date technologies as much as possible, so even our legacy code is pretty modern.
As a front-end developer at Debricked, you will be working on creating interfaces to present large datasets covering all aspects of Open Source Software, ranging from vulnerability definitions to GitHub star scores. an open database that displays metrics for every repository on GitHub, with visualisations of how those metrics vary over time and how they compare with other repositories
a rule building interface for our automation engine that allows the creation of highly custom rules with conditions set on a variety of data types
a dashboard showing users the effects of all their actions in the tool

JavaScript

CSS (and preprocessors such as SCSS or LESS)
git

Knowledge of Cypress or similar test frameworks

Familiarity with running Docker containers

Enthusiasm for design and user experience
Interest in Open Source Software and/or security

This position can either be hybrid or fully remote.

Apart from that, we offer several generous company-wide benefits including paid holidays, pension and insurance.

Join us in the fight against antibiotic resistant bacteria!
1928 Diagnostics combines software technology and genomics to analyze DNA from infectious bacteria and help hospitals detect, stop and prevent outbreaks. In-depth characterization of the bacteria can also guide the physicians in how to treat the patients. Apart from saving lives, we also reduce costs and diminish the spread of antibiotic resistant bacteria.
We are now expanding our development team with highly motivated and engaged developers to be part of the challenge. You will join a development team consisting of 5 software developers and 3 bioinformaticians. Your team is creating a custom-made processing platform for analyzing DNA data and a web application, where the challenge is to present complex and dynamic data with a focus on quality and user-friendliness. Everything is running in a Kubernetes cluster which is scaling on the computational needs. We primarily work with Python, React.js, Typescript, CSS/LESS, Django, RabbitMQ, PostgreSQL and other things that we find exciting. We want to continuously challenge ourselves and keep learning new things.
We are looking for a software developer with a focus on front-end development. For this role, you should be passionate about delivering a user experience that supports the customer. You have an interest in design and you like the challenge of visualising and presenting complex data in a user-friendly way. You will be involved in the whole development process, from idea to production release. You also take joy in working in a fast-paced, growing organisation that is continuously evolving. You will be close to the product every day and your thoughts and ideas matter, all the way to the end-user.
1928 Diagnostics was founded by three scientists and a serial entrepreneur in 2014. As of now, we have a full outbreak analysis platform that is sold to clinics in different parts of the world. In 2018, 1928 Diagnostics was awarded as Technology Pioneer by the World Economic Forum, for our innovative technology that is poised to have a significant impact on global health, society and business. We have also been on 33-listan 3 years in a row and by that received the title “Gold company”.
We are a very committed and diverse team, today 19 people and growing, with competences within software development, bioinformatics, molecular biology, QA/RA, sales, marketing and finance. The team is led by two of the founders, Kristina Lagerstedt and Susanne Staaf, who together have a long experience within life science research and development.

Running a small business is harder than it should be! Small businesses are 99.8% of all enterprises in the world and the backbone of the economy. But, far too much time and money is spent on administrative tasks that don’t create value.
   Bokio makes it super easy for everyone to run a business through automation of financial services, accounting, payments and taxes. We make sure our users understand their finances and have the right tools to make the best decisions for their businesses.
   Sounds exciting? Join the team and help us make an already awesome product even better!
   As a frontend focused developer, you will be working with most of the relevant layers of the product - from UX features, react components and CSS styling to backend services and database layer. You will work on designing, developing and deploying services and features; as well as on maintaining and supporting them.
   More details can be found below, but in a nutshell:
   
    Your main playground will be React/TypeScript and C. 
    You will be part of a small, cross-functional team that has full responsibility and accountability for their product area. 
    You will help to expand and manage a large frontend repository. 
  
   Who you are
   
    You have empathy for end-users and truly care about improving their experience. 
    You have a growth mindset and are always looking for ways to improve and learn, both as a professional and as an individual. 
    You are a good communicator and comfortable with spoken and written English. 
    You know, care about and use sound engineering practices to develop well-crafted software. 
  
   What’s in your backpack
   
    You are great with React and javascript. 
    You have an interest to learn C and backend development. 
    It would be considered a bonus if:
     
      You have/had your own company and understand the perils of running a small business. 
      You have experience with Typescript. 
      You have experience with managing a large frontend repository. 
      You have experience with Webpack. 
      You are familiar with accounting, invoicing or fintech. 
      You have worked with single-page applications (SPA) before and understand how to measure and improve performance in a SPA. 
     
  
  What’s in it for you
   
    An opportunity to grow and learn from knowledgeable colleagues. 
    A diverse workplace, with skilled and kind people from all over the world. 
    Flexible working hours 
    Awesome offices in central Gothenburg & Stockholm. 
    Wellness grant, pension and other benefits. Including waffles! 
  
   Location
   We have a Hybrid work model with central offices in Gothenburg and Stockholm. This position is located in Gothenburg with the possibility to work flexible remote.
   Finally
   You are welcome at Bokio for who you are, no matter where you come from or what you look like. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace! We are creating a culture at Bokio where empathy, diversity, respect and courage are front and centre. Get a glimpse of Life at Bokio here, here and here.
   Do you feel that you don't match all our criteria? We are looking for the right person at heart, not the right person on paper. So if you really feel passionate about our mission and our users, and feel you can contribute, you can still apply! 
  Are you the one we are looking for? Apply now!

What you'll do
Work with our designers and developers to create elegant and powerful features that scale
Take a lead in architecting technical solutions for our desktop and mobile apps
Play a key role in building solutions for our streamlined user interfaces
Participate in the creative process and use your technical expertise to ensure the feasibility of designs
What we offer
Work with real impact. GpsGate helps companies worldwide in their day to day business managing deliveries, cutting fuel emissions, ensuring the safety of their staff and much more!
We are a flat company and your ideas will matter. Projects move from idea to construction quickly so we can focus on continuously learning.
Career paths aren't set in stone. You drive your own learning and can pitch projects that you are passionate about.
You're joining a collaborative team. We work hard to reach our goals but make sure to have fun on our way there. Whether it's the annual company conference or running the half marathon together, there's always something going on!
Feel free to pick the tools that make you happy. Windows, or ? Doesn't matter! We won't tell you how to do your best work.
You'll be working with the latest and greatest tech and tools. We're always on the look out for technologies that help us in our mission. If it fits, we'll be using it.
What we'd like from you
You're a team player who is used to collaborating with designers and other developers
3+ years work experience with JavaScript (ES6+) and HTML/CSS with for React
A passion for UX and putting the user first
A desire to work in a dynamic company with no micro-management
Fluency in both written and spoken English
Bonus points
Any experience in React Native, Android or iOS native SDKs, a modern JavaScript build toolchain
Industry experience or education in a design-focused discipline

Our SaaS platform helps real estate owners manage buildings in a form of virtual representations of their assets. The result is a more efficient and sustainable use of time and resources, and a more joyful working experience for our clients.
Our grand ambition is to make the most of the world's man-made environment and connected information organized and searchable. As a team member you can have an enormous impact on our product, our company, and our vision.
Our office is located in Kungsholmen, Stockholm. We offer the flexibility of remote work at times, friendly atmosphere and inclusive work environment.
Our main day-to-day challenge is delivering a reliable, modern and delightful user experience to our clients by:

providing 2D/3D virtual representation of real-world structures
searching and managing virtual objects and associated data
managing issues, tasks and work orders
integrating with and visualizing data from external APIs and sensors

We are building our front-end on top of React, Relay, GraphQL, Material UI, three.js, and in TypeScript. Our back-end is powered by Node.js, and PostgreSQL.
We try to keep our technology stack lean, but are constantly on the lookout for better tools and components. We strive for simplicity, pragmatism, flexibility, and modernity in our technology choices. We are moving fast, and are proud of our developer experience.
On a day-to-day basis, you will:

work in a great team
improve and develop features for our main single-page application
help design and possibly implement new APIs
work closely with designers and build a great user experience
suggest improvements to our tech stack, product, or work process
You probably have:

several years of experience developing single-page applications
deep knowledge of React ecosystem, GraphQL and TypeScript
experience of designing APIs, and are able to reason about various tradeoffs in their design
insightful and nuanced views on code quality and UX
It would be awesome if you have:

worked at a startup or in a similar fast-moving organization
experience in working with WebGL, Google Maps API, Docker, Kubernetes, and on-demand cloud computing platforms
What we offer:

an agile and humble team with openness for constructive feedback, fostering a growth mindset
stock options/co-ownership
opportunity to develop your role within the company
bright and spacious office located in Kungsholmen, Stockholm
flexibility of remote work enabled by a great digital workflow setup
fun team building activities and hangouts held on a recurring basis
Does it sound like a good fit for you? Let's get connected!

About Us

We love pets - which is why we're on a mission to make the world a better place for pets and their parents. We offer pet insurance policies with generous pet health benefits that are designed with their needs in mind. We've helped over half a million pets stay happy and healthy since 2017 - and many more customers throughout the world are joining us every day. We've won numerous awards, have offices in the USA, UK, and Sweden - and we now employ over 400 people globally.

Award-winning, innovative technology and exceptional customer service are at the heart of our offer: our "Complete" policy ranks top of the Which? cat and dog insurance Best Buy tables. (December 2021) We've also been voted the Pet Insurance Provider Of The Year in the Moneyfacts Consumer Awards (2021) - and we've received over 21,000 5-star Feefo reviews in the past 12 months.

We're proud to be driving unprecedented change in insurance and have doubled our revenues annually for the last 4 years with more ambitious growth still to come. Our latest Series D funding round was $350m which values us at over $2bn.

Our company is fast-moving, respectful, fun-loving and (most importantly) passionate about pets and their wellbeing. We think big and we can only do that if we have a wonderful array of different people who are able to bring their whole selves to work every day. Throughout our business you'll meet people who think differently, aim for impact and love to try new things. Want to join our pack? Join us. Love every moment. Love ManyPets.
The Opportunity

We're on an impressive journey to make the world a better place for pet-parents. We have ambitious growth plans, and this role will be a pivotal part of our success (and continued growth) in the UK, Sweden, the US and beyond.

We are scaling-up our Engineering, Product and Design ("EPD") team and you'll be a critical member of one of our durable Agile squads. You'll collaborate with our other Front-End Developers and Engineers, Design, Product Management and QA to build the next generation of our digital product. You'll work to ensure we are building and designing our JavaScript based solutions with quality in mind. We'll rely on you to strive to improve (and automate) our "road to production" by using and advocating for improvements in our Global APIs.

Your Focus
Contribute to the overall technical direction of our Front-End development, using frameworks, pre-compilers and other technologies.
Build production-ready user interfaces.
Work alongside other developers in EPD, to ensure your code fits in with the overall design and coding standards.
Contribute ideas and innovations, wherever you see opportunity for improvement
Work collaboratively with our multi-disciplinary squads
Work within (and help to improve) our self-organising squad model
Work collaboratively across the whole business, building relationships across all teams.
What Leads to Success

Here are a few of the skills we are looking for in this position. Don't worry if you don't tick every box as it's important for us to support you in your role and help you to develop along the way.

UX is your heart and soul. You're the sort of person who needs to know that everything works well and beautifully for our customers.
Nothing makes you smile like a high-quality, slick user interface. Every pixel must have its' place!
You value diversity and are sensitive to different environments and cultures.
You recognise when the solution is getting too complex and it's time to adjust the requirements (or when it's time to delete, refactor, and simplify.)
You've got nose for problems: you have a sixth sense for issues before they happen.
Your colleagues say you're the sort of person who likes to move fast, pragmatically seeking problems and thinking about the wider impact.
You make changes happen by working well and with others.
What's Important
Solid commercial experience working as a hands-on engineer.
Experience of delivering production code to a large user base.
You want to be part of a fast-paced, product centric environment like ours!
We use Agile software development techniques, so you should be happy working with Agile or Kanban methodologies.
Experience in leading and coaching others, both in person and via remote.
Knowledge of relevant languages and tools:
Javascript (ES6, Node.JS)
JS Web Frameworks (Vue.JS, React, Angular)
Build Tools (webpack, rollup)
CSS tooling (SASS or LESS)
Responsive HTML & CSS
UX and Accessibility
Test Automation (Jest, Selenium, Cypress)
Front-end security architectures and practices
Inclusion at ManyPets

We believe diversity, belonging and inclusion are more than just words or things we should be 'seen' to be doing. Having diversity at the core of our business makes us stronger - and the responsibility for creating an inclusive workplace rests with all of us. We believe Black Lives Matter and we want you to join a company that makes unbiased choices and is committed to being anti-racist. If you'd like to read more about this, please download our Approach to Inclusion pack.

We promise to give you the same opportunities as everyone else and we won't discriminate against you at any point in the process. This includes how we source talent, our interview process, our conditions of employment (including pay) and feedback.

Hybrid-Working

Everything changed overnight when the pandemic happened. Suddenly everything was different: whether we were in a home office, spare room, or makeshift desk: we were working on our own and dealing with Zoom calls, bad Wi-Fi, and a very different working day. We now work from home and our company office, so we've created our Making Work, Work guide, which explains it all.

We offer a fantastic range of company benefits to suit everyone in a remote-first world, with a focus on supporting our physical and mental wellbeing. Coupled with a generous holiday allowance and regular care packs, we're always looking for new ways to look out for our people.

Our Values

Our company values drive everything we do - and they are:

Show You Care | Do The Right Thing | Think Big | Work Together | Be Tenacious

Connect With Us!

LinkedIn | Instagram: UK USA Sweden| Facebook: UK USA Sweden | Twitter: UK USA | TikTok | Glassdoor | Indeed | FeeFo | Trustpilot | Crunchbase

Reasonable Adjustments and Support

If you need any help, support or advice at any point during the hiring process please email our Inclusion Council in complete confidence. Our Inclusion Council is a cross-functional group of people from our global business - and they are not the hiring managers for this role. We're here to make sure everyone has a fair and equitable experience when they're considering joining us. If you want to talk or ask any questions, we are here to listen (and we'll do what we can to flex our approach to a process that suits you.)

Join our team Flamingo and work, learn, play and grow together with experienced developers (and music enthusiasts) to create an evolved music ecosystem that empowers all those involved.
At Utopia, Front-end Engineers make the music data come alive by building user experiences that are intuitive and solve the problems for our customers. They work closely with designers to iterate on concepts, prototypes and make data driven decisions.
WELCOME TO UTOPIA
Music is incredible. It can excite hundreds, and unite thousands. But as an industry, it has been slow, complicated, and disparate. While the tech world has moved into the future, the music industry continues to be shaped by inefficient systems of the past. At Utopia we believe there is a better way. Which is why today we are setting out to transform the entire industry; creating new revenue streams, consolidating the data and decluttering the admin. Unlocking the industry’s full potential by unifying it all in one truly holistic space. Some might call that a Utopia.
Funnily enough, so do we. Welcome to Utopia. Where music lives.
WHAT UTOPIANS DO
We are building a better world for music with innovative big data technology that tracks online music sources and translates them into meaningful music consumption reports for royalty collection. The solution we’re building does not threaten to usurp the role of industry incumbents - it is about bringing transparency in the industry and supporting efficient royalty collection.
FOCUS OF THE ROLE
You will be working on Utopia products targeted for artists, copyright holders and royalty collection societies. The products are built on the top of the Utopia data platform providing insights into vast amounts of music consumption data. You’ll work with the data analysts to extract insights from the data and provide actions for customers to take based on the insights.
ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES
Collaborate with other engineers, designers, product managers and data analysts to build the right user experience for each customer category and use case.
Develop an understanding of our customers and their “jobs to be done”.
Craft intuitive and beautiful user experiences that are valuable for our customers.
Make data driven decisions using instrumentation, A/B testing and other quantitative and qualitative tools.
THE IDEAL SKILLSET
5+ years experience building user experiences for web based products.
2+ years experience working with React or other Javascript based frameworks, good understanding of ES6 and TypeScript.
5+ years of experience with HTML/CSS, including concepts like layout, specificity, cross browser compatibility, and accessibility.
Experience with browser APIs and optimising front-end performance is a plus.
Track record of working with the Material UI would be a plus.
Fluency in English, both written and verbal.
Excellent communication skills.
Passion for data and data visualisation.
WHAT WE OFFER
A unique opportunity to be part of building the Engineering function in Stockholm and work in an impact oriented, autonomous and empowered team
Great atmosphere - we live, love & breathe music & tech!
An experienced team to learn from, with experience in multiple startups and big tech companies
Sublime office of hundreds of square meters with a pingpong table, playroom, gym in the basement and seriously good coffee. We love our vibrant office culture and daily breakfasts!
And if you may prefer being on your own and working from home - we’re fine with that too!
Swedish benefits such as pension, insurances, famous Health care allowance, phone and subscription
We are supporting work permits for employees that moved here from countries outside the EU
THE HIRING PROCESS
You send us your CV in English.
We invite you for an introductory phone/video call to get to know you better and share more about us.
You get a programming exercise and unlimited time to send us your solution.
Our lead developers evaluate it and we provide you with the feedback.
You meet our lead developers for the technical interview.
You meet the hiring manager for the culture fit interview.
UTOPIANS
We come from diverse backgrounds and we welcome everyone who identifies with the above to apply. Welcome to Utopia - Where Music Lives!
We’re eager to meet you! :)

From our technology to our team members, Neo4j is built on relationships.
As part of Neo4j product engineering, you will work together with a diverse team of talented colleagues from around the world. Our culture encourages engineers who want to become deep experts in a particular field – or to build broad expertise across several technologies. Our engineers regularly work with peers in field engineering and experience the full lifecycle of the systems they build.
We build technology that helps cure cancers, addresses diabetes, and gets humans to Mars. We're proud to fight fraud, crush pandemics, and even help journalists uncover the truth. Neo4j’s engineering teams are located in Malmö, Sweden and London, UK.
Please submit your CV and cover letter in English.
The Team
Our team makes Neo4j Browser, a slick web application for running queries, and the main user interface for the Neo4j graph database. Neo4j has its own graph query language called Cypher, with a SQL-like structure.

Neo4j Browser is an open source product that provides an interactive Cypher editor including syntax highlighting and context-aware auto-completion. In addition to traditional tabular formats for query results, Neo4j Browser can display graphs as an interactive visualisation, allowing users to intuitively see the structure of their data.
Neo4j Browser is the first surface that developers see when they enter the world of graphs, and its capabilities are a key factor for the success of Neo4j and the Graph Database industry as a whole.
Your Contribution will be to:
Build things that you won’t find in a normal web application (interactive visualisations, intelligent code editors, and high efficiency processing of large volumes of data)
Have a positive impact on others developers’ day to day work
What You'll Bring:
Strong UI/Front-end development skills with a solid knowledge of modern JavaScript / TypeScript, HTML, and CSS
Experience working with libraries such as React, Redux, and RxJS
Proficiency with JavaScript testing frameworks
Comfortable working in a distributed team and ability to work autonomously and with initiative when necessary
Nice to have:
Experience with IDE / Editor development such as Monaco
Knowledge of data visualization libraries like d3.js

Why Join Neo4j?
Neo4j is one of the 20 most popular databases in the world, and the leader in the rapidly emerging Graph Database category. We’re building the technology that enables connected data to solve the world’s most pressing problems. You’ll work on unique engineering projects that challenge what’s possible.
We have customers in every industry across the globe, and our products a proven product/market fit. Joining our team is an opportunity to shape the future of data and analytics.
We pride ourselves on being a welcoming team. Most of us would agree that one of the best parts of working at Neo4j is the people we get to work with.
We encourage you to apply even if you don’t 100% fit the qualifications above. Why? Because we are committed to building an environment that fosters belonging, which means valuing intellectually honest discussions and being receptive to new ideas and perspectives.
One of our central objectives is to provide an inclusive, diverse, and equitable workplace for everyone to develop their potential and have a positive, career-defining experience.
About Neo4j:
Neo4j is the leader in graph database technology. As the world’s most widely deployed graph database, we help organizations – including NASA, UBS and Volvo Cars – to reveal and predict how people, processes and systems interrelate. Using this relationships-first approach, applications built using Neo4j tackle connected data challenges such as analytics and artificial intelligence, fraud detection, real-time recommendations and knowledge graphs.
Neo4j is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. Please read the privacy notice regarding Neo4j's recruitment process to understand how we will handle the personal data that you provide.
More information at www.neo4j.com.

Since you’ve landed on this page, you already know Hedvig is a mover and shaker in insurtech, and think you might have what it takes to join us. As the only loved insurance company in Sweden (in the world?), we’ve proven that it’s possible to disrupt an entire industry with people’s best interests at heart. But our journey is just beginning, starting with Sweden, Denmark and Norway! We’ve been working hard since the very beginning to change an industry that is hard to love – to something at least likeable. At Hedvig we believe the only way to do so is to work with loveable people.
   
   
   
     The frontend team shapes the purchase journey of potential new Hedvig members as well as existing ones. The user experience is central for Hedvig which makes the team dear to the company. The team is relatively small yet very skilled. The team is working hard to build Scandinavia’s most loved insurance company. We work closely with product, design, back-end, as well as Mobile app developers to create the best experience for our customers. Currently and due to Hedvig’s expansion in terms of markets and products we are hiring an Engineering Manager to lead the team.
   
   
   
     What about the role?
   
   
    As an Engineering Lead, you will never be far from solving problems and writing code, yet you will have the responsibility of leading and coaching our talented but small front-end team.
   
   
   
     You will have the responsibility of communicating with stakeholders by explaining solutions and technical trade-offs. This role aims to bring clarity to the organization over what we do and how we do it.
   
   
   
     You’ll make decisions and solve issues such as code scalability and exiting UX challenges as Hedvig is currently expanding its product offering and new markets.
   
   
   
     In addition to the support on daily tasks, you will ensure that your team is constantly developing their skills and capabilities.
   
   
   
     What about you?
   
   
    You’ve most likely been working with front-end web development for some years, and you have some coaching or leadership experience. But more importantly, you have a strong interest and motivation to develop in this direction.
   
   
   
     A big part of the role includes hands-on coding, and you should be familiar with our tech stack. The site is powered by React, Emotion, and TypeScript, and on top of this, we also use GraphQL with Apollo, a little bit of Koa, and the headless CMS Storyblok.
   
   
   
     Again, those are not hard requirements! If you have a different profile but you see that you have relevant skills and you think you can do a remarkable job, apply and send an email to us motivating why we should meet you. We believe that a good developer is a problem-solver who is capable of learning any new tech stack. We highly value both a good attitude and personality as a leader and place a lot of emphasis on these "soft skills".
     
   
   
    
   
    What about us?
   
   
     As part of the Hedvig team, you quickly notice that "general truths" are not accepted without being questioned. We're an enthusiastic group of people who love to challenge each other to find the best way forward. We don't care who says something; we care about what's being said. We put a lot of effort into building a trusting culture where freedom, collective thinking, and individual ownership have center stage. We're not perfect–far from it – but we talk about and learn from our mistakes and imperfections to improve continuously. And we have a lot of fun along the way! As individuals, as a team, and as a company.
   
   
  
   
    Sounds like your next challenge? You can start by sending us an application. If you don't feel ready maybe you want to know more about us? Then check out our LinkedIn page where we regularly post inspiring thoughts from our people, and also our Career page where we (try to) share our values If you have questions regarding the position, please feel free to write to careers@hedvig.com.
   
   
   
     What the process will most likely look like (we will let you know if there are any changes)
   
   
     30 minute chat with to learn more about you – and tell you more about us!
   
   
     Interview with one of our hiring leaders.
   
   
     Case interview with our developers from the team.
   
   
    ️Final interview with one of our founders. 
   
   
    
   
    FYI: We may ask candidates to complete a Personality and Logical Thinking test in order to understand your profile better during the process. We use these tests to avoid biases in the recruitment process. You will get to see your results and hopefully learn more about yourself as well! If you have any opinions or questions about these assessments, please feel free to let us know, we like to receive feedback and continuously rethink our processes.

Work close with everyone in the Product team adding new features and improving existing
Be challenged, learn, and share your own learnings
Have a big impact on our ways of working, with the strive to always be better

The role is perfect if you have experience and interest in...
Mobile Development with React Native
Creating Animations
UI/UX Design and Beautiful Apps
NodeJS and GraphQL

Hos oss kommer du snabbt in i gemenskapen genom våra interna och externa aktiviteter där vi träffas och hittar på något roligt tillsammans.
        
       För den här tjänsten lägger vi stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper. Vi tror att du har ett genuint intresse av människor och drivs av att förstå och hjälpa andra. Brinner du dessutom för utveckling och vill utvecklas inom området kommer du att bli en uppskattad kollega hos oss.
        
        Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning på heltid med en provanställning på 6 månader. Vi vill gärna att du börjar så snart som möjligt. Vi finns i Solna Centrum. 
      
     
     
      
       Ansökan 
       För mer information om tjänsten eller för att ansöka, kontakta oss på career@trustit.se 
       Din ansökan ska skickas in i form av ett personligt brev och CV. 
       Vi behandlar ansökningarna fortlöpande och tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas före sista ansökningsdag.
        
       Omfattning: Heltid, start snarast möjligt
Några av våra kunder:Det här kan vi erbjuda dig:Kunskaper vi söker hos dig:Front-end:CMS:E-handelsplattformar:Molntjänster:Värderingar och egenskaper vi söker hos dig:Placeringsort:

Arbetar du som utvecklare idag? Eller är du intresserad av att ta nästa steg i din karriär? Gillar du att jobba med olika projekt, med apputveckling och vill vara med att förbättra arbetsmiljön för personal inom tandvård- och hälsovårdsbranschen? Då är vi intresserade av att ha en dialog med dig!
   På Service Well jobbar vi inhouse i fasta team. Dina kollegor är dina vänner, mentorer och rådgivare. Vi drivs av att ha kul på jobbet och leverera den bästa möjliga lösningen till våra kunder. Vi sitter i nyrenoverade och fräscha lokaler på gågatan i centrala Lund. Gångavstånd till centralstationen, nära till butiker och restauranger.
   Om tjänsten
   Som Fullstack/Front-End utvecklare på Service Well kommer du tillsammans med dina kollegor att arbeta med innovativa projekt som driver digitaliseringen av tandvården och hälsovården. Du kommer att vara involverad i en tidig fas av utveckling i en vård plattform. Din roll kommer involvera front-end utveckling av IP och våra befintliga produkter.
   Vad vi erbjuder
  
    En utmanande och innovativ miljö med friheten att utforma ditt eget arbetssätt.
    Djup insikt inom hälsa-och tandvården, dess nuvarande och framtida möjligheter och utmaningar.
    En kompetent, aktiv och trevlig arbetsmiljö med stödjande och entusiastiska kollegor.
    En välkomnande mångfald och vi värdesätter varje medarbetares unika perspektiv och egenskaper.
    Möjlighet till professionell- och kompetensutveckling genom utbildningar i linje med karriärsmål eller egna önskemål.
  
   Din profil
   För att passa in i vårt team tror vi att du som individ har en fallenhet för att bolla idéer och tankar med dina kollegor samt har förmåga att ta initiativ och ägandeskap för dina förslag och kunna kommunicera dessa till övriga i organisationen. Du kommer att jobba med väletablerade verksamheter inom tandvården och vården där den personliga kundrelationen är viktig för oss. Därför lägger vi stor vikt vid att du är ödmjuk, bra lyssnare och har hjärtat på rätta plats.
   Vi söker dig som älskar teamwork och programvaruutveckling och kan arbeta som front-end utvecklare alternativ full-stack.
  
    Vi ser att du har bredd av kunskaper och principer inom mjukvaruutveckling.
    Du har minst 5 års erfarenhet av programmering då gärna i JavaScript, React, C# .Net och OAuth.
    Intresse för teknik och programmering.
    Önskvärt om du varit med från start i utvecklingsprocesser.
    Önskvärt men inget krav om du har kunskaper inom HL7 FHIR.
  
   Övrig information
  
    Start: Enligt överenskommelse
    Omfattning: Heltid
    Placering: Grönegatan 1C, 222 24 Lund
  
   Om Service Well
   Service Well AB är ett väletablerat företag med ett tajt och kompetent utvecklingsteam som under de senaste åren framgångsrikt utvecklat molnbaserade affärssystem och integrationslösningar för tandvårds-och hälsosektorn. Vi arbetar med utveckling av applikationer för den nordiska marknaden och skapar programvaror och integrationer som effektiviserar det dagliga arbetet. Som konsult- och produktbolag arbetar vi både med nyutveckling och förvaltning av befintliga kundlösningar. Våra uppdrag är en mix av mindre kundanpassade lösningar och större nationella projekt.

Vi inom IT DEVELOPMENT vill bli fler och ser fram emot att få in fler professionella och drivna kollegor!

Går du igång på välformulerad och strukturerad kod?

Brinner du för att jobba agilt, dela med dig av dina kunskaper och ta del av andras?

Vill du vara med och göra våra kunder framgångsrika?

Vill du ingå i det lilla bolaget med de stora möjligheterna?

Vill du ha möjligheten att vara med och bygga Advanze?

DU:

brinner för system- och/eller webbutveckling (särskilt front-end), uppskattar arbetet som konsult och sätter kunden i centrum. Du har minst fyra års erfarenhet av att jobba som utvecklare, och då med fokus på gränssnitt, användarvänlighet och design. Du håller dig uppdaterad om den senaste tekniken, är prestigelös och motiveras av att ta eget ansvar. Du är strukturerad, lösningsorienterad och tänker proaktivt. Du vill vara med och bygga grunden för vårt nya utvecklingsteam!

VI:

tillhör IT Development som är ett nystartat utvecklingsteam på Advanze. Vi sätter fokus på öppenhet och prestigelöshet genom att bland annat stötta och coacha varandra i våra uppdrag. Vi har högt i tak och tillsammans både påverkar och utvecklar ITD-teamet bolagets utveckling. På Advanze främjar vi en fortsatt personlig och professionell utveckling inom de senaste teknikerna, liksom konsultmässighet för att alltid vara redo för nya utmaningar och utvecklande uppdrag.

Våra kompetenskrav är att du har relevant erfarenhet av att jobba med system- och/eller webbapplikationer av olika komplexitet, är konsultmässig och van att hantera kunder, leverantörer och medarbetare från olika länder och med olika kulturer.

Vi vill att du har:

Eftergymnasial utbildning eller motsvarande kompetens
Minst 3 års erfarenhet av gränssnittsutveckling, med ett medvetet fokus på användarvänlighet och snabba svarstider
Erfarenhet av agilt arbete, continuous delivery och responsiveness
Kan efter behov applicera olika typer av js-ramverk (från Angular till Node) och css-tekniker
Erfarenhet i någon grad av olika typer av e-handelslösningar, CMS, CRM och systemintegrationer
God kännedom om verktyg så som Github, Octopus Deploy, Docker och motsvarande
Det är en stor fördel om du kan påvisa förståelse för hela utvecklingskedjan, även om just front-end är det just DU brinner för!

Intresserad? Ta kontakt med David Lundgren på david.lundgren@advanze.se, 073-558 35 28.

column1: Front-end utvecklare med kunskap inom React sökes till BusinessWith
column4:
Här får du möjligheten att vara med och utveckla ett start-up bolag i expansionsfas! Om du motiveras av att växa i ett företag, där din kompetens värdesätts, så är detta något för dig! Du erbjuds en bred roll och välkomnas till ett ambitöst team där kulturen präglas av utvecklingsfokus. Har du goda kunskaper i JavaScript eller React och vill fortsätta utvecklas inom frontend? Sök tjänsten redan idag då vi rekryterar löpande!
Om tjänsten
BusinessWith är ett start-up bolag som vill underlätta för företag att hitta rätt system, genom att skapa en digital marknadsplats där olika systemlösningar jämförs. Kunden får en snabb och tydlig överblick i vad som skiljer dem olika system åt. Kunden kan jämföra allt från pris och systemegenskaper till produktfunktioner och omdömen. Utifrån kundens behov och förutsättningar genereras sedan en rekommendation.

Idag arbetar fyra medarbetare på BusinessWith. Du erbjuds här en möjlighet att ansluta till teamet i ett tidigt skede. Detta innebär goda karriärmöjligheter och en chans att vara med och utveckla organisationen.

Arbetsuppgifter
Underhålla och vidareutveckla företagets externa webbapplikation genom implementation av design.

Ansvara för företagets SEO och optimering.

Implementera och skapa nya moduler till webbapplikationen.

Förbättra användarvänligheten genom analysering av webbapplikationen

Vi söker dig som
Har en eftergymnasial utbildning inom systemutveckling/front-end, datateknik och/eller motsvarande utbildning.

Har goda kunskaper inom HTML, Javascript och React. Denna kunskap kan du ha fått genom studier eller tidigare arbete.

Har goda kunskaper i både svenska och engelska.

Det är meriterande om du har tidigare arbetslivserfarenhet inom React eller Javascript.

Vi lägger stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper och söker dig som är:

Självgående
Ansvarstagande
Initiativtagande
Samarbetsvillig

Omfattning: Heltid.
