column1: Front-end utvecklare som vill göra Skillnad!!
column4:
SKILLNAD
Är du vår nästa front end-utvecklare?
Nu letar Skillnad efter nästa kollega som vill vara med och lägga grunden för vår framtida produktportfölj och tillväxt.
Är du nyfiken, älskar att lära nytt och vill arbeta i ett litet bolag med ambitionen att växa? Då kommer du att trivas hos oss på Skillnad.
Vi vill sätta teamutveckling på kartan och göra det tillgängligt för fler. Vi vill att teamutveckling ska bli en del i vardagen för våra kunder och därför skapar vi verktyg och produkter som enkelt kan användas digitalt och som löpande finns som ett stöd för dig och ditt team.
Med våra verktyg kan våra kunder exempelvis:
Göra teamutveckling till en del av vardagen och tillgängligt för alla i en organisation. Med hjälp av uppdrag, uppmaningar och tips hjälper verktyget teamet att ta ansvar för sin egen utveckling
Kartlägga ett teams styrkor och svagheter för att sätta fokus på de områden ett team behöver jobba lite extra med och belysa de områden som teamet redan är starka i
Följa och stötta beteendeförändringar och mål som ett team eller en individ vill nå, digitalt och över tid

Våra kunder är både stora och små organisationer och myndigheter men vi arbetar även i partnerskap med andra konsultföretag som tillhandahåller utbildningar till företag.
Rollens ansvarsområden
Vi är idag ett litet bolag med stora ambitioner där du får möjligheten att vara med och påverka på riktigt. I rollen som front end-utvecklare hos oss får du en nyckelroll på bolaget där du får vara med och forma utvecklingen av våra produkter inom allt från arkitektur och teknikval till processer och framtida rekryteringar.
Som front end-utvecklare på Skillnad kommer du att ta ansvar för Skillnads samtliga front end-applikationer där du både självständigt och i team arbetar med att driva förbättringar och ta ansvar för lösningen. Du kommer jobba i nära samarbete med framför allt vår back end-arkitekt och VD, det är även VD du rapporterar till.
Vem är du?
Vi söker dig som har minst 3-5 års erfarenhet av arbete inom front end-utveckling, gärna med UX-kompetens.
Du har en kandidatexamen eller motsvarande inom programvaruutveckling och kompetens inom både Arkitektur och Utveckling. Du är självgående, drivs av utmaningar och vill vara med och utveckla och leverera produkter som gör skillnad.
Du har stor vana av och är kompetent inom Javascript och React. Det är även meriterande om du har jobbat med .Net eller Java, Tillgänglighet samt molnbaserade lösningar som AWS, Azure eller Google Cloud.
Vi ser även gärna att du har erfarenhet av:
HTML, CSS och TypeScript
JavaScript-ramverk/bibliotek som React, Angular och/eller Vue.js
Node.js och Next.js/Nuxt.js
SASS/LESS
Agila arbetsmetoder som Scrum, Kanban eller SAFe
UX/UI
Php

Om oss
Vi vill att alla människor ska känna sig sedda och hörda, utvecklas, vara engagerade och trivas på jobbet. Kort och gott att älska måndagar! Därför finns Skillnad.
Med hjälp av digitala verktyg byggda på forskning och beprövade metoder skapar vi beteendeförändring och stöttar deltagare och organisationer att uppnå verklig utveckling.
Skillnad bildar partnerskap med företag, myndigheter, kommuner och organisationer som vill stötta, driva och påverka sina medarbetares och ledares arbetsvardag med hjälp av träning, metodik och stödsystem för att uppnå verklig utveckling och för att själva kunna ta ansvar för detta.
Vi är idag ett litet team i Skillnad som arbetar i nära samarbete med vårt moderbolag Move Management.
Förmåner
Friskvårdsbidrag (3500 SEK/år)
Tjänstepension
Företagstelefon
Dator (PC/Mac)

Övrig information om tjänsten
Omfattning: Heltid
Start: Mitten av april eller enligt överenskommelse
Plats: Stockholm, Växjö, Karlskrona med möjlighet till hybridupplägg – dock inte 100% på distans
Deadline för ansökningar: Tjänsten tillsätts löpande, skicka in din ansökan så snart som möjligt.
 Besvara gärna följande två frågor i ditt personliga brev.
Varför vill du jobba i ett litet bolag, och på Skillnad i synnerhet?
Beskriv hur du arbetat tidigare i en liknande roll där du tog ansvar för de delar vi söker i rollen. Lyft fram detaljer i hur du lagt upp ditt arbete och egenskaper samt berätta vad som lyckats bra och mindre bra.

Vi ser fram emot att träffa dig!

column1: Front-End utvecklare till Castra, Sveriges attraktivaste...
column4:
Vi utmanar de traditionella konsultbolagen och vi kan med stolthet säga att Castra är konsultbranschens mest utvecklande arbetsplats där allt är möjligt. Känns det här som företaget för dig så läs gärna vidare.
Är du eller någon du känner sugen på en ny utmaning? Castra är IT bolaget för dig som vill ta nästa steg. Hos oss får du både intressanta uppdrag, och stor möjlighet att påverka det som betyder mest för dig. Det kan vara arbetstid, arbetsuppgifter, lön, utbildning, delägarskap och mycket mer.
Vem är du?
Du älskar att koda och JavaScript sitter i ryggmärgen. Du manipulerar DOM:en utan jQuery och att jobba med moderna byggverktyg känns självklart för dig. Dessutom har du naturligtvis koll på HTML/CSS, webbstandards, mobil utveckling och ditt defaultläge är att jobba agilt. Du bör vara intresserad av det som trendar just nu (exempelvis React, Vue.js, Angular, Node.js, TypeScript, Cloud-plattformar och Continuous Delivery).
Vi ser gärna att du har en längre arbetslivserfarenhet efter dina studier från något tekniskt universitet. Sannolikt är du systemvetare eller ingenjör. Viktigast är dock att du är en relationsbyggande person som trivs i konsultrollen.
Varför ska du välja oss?
Här tror vi på frihet, möjligheter och medbestämmande. Att du som medarbetare ska ha möjlighet att utvecklas och forma ditt arbete utefter dina intressen och prioriteringar i livet. Att alla får vara med och forma och påverka bolaget genom delägarskap, advisory board och projektgrupper. Att det är viktigt att ha ett sammanhang, känna tillhörighet och att man har kollegor som stöttar, utvecklar och tror på en.
Om Castra
Castra är en entreprenörsdriven konsultgrupp inom IT, management och systemutveckling. Bolaget ägs gemensamt av medarbetarna och tillsammans bygger vi det företag vi själva vill jobba på.
Vår vision är att vi ska vara Sveriges bästa arbetsgivare för konsulter. Att vi blivit certifierade av Great Place to Work fem år i rad är ett bevis på våra höga mål kring företagskultur. Våra tankar om delaktighet, påverkansmöjligheter och respekt för individens egna val och möjligheter fungerar.
Företaget har kontor i Göteborg, Stockholm, Helsingborg, Malmö, Linköping, Norrköping, Örebro och Jönköping. Mer information om Castra-koncernen hittar du på vår hemsida www.castra.se.
Har vi lyckats väcka din nyfikenhet? Sök direkt via länken eller kontakta Mikaela.Friberg@castra.se Tfn: 0763249431

Since you’ve landed on this page, you already know Hedvig is a mover and shaker in insurtech, and think you might have what it takes to join us. As the only loved insurance company in Sweden (in the world?), we’ve proven that it’s possible to disrupt an entire industry with people’s best interests at heart. But our journey is just beginning, starting with Sweden, Denmark and Norway! We’ve been working hard since the very beginning to change an industry that is hard to love – to something at least likeable. At Hedvig we believe the only way to do so is to work with loveable people.
We are currently hiring for our “Purchase Journey” team who work mostly on developing our public website. They collaborate closely with product, design, back-end, as well as app developers, to create the best experience for our customers. The website is powered by React and TypeScript. On top of this, we also use Koa, GraphQL with Apollo, and the headless CMS Storyblok.
What about the role?
As a front-end web developer at Hedvig, you will:
Solve complex problems in our front-end projects.Spend time developing and improving our platform in collaboration with our designers.You’ll solve issues of code scalability as well as exciting UX challenges, as Hedvig expands both in number of products and to new markets.

What about you?
We look for developers who aim high and don't play it safe. We love creative problem-solvers who are not afraid to try new things and keep learning with other people.
We generally believe the following would make you a perfect fit:
You are fluent in modern Javascript and React, preferably also Typescript.You have some experience with GraphQL and ApolloMight be familiar with headless CMS such as StoryblockYou are comfortable with CI/CD pipelinesYou truly value knowledge sharing and learning together since you will be part of a team that enjoys pair programming and takes code reviews to heart.

What about us?
As part of the Hedvig team, you quickly notice that "general truths" are not accepted without being questioned. We're an enthusiastic group of people who love to challenge each other to find the best way forward. We don't care who says something; we care about what's being said. We put a lot of effort into building a trusting culture where freedom, collective thinking, and individual ownership have center stage. We're not perfect–far from it – but we talk about and learn from our mistakes and imperfections to improve continuously. And we have a lot of fun along the way! As individuals, as a team, and as a company.
Sounds like your next challenge? You can start by sending us an application. If you don't feel ready maybe you want to know more about us? Then check out our LinkedIn page where we regularly post inspiring thoughts from our people, and also our Career page where we (try to) share our values If you have questions regarding the position, please feel free to write to careers@hedvig.com.

Location: Gothenburg, Sweden

Function/department: Public Safety

Front-End WPF/XAML Developer saving lives

An ambulance with emergency lights on quickly navigates through traffic to rescue a person in distress. The feeling that you have contributed to the rapid response of the ambulance is very rewarding. The contribution to society is evident when you work with technology that saves lives.

We are about 100 people at CSAM Public Safety. The majority are located in Gothenburg, but we also have offices in Oslo, Karlstad, Stockholm, Valencia (Spain), Reading (UK) and Auckland (NZ). Of course, we also have “home offices” and it is perfectly ok to be working from home too. We are expanding and growing our team looking for a software developer who is passionate about innovation and want to contribute with new ideas and breaking new grounds. We have a culture of collaboration and knowledge sharing. If you want to work in this inspiring environment where you also contribute to society – then this might be the position for you!

Your daily work
You will systemize and develop software for mission critical operations such as Emergency Response (112) or Search and Rescue. You will work with implementing new technologies, new functionality, and be part of our journey to migrate our architecture to run on containers and move into the cloud. Your role will be to work in the development team together with the other developers, product owners and solution architects to ensure that this is systemized and implemented in the best way.

You will initially work primarily with front-end (user interface) based on input from UX design. Since we have a complete software stack, it is possible to work also with the back-end over time. Our products’ target characteristics are user-friendly, automation and simplicity. We also make sure to have fun at work – we believe that if you have fun together with your colleagues, you also do a good job!

Who are you?
You have a passion for systemization and programming and constantly want to develop your skills and are happy to share your knowledge and ideas with the entire team. In addition to your university degree in software engineering, you are a team player with a positive attitude and can-do mentality. Furthermore, you are good at finding solutions that you are explaining verbally and in writing.

We expect that you have at least five years of relevant experience in:

.NET and C#
Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) and XAML
Git

It is a merit if you also have experience of one or more of the following:

Web technologies and development tools, such as React/Redux
New development technologies like WinUI, MAUI, Blazor etc.

Swedish citizenship is required, as well as full proficiency in English and Swedish, both spoken and in writing.

Want to know more?

If you want to know more, contact Mattias Litzell at mattias.litzell@carmenta.com or mobile 072-968 63 61. You are welcome to submit your application. Since selection and interviews are conducted on a continuous basis, we ask you to submit your application as soon as possible.

About CSAM and CSAM Public Safety
CSAM Public Safety is a growing software business area that develops information technology solutions for mission-critical systems in an international environment. Our products and solutions are used, for example, in advanced management systems for emergency response authorities as well as in public web portals where high demands are placed on performance and reliability. We are part of the CSAM Health Group with more than 250 employees. CSAM Health AS is headquartered in Oslo.

War On Cancer is a Stockholm-based tech startup that aims to radically improve the wellbeing of everyone affected by cancer. The first step towards achieving that has been to create the social network and app; War On Cancer.
You will be joining a fast paced company in a very interesting time with the possibility to shape processes, our ways of working and the company as a whole. Our Engineering team today consist of 10 engineers and we have the ambition to double that over the coming year.
What you will be doing:

Work across our tech stack (React, next.js, node.js, Docker/Kubernetes, Github Actions, Elasticsearch, Kafka and much more)
Build and maintain scalable applications, implement smooth user experience with high quality
Be a part of the product development process including design, planning, testing, implementing, shipping and so forth
Constantly learn new things, explore technology, integrations and best practises together with self and team-improvements
Work in a fast-paced, collaborative, and inclusive environment, with a high level of freedom and responsibility

What you'll bring to the team:

A couple of years’ experience with software development and a bachelor in Computer Science or equivalent
A strong coding ability in Javascript with a clear quality first mindset
Solid knowledge in React and Nodejs or equivalent, together with an awareness of best practices for web development.
A "doer" mentality and growth mindset, with a passion for solving problems wherever they are in any shape
Experience working with tools such as Git together with CI/CD pipelines
Passion for building high quality products with the user in focus

You would join as one of the initial hires within Web in our Stockholm Engineering team and would have a great opportunity to be part of shaping the processes, building the team and setting the ways of working moving forward. This is your chance to be part of something big that will have an impact on peoples health and wellbeing, physically, emotionally and psychologically. We encourage personal development and an open environment where no ideas are bad ideas.
We strongly believe that great engineers wants to and can learn new technologies quickly so in case you are not familiar with everything above; don't worry, you'll learn on the job!
If you have any questions regarding War On Cancer, jobs or recruitment process don't hesitate to contact us.

Frontend Architect
As we grow, we want to create a unified look-and-feel for the SeenThis’ products and applications. Therefore, we are now hiring a frontend developer and architect for the SeenThis tech team.
If you are motivated by leading frontend initiatives with state-of-the-art technologies, this should be the perfect fit for you.
We are looking for someone who has been deep diving in Vue.js the last few years (or other modern frontend frameworks) and is casually scrolling through Dribble or Behance with their morning coffee.
You probably have a good sense for design, user experience and work best in a role where you can be close to the craft (code) – but still have the ability to zoom out and contribute to the bigger picture as well.
About SeenThis
Since 2017, SeenThis has been evolving screen experiences for everyone, everywhere. With our groundbreaking adaptive streaming technology, we are transforming the distribution of digital content, to increase performance and reduce impact on the climate.
With billions of streams served for more than 1,000 brands in over 40 countries, we push petabytes of data through our systems each month. If you’re wondering about requests per second, we’ll tell you over a Zoom coffee.
“That sounds cool, but what about the people?”
Well, here you can find pretty much everyone. Nerds, introverts, extroverts, sales gurus, start-up junkies, 9-to-5ers, daydreamers, visionaries – yes, we even have an office plant named Fred.
Our tech team describes our culture as encouraging, inclusive, and innovative. They believe that both personal and professional growth comes from relentlessly solving new and evermore complex problems by testing new solutions together with people that both challenge you and make you laugh. They believe in you, and your ability to deliver what is expected, and will give you the freedom to choose how.
We are growing fast and raised a new round of financing to fuel the buildout of our organization and the resulting global expansion. Although we’ve already come a long way, we feel like our journey just has begun and hope that you want to join this fantastic team on our mission to reshape the internet — for good.
About the role
As Frontend Architect, you will have the opportunity to develop our frontend, design, user experience – and take it to the next level! In this role, you will be hands on with coding while simultaneously setting the standard for our front-end vision and strategy.
As the team is mainly focused on back-end development today, you will be responsible for initiating, driving, and leading frontend initiatives – of course, with the support of your other team members.
We are currently developing our CMS as well as our client-facing applications “Video Drop” & “Image drop”. In addition to frontend development, we hope you will analyze our customer flows, to develop and optimize the user experience accordingly.
Our goal is to create a common component library to be able to reuse and make the development process more efficient. Also, it is great if you can contribute to the documentation of the frontend parts so that we can share knowledge with existing and new members of the team.

Do you have the ambition to take a Team Lead role in the future? Great! As the teams are growing, we are strongly encouraging those who want to help take responsibility for others.
We expect you to:

Have approximately 5 years of experience with frontend development

Be highly experienced with Javascript (preferably Vue.js)

Have been involved in bigger frontend projects and created a uniform, yet creative frontend/design

Have a passion for driving change, setting the structure, and sharing knowledge across teams

Professional proficiency in English

We offer you:

The opportunity to grow with a Swedish tech company

An exciting role with ownership for the frontend strategy
Great compensation for great work

A flexible workplace with a remote hybrid policy, and a social HQ office by the water, close to Södermalm in Stockholm

Please apply as soon as possible as we review applications and interview on a continuous basis.

Besides our smoking cessation app that is live, we are currently developing a DTx treating anxiety and depression in patients with a rare lung disease. Projects targeting cancer, obesity, fatigue, and more are in the pipeline.
   We are looking for an ambitious engineer with an entrepreneurial mindset who wants to make a positive impact on the world. You will become a core member of the tech team and take on a broad set of responsibilities, working closely with a small and highly skilled product development team. This is a great opportunity to become an important team member of a startup with huge growth potential and to join the adventure that lies ahead!
   Your profile
   You enjoy programming and like to get things done. No task is too big or too small for you. If you do not know how to solve a problem, you see that as a possibility to learn something–not as an obstacle. You take ownership over your tasks and strive to deliver high quality results. You are excited about the opportunity of working in a fast-paced and fast-growing startup where your work will have a large impact on the company–and a positive impact on the world. You have experience as a frontend developer, or you are confident that you can learn quickly with the help of those around you. Aside from technical skills, you are a strong problem solver.

   Fluent in English 
   Holding required permits to work and live in Sweden

    This is a full time position. 
   Part-flexible location with the Alex Therapeutics office located at Upplandsgatan 7, Stockholm 
   5 weeks paid vacation, pension and wellness benefits

We are growing and looking for our next Frontend Developer that wants to be a part of the future of esports!
What you'll do
We have several teams working with modern JavaScript technologies and are currently mostly using React, Redux and NodeJs.
As a Frontend Developer at G-Loot you will have an opportunity to greatly impact and shape the esports industry. You will be given a lot of freedom and responsibility to create and shape our product.
You will grow and develop our platform, mainly focused on PC, by developing new and scalable features. This includes being involved in the whole development cycle, working tight with other developers, product owners, and designers.
Please note this position is located in Stockholm, Sweden - we will not be able to provide a visa or travel re-location for this role.
Who we think you are
First of all, you can't wait to enter the fast paced world of esports!
As our new colleague, we believe you genuinely care about web technologies and love modern JavaScript, just as we do. You highly value writing quality code but don’t back out from taking risks for greater causes. We think you have an adaptable and creative way of solving problems.
You should be a team player and have good communication and social skills.

You have experience developing front-end applications using modern frameworks such as React, Angular or Vue
You have at least 4+ years of experience using modern web frameworks
You know how to build web applications from the ground up
You are used to Git
Deep knowledge about state management and other, broader programming principles; Redux, MobX
You have experience building and using of RESTful APIs
Big plus if you

Have a Engineering degree or equivalent
Have any experience with electron or similar type native JavaScript application
Have experience as a Tech Lead or equivalent
Have a passion for design and UX
Have a passion for gaming and esports
What’s in it for you?
At G-Loot we believe it’s a team effort to build really great esports products. We’re a tight team that loves to challenge each other, and share a vision on making esports available for everyone.

Work in a startup culture that live and breathe esports, where you will be growing our platform for the latest games.
Enjoy being part of a fast-paced and creative environment, where AW's and esports tournaments are a part of our everyday life.
Health benefits and pension.
Great potential for personal growth.
Hack Days - we want to learn from each other, and value a knowledge-sharing culture.

We look forward to get to know you!
Our mission
G-Loot enables gamers across the world to compete in skill-based games they already love and play. Through our unique online platform we host fun and exciting esports tournaments in some of the worlds biggest game titles on both PC and Mobile. In 2017 we launched our brand and platform GLL where we broadcast global esports tournaments and leagues to millions of fans worldwide.
Today we are the world’s first cross-platform company in esports. Our mission is to make esports available for all.
Our philosophy on inclusion is simple; how do we successfully reach and engage our gamers and users across all continents? By focusing on hiring a diverse team, always encouraging applicants from all demographics, backgrounds and cultures!

GeoGuessr är ett spel där du får upptäcka världen och testa din förmåga att lista ut var du befinner dig. Vår resa började redan 2013, men har i många avseenden precis börjat. Under de senaste åren har vi fokuserat på att bygga ett fantastiskt team och investera i att förbättra vårt spel och skapa fler spellägen. Och intresset för att spela GeoGuessr fortsätter att växa starkt, där vi nyligen passerade över 40 miljoner registrerade spelare i fler än 140 länder. 
  Vi är idag 25 personer som arbetar på GeoGuessr och omsatte drygt 120 MSEK föregående år med fortsatt hög tillväxt under 2022. Nu går vi in i nästa fas mot vår vision att få alla att upptäcka hur roligt det är att utforska världen med GeoGuessr, och ta vårt spel till en trippel-A spelupplevelse både på webben och i våra appar. För det behöver vi just dig!
  
   Rollbeskrivning
   Vi söker frontendutvecklare till vår tech-organisation. Du kommer att ingå i ett av våra tvärfunktionella team där du ansvarar för att leverera välstrukturerad kod av hög kvalité.
   Tillsammans utvecklar vi en fantastiskt spelupplevelse i en snabbrörlig miljö där du och ditt team har ett helhetsansvar för leveransen, och du värdesätter att vi dagligen får ut förbättringar och nya funktioner till våra miljontals spelare.   Du gillar att se det som vi bygger utifrån spelarnas perspektiv, och du använder de tekniska verktyg och färdigheter du besitter för att balansera spelarnöjdhet med teknisk kvalité.
   Du kommer att arbeta med tekniker som t.ex. TypeScript, React och Next.js.
   Vem är du?
   
    Solid erfarenhet (minst 3 års arbetslivserfarenhet) av JavaScript/TypeScript, React och CSS 
   Erfarenhet av att bygga produkter som riktar sig till slutkonsument 
   God kunskap om att integrera med API:er 
   Högskoleutbildning inom datavetenskap eller motsvarande erfarenhet
  
  
   Meriterande
   
    Design och UX 
   Animationer och ljud 
   Three.js/WebGL 
   Spelutveckling
  
  
   Förmåner
   
    Pension och försäkring enligt ITP1 
   Optionsprogram 
   Work from anywhere 
   6 semesterveckor 
   50 000 kr i årlig kompetensutveckling 
   5 000 kr friskvårdsbidrag
  
  
   Som en del av GeoGuessr kommer du att märka att vi är en framåtlutad organisation som hatar att förlora. Vårt recept för att vinna är att ge alla medarbetare tillit, ansvar och befogenheter. Vi gör resan tillsammans och det är bara genom samarbete och en gemensam vision vi kommer att lyckas. 
  Vi vill att våra medarbetare i stor grad ska kunna välja sin arbetsplats så länge det planeras tillsammans med sitt team. Vi satsar samtidigt på att skapa vårt alldeles egna och unika hem på Katarinavägen 17, i glashuset vid Slussen, där alla ska vilja hänga och umgås tillsammans. Där kommer det bland annat att serveras både frukost och lunch.
   Träning och kultur är viktigt för oss. Därför uppmuntrar vi träning under arbetstid, att besöka museum eller bara ta en skön stund och njuta av konsten vi har på kontoret. Självklart fixar vi med tvätt av träningskläder, handdukar och ett stort utbud av snacks och dryck för återhämtning. Ett hem att trivas i helt enkelt.

”På PriceRunner är vi ständigt up to date med de senaste teknologierna och har ett klimat där det är enkelt att ställa frågor och diskutera lösningar, vilket göra att man hela tiden utvecklas och får testa nya grejer”

Vårt huvudkontor ligger bredvid T-centralen. Varför bli en ”PriceRunner”?
Vi erbjuder dig en arbetsplats i teknisk framkant som främjar att våra utvecklare får jobba med tekniker just de brinner för. Du erbjuds en ambitiös arbetsmiljö med en stark framåtanda där vi hela tiden jobbar för att utveckla nya saker och ny funktionalitet för ständig förbättring av vår site. Förvaltning är helt enkelt inte vår grej!
Vänta inte, bli en av oss nu!

Jobbeskrivning
Att finna synergier mellan olika branscher är viktigt både för våra kunder och för oss på AFRY. Vi jobbar för att våra konsulter skall har ”flera ben” att stå på. Detta innebär att både AFRY och våra konsulter utvecklas kontinuerligt, tillsammans. Just nu utökar vi våra två utvecklarteam i Stockholm med kompetens inom Frontend utveckling, då vi har flera pågående projekt med behov. Därför söker vi dig som har en gedigen bakgrund inom området och vill vara med och utveckla och leverera kvalitet i våra kundprojekt.
På vårt kontor i Stockholm har vi en stor inhouse-verksamhet inom IT där vi utvecklar produkter inom flera olika branscher. Vi har kunder både nationellt och internationellt där vi bedriver helhetsåtaganden. Det ställer höga krav på oss och våra konsulter, både vad gäller kompetens och leveransförmåga. För att möta kraven har vi en genomgående strategi att arbeta fokuserat på kompetensutveckling för våra konsulter. Det görs genom kompetensprojekt, seminarier och utbildningar inom olika områden. Allt skräddarsytt för dig som konsult.
Har du en bakgrund som möter kraven nedan? Välkommen med ansökan, vi rekryterar löpande till våra spännande uppdrag.

Våra värdeord Brave, Devoted, Teamplayers kännetecknar hur vi ser på oss själva. Frontend developer
THE OPPORTUNITY
At Boozt we work in small cross functional teams of up to six developers in a big community. In total we are 170 developers spread across 5 locations. At Boozt, a high standard of code is important, which we manage through the latest technology stack, internal code reviews and sharing knowledge through hackathons, conferences and weekly talks. Here we love to develop, not only the code but also ourselves as developers!
Our front-end developers are constantly looking for ways to improve front-end performance and be on top of user-centric metrics like the Core Web Vitals. In our infinite quest for better performance we use Datadog RUM (real user monitoring), to look at real time data from our users, create dashboards and define our SLOs. We also develop our own systems and improve our ways of working throughout the whole organization.
We are currently looking for two frontend developers. One of you will be focusing and be a part of a team that is building our UI component library. The UI component library is a design system that will make our work more efficient - easier onboarding, faster time to production for features and better maintainability with trickle down updates throughout our webshops - this will allow us to focus on even more new cool features to improve the experience for our users.
The other one main task will be to continuously improve and add new features to “the Editor” in our CMS. This is an own developed desktop-like application (called “the Editor”), as part of our Content Management System, which makes it possible for our internal stakeholders to create and publish landing pages and campaigns on our webshops, without any real time help from a developer. Working very close to business for us is a must as we can get immediate feedback, create new features and improve the user experience.
WHAT YOU WILL DO
Front-end development in Typescript and Javascript. We use React and Redux.
Develop and deliver high-quality products and services, for example build and develop our new UI component library or our own developed CMS Editor.
Participate in design and code reviews.
Identify and address performance bottlenecks.
Identify areas of improvement and proactively implement those with your team.
 YOUR PROFILE
At least 2 years experience within JavaScript
You have experience with at least one Javascript frameworks, such as React, Vue.js or similar.
BS or MS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field desirable.
Fluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered)
To be successful in our culture it is a lot about enjoying working in an agile, dynamic and team based environment. Here we love to discuss our solutions in order to always improve. You are a person that is open to sharing your knowledge, are curious and humble about the fact that the only thing consistent in technology is change.
Please apply for this position as soon as possible as we work with ongoing selection and interviews.

Welcome with your application!

Froda was founded in 2015 with a clear vision – to revolutionize the banking experience for entrepreneurs by making it easy and affordable for them to invest in their ideas. Today, we are one of Sweden's fastest growing fintechs with major international growth plans. We are a creative tech company with the ambition to turn a historically expensive and unfair industry into something ethical, sustainable, and forward-thinking. Behind the company are several well-known investors and talents from e.g., Avanza, Spotify, Google, and Klarna.

In order to create a great banking experience for our customers, we want to grow with more talented frontend developers. You will work and collaborate closely with other developers, UX designers, and product managers.

We are a passionate team with an open culture, and we truly believe that the best decisions are taken by combining people's knowledge!

About ComplyLog
ComplyLog is today owned by a company called Euronext. Euronext owns the stock exchanges in Amsterdam, Brussels, Dublin, Lisbon, London, Milan, Oslo and Paris. This means that we can offer a corporate environment that combines the small startup with elements of being part of an international group.
ComplyLog's products simplify and automate corporate needs in regulatory compliance, through easy-to-use and efficient digital tools. We have the leading solution for insider list management in the Nordic region and are now expanding across Europe with a broader product portfolio.
InsiderLog is a web-based platform based on an annual subscription model and has already managed to attract more than 800 customers including well-known blue-chip companies, banks and law firms since the start in 2016.
IntegrityLog is a simple online tool that enables anonymous reporting of all potential ethical violations and errors. With the implementation of the EU's whistleblowing directive 2021, IntegrityLog ensures that companies follow the rules and guarantees a secure platform for whistleblowers.
LiabilityLog is a digital liability register that saves time and ensures that you comply with Finnish municipal law.

About us

We believe that a diverse and flexible environment, whilst having fun and the freedom to make decisions about your own daily work, is the key to building great teams and staying innovative. Our main values are: We act, we care, we deliver. Not only as a business to our customers, but also as colleagues and team members towards each other. We want to work with people with diverse backgrounds, interests, and experiences, as it makes us stronger as an organization.

The role
We are looking for curious Frontend Developers with all levels of experience to further strengthen our development teams' ability to turn user stories into shippable code.

You will be part of a cross-functional, self-organizing and supportive team where you will work using the Agile principles with the goal of delivering high quality code and improving our product and processes.

You will take part in discussions with your product owner to give technical insight, as well as trouble-shoot and solve production incidents.

To fit well in the team, you should

Have a curious mindset
Be triggered by challenges
Enjoy learning new things
Take ownership of the things you and your team own
Have React experience

Our backend is powered by a LEMP stack, GraphQL and we rely on Vue.js for our frontend. Other technologies we work with are LXC, Redis, Cassandra, ElasticSearch, and Hadoop to mention a few. We are inherently a curious team and are always on the lookout for new technologies that could potentially be incorporated into our stack.
  
   You will: 
  
   Design and implement new Frontend features.
   
  
   Perform functional requirements analysis.
   
  
   Propose and own architectural solutions across multiple projects.
   
  
   Write high-quality code and documentation.
   
  
   Maintain and improve code in multiple projects including legacy code.
   
  
   Work closely with other developers, QA, and product teams.
   
  
   Apply analytical skills and be committed to quality.
   
  
   Help track requests, issues, work progress, and any other changes using our project management tools.
   
  
   Provide estimates and technical documentation on request.
   
  
   Be sensitive to the performance, reliability, and maintainability of your code.
   
  
   Work in collaboration with external partners when required.
   
  
   Manage your code changes using our version control system.
   
  
   Perform code reviews.
  
  
   Who are you? 
  
   You have a minimum of 2 years of experience in a comparable role.
   
  
   You have hands-on experience with JavaScript ES6, HTML5, CSS, and Vue.js (or similar JavaScript frameworks – React or Ember.js)
   
  
   You are familiar with Webpack or similar modern JS tools.
   
  
   You understand the principles of User Experience (UX) analysis/design.
   
  
   You are experienced with solving browser and device-specific issues.
   
  
   You can multi-task, prioritize and be able to work on your own initiative .
   
  
   You have a good command of both verbal and written English.
   
  
   Experience in iGaming would be considered an advantage.
   
  
   Having a degree in Information Technology or another related field would be considered an advantage.
  
  
   What do we offer? 
  
   Flexible start and finish times
   
  
   30 paid vacation days a year
   
  
   Relaxed working environment
   
  
   Private health insurance

Company Description
   Devoteam Creative Tech Malmö is filled with curious, bold and humbly brilliant people. We are divided into five creative tech studios and part of the Devoteam family, incorporating ‘design thinking’ and ‘data thinking’ into everything we do. Our culture builds on individual empowerment and contribution, knowledge sharing, continuous improvement and learning. If you want to know more about what it’s like to be a part of us, get in touch and join us on our journey!
 
  Job Description
   The main purpose of the team is to develop and deliver innovative and high-quality solutions for clients that provide actual business value. As a front end developer you will contribute by designing well-performing, accessible and testable web apps. Being part of a team also means you have a shared ownership and responsibility of helping the team in the development process to solve the right problems in the right way. You’ll get to use both your creativity and your problem solving skills in this role and there are many opportunities to learn new things and grow within the role.
 
  Qualifications
   To succeed in this role, we believe that you are open-minded to new ideas and flexible when meeting new challenges. You enjoy collaborating and are comfortable sharing your knowledge with your colleagues and clients. To thrive in this role and at Devoteam Creative Tech we also believe you are humble and have a solution oriented approach.  Some things we’d like you to be good at:
  
    JavaScript/TypeScript, CSS, HTML
    Responsive design
    SEO
    Web accessibility
    Test libraries such as Cypress, Jest or similar
    Git
  
   Also beneficial if you have experience with:
  
    CI/CD pipelines
    Understanding of UX
  
   Additional Information
   At Devoteam Malmö you get:
  
    10-12 competence days per year, where we attend conferences, internal sharing days, travel abroad for inspiration and benefit a great internal network of competence
    Challenging and rewarding assignments; many of them end-to-end
    Wellness grants for sports activities (5000 SEK/year)
    Computer, phone and telephone subscription
    Passionate and skilled colleagues
    A human-centric and value-based culture
    A variety of social events
  
   About Devoteam Creative Tech We are a part of Devoteam, a leading consulting firm focused on digital strategy, tech platforms and cybersecurity. With 25 years experience and 8,000 employees across Europe, Middle East and Africa, Devoteam promotes responsible tech for people and works to create better change.
   Combining the perks of a smaller company with the resources and opportunities of a major global player, Devoteam Creative Tech Stockholm is a small studio and part of a network of studios and companies within the global Devoteam group. The smaller studios make sure you are always seen and help facilitate your growth and development while the global network opens up endless opportunities to create a large impact.
   Creating high quality digital products by combining creativity, design and development is what we do. We focus on running long term projects that deliver measurable business value for the clients we choose to work with. We incorporate ‘design thinking’ and ‘data thinking’ into everything we do.
   Competence development is at the center of our company culture and we invest both time and money in supporting our employees’ growth. With established competence communities you are always able to discuss and review solutions, technical ideas and issues with others within your competence areas. We also have 10-12 dedicated competence days per year and regularly have internal knowledge sharing days.
   A fair chance. Devoteam Creative Tech is open to applications from all sections of society. We believe diverse teams help us make better products. We welcome all people regardless of age, gender identity or expression, experience and background.
   Our recruitment process. We invite all suitable candidates in for interviews to learn more about you and introduce ourselves. If our culture and expectations align, we ask you to do a technical assignment before inviting you to a technical interview. After this is a final interview with the studio lead.
   We apply continuous recruitment, so make sure to send in your application as soon as possible as the position can be filled before the last application day.

column1: Frontend Developer - React focus to Agria Vet Guide!
column4:
Help animals get better care with your coding skills
   At Agria Vet Guide (Agria Vårdguide) we’re creating the future of animal care. Our team develops a platform that helps pet owners get in touch with veterinarians so they can make better decisions about the healthcare needs of their pets.
   As a developer at Agria Vet Guide you will use your skills to help people who are in the vulnerable situation of having an unwell pet by improving both our customer facing apps and the internal tools used by our specialists and admins. No workday will look the same and your work will make a huge impact for thousands of people as part of our small agile team.
   We need your help to scale our solution
   We’re growing fast and our solution is expanding. In order for us to continue this exciting journey we think we need to further improve our DevOps practices, cybersecurity, cloud architecture and overall code quality. We think you’re strong in one of those areas and that you want to help us improve it and spread your knowledge about the area to other team members.
   Our Stack: React, React Native, Node (Nest), TypeScript, MySQL, AWS
   What we expect you to do:
   
    Work closely with designers and developers as part of our small agile team with a primary focus on improving our frontend React and React Native code 
   Help us automate the testing of our apps so that our solution can expand without requiring an excessive amount of manual testing 
   Share your React knowledge with your developer colleagues to help the whole team get stronger 
   Bring a your perspective as someone specialized in React into discussions with product management and the rest of the team about how we should define our solution roadmap 
   Lead the development of the frontend in our React and React Native apps, taking on a wide variety of tasks to get best practices in place 
   Select the most suitable tools and methods for the job at hand 
   Help us make better use of React to create a better experience to our customers, veterinarians and admins 
  
   Why you’ll love it:
   
    You’ll define the future of animal care as part of the market-leading animal insurance company Agria Djurförsäkring 
   You’ll be joining a small agile team where your efforts will reach customers within days or weeks rather than months or years 
   You’ll work collaboratively with your open-minded colleagues from home and/or from our office in the Waterfront Building in central Stockholm 
   Competitive salary and benefits 
  
   Who you are:
   We believe you’re passionate about frontend development and React specifically. You love sharing your knowledge and helping us make our apps better. You’re a self starter who is eager to get the responsibility to drive large changes through to completion. You’re flexible and understand the power of collaboration and open feedback with your team. And of course, if you love animals as much as we do that’s always a plus!
   We care more about your skills and attitude than your CV. If you think this is the place for you, please get in touch and apply now!

"Looking for talent with an eagerness to learn and a passion for delivering quality software to hundreds of thousands of daily users?
APPLY TO US!
TechBuddy is a Swedish tech company based in Stockholm, Barcelona and Tel Aviv, and now we’re coming to Germany. We are the answer to all tech related questions and our thriving expert community of Buddies supports our clients on how to make the most of their electronic and connected devices.
We offer best in class tech support to customers at home, as well as through our partners in the consumer electronics sector such as MediaMarkt in Spain or Telia in Sweden. Apart from providing our customers with services, we offer our platform Buddy.inc to entrepreneurs and businesses to manage their products and services all from one single place.
We are currently looking to strengthen our Development Team, with another skilled developer that brings a strong frontend focus. We think you are a curious person, passionate about learning and exploring new ideas, technologies. A broad spectrum of knowledge is favored over being specialized in a certain area, although being a specialist is not something we would frown upon :)
We want a candidate with a strong background in product development, but who is not afraid of the R&D aspect of working.
Developer Responsibilities:

Develop and maintain our web and mobile applications
Potentially lead and manage our frontend team
Coordinate, discuss and decide upon solutions, improvements and implementations in your line of expertise.
Report to and work closely with appointed members of the development team.
Develop a close relationship with marketing, sales and CX relations to bring improvements and life cycle management needs to the table.

 Developer Requirements:

Prefearly 4-5 years of experience are what we believe you have in your baggage.
Expert/Ninja in Javascript, frameworks, API integration and related stuff.
Master of CSS with design, styling and general cleverness applied.
Experience with mobile hybrid frameworks (We use React Native).
Experienced in API Design, LCM & implementations (like REST API, OpenAPI specs).
Experienced with DDD/TDD.
Experienced with CD/CI.
Worked in fast paced environments with Lean Startup, Agile and similar methodologies.
Not afraid to get, have or handle responsibilities.
Eager to learn, show off and teach others about new findings, technologies and methods.
Very good skills in english, spoken and written. Communication is everything! We do dailys.
We need a person that is agile and adaptable to change.

What we offer

A fast paced environment, adopting new technologies if we find them useful and helpful that do not mess with our long term goals.
A very modern approach to the stack, separation in both the vertical and horizontal levels.
We use MongoDB Atlas, Amazon EC2/S3, K8s, Serverless, API Mgmt f.e.
A modern workplace with offices in Stockholm, Sweden and in Barcelona, Spain and most recently Münich, Germany.
We work with trust and we trust you, you will have a great opportunity to work, evolve and be a central part of our company and our platform that enables the gig-economy.

How we work

Our company uses Lean Startup as the foundation for innovation.
We use API First as a way to create exponential growth in development.
We aim to automate everything, so you can focus on coding, not the boring stuff.
We collect data, the more the merrier.
We focus on our customers, our partners and our employees.
We work in teams as a team.

Sourcing
Candidates will be interviewed and eventually also be requested to show their skills in coding and problem solving situations.

Job Description
Are you passionate about front-end development? Do you happen to also be interested in working with the cloud? Are you more precisely interested in working with taking a highly pressured platform to the next level? Then you should definitely look this way! Perhaps this feels like a stretch regarding your competence. No worries, Symplify are looking for someone excited to learn and are offering a position where such learning will be provided.
About us
Symplify has over 20 years of experience in digital marketing and is the leader in cross-channel marketing automation for marketers and CRM teams. The success comes from working closely with our customers, developing features that are tuned to their needs thus ensuring that Symplify keeps delivering an agile and powerful experience for all marketers and CRM teams out there.
About the position
As a front end developer at Symplify you will entertain and optimize existing functionality but also be a big part of new exciting features. You will be the person that keeps the UI on the edge, which essentially keeps the customers happy! Besides handling daily programming work you will also be able to work strategically and explore the future technical choices that Symplify will take.
In this role you will have a lot of freedom, both in designing your work and executing it. A good match with this small and familiar team is someone who is humble and takes a lot of initiatives. Moreover, Symplify sees that you are interested in Amazon and are willing to become an advanced user on the matter.
New functionalities are written in React and we highly value previous experience in that. Apart from React, JavaScript and .NET are used.
We work in an agile environment so experience in sprints is also valued.
Since we host our own platform it is a part of the role to have a scheduled standby-duty every fourth week.
Requirements

 2-4 years of similar experience
 Experience from Windows, Linux, JavaScript, .NET, React, SQL
 Good knowledge about web servers and UX
Nice to have

Experience from working with cloud services such as AWS.
Experience with converting deprecated languages to newer such as React
Does this sound interesting? If you have any questions about the position, please contact patrik.fast@symplify.com.

Hemnet has 65 million monthly visits. People come to Hemnet to find joy, inspiration and – most important - their new homes. As a Developer at Hemnet you will face fun challenges when developing ideas for products affecting people's lives in a positive way.
   As a Frontend Developer in team Seller’s Experience you will contribute to all stages in the product life cycle: design, implementation, testing, deployment, and maintenance. You and your team implement the solutions the team have designed and deploy them to production several times a day. Together with the team, you will have the ability to have a big impact on what we build and how we build it. You’ll be involved in product development discussions and make use of and contribute to Hemnet’s design system.
   Team Seller’s Experience
   Our team consists of five Product Developers, one UX Designer, one Product Manager, and one Development Manager working closely together to continuously deliver smart and valuable solutions to the users selling properties on Hemnet. The team mission is to provide the property seller with insights, services, and products to get the most out of their selling experience to enable a successful property sale.
   Some examples of what we do:
   
    Property seller products 
   Product upselling and cross-selling 
   Price calculations 
   Data and information service for property sellers.  
  
  Background & Skills
   You are a seasoned developer with skills in dynamically typed languages who have been working with development for at least five years. You're comfortable leading yourself and are not afraid to take the first step.
   You have a strong interest when it comes to system development, building short and long term solutions in close collaboration with other developers. We are looking for you who has frontend development as your main expertise, but also think it sounds fun to help out on the backend from time to time (no problem if you don’t have any backend development experience - frontend will be your focus and at Hemnet you can learn as you go).
   Your home base is: 
  
   JavaScript (React/Vue/Angular. We use React.js) 
   HTML/CSS.  
  
  Bonus points:
   We’ve created our own design system and component library (which you can read more about in this blog post). So an interest or previous experience working with design systems or component libraries is definitely beneficial. And of course, if you have any experience from other parts of our current tech stack, that would be a plus:
   
    React.js 
   Next.js 
   Testing library (We use jest) 
   TypeScript 
   GraphQL 
   Ruby & Rails (or similar OOP languages and framework i.e. Python/Django, PHP/Laravel) 
   PostgreSQL 
   Docker 
   AWS.  
  
  You’ll love working here if:
   
    You like testing new approaches with the team and enjoy working close to customers 
   You like product development and want to understand how the things you and the team decide to implement impact the experience for the end user. 
   You understand the value of quick releases of features to increase learning and iteration 
   You enjoy having discussions around our insight of what our customers need to enjoy working with us 
   You’re a firm believer in writing robust tests.  
  
  A hybrid model: 
  All employees at Hemnet will have the possibility to work from the office in the central part of Stockholm. We will also have the opportunity to work the majority of the time from home (but not 100% remotely). Currently, the team is having one team day per week when we aim to physically get together.

      About Tietoevry
      
     ﻿﻿Tietoevry creates purposeful technology that reinvents the world for good. We are a leading technology company with a strong Nordic heritage and global capabilities. Annotell is a fast-growing startup on a mission to make safe perception for autonomous mobility possible. We provide our clients with the ground truth information to build and validate their systems and the insights to know they have the right data for their use case. That means we provide the labels telling what is in the data.
   You will join the Annotation team within our Ground Truth Production product area. The team’s mission is to enable effortless and efficient production of high-quality ground truth. It is responsible for the tools used by annotators on camera, LiDAR, and radar data. The cross-functional team identifies valuable improvements and suitable solutions. Some current skills in the group include UX/UI design, frontend and backend development, and machine learning. We are now looking for additional product developers strong in frontend development to join.
   What you will do
   Our users’ job is to produce high-quality ground truth, and they rely on us to provide the tools enabling them to do that. Speed is essential, but also accuracy. We need to minimise the annotation time while keeping the quality high. A straightforward and precise UI for professional users is at the job’s core. 2D and 3D performance, as well as loading times, are other essential parts. Beyond the pure frontend parts, interactive machine learning tools can simplify or even automate many tedious tasks. Together with the team, you will prioritise what to build based on usage data and the value you expect from each solution.
   As part of a team, you succeed with the team. At Annotell, we empower our teams to be bold and make decisions; you are the ones closest to the information. You own your mission, and you are vital for our success. Our teams are agile and self-improving. They discuss needs with users and clients and negotiate priorities with stakeholders. The teams are end-to-end responsible for the things they build.
   Our tech stack
   Our web app is modularly built using TypeScript and React. We develop our backend with Scala and Python and deliver the complete solution using Kubernetes on Google Cloud. We rely on ElasticSearch to enable real-time search capabilities.
   Who you are
   We are looking for several candidates with solid skills in building web applications using TypeScript and React. Experience in video, 3D, drawing apps, or experience using D3 or Three.js is a great plus. An interest in metrics or testing user interactions is also meritorious.
   At Annotell, seniority means deepening and broadening individual skills, helping the team and colleagues grow and succeed, and improving the team’s effect by finding better solutions for more valuable problems. Seniority consists of both personal skills and understanding of the Annotell context. We are looking for both new senior colleagues and those earlier on their journey.
   You will be a part of a team at a startup with grand ambitions where we help each other to ensure everyone succeeds as Annotell succeeds. We believe you are an excellent fit if you enjoy working in a growth environment where you sometimes have to act under uncertainties and if you appreciate the responsibility that comes with our mission-driven and self-organising style. You are always up for learning new things and are inspired by reaching challenging goals as a team.
   What is in it for you?
   Other than working with our excellent team in an inspiring and collaborative environment, we also offer you this:
   
    Strong values and purpose-driven company 
   Being part of defining and building the ground truth product 
   Workplace flexibility and work-life balance 
   Competitive salaries 
   Exciting career opportunities in a dynamic and fast scaling startup! 
   Parental pay, salary exchange, maximum health benefit, order your workstation, 30 days vacation, place your pension – to name a few. 
  
  Application
   We recommend you submit your application as soon as possible. We select and interview continuously. If you have any questions regarding the position, please contact our VP of Engineering, Jakob Andersson, at jakob.andersson@annotell.com.
   About annotell
   Annotell was founded in 2018 by Oscar Petersson and Daniel Langkilde, two engineering physicists working in the field of Deep Learning. Our mission is to make safe perception for autonomous mobility possible. We now support world-leading companies in Autonomous Driving, Advanced Driving Assistance Systems and Active Safety development worldwide.
   Our office is at Lindholmen, just by the beautiful waterfront and Lindholmen Science Park.

Nasdaq is continuously revolutionizing markets and undergoing transformations while we adopt new technologies to develop innovative solutions, constantly aiming to rewrite tomorrow. Nasdaq Pre Trade Risk (Nasdaq PTR) gives Exchange members the ability to define, supervise and implement risk limits on the trading activity of their trading participants. Also, they can control the trading risk exposure at the level of a single trading participant, or for a group of trading participants. PTR will enforce the risk limits, rejecting orders that exceed the limits, and also notify PTR users when pre-set limit thresholds are crossed.
Role and responsibilities:
As a Frontend Developer, you and the team will work with PTR focusing on programming large, distributed systems with high availability. We are a small, but diverse, group of talented Java and React developers. Our high availability, mission-critical software runs in customer data centers around the world. Come join our team at Nasdaq, and help us expand our innovative solutions in fin-tech!
If you have a strong foundation within web- and frontend development, preferably React and Typescript, are detail-oriented, methodical, take pride in your work, and enjoy investigating new technologies, this job is right for you!
What you will be doing?
Designing, developing, modifying, adapting and implementing short and long-term solutions to customer needs through new and existing fronted applications.
Modifying existing internal software products to add to new functions, improve performance and enhance product usability.
Providing technology trends and competitive landscape expertise and makes technology decisions to drive opportunities and competitive advantage for our clients.
Taking part in the architectural and infrastructural design of our frontend applications.
We expect you to have:
Bachelors degree in Computer Science or other related fields
Relevant experience within the field of expertise
Solid and extensive technical background with an emphasis on frontend and web development, particularly React and Typescript
Excellent communication skills together paired with a strong client service attitude
A strong inner drive, you should thrive in supporting high demanding users in a fast-paced environment
It would be great if you have:
Experience in a Financial Field
Experience as a Java developer
Further qualifications/certifications across a number of specialist subject areas relevant to the role.
Does this sound like you?
This is a permanent full-time position located in Stockholm. As the selection and interview process is ongoing, please submit your application in English as soon as possible.
About Nasdaq
Nasdaq was founded in 1971 as the world's first electronic stock market. Through the acquisition of OMX with headquarters in Stockholm in 2008, Nasdaq became a global player. Today, Nasdaq is the largest provider of technology to Financial Markets, delivering top-of-the-line trading, clearing, settlement, surveillance, and anti-financial crime technology to partners around the world. Nasdaq is continuously revolutionizing markets and undergoing transformations while we embrace new technologies to develop innovative solutions, constantly aiming to rewrite tomorrow.
Nasdaq Sweden provides its employees with 32 annual vacation days as well as 2 optional paid volunteer days. We offer a competitive salary package that includes annual bonus and equity plans as well as an employee stock purchase program along with several other health benefits and insurance.
Come as You Are
Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

Company Description
   Handling billions of transactions annually, Nets is among the solid payment processors in Europe. We keep a tight focus on making it even easier and more intuitive for our customers to handle digital payments and related services. This has made us a trusted partner to more than 700,000 merchant outlets, including 140,000 online merchant outlets, more than 260,000 enterprises and over 250 banks across Europe.
  
   Changing the future of payments takes great personalities!
  
   At Nets, you’ll develop in a fast-growing tech company in a high-paced, high-impact market. Working to change the future of payments, it’s not just skills and motivation that gets the job done, it’s the full package that makes the difference. Together, we impact the lives of everyone around us by powering an easier tomorrow for every citizen, bank, business and colleague. What powers you at work?
 
  Job Description
   This job is in the Payment Services team, a newly formed group at Nets, who will create a next generation distributed payments processing system for Nets eCommerce and Point of Sale. The team consists mainly of payment developers from a variety of backgrounds who are primarily “hands on keyboard” working on Azure cloud and whose primary product is a set of robust RESTful APIs. The team has a digital first approach (even post pandemic), a modern, green field tech stack built on Azure. The goal of the team is to be the central payment processing connector for the entirety of Nets and third party PSPs.
  
   Engineering at Nets is an inspired, customer focused community, committed to crafting solutions that redefine our industry. Working in small, highly collaborative and cross functional Agile teams, you and your team will have a clear mission and ownership of an important outcome that supports Nets and our customers. We optimise for quality, flow, fast feedback, focusing on end-to-end ownership, continuous improvement, testing, monitoring and experimentation. We aim for teams that are inclusive, helpful, and have a solid sense of ownership for the things they build.
  
   Our engineers make some of the most significant decisions for the company and we are looking for forward thinking, open and curious developers.
  
   Some of the technologies you’ll get to work with:
  
    Javascript
    React/React Native
    Redux
    Node.js
    Azure
  
 
  Qualifications
   Skills, motivation and that little personal twist make you achieve goals
  
   Your professional skills and experience form most of your qualifications, but it’s also your personality that makes the difference at Nets.
  
   What we are looking for:
  
    Solid coding ability in Javascript
    Experience with advanced JavaScript libraries and frameworks
    Experience with RESTful APIs and commercial product development
    Experience for writing clean and testable code
    Experience with Agile/XP practices (Pairing, TDD, BDD, Continuous Integration, Continuous Delivery
  
   Payment Services at Nets is a hub for innovation and green field work at Nets. We are a meritocracy where the best ideas win, people are given a chance to try new things and fail on their way to success.
  
   Culture - You'll work with a diverse crowd of people from 20 different countries based in our offices around Europe and your home office.
  
   Operational independence - We are the tip of the spear for innovation at Nets and you will have high visibility and high impact here at Nets.
  
   Education - We are an environment where we emphasize knowledge sharing, education, conferences and internal technical talks.
  
   Wide reach - Nets has targets for what it wants to achieve in the next 5 years. To get there we will provide opportunities for travel across Europe to other Net's offices in Stockholm, Berlin, Milan, Oslo and more.
   Additional Information
   Apply now to power your career!
  
   Apply now or contact Ted Bowman ebowm@nets.eu if your interested to learn more about the job and Nets. We will call people in for interviews on a continuous basis.

This is a new team enabling database admins to monitor, troubleshoot and optimize Neo4j database clusters and we have a lot of exciting ideas in the pipeline!

You share your ideas and continuously improve yourself and the team around you

You have created an open-source project and you are still an active contributor You have experience with public speaking and/or writing

Vi har en varm, snabbfotad och entreprenöriell kultur och vi hoppas att du vill bli en del av oss.
   Rollen är en tillsvidareanställning med heltid placerad i Stockholm med flexibelt kontor och hemarbete. Vi erbjuder bland annat generös friskvård och har självklart pingisbord på kontoret.
   Om Offerta Offerta är Sveriges största marknadsplats för tjänster och varje år använder närmare 100 000 personer oss för att hitta rätt hjälp, framförallt inom bygg, flytt och städ. Offerta grundades 2008 med syfte att förändra och förenkla sättet att köpa tjänster. Vi vill göra det lika enkelt för företag att hitta nya kunder som för kunder att hitta ett bra tjänsteföretag. Därför har vi på Offerta samlat tjänsteföretagen och kunderna på ett och samma ställe så att det blir enkelt att hitta, jämföra och välja rätt hjälp till sitt projekt. Sedan i mars är vi en del av Fortnox vilket ger oss nya möjligheter att utveckla produkten vidare. En minst sagt spännande resa har precis påbörjats!
   Om Fortnox
   Fortnox AB (publ) är en företagsplattform som knyter samman människor, företag och organisationer. Vi hjälper företag starta, växa och utvecklas. Med smarta tekniska produkter, lösningar och tjänster, och möjlighet att koppla ihop dem med hundratals externa parter, är vi ett nav för företagande i Sverige. Vår vision är att skapa ett välmående samhälle format av framgångsrika företag. Fortnox grundades 2001 och har huvudkontor i Växjö samt kontor i Malmö, Linköping och Stockholm. Aktien är noterad på Nasdaq Stockholm. För ytterligare information se www.fortnox.se.
  
   Jag ser fram emot att höra från dig! För frågor eller ansökan kontakta Pär Stigenberg, Utvecklingschef - Offerta.

You will be a part of our upcoming Data Quality team developing products that enable our customers to objectively reason about their data quality and its implications on their end system.
   Annotell is a fast-growing startup with a mission to provide the world’s best platform to make safe perception for autonomous mobility happen. For that, clients need to understand their system performance. One critical step in this process is understanding the uncertainties and error contribution from the underlying data. We are at the beginning of this journey, and we have now decided to create a product area for this cause: Enable our customers to understand how their data quality affects their ability to develop autonomous vehicles.
   What you’ll do
   Our users will rely on an excellent, fast, and simple user interface to quickly navigate the quality of their data - the UI you will help build. You will work in a cross-functional team with colleagues of various skill sets such as UX design, statistics, and backend. Together with the team, you will define what constitutes an excellent product for data set quality and make that vision happen.
   Our tech stack
   We use modern tools, and our web app is modularly built using TypeScript and React. We develop our backend with Scala and Python and deliver the complete solution using Kubernetes on Google Cloud. We rely on ElasticSearch to enable real-time search capabilities. 
  Who you are
   We are looking for a candidate with solid experience building web applications using JavaScript, TypeScript and React. Previous experience from creating interactive data visualisations and working with Elasticsearch would be a great plus.
   You will be a part of a newly created team at a startup with grand ambitions. This means we help each other to ensure everyone succeeds as Annotell succeeds. We believe you will be an excellent fit for us if you enjoy working in a growth environment where you sometimes have to act under uncertainties. You are always up for learning new things and getting inspired by working as a team to reach challenging goals.
   What is in it for you?
   Other than working with our excellent team in a fun and creative environment, we also offer you this:
   
    Strong values and purpose-driven company 
    Being part of defining and building the Data Quality product 
    Workplace flexibility and work-life balance 
    Competitive salaries 
    Exciting career opportunities in a dynamic and fast scaling startup! 
    Parental pay, salary exchange, maximum health benefit, order your workstation, 30 days vacation, place your pension – to name a few. 
  
   Application
   We recommend submitting your application as soon as possible as we select and interview continuously. If you have any questions regarding the position, please contact Isak Hjortgren, Product Area Lead - Data Quality, isak.hjortgren@annotell.com.
   About annotell
   Annotell was founded in 2018 by Oscar Petersson and Daniel Langkilde, two engineering physicists working in the field of Deep Learning. Our mission is to make safe perception for autonomous mobility possible. We now support world-leading companies in the field of Autonomous Driving, Advanced Driving Assistance Systems and Active Safety development worldwide.

We’re searching for a talented Frontend Engineer to join Solidsport and our journey to revolutionize the world of sport streaming. As a Frontend Engineer, you will help us build and develop the leading sport streaming platform in Europe.
   What you will be doing
   In this position you will be part of a self-organizing team, working closely together with business people, UX-designers and other fellow engineers. General responsibilities includes, but not limited to:
   
    Develop and maintain front-end for web and mobile 
   Implement and iterate on UIs for new features 
   Test, implement and suggest UX improvements 
   Improve code structure and architecture in service of testability and maintainability, and ensure the web stack stays up to date and best practices 
  
   Your responsibility is not limited to writing good code, but also truly caring about the product you will be working on.
   Who you are
   A qualified applicant is proficient in modern frontend ecosystems with at least three years working with Javascript, Typescript, ReactJS, and related paradigms and libraries. You may have come across some of the following technologies:
   
    SPA, Micro frontends 
   NodeJS 
   GraphQL 
   Docker 
   AWS 
  
   Competence and experience are important, but personality and potential are key! What matters the most for us is your personality, motivation and competitive spirit:
   
    Anticipates problems, sees the big picture and identifies solutions 
   Generates innovative ideas and solutions that address customer’s needs 
   Enthusiastic and positive even in tough situations 
   Last but not least, you are a great team player 
  
  What we offer
   Your next big opportunity in a creative, motivating, and welcoming company where everyone can be themselves. We offer a fast pace in a developing environment where only our own creativity sets the limits.
   Our office is located in newly built Stockholm 01, with great communications, a walk into the city and a breathtaking view.
   About Solidsport
   Live streamed sport is what we know best and our vision is that all sports on all levels should be broadcasted live. That is by making it simple for every team or club to do so, using only a smartphone.
   Solidsport is now scaling up both nationally and globally. During 2020, more than 40.000 sport events were streamed live, and today our platform has passed the 1 million user mark.
   Interested?
   Start and end time to be discussed with the recruiting manager.
   We look forward to hearing from you! :]

Company Description

Our licensees’ players can move flawlessly between mobile, tablet and desktop to play slots or live casino, which feature real tables with real dealers in real time. Our innovative and high-quality offer includes brands like Evolution Live, Red Tiger and NetEnt, and multiple award-winning international player product favorites, such as Crazy Time, Lightning Roulette and Gonzo’s Quest. Evolution is listed on Nasdaq Nordic with a MCAP of EUR 20+BN.

Evolution provides a dynamic and creative work environment with a unique opportunity for the right people to enhance their skills and drive their passion.   Job Description
   We are now looking for a skilled Frontend Developer who wants to build the next-generation Framework for game development! As a developer with us, you have the opportunity to work in an agile and cross functional team contributing in all stages of the development process.
   Besides technical knowledge, you enjoy solving both technical and business-related challenges together with your team and are comfortable with taking architectural decisions on the front-end side. You are able to take responsibility for the quality of your code, and you are accustomed to showing initiative in undertaking a project.
   We have three teams that are currently looking for new colleagues:
   CoreTech – development and maintenance of game framework components to simplify and improve game development.
  
    Required skills: TypeScript, ES6, HTML, Git, webpack
    Optional skills: Jenkins pipeline, Github Actions, npm, MobX/Redux, NodeJS, docker, GCP
  
   PlayerTech – development and maintenance of game client UX components using React, VanillaJS, Canvas
  
    Required skills: TypeScript, ES5/6, React, jest/karma, Git
    Optional skills: webpack, parcel, docsify, markdown, Styled Components, GitHub Actions
  
   Game Delivery Platform - Development and maintenance of Game Information system
  
    Required skills: TypeScript, Angular, Git
    Optional skills: Karma, Sass, Docker, GCP, Github Actions
  
   We offer:
  
    A healthy mix of startup-like culture of the company, which will enable you to try new approaches and technologies and remain on the edge of technological development and enterprise, with stability and supporting functions to help you focus on your job
    Business recognition, which translates to competitive salaries and a supportive attitude
    Developing games state-of-the-art gaming solutions, serving customers around the world
    Modern and developer-friendly delivery processes, including Agile (Scrum / Kanban), JIRA issue tracking, Confluence wiki, Jenkins continuous integration and delivery, modern hardware and software for development (an IDE of your choice)
    Being a part of an international team in a successful, publicly-traded company
    Health insurance, contemporary office environment, and other benefits and perks.
    Hybrid work model (work from home/work from the office)
  
   Please note that we are primarily looking for candidates who have a work visa for the EU, and are based in Stockholm or planning to move there in the near future.
