Du älskar att koda. Och om du får välja så fokuserar du på gränssnittet eftersom du uppskattar interaktionsdesign och snygg form. Det är hos dig “teorin” för digitala gränssnitt kommer till liv.
På Äventyret vill vi komma till skott så snart som möjligt och är lite otåliga med pappersexercisen. Google sorterar in oss som “affärsutvecklare” och det är inte helt dumt — vi är teknikagnostiker som är intresserade av effekten av vad vi tar fram åt våra beställare. Med det sagt trillar våra lösningar alltid ut i digitala format såsom appar, inloggade tjänster på webben, teknikekosystem, digitaliseringsprospekt, prototyper för nya affärsgrenar etc.
Vilka är Äventyret?
Vi är utvecklare, konceptutvecklare, designers, problemlösare, arkitekter, affärsutvecklare och UI-kreatörer. Flera miljoner människor har använt de produkter och tjänster som vi har utvecklat för våra kunder. Dessa kunder kan nu erbjuda bättre nytta till sina användare, framtidssäkra sina organisationer och tjäna pengar på bättre sätt.

Våra anställda arbetar på Äventyrets kontor i Stockholm, på vårt kontor i Örebro eller någon annanstans där det finns internetuppkoppling. Vi har dessutom kunskapsdelningar och såklart konferenser – för hela Äventyret.
Att jobba som frontendutvecklare på Äventyret
Det är rimligt att vara med i 2-3 projektteam parallellt, och du växlar ditt fokus mellan dessa under en vanlig arbetsvecka. Projekten på Äventyret är nästan alltid från ax till limpa. För att limpan ska smaka riktigt gott är det viktigt att du som utvecklare är med även i idé- och konceptfas. Projekten blir bäst med löpande inspel från hela teamet, över alla dess faser. Ni bestämmer själva vad som ska göras/byggas/fortbildas utan krav på projektleverabler och kompetensteam för interna förbättringar sätts upp på egna initiativ.
Vem är du då?
Du säger check på följande fyra punkter:

Du har jobbat med Javascript i några år och skapar högpresterande, tight och snygg kod.
Du är grym på HTML, CSS och skriver modulär frontendkod som hjälper till att komponentifiera gränssnittet.
Du överjobbar inte en prototyp som ska slängas efter ett första användningstest. Och du fuskar inte heller med produktionskod.
Du har gjort minst ett (lyckat) projekt i React, Vue eller varför inte Svelte.
Du kanske inte tycker dig ha 100% på alla andra punkter ovan — men du kan en massa annat bra. Du är framförallt hungrig på att lära dig nytt i en prestigelös atmosfär. Du kan lite svenska. I brist på lite svenska kan du bra engelska. Du kan uttrycka dig i skrift.
Är du redo för Äventyret?
Ansök redan idag då intervjuer sker löpande. Vid frågor eller mer information kontakta Klara Himmelstrand på +46 72-050 78 44 eller klara.himmelstrand@aventyret.com

Frontendutvecklare till Nexer
Roll
Front-end Developer
Kompetens
Data/IT
Publikationsdatum
7 Apr 2022
Land
Sverige
Stad
Göteborg
Sista ansökningsdatum
7 May 2022Vi vill bli fler i vårt frontend-team på Nexer! Hos oss arbetar du som konsult med huvudfokuset frontend inom JavaScript med ramverk så som React, Angular, VUE etc. och bidra till vår grupp med din kreativitet och ständiga vilja att hitta en bättre, snyggare lösning. Vi söker dig som brinner för teknikerna runt JavaScript och som vill bli en del av ett team där utveckling och kompetens står i fokus.


Hur ser rollen ut?

Nexers frontend-team i Göteborg består idag av ca 15 utvecklare som arbetar i olika uppdrag hos våra kunder. Vi erbjuder en stor bredd av uppdrag och därför kan jobbets karaktär variera. Gemensamt för alla uppdrag är att de är långsiktiga, kvalificerade och utmanande, samtidigt som du garanterat har roligt på jobbet!
Vi håller en kompetensmässigt hög nivå och många av oss har arbetat länge inom frontend och det finns därför stora möjligheter att lära av varandra. Vi brukar träffas på kontoret regelbundet för att gå igenom våra egna projekt och diskutera det senaste inom frontend. Dessa träffar avslutar vi alltid med att testa en ny teknik eller metod som vi tycker är intressant. Som en del av detta team får du alltid stor möjlighet att själv påverka inte bara vilket uppdrag du arbetar med utan vilka tekniker du vill fokusera på, och utvecklas inom.
Tillhörighet är viktigt för oss och detta arbetar vi med kontinuerligt genom sociala aktiviteter, kompetensutveckling och annat som syftar till att öka trivseln inom gruppen. Du har en nära kontakt med din chef som hela tiden arbetar för att du ska få ett så utmanande och utvecklande uppdrag som möjligt.

Din bakgrund

Vi tror att du har jobbat som frontendutvecklare i minst 3 år och är bekväm med teknikerna runt JavaScript och har kännedom kring relevanta ramverk, så som React.js, Node.js eller Vue. Du tycker det är roligt att ta dig an nya utmaningar genom olika uppdrag och kundprojekt.
Du har troligtvis en utbildning inom Datateknik eller motsvarande, men är du självlärd och har flera fritidsprojekt att visa upp tar vi gärna emot din ansökan!
Dina personliga egenskaper är viktiga för oss då vill behålla den atmosfär vi har idag. Våra medarbetare kännetecknas av en affärsmässig och kundorienterad attityd, samt förmåga att snabbt ta till sig ny information och omvandla den till kreativa lösningar. Du respekterar dina kollegor och har en stark vilja att dela med dig av dina kunskaper till andra samt lyssna och lära.
Sist men inte minst, vi vill att du skall fortsätta att utvecklas och ha kul på jobbet!

Varför Nexer?
Inom Nexer finns det en uttalad utmaning som genomsyrar alla uppdrag och företaget som helhet: finns det en smartare lösning så hittar vi den. En strävan som varje dag utmanar oss och låter oss att tänka utanför de givna ramarna och tillsammans med våra kunder ta de modiga beslut som krävs för att skapa utveckling.
Vi erbjuder problemlösning, allt från att utveckla ett nytt system till att designa en webbshop eller något annat där vår breda och spetsiga kompetens inom teknik kommer till sin rätt. Våra uppdrag har ofta internationell karaktär, därför är flytande svenska och engelska i tal och skrift är en naturlig del i arbetet. Konsultuppdragen finns dels på vårt kontor och oftast hos våra kunder, därför är resor i närområdet en del av vardagen.

Ansökan
Varmt välkommen att skicka in din intresseanmälan nedan. Vi har tyvärr ingen möjlighet att ta emot ansökningar via mail, men du som har frågor är mycket välkommen att kontakta ansvarig rekryterare Josefine Pettersson på josefine.pettersson@nexergroup.com.

column1: Frontendutvecklare till SPM Instrument i Strängnäs
column4:
Vår R&D-avdelning utvecklar programvara och mätinstrument för stötpuls- och vibrationsmätning på industriella maskiner. Vi behöver nu förstärka vårt härliga och lättsamma team med ytterligare en frontend-webbutvecklare, som vill arbeta med de senaste webbteknikerna och verktygen. Hos oss får alla utlopp för sin kreativitet och vi är måna om att bidra till din utveckling! Varmt välkommen med din ansökan! 
  Vi strävar ständigt efter att förbättra och vidareutveckla våra system med nya smarta och innovativa funktioner för att tillgodose våra kunders behov, förenkla deras vardag samt, inte minst, se till att deras maskiner och tillverkningsprocesser fungerar optimalt.
   En avgörande faktor i att vi lyckas, är att vi kan presentera den data vi samlat in och genererat, på ett modernt, lättillgängligt och tilltalande sätt. För detta använder vårt utvecklingsteam bland annat webbtillämpningar byggda med React och TypeScript, dit vi nu söker ytterligare en duktig och driven utvecklare.
   Dina arbetsuppgifter Som Frontendutvecklare hos oss, arbetar du i huvudsak med programmering, men även viss specning och design kan ingå i arbetet. Det du programmerar, sker i öppet och nära samarbete med både kunder och våra egna vibrations- och applikationsspecialister. Ditt behov av kreativitet och att få göra spännande tekniska lösningar kommer till sin rätt hos oss. På vår utvecklingsavdelning finns många erfarna kollegor inom såväl mjukvara som elektronik, hårdvara och mätmetoder, som kommer att inspirera och stötta dig i ditt arbete.
   Det du utvecklar, kommer att användas av professionella användare i olika industrier, runt om i hela världen.
   Utvecklingen sker med moderna verktyg och utvecklingsmiljöer med kraftfull utrustning som du själv är med och väljer.
   Vi söker dig som
  
    Vill jobba med utveckling av inbyggda system och moderna webbtillämpningar med React och TypeScript för användning i industrin.
    Har erfarenhet av webbutveckling (helst React och TypeScript, men även javascript, CSS mm).  
  
  Rollen kan till viss del anpassas, varför din bakgrund kan variera från ovan. Till exempel kan möjlighet finnas att kombinera rollen med backend-relaterat utvecklingsarbete.
   Vårt koncernspråk är engelska och du behöver därför behärska språket i både tal och skrift.  
  Om dig Vi värdesätter egen drivkraft, noggrannhet och analytisk förmåga. Du uppskattar utmaningar, är en kreativ problemlösare med stort engagemang och lockas av att arbeta i en miljö med internationell prägel. Du är van vid att ta ansvar för ditt eget arbete samtidigt som du har god samarbetsförmåga och gärna delar med dig av dina kunskaper.
   Placeringsort Tjänstens placeringsort är Strängnäs med tillsättning så snart som möjligt.
   SPM Instrument i Strängnäs utvecklar, producerar, marknadsför och säljer avancerad utrustning för tillståndskontroll av maskiner. Som en av de ledande aktörerna inom vårt område finns vi på ett sextiotal exportmarknader runt om i världen. Med en starkare produktportfölj än någonsin och med kunder i ett brett spektrum av branscher över hela världen befinner vi oss i en expansiv fas. Tillsammans med våra dotterbolag och distributörer arbetar vi med ett starkt fokus på intensifierad marknadsföring och ökad försäljning av våra unika produkter. Läs gärna mer om oss på www.spminstrument.se
   Låter den här tjänsten intressant för dig? Vi berättar gärna mer. Kontakta ansvarig rekryterare Lisa Tojkander på 021-81 18 88. Din ansökan registrerar du på www.norenlindholm.se genom knappen nedan, senast den 24 april. Notera att urval sker löpande och att tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas före sista ansökningsdatum, så skicka in din ansökan så snart som möjligt.
   Hos N&L testar vi tidigt i rekryteringsprocessen. Både på ett logiskt och personligt plan. Med hjälp av Alva Labs genomför vi en objektiv rekryteringsprocess. Testerna tar ungefär 10 minuter vardera. SPM Instrument tillämpar arbetsprov i ett senare skede.
   Välkommen med din ansökan!
 
  Publiceringsdatum 
  15 mars, 2022 
  Företag 
  SPM Instrument 
  Ort 
  Strängnäs

Vi söker nu en frontend-utvecklare som vill bli en del av vårt frontend-team som ansvarar för Sveas internetbank. Vi arbetar i en komplex miljö och utvecklar banbrytande nya lösningar med hjälp av de senaste teknikerna. Detta är en unik möjlighet att vara del av utvecklingen av en helt ny bank från grunden!Varför jobba hos oss?Hos oss får du möjligheten att jobba med moderna tekniker i nya projekt tillsammans med ett värdeskapande team. Enligt ett agilt arbetssätt jobbar teamet för att medarbetarna ska kunna dela sina idéer och lösningar. Detta med anledningar av att skapa ett värdegrundat arbete och för att du som medarbetare ska kunna utvecklas i rollen som frontendutvecklare. Inom Svea blir du en del av en spännande resa som innebär finansiella och affärsmässiga lösningar för företagare och konsumenter.Om rollen**Du blir en del av ett självorganiserat team som arbetar enligt arbetssättet Kanban och i nära samarbete med Backend-utvecklare, QA, UX-designer, Produktägare, iOS- och Android-utvecklare. Du som frontutvecklare hos oss är den som sätter ett ansikte på alla funktioner som Svea bank erbjuder. I praktiken är det du som arbetar med underhållning men också en hel del nyutveckling kopplat till banktjänster. Din så kallade vardag består av:Bygga integrationer och samarbeten med tredjepartstjänster såsom SwishForma kravet från verksamheten och omvandla interaktivt användargränssnittUppdaterar och vidareutveckla nya funktionerImplementera och säkerställer bästa möjliga kod genom testautomatiseringVår utvecklingsmiljö består av JavaScript och react, redux, Jest, Cypress, Webpack, Yarn, babel.Vem är du?* ‍*️För att trivas hos oss ser du dig som en kommunikativ lagspelare som uppskattar ett arbete enligt ett agilt arbetssätt. Du har ett genuint intresse och förståelse för modern webbutveckling och uppskattar att arbete enligt en clean-code approach och med hög kodkvalitet. Du är öppen för att lära och att dela dina kunskaper inom teamet och är van vid att sätta användaren i fokus. Du har god förmåga och är van vid att kommunicera problem och lösningar med en rad olika grupper, både tekniska och icke-tekniska. Under din jobbresa har du skaffat dig:️ Några års arbetserfarenhet av JavaScript (eller Typescript) och React️Erfarenhet av testautomatisering och dess verktyg såsom Jest och/eller Cypress️God förståelse för UX-design️Mycket goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska i både tal och skriftEtt plus i kanten är om du god kännedom om funktionell programmering i JS eller domänkunskap inom bank/fintech.Om Svea bank**Svea Bank tillhandahåller flera tjänster med syfte att underlätta sina kunders vardag, exempelvis fakturaköp, företagslån, företagskonto och sparkonto. Genom personlig service och smart teknik ämnar vi erbjuda marknaden effektiva och anpassade lösningar. Gemenskap är viktigt för oss och vi jobbar för mångfald och att alla ska känna en delaktighet och möjlighet att kunna påverka. På Svea värdesätter vi worklife balance och har en tydlig gräns mellan arbetsliv och privatliv.Vi sitter i nya och fräscha lokaler i Arenastaden, Solna.️AnsökanOm du har frågor om tjänsten går det bra att kontakta Ken Vu på ken.vu@svea.com Urval och intervjuer sker löpande och vi önskar tillsätta tjänsten så snart som möjligt, så skicka din ansökan redan idag.Välkommen med din ansökan och lycka till!Location: Evenemangsgatan 31 A,169 79,Solna, SolnaJobbtyp: Heltid

Vi söker nu Frontendutvecklare som gillar att jobba nära slutanvändaren och vill göra det dagliga arbetet enklare för alla sina utvecklarkollegor. Join us!
   Vad kommer du att göra?
   I rollen som Frontendutvecklare driver du arbetet med vår utvecklarportal som är utvecklarnas gränssnitt mot CI/CD-flödet. Du får möjlighet att skapa den bästa portalen som används av alla utvecklare på hela Svenska Spel. Det gör du tillsammans med ett tvärfunktionellt team men du har också nära kontakt och samarbete med övriga team för att ständigt få snabb användarfeedback.
   Vi har nyligen bildat ett Technical Operations Center (TOC) som kombinerar vår driftcentral, tooling och övervakning. TOC:en ansvarar för den operativa driften och jobbar med att hela tiden öka vår förmåga inom bland annat incident management, SRE och IT-säkerhet. Du blir en del av ett taggat team som tillsammans skapar en övervakningsfunktion som kännetecknas av proaktivitet, automatisering och förmågan att snabbt hantera IT-säkerhetsincidenter.
   Du rör dig i teknisk framkant och jobbar för att göra den dagliga IT-arbetsmiljön enklare för Svenska Spels alla utvecklare.
   Är du den som kommer att göra det?
   Vi ser att du är en kreativ och nytänkande person som trivs bäst som en del av ett tight team där alla bidrar till gemensamma mål och stöttar varandra vid utmaningar och i problemlösning. Du har lätt för att skapa nya relationer både inom teamet men också med samarbetsteam och övriga organisationen.
   Utöver ovanstående sitter du på följande erfarenheter och kompetenser
   
   Några års arbetslivserfarenhet av frontendutveckling 
   Erfarenhet av TypeScript och React 
  
  Det är också meriterande om du har arbetat med Backstage eller har erfarenhet av UI/UX.
   Om Tech på Svenska Spel
   På Svenska Spel hanterar vi 10 000 000 transaktioner varje dag, året runt och på sex dagar har vi hanterat samma transaktionsvolym som den största pengaöverföringsappen gör på en månad. Varje dag utvecklar, driftar och supportar vi ett av världens mest avancerade spelsystem, vi är med andra ord ett techbolag som sysslar med spel - inte tvärtom. Och som ett techbolag som sysslar med spel kommer ett ansvar, både för folks drömmar och spänning, men även för deras spelande. Det är också därför du kommer märka att vårt spelansvarsarbete genomsyrar hela företaget från första dagen du börjar jobba hos oss.
   Vi är Svenska Spel
   Vi är modiga, nyfikna och vi strävar efter enkelhet i allt vi gör. Vi vill att spel ska vara till glädje för alla – för våra medarbetare, kunder och gäster, för idrotten och för samhället i stort. Vi sponsrar idrottsrörelsen på alla nivåer, förebygger spelproblem och låter vinsten gå tillbaka till samhället.
   Och du har väl förresten inte missat att läsa om våra fantastiska förmåner?
   Ansökan och kontaktuppgifter
   Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning med placering där det passar dig bäst. Vi har kontor i Visby och i Solna och det vore förstås toppen om du bodde i närheten men det går också bra att utföra arbetet hemifrån någon annanstans i Sverige. 
  Vi utför intervjuer och urval löpande så tveka inte på att skicka in din ansökan så snart som möjligt.
   För frågor om tjänsten, kontakta Björn Flodman, Chef Tech Operations Center, bjorn.flodman@svenskaspel.se
   För frågor om rekryteringsprocessen, kontakta Team Talent Acquisition, teamta@svenskaspel.se
   LI-REMOTE

column1: Full - stack C# Developer - Fintech Sector - Stockholm
column4:
Full-stack C# Developer - Fintech Sector - Stockholm
    
    
   My market-renowned client in central Stockholm (Stureplan) has a brilliant opportunity for an experienced C# Software Developer to join their highly skilled team making a strong impact in the fintech industry. Within this position you would work cohesively within an experienced development team on ethical and scaleable greenfield projects, utilising the latest techniques and technologies. This is a great opportunity for any developer looking to challenge the market daily and be involved with a product directly having a positive impact on the society they live in. If you are passionate about making a difference and excel working in the proximity of others, this could be for you!
    The long-term objective of this role is for the successful candidate to be given guidance and support to progress to a tech lead position. My client is looking for someone to provide sincere guidance and direction to the development department, and be responsible for new solutions the team will develop.
    The ideal candidate will demonstrate:
   
     Widespread experience with .NET/C# and Microsoft technologies (.NET Core and Azure).
     
     Solid database knowledge (MS SQL, EF Core).
     
     Strong passion for development and not afraid to influence technical decisions.
     
     Front end and cloud experience would also be beneficial.
     
     Familiar working with Scrum and Sprints.
     
     Ambition to progress towards tech lead.
     
     Swedish speaking.
   
    
    
   About the client
   
     Hiring as a result of strong organic growth on the fintech market.
     
     Maintained a flat company structure with self-organised development team.
     
     Attend regular conferences and collaborations globally.
     
     Build new development features for an ethically oriented healthcare product
     
     Scalable solution which is not deadline focused.
     
     Place a large focus on the wellbeing and success of their employees.
     
     Clear and structured path for internal growth and progression.
   
    
    
   Joining my client will provide you with great benefits, such as:
   
     Strong pension package with option for salary sacrifice.
     
     Budget for gym/wellbeing.
     
     Regular team building activities both inside and outside of work.
     
     Team breakfast provided daily.
   
    
    
   If you feel your profile and personality matches this description and you would like to learn more about this opportunity, apply today or reach out at the details below!
    Email your CV to t.hague@nigelfrank.com or call 46 77 588 86 03 to discuss this confidentially.

OpusCapita is a leading European provider of e-invoicing solutions, O2C and P2P messaging services, and advanced procurement services for large and mid-sized companies. With our cloud-based solutions, we help our customers better manage their procurement, supply chain and AP&AR, getting payments in faster, lowering processing costs, and bringing savings. Founded in 1984, OpusCapita has customers in over 50 countries. To learn more, please visit www.opuscapita.com

Full Stack Developer
frontend + backend + node + react + js + ts + (REST+kafka+rabbitMQ) = opuscapita.com

At OpusCapita our vision is to be the number one value provider of procurement and finance processes. We are seeking talented and experienced professionals to join our software development unit. You may work from one of our offices in Toruń, Poland, Riga, Latvia or Stokholm, Sweden or fully remotely from those countries. The team is responsible to create and scale our own cloud platform in order to bring our next-generation products to market towards a SaaS-only future.

Technologies in our ecosystem
Microsoft Azure for our public and private cloud infrastructure needs
Microservice architecture, which is containerized on top of Docker, which is orchestrated through Docker-swarm and Kubernetes.
Most of our development work is done in JavaScript, TypeScript and Java.
Other technologies we take advantage of: ELK stack, Kong, Redis, SQL,NoSQL, MySQL, ElasticSearch, express.js and OAuth2.0 to name a few.
Github based development process using PRs
CI/CD based on Github with Jenkins or CircleCI
Atlassian product family for development management and information sharing

 Your responsibilities:
Develop full stack domain microservices for the Business Network Portal based on our favorite technologies (Node, React, Docker, Github and Jira)
Cooperate closely with product management and scrum masters

What we would like from you?
You speak English fluently
You know how to handle/avoid software performance, optimization and concurrency problems
You are fluent in writing and understanding real code nyc mocha -R mocha-junit-reporter mocha *.spec.js
For you a programming language is a tool and not the final destination
You are not afraid to review JavaScript code created by your or other teams to ensure high-quality feature output
You like to improve yourself and are eager to learn

What makes OpusCapita a Great Workplace?
When asked what they like best in our company, OpusCapitans say that they most of all appreciate the relaxed atmosphere and the people they work with. People here care for one another and help is always there if needed. Family feeling is mentioned every time in our annual employee surveys. OpusCapitans feel they are trusted by our management and that they can actually make a difference. At OpusCapita even making mistakes is seen as an opportunity to learn so honest mistakes are seen as part of just doing business! Flexibility in the working hours is valued as well as the possibility to remote work. We are all fuelled by the same passion to succeed.

In addition we offer:
International collaboration and atmosphere
Possibility to work remotely (during pandemic times we are working fully remotely)
All the basic benefits (sport & culture, medical insurance, life insurance, company pension scheme, bonus plan etc.)
Monthly peer recognition campaigns in order to praise our colleagues
Unique benefits via I love Mondays club

Questions in mind?
For more information please contact Edyta.Michalska-Paszko@opuscapita.com Please submit your application and we will contact you - we start conducting interviews and make hiring decisions as soon as the suitable candidate is found.

Job Description 
   Pagero’s expansion continues at an even higher speed and we are now looking for developers to work on added Services to our platform. In this role, you will design and develop new services and infrastructure as well as maintain the existing offering related to our processes and applications for companies to exchange business documents and trade electronically. 
   We are looking for new members to our development team building services that add value on top of the document processing offering from Pagero Online. The work will involve both backend and frontend development, so experience in both areas is preferable but not a requirement. 
   We think that you are a self-motivated person who enjoys solving problems and who is also eager to learn new things. We value good communication skills and that you can work in a team. In turn you will enjoy an open-minded culture always open to new ideas where you will have a great deal of influence over your daily work.
   
   
   Working at Pagero 
   We are working in a Microservice architecture with a DevOps culture. This means that teams have complete full-stack responsibility for their parts of the architecture, including continuous integration and continuous delivery, which gives each team a lot of freedom with developing their services. Our team likes to bring concepts from functional programming into our existing stack, where it is applicable. 
   Because of the full-stack responsibility of our teams, experience of working with full-stack development is highly desirable, but there is also room for frontend or backend specialists. 
   As member of a team, you will have the following responsibilities: 
   
   Collaborating closely with all members of the team to take shared responsibility for the overall efforts that the team has committed to. 
   System-level design of new applications and features 
   Taking responsibility for the quality of the code through automated testing, code reviews etc. 
   Continuous maintenance and improvement of the team’s existing codebase 
   
  In addition, we provide a dynamic environment and a lot of opportunities to pursue areas of personal interests, such as Pagero Labs where cross-teams are focusing on new areas, Special Interest Groups (SIG:s) and sponsored conference attendance.
   
   
   Qualifications 
   Fluent in both spoken and written English 
   Previous experience from working in a JVM-based environment 
   Backend 
   For backend development, experience with the following technologies are highly preferred: 
   
   Scala 
   Databases / PostgreSQL 
   Build tools like sbt 
   Microservices architecture 
   
  Experience with the following technologies are also valued: 
   
   REST APIs 
   Protobuf 
   RabbitMQ 
   Akka HTTP / Play Framework 
  
  Frontend 
   For frontend development, experience with the following technologies is highly preferred: 
   
   Typescript or Javascript 
   JSX & plain HTML 
   CSS 
   Proficiency in one or more frontend frameworks like React, Angular, Vue and Svelte, preferably React 
   
  Experience with frontend tools such as yarn or npm, lerna, webpack 
   Experience with the following technologies is also valued: 
   
   StencilJS / Web components 
   js 
  
  Tools 
   Experience with the following tools is highly preferred: 
   
   Git 
   Go CD 
   Docker 
   
  What we offer 
   Scope: Full time (6-month probationary period)

Welcome to the makers of the popular adventure game Star Stable Online – the currently 1 ranked and fastest-growing horse game in the world. Our vision in 2011 was to build a game that encouraged girls to be the hero of their own adventure, today we have brought that adventure to more than 8 million active players all over the world. Over the years we have extended our product line to music, publishing, and several apps, continuously working to improve, grow and fulfill what’s at the heart of our mission – to inspire, and to have a meaningful global impact, transforming the gaming industry into a more open-minded and inclusive environment.
Whom are we looking for?
Right now our Core Team needs backup in order to bring our great gaming experience to even more players. We are looking for a Fullstack Developer that is ready to implement new technologies and bring our great gaming experience to even more players!
The tech stack for this role:
Today, our Tech teams currently works with Python, REST APIs, Cloud (AWS), Serverless, Docker, React and Typescript. We believe that you can navigate in Python and React, but you will have a lot of freedom in deciding what to use in order to build robust and scalable solutions. Together with the team's creative culture and an open perspective, you will have the opportunity to implement new technologies.
What can we offer you?
We are a passionate and happy bunch of 200+ creative brains from 20 different countries, dedicated to creating immersive and inspiring experiences for a global audience of girls as well as keeping being a tight-knit team. We offer remote work the majority of the time, but there are expectations that you can enter the office (Central Stockholm) when needed, for example at workshops and team meetings. The office of course welcomes you with open arms more often too!
General benefits
A growing journey where you will have a lot of impact on the player experience within our flagship product, Star Stable Online exists on multiple platforms.
A pretty sweet mission. We want to build quality games for girls and we take that vision very seriously. We strive to hit that mark every single day.
We may be a big group, but we’re a tight-knit team! A diverse team of friendly, fun, and supportive co-workers from 20 different countries!
We’re more than 50%female identifying! YES to WomenInTech!
30 Vacation Days
ITP1 Insurance Plan
Parental pay top up to 90 %
5,000 SEK per year Health allowance

Sounds exciting? Reach out and apply! We are super curious to hear more about you!

Our employees are engaged and happy, and we have the data to prove it! We believe in giving our employees freedom, responsibility, and opportunities to grow. Together, we create a market-leading product that helps our customers become more engaged, happy, and perform better. The success of Eletive results in millions of people having a happier everyday life! If you want to work alongside fun, driven, and supportive colleagues while creating better workplaces around the world - Eletive is the place for you! By joining a fast-growing company you will get the opportunity to influence and impact the journey ahead.
We are now looking for Full Stack Developers in the early stages of their career with some experience in modern JavaScript applications, preferably React and Node.
Job description
As part of our product team, you are expected to build a product that provides the greatest possible value to our customers and users. The product must also be stable and easy to maintain and further develop. We are constantly looking for opportunities to improve and simplify our product using a DevOps mindset. In this role, you will have the opportunity to work with many different parts. Tasks include, but are not limited to:

Working with React/Redux and Node.
Contribute to various areas such as development, UX, testing, release, and maintenance.
Work with simple, clear, and transparent processes.
Collaborate and exchange experiences with colleagues to arrive at the best solutions and constantly evolve.
Learn new things. We are constantly looking for new solutions, services, and opportunities to make ourselves better and more efficient as teams and individuals.
Have fun at work and feel proud that you are part of and contribute to a more prosperous society.
What are we looking for?
To grow and thrive in the role we believe that you:

Have some understanding and experience of creating modern JavaScript applications using, for example, React and Node.
Have some experience working with JavaScript in a software team.
Are familiar with or willing to learn Agile Practices, such as Scrum, Automated Testing, Code Reviews, Continuous Delivery, etc.
Have a passion for creating fantastic products with the user in focus that is aesthetically pleasing.
Like to be a part of and work as a team.
Are structured and have a desire to create innovative solutions that follow best practices and that others understand.
Have a self-starter mindset; you proactively identify opportunities for improvement and are a driving force in the work.
Write and speak fluent Swedish and English.
What do we offer?
We want you to love your work, your co-workers, and your workplace. We also want you to feel inspired, included, and have a lot of fun. Our aim is to be the best employer in the world!
At Eletive, you will work together with passionate, driven, and smart colleagues. We have a lot of fun together and there are many opportunities to socialize. You will also have the opportunity to have an impact on the work we do. Apart from that, we offer several company-wide benefits.
In addition to a great workplace and colleagues, you will end your day with a great feeling knowing that you are making a positive difference for people all over the world.
Application
Do you want to become a part of our amazing team? We recruit continuously, so send in your application immediately. Apply by clicking the button below!

Köket.se är en del av TV4, ett av Sveriges största mediehus. Köket erbjuder inspirerande och engagerande matinnehåll genom TV-program, recept, artiklar, videoklipp, onlinekurser, poddar, mm. Vi samarbetar med flera av Sveriges populäraste kockar och når varje vecka ut till ca 2 miljoner användare genom våra olika kanaler. Vår vision är att bidra med inspiration och matglädje för alla.
   Vi söker erfaren fullstackutvecklare till Köket.se!
   Ta chansen att jobba med ett härligt gäng inom ett spännande område. Kom till Köket! Här får du jobba i ett litet, oberoende team tillsammans med erfarna personer inom backend, frontend och design/UX.
   Vårt utvecklingsteam ansvarar för allt utvecklingsarbete i vår viktigaste kanal, Köket.se, som är en av Sveriges största matsajter. Vi arbetar agilt med alla delar av webbplatsen, från idé/design och planering till genomförande och testning. Vi är ett litet och sammansvetsat team som har kul och jobbar bra ihop. Utvecklingsteamet är en del av Kökets organisation som även består av redaktörer, säljare, producenter, analytiker, produktionsledare och affärsutvecklare. 
   Kom och jobba med oss!
   Är du webbutvecklare med erfarenhet och kompetens inom både backend och frontend? Toppen! Hos oss får du jobba med alla delar av sajten och med varierande arbetsuppgifter. Du får stora möjligheter att påverka, driva och utforska både teknik och funktionalitet. Vi har korta beslutsvägar och releasar kontinuerligt. Du får också chansen att jobba nära andra roller och team inom Köket.
   Vi ser fram emot att välkomna dig hit. Vi hoppas att du, som vi, gillar att samarbeta, är lyhörd och gärna delar med dig av kunskap. Vi hoppas också att du är intresserad och håller dig ajour med teknikutvecklingen inom ditt område. Du behöver prata svenska obehindrat och ha mer än tre års erfarenhet av följande:
  
    Node.js
    React
    Next.js
    CSS/SCSS
    GraphQL
    MongoDB
    Heroku eller annan molnbaserad hosting
  
   Praktiskt
   Vi sitter i TV4-huset på Tegeluddsvägen, ett stenkast från Gärdets t-banestation. I huset finns förutom hela TV4s verksamhet även vår egen Köket-studio, goda luncher på vår restaurang samt ett eget gym med träningsgrupper. Vi arbetar enligt en hybridmodell där vi bedriver arbetet både från kontoret och distans. Tjänsten är en tillsvidare-anställning.
   Intresserad?
   Tveka inte att skicka in din ansökan om du vill bli en del utav vårt team! Om du vill veta mer om jobbet är du välkommen att kontakta mig på erik.liden@tv4.se, 0709-900 576
   Vi ser fram emot din ansökan. För att kunna hantera dina personuppgifter på ett säkert sätt, ber vi dig att ansöka via vårt rekryteringssystem. Vi har inte möjlighet att ta emot ansökningar via e-post eller andra kanaler. Urval och intervjuer sker löpande. Sista ansökningsdag är 2022-05-13.
   Välkommen till TV4 - Home to your next big opportunity!

PayZlip är ett snabbt växande Startup med kontor mitt i centrala Helsingborg. Vi är på ett uppdrag för att revolutionera hur svenska företag hanterar och betalar ut löner med hjälp av full automatisering, datainsikter i realtid och On Demand-lönebetalningar. Vi söker nu en B2B Sales som vill vara med på vår spännande tillväxtresa!
Your opportunity
Join a development team which focuses on building robust, scalable high-quality software using principles such as TDD, event sourcing and microservices. As a developer at PayZlip, you'll work cross-stack with both our React frontends, our mobile Flutter applications and our microservices and APIs, written in Nest.js. We also make heavy use of automated testing and deployments.
What's important
We believe that the one we're looking for is interested in new technology and want to be constantly challenged to learn new things. We also believe that you are just as comfortable working with APIs and backends as you are with React and frontends.
You don't need to know everything about microservices, event sourcing or mobile development, but we believe that you're someone with the appetite, ability and drive to learn these skills at the workplace.
Expected knowledge:
JavaScript and TypeScript, including build tools such as webpack.
Version control with Git
Previous experience with React
Previous experience with Node.js and express or equivalent framework
Previous knowledge about testing on some level (unit testing, e2e etc.)
Qualifying knowledge:
Dart & Flutter
Previous experience with Nest.js
Devops and AWS (CDK and CloudFormation) knowledge
Experience with EventStoreDB
Previous experience with CQRS, Event sourcing and microservices
Previous experience with testdriven development
CI/CD experience (Github Actions)
Our modern and techy office is in central Helsingborg, just two minutes from the train station. We believe that you know best when and where you are most productive but we would love to see you at the office a couple of days per week.

Full Stack Developer
   Would you call yourself a “Full Stack” developer? Do you have 2+ years of professional experience in JavaScript, Node.js and modern frameworks like Vue.js and React?
   Do you aspire to work in a smaller, but growing company that values flexibility, fast-forwardness, and having fun along the ride? 
  Then this is a great opportunity to join our talented team of 11 engineers in Stockholm. 
  Our tech team is developing state of the art streaming technology for video and images. As a Full Stack developer at SeenThis, you will work with both internal and client facing tools and applications, to help our product reach its full potential.
   Expect to grow and be challenged!
  
   About SeenThis
   Since 2017, SeenThis has been evolving screen experiences for everyone, everywhere. With our groundbreaking adaptive streaming technology, we are transforming the distribution of digital content, to increase performance and reduce impact on the climate.
   With billions of streams served for more than 1,000 brands in over 40 countries, we push petabytes of data through our systems each month. If you’re wondering about requests per second, we’ll tell you over a Zoom coffee.
   We are on a journey to reshape the internet — for good. And the X factor to this success is our people. 
  We are a tight-knit team of 100+ employees working across the globe from our offices in Stockholm, Oslo, Copenhagen, London, Paris, Singapore, New York, and Sydney. We’re growing at a rapid pace, across all business areas, and are constantly looking for new colleagues to join our team. 
  We hire the best people and believe in their ability to create success and grow at the same time. We are global, yet close to heart – and we have ambitious goals, yet down-to-earth people.
   Do you want to be part of our expansion journey and have a lot of fun along the ride?
   We offer you:
   
   The opportunity to grow with a Swedish tech company 
   To learn and get support from experienced colleagues, enjoy hackathons and great discussions by the coffee machine 
   To work with state of the art technology 
   Great compensation for great work 
   A flexible workplace with a remote hybrid policy, and a social HQ office by the water, close to Södermalm in Stockholm 
  
  
   
  About the role
   Your work here will help establish our streaming technology as the new standard for delivering videos and images on the web – to deliver content faster, using less data, and in higher quality. If you’re thinking about the “middle out compression” joke from Silicon Valley, you’re not the first. We’re also big fans of Aviato and Erlich Bachman.
   We are currently hiring several developers to our applications team, to optimize and keep adding new functionalities to our CMS as well as our client-facing applications “Video Drop” & “Image Drop”. That means you will both work on our internal tools, where creative solutions and fast implementation is key, as well as on our external client-facing applications where design and usability are of high importance. 
  Our stack is JavaScript-based with Node.js, and we are using mostly Vue.js and (some) React.js for frontend. The communication between our frontends and backends is mostly through GraphQL and REST APIs.
   Your work task will be varied and will most probably involve things from all across the stack. This is a great opportunity to learn and develop in several areas that you are interested in!
   Do you have the ambition to take a Team Lead role in the future? Great! As the teams are growing, we are strongly encouraging those who want to help take responsibility for others.
   About you
  
   Required
   You have a minimum of 2 years’ experience with JavaScript and Node.js.
   Preferred
   Vue.js, GraphQL, Docker & Postgres
   Bonus Points
   AWS & Serverless
   We really appreciate developers that enjoy a passionate tech discussion by the coffee machine. Our team members are always curious to learn new things, and we are open to new perspectives and are especially interested in people who are updated on the latest trends and technologies!
   Looking forward to your application.
   Application
   We are excited to welcome you to the SeenThis-family! 
  Please apply sooner than later, as we review applications and interview on a continuous basis.
   If you have any questions regarding the role please contact Talent Acquisition Manager Ronja Hultkrantz, ronja@seenthis.se

From our technology to our team members, Neo4j is built on relationships.
   
   
   
     As part of Neo4j product engineering, you will work together with a diverse team of talented colleagues from around the world. Our culture encourages engineers who want to become deep experts in a particular field – or to build broad expertise across several technologies. Our engineers regularly work with peers in field engineering and experience the full lifecycle of the systems they build.
   
   
   
     We build technology that helps cure cancers, addresses diabetes, and gets humans to Mars. We're proud to fight fraud, crush pandemics, and even help journalists uncover the truth. Neo4j’s engineering teams are located in Malmö, Sweden and London, UK.
   
   
   
     Please submit your CV and cover letter in English.
   
   
   
     The Role
   
   
     Our team develops Neo4j Bloom, the graph visualisation product from Neo4j. It allows business users to search and explore connected data, and is used for example by large international banks to detect fraud, automotive suppliers to keep track of their parts and medical researchers to develop new cures for diseases like cancer and diabetes.
   
   
   
     We have close integration with the Neo4j database, making use and showcasing all the latest features. The Bloom application is central to Neo4j and we are growing the team building it.
   
   
   
     You will work in the forefront of technology and with an opportunity to innovate. The role also includes the possibility to assist at conferences or training events internally in Neo4j and to the wider community.
   
   
   
     This is an exciting time to join the Neo4j Bloom team!
   
   
   
     For a quick introduction to Neo4j Bloom, see this video
   
   
     (https://youtu.be/y9trGgqFu_k)
   
   
  
   
    What You Will Get To Do 
    
     Work on innovative features across Blooms tech stack Develop the Neo4j database plugin written in Java Optimize performance at all levels to make sure Bloom is responsive Work on the database connectivity layer and query generation code Develop UI components with React, service layer and Redux store Make software that people use to get their daily job done
    
   
  
   
   
  
   
     What You Will Bring 
    
     Experience from back-end development Experience with a client-side frameworks and libraries such as React, Redux, Angular.js, Vue.js and CycleJS Good debugging and optimization (performance and networking) skills Working knowledge of Java Bachelor or master degree in relevant computer science Good communication skills
    
   
   
  
   
    Bonus For The Following 
    
     Knowledge of and experience with a graph database, such as Neo4j Experience with BDD, TDD, and JavaScript testing frameworks (Jest, Jasmine, Mocha/Chai, Selenium) Experience with build tools such as Webpack or Rollup Comfortable working with a distributed team in an international business environment. User-first design thinking
    
   
   
  
   
    Location 
    
     SE
    
   
   
  
   
    Neo4j Values:
   
   
     Our work in Neo4j Engineering is guided by our company values:
   
   
   
     (we)-[:VALUE]->(relationships)
   
   
     (we)-[:FOCUS_ON]->(:UserSuccess)
   
   
     (we)-[:THRIVE_IN]->(:Culture {type: [‘Open’, ‘Inclusive’})
   
   
     (we)-[:ASSUME]->(:Intent {direction:’Positive’})
   
   
     (we)-[:WELCOME]->(:Discussions {nature: ‘IntellectuallyHonest’})
   
   
     (we)-[:DELIVER_ON]->(ourCommitments)
   
   
   
     Why Join Neo4j?
   
   
     Neo4j is one of the 20 most popular databases in the world, and the leader in the rapidly emerging Graph Database category. We’re building the technology that enables connected data to solve the world’s most pressing problems. You’ll work on unique engineering projects that challenge what’s possible.
   
   
   
     We have customers in every industry across the globe, and our products a proven product/market fit. Joining our team is an opportunity to shape the future of data and analytics.
   
   
   
     We pride ourselves on being a welcoming team. Most of us would agree that one of the best parts of working at Neo4j is the people we get to work with.
   
   
   
     We encourage you to apply even if you don’t 100% fit the qualifications above. Why? Because we are committed to building an environment that fosters belonging, which means valuing intellectually honest discussions and being receptive to new ideas and perspectives.
   
   
   
     One of our central objectives is to provide an inclusive, diverse, and equitable workplace for everyone to develop their potential and have a positive, career-defining experience.
   
   
   
     About Neo4j:
   
   
     Neo4j is the leader in graph database technology. As the world’s most widely deployed graph database, we help organizations – including NASA, UBS and Volvo Cars – to reveal and predict how people, processes and systems interrelate. Using this relationships-first approach, applications built using Neo4j tackle connected data challenges such as analytics and artificial intelligence, fraud detection, real-time recommendations and knowledge graphs.
   
   
   
     Neo4j is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. Please read the privacy notice regarding Neo4j's recruitment process to understand how we will handle the personal data that you provide.
   
   
     More information at www.neo4j.com.

column1: Full Stack Developer - Game Operations Platform
column4:
Craft:
Technology & Development
Job Description:
We are looking for a Full Stack developer to shape the future of the Game Operations Platform where King teams build, monitor and operate some of the most popular mobile games in the world such as Candy Crush Saga. The platform contains a suite of software products designed to provide a central, high- quality, robust and extensible toolset with a consistent and stable user experience.
The Game Operations Platform team aims to provide a competitive technical ecosystem including front- end & back- end framework, core APIs and self- service tools that allows internal teams to easily develop and expose game operational tools with consistent end- user experience, excellent interoperability and efficient developer experience.
Your role within our Kingdom
As a member of the development team, you will play an important role to influence how technology evolves at King and how King teams develop their internal applications that bring great value to our games. Your responsibilities might include:
Develop and maintain King internal tech stack including front- end & back- end libraries, framework, core APIs and self- service tools.
Improve developers experiences throughout the application development lifecycle
Develop new features that enhance the experience of our end- users who use the platform to monitor and operate king games.
Co- develop internal applications with other application and game teams
Research and drive technology innovations across teams
Skills to create thrills
Solid experience with front- end frameworks/libraries such as React or similar
Good experience working with modern Java frameworks and standards
Good experience working with APIs and frameworks
Focus on testing as part of the development
Bonus points
Understanding of micro service architecture
Experience of Python
Knowledge of cloud technologies such as GCP or AWS
Like dev- ops culture
About King
King is the game developer behind the world- famous Candy Crush franchise, as well as mobile game hits including Farm Heroes, Bubble Witch and Pet Rescue. Candy Crush is the top- grossing franchise in US app stores, a position it has held for the last two years, and King’s games are being played by 245 million monthly active users as of Q3 2021. King, which is part of the Activision Blizzard group since its acquisition in 2016, employs nearly 2,000 people in game studios in Stockholm, Malmö, London, Barcelona and Berlin, and offices in San Francisco, New York, and Malta.
A Great Saga Needs All Sorts of Heroes
Making games is fun. Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply cannot expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes.
Making the World Playful
Making the World Playful is what inspires us to create new experiences and raise the bar. It’s what makes King a place where we can all dream bigger, continue to add innovation to our games, broadening the portfolio and exploring new territories in mid- core and casual. We take the art and science of gaming to the next level through our curiosity for the unexplored, passion for games, respect for each other and love for our players - and we’re not afraid to have fun along the way. In fact, together with our parent company Activision Blizzard and experts around the world, we believe having fun is good for you. There has never been a better time to join us. We're dreaming bigger and see a world of possibilities ahead. If you share our passion, our values, and our hunger to shape the future, join us in Making the World Playful!
Applications need to be in English.
Discover King at careers.king.com

Would you like to help us build the Nordic champion of corporate learning platforms?
   About Collegial:
   Collegial is a Stockholm-based EdTech company with partners, learners and employees across the globe. Being in the EdTech industry, we strive to walk the talk – to develop ourselves and those around us, building an inclusive culture of continuous learning.
   We founded Collegial with the philosophy that sharing knowledge across companies and industries will help all involved move faster together. We are developing a Corporate Learning Platform that enables companies and public sector organizations to accelerate continuous professional development in the workplace and in society-at-large.
   To reimagine the way we learn in the workplace we have gathered a team of creative developers and learning designers alongside senior leaders from industry, public sector and academia. Together we work to create great learning experiences for our community of learners and constantly strive to develop ourselves and those around us - building an inclusive culture of continuous learning.
   Our vision is to offer the most engaging and impactful corporate learning experience in the world. We are in an exciting scale-up phase with launching new customers and constantly developing our platform and that is where we need your help.
  
   What you will do:
   With over 15 000 users worldwide, you will join our quest to create the most engaging and accessible corporate learning experience in the world. As a part of a tight knit development team you will work on our data platform, analysis algorithms and the visualizations that allow learning activities to be aggregated and tracked by individuals as well as administrators across platforms and organisations.
   You will augment a small team that is focused on integrating progress (and other) data from all the different learning platforms we support, crunching and aggregating this data such that it can drive visualizations and metrics.
   You will work in a cross-functional Agile team of skilled developers and together with your team develop the platform that supports companies and users in keeping up with the growing need of continuous learning.
  
   Who are you?
   To succeed in this role we see that you have an understanding of what it takes to build Software as a Service. You have a good grasp of the shifting technology landscape, what technologies and practices are gaining traction and how to future-proof the stack. You subscribe to the DevOps culture and an Agile way of working. In this role you get to be creative and it is essential that you enjoy solving tricky technical problems that require out-of-the-box thinking.
   You have a broad software development experience perhaps with a special interest in cloud native development and the go programming language. You write beautiful, easy to follow and idiomatic code. Furthermore, you write unit tests for your own sake because it makes you feel good to know that you can refactor your code without fear of breaking it in unrelated ways.
   It is important for you to work in a team that holds itself to a high standard of quality, embraces code reviews and keeps a green build and clean commit log. You feel comfortable with concurrency and delight in getting the most out of a multicore processor using goroutines, channels, mutex and wait groups.
  
   You would like to work with some of these technologies:
   
    Go 
   React / Typescript 
   GraphQL 
   PostgreSQL 
   MongoDB/DocumentDB 
   Redis

Would you like to help us build the Nordic champion of corporate learning platforms?
   About Collegial:
   Collegial is a Stockholm-based EdTech company with partners, learners, and employees across the globe. Being in the EdTech industry, we strive to walk the talk – to develop ourselves and those around us, building an inclusive culture of continuous learning.
   We founded Collegial with the philosophy that sharing knowledge across companies and industries will help all involved move faster together. We are developing a Corporate Learning Platform that enables companies and public sector organizations to accelerate continuous professional development in the workplace and in society-at-large.
   To reimagine the way we learn in the workplace we have gathered a team of creative developers and learning designers alongside senior leaders from industry, public sector and academia. Together we work to create great learning experiences for our community of learners and constantly strive to develop ourselves and those around us - building an inclusive culture of continuous learning.

If you enjoy variation, you can also get involved in projects to develop our Go-based analytics platform. You will work in a cross-functional Agile team to develop the platform that supports companies and users in keeping up with the growing need for continuous learning.
  
   Who are you?

You have a good grasp of the shifting technology landscape, what technologies and practices are gaining traction and how to future-proof the stack. We believe that you subscribe to the DevOps culture and Agile ways of working.
   We believe that you are a TypeScript developer with strong JavaScript fundamentals and have experience with React and related patterns and technologies including GraphQL / Apollo. If you also know Golang that would be another feather in your cap. You feel comfortable when you know your Unit and Integration tests cover the key functionality in what you have developed, and you can refactor code and deploy changes with confidence.

Hello there!
Our client work on building an awesome team that works on creating epic products with a challenging vision: transforming the insurance industry with Visual Intelligence solutions.
We reached 33 insurers, scaled our operations to 22 countries, raised a 5M-euro series A led by international VCs, and were able to grow revenue by a factor of 3 with the business of our loyal and new customers.
We couldn't be happier with the results and this year we are focused on achieving much more. We've grown the team to around 80 people, we have just opened offices in Munich and London and we've launched a new product for the property industry that we believe will become a game-changer.
I am lucky enough to say that we have built a team of dreamers and movers, committed to making the insurance and claim processes easier for users and more efficient for companies. We are doing it by building the most advanced Visual Intelligence SaaS technology.
Growing the team for our new property solution
We are now developing a new product focused on automating property claims. Probably you are wondering why...
How insurers manage a property insurance claim is one of the most sensitive touch points in terms of customer loyalty. We want to help companies reduce the time between the notification of a claim and its resolution. Our goal is to provide a technological solution that allows companies to automate processes, be more efficient, and improve customer expectations.
We launched a beta version and now we need to expand the value proposition. We are looking for new developers that want to join us in our mission to give companies the power to change the industry.
Do you like transforming the way companies do things? Do you believe any process can be improved in order to make it more efficient? Do you love technical challenges? Do you want to join a team in which you can have a high impact? We are looking for you!
About the role
You will have the opportunity to participate in the definition and development (frontend/backend) of a powerful solution based totally on Javascript with serverless and microservices where we use NodeJS/Typescript with Amazon in the backend and Angular in the frontend).
We are already working on a major change in our architecture to use Microfrontends and Clean Architecture. We hope you be part of these changes and participate in decisions on how to design and implement them.
You will join a bunch of inspiring and hard-working people (product, design, front, and back-end experts, QA engineers) designing, developing, testing, and deploying components with a focus on high availability, low latency, and easy scalability.
You will work closely with our Artificial Intelligence and Data team. So if you are interested in knowing more about how Artificial Intelligence is changing the way we work and live, you will very much enjoy the ride.

Responsibilities
Participating in the design and creation of a scalable SaaS platform.
Writing clean, functional code on the front- and back-end.
Work with development teams and product managers to ideate software solutions.
Design client-side and server-side architecture.
Build the front-end of applications through appealing visual design.
Develop and manage well-functioning databases and applications.
Write robust, efficient, and secure APIs.
Test software to ensure responsiveness and efficiency.
Troubleshoot, debug and upgrade software.
Create security and data protection settings.
Collaborate to create and maintain CI / CD pipelines for automation and deployment processes.
Testing and fixing bugs or other coding issues.

About you
Required degree (it is preferred technical formation).
4+ years of experience in development teams of apps based on Javascript.
Knowledge of Angular 6+ ( preferred), React, Vue or any other major frontend development framework.
Git advanced knowledge.
Experience working with SQL and NoSQL.
Knowledge of HTML, CS33 and SASS
Knowledge of CSS grid and Flexbox.
Knowledge of Javascript / NodeJS / Typescript, especially with asynchronous operations.
Experience working with Agile methods.
Additional knowledge of Angular.js
Testing of Javascript apps.
CI/CD knowledge.
Basic knowledge of AWS or any other major cloud provider.
Be proactive, engage in collaborative work in a cross-functional agile team.
Work both on new features and verification and optimizations of current ones.
Source inspiration from our SMEs, clients, and views from outside our industry to create game-changing products.
Disrupt our thinking! Show us how we could be better at what we’re already better at.
Bring the latest and greatest technologies to benefit us and our clients

About the process
Quick call with our HR manager (30min)
Quick call with our Tech Lead and our Team Lead (1 hour)
Technical exercise and defence (1 hour)
We send you an offer
Perks
If you join us, you will be able to enjoy the following perks:
Besides the 22 days of vacation per year (plus Spanish public holidays) you will enjoy paid time off on:
The 24th & 31st of December
Your birthday or your kids' birthday (although you will have to take to the office an awesome birthday cake in return)
Flexible working hours
 Intensive working hours on Fridays & Summer
Private medical & dental insurance policy
‍Weekly English classes
Training budget
Flexible compensation scheme: meals, transport, etc
Free fruit, tea & coffee every day
These benefits have been temporarily suspended until we come back to the office.

The ustwo Europe Studio is looking for an experienced senior full-stack software developer to help us grow our digital product team. Specifically, we're looking for someone who can work across the web stack, but has a particular emphasis on backend and infrastructure development.

Here at ustwo, we're renowned for crafting amazing digital experiences. Whether for our roster of international clients and partners, or for our homegrown ventures, we shape, design, build and test digital products/services with users at the very heart of our approach.

As the world changes around us, the challenges our clients are asking us to take on are becoming more fundamental, more strategic and more vital than ever to the success of their organisations.

As a developer you will work to solve difficult problems and build beautiful and intuitive products within a cross-functional team of technologists, designers, product owners and agile coaches.

You are:

Current in your practice. You have solid software development fundamentals and a working understanding of modern, best-practice software development practices and workflow. You keep up with the latest trends in technology.
Highly Collaborative. Able to work collaboratively in multidisciplinary teams of designers, developers and product managers using Agile and Lean principles.
A clear communicator. Capable of conveying ideas and breaking down concepts clearly to a diverse range of stakeholders (verbally and written).
Open to sharing. Whether that be your thoughts, ideas and work in-progress.
Want to grow. You seek out opportunities to learn, promoting regular feedback with those who you work with.
Resilient. Can handle pressure and work in a dynamic and fast-moving environment.
Adaptable. Can handle ambiguity and are comfortable switching contexts and able to apply your practice across a range of industries and different deliverables and goals.

Must haves

You have a minimum of 4-5 years professional development experience.
Strong experience in Node.js for backend services (e.g. Express).
Strong experience with React, or another major web framework such Angular.
Experience with containerised services and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, etc.)
Working knowledge of modern cross-browser HTML5+, ES6+ and CSS3+
Applying the best design patterns for various application requirements (MVC, MVVM, Mediator, Rx, Flux, etc.)
Awareness of the most established libraries, their ecosystems and how to choose between them
Knowledge about choosing the best databases and their characteristics (SQL / NoSQL / real-time, etc.)
Experience with API integration / testing / design / implementation (e.g. REST, GraphQL, etc.).
Knowledge of Continuous Integration / Deployment
Experience with automated testing (e.g. unit, integration, API, etc.)
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Experience working within agile environments including Scrum / Kanban.

Nice to have

Experience with deploying, hosting, securing, monitoring and scaling in the cloud (Google Cloud Platform or AWS) and experience with configuration management tools (e.g. Terraform, Chef, Puppet, KMS, etc.)
Experience in building highly scalable and resilient web applications
Practical experience with TDD and / or BDD (using frameworks such as Mocha, Jest, Cucumber, Rspec, Capybara, Selenium, etc.)

We strongly believe in hiring for diversity, and we want to hire people who display strong potential. The key to your success and our success is hiring people who have a passion to constantly learn, share knowledge with others and display constant curiosity. We believe in the power of the introvert and extroverts and our Studio culture provides opportunities for colleagues of all persuasions to be heard, have ownership and clear opportunities to progress.

We have a very warm and welcoming culture. We are a very transparent company and work hard to distribute leadership across the studio. We are an equal opportunity employer and very much value diversity and inclusion. We believe diverse teams help us make better products and we actively hire for cultural growth. We seek people of all ages, genders, stories, cognitive capabilities and backgrounds.

Ansök nu 
    
   
   
   
    
     Köket.se är en del av TV4, ett av Sveriges största mediehus. Köket erbjuder inspirerande och engagerande matinnehåll genom TV-program, recept, artiklar, videoklipp, onlinekurser, poddar, mm. Vi samarbetar med flera av Sveriges populäraste kockar och når varje vecka ut till ca 2 miljoner användare genom våra olika kanaler. Vår vision är att bidra med inspiration och matglädje för alla. Vi söker nu en erfaren fullstackutvecklare till Köket.se! 
      Ta chansen att jobba med ett härligt gäng inom ett spännande område. Kom till Köket! Här får du jobba i ett litet, oberoende team tillsammans med erfarna personer inom backend, frontend och design/UX. 
      Vårt utvecklingsteam ansvarar för allt utvecklingsarbete i vår viktigaste kanal, Köket.se, som är en av Sveriges största matsajter. Vi arbetar agilt med alla delar av webbplatsen, från idé/design och planering till genomförande och testning. Vi är ett litet och sammansvetsat team som har kul och jobbar bra ihop. Utvecklingsteamet är en del av Kökets organisation som även består av redaktörer, säljare, producenter, analytiker, produktionsledare och affärsutvecklare. 
      Kom och jobba med oss! 
      Är du webbutvecklare med erfarenhet och kompetens inom både backend och frontend? Toppen! Hos oss får du jobba med alla delar av sajten och med varierande arbetsuppgifter. Du får stora möjligheter att påverka, driva och utforska både teknik och funktionalitet. Vi har korta beslutsvägar och releasar kontinuerligt. Du får också chansen att jobba nära andra roller och team inom Köket. 
      Vi ser fram emot att välkomna dig hit. Vi hoppas att du, som vi, gillar att samarbeta, är lyhörd och gärna delar med dig av kunskap. Vi hoppas också att du är intresserad och håller dig ajour med teknikutvecklingen inom ditt område. Du behöver prata svenska obehindrat och ha mer än tre års erfarenhet av följande: 
      
      Node.js 
      React 
      Next.js 
      CSS/SCSS 
      GraphQL 
      MongoDB 
      Heroku eller annan molnbaserad hosting 
      
     Praktiskt 
      Vi sitter i TV4-huset på Tegeluddsvägen, ett stenkast från Gärdets t-banestation. I huset finns förutom hela TV4s verksamhet även vår egen Köketstudio, goda luncher på vår restaurang samt ett eget gym med träningsgrupper. Vi arbetar enligt en hybridmodell där vi bedriver arbetet både från kontoret och på distans. Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning. 
      Intresserad? 
      Tveka inte att skicka in din ansökan om du vill bli en del utav vårt team! Om du vill veta mer om jobbet är du välkommen att kontakta mig Erik Lidén,  team lead och produktägare, via mejl eller telefon, erik.liden@tv4.se, 0709-900 576. 
      Vi ser fram emot din ansökan. För att kunna hantera dina personuppgifter på ett säkert sätt, ber vi dig att ansöka via vårt rekryteringssystem. Vi har inte möjlighet att ta emot ansökningar via e-post eller andra kanaler. Urval och intervjuer sker löpande.

column1: Full Stack Developer to Levels Group
column4:
We are looking for full stack developers with at least 3 years of experience to join us on our journey. Together we build complex and compelling web applications for big and exciting clients, help develop products for new and promising start-up companies, and at times even pitch our inhouse-bred product ideas in front of investors! It is up to you if you want to work with one or more clients. We are looking for curious, collaborative people who are eager to teach what they know and who jump at any opportunity to explore new uncharted territories. Does this sound like you? Then we'd love to hear from you!
   Here is where you enter the picture:
   You will join our friendly team of developers and designers in developing web applications for our clients. At this moment we are currently working swiftly with Kubernetes, Docker, Kotlin, React, Modern JavaScript (ES6+), and CSS. But as we are always looking to improve ourselves, we are always open to new ways of working.Some of our projects originate inhouse such as Strike, whereas others are border-crossing start-ups in East Africa such as Kupatana and Afripods, as well as promising startups based right here in Sweden such as Storage365 and Target Aid.
   We are looking for you who:
   
    Are an eager learner with the ability to pick up new skills quickly

   Have experience working with CI and CD 
   Have attention to detail as well as passion and drive to create top-quality user experiences and technical solutions 
   Are a team player 
   Live in Sweden and speak Swedish fluently 
  
   What and how will you be working?
   
    You will have the opportunity to work for big and exciting unicorn companies, either at their premises or in our office 
   You will be working for promising start-ups where your expertise will be put to good use to build its fundamental base 
   You will be working in a team consisting of designers and developers with varying skill sets 
   Teaching and learning are a natural part of your daily work 
  
   Who are we? In a digital world, where the only constant is change, Levels aim to take businesses, and ourselves to the next level. We are a team of curious and entrepreneurial-minded people who love helping our partners grow their ventures. How do we do this? By integrating our expertise within strategy, scaling, development, design, venture capital, and talent development and recruitment we are able to not only pursue brilliant ideas but also turn opportunities into game-changing businesses.
   Perks and benefits:
   
    Being a part of building a great company! 
   Working alongside brilliant colleagues who are passionate about what they do 
   Opportunities to advance your career

   Kick-ass parties and after-work events 
   A mentorship program with the aim of making sure that you feel fulfilled at work and have all the tools to grow 
   Hack days where we team up to explore new and exciting projects together 
   Flexible work hours 
   Competitive salary and compensation

    wearelevels.com
