Continental Bakeries is a European bakery group specialized in the production of biscuits, bread replacements and toast. They focus on private label products and several well-known brands such as Haust, Grabower, and Brinky. Most certainly you’ve probably heard about, or even more certainly eaten, a biscuit from the brand Gille? Continental Bakeries has fifteen “Production Centres of Excellence” in Western Europe with a total of 2,500 employees. All of their production facilities are certified in accordance with IFS and BRC standards.
  
   Continental Bakeries export products worldwide, with Western Europe as one of their most important markets. It is important that the customers can count on them supplying the best quality with a very high level of delivery reliability. They keep their promises while being an innovative partner: Continental Bakeries do not only react quickly to market demands, they also follow regional, national and European consumer trends closely and are quick to anticipate customer needs. Finally, they place a great deal of importance on sustainability by minimizing their impact on the environment, commit themselves to the welfare of people and animals and to improve the nutritional value of their products.
   Read more about Continental Bakeries here. 
  
   
   
  ABOUT THE ROLE
   Continental Bakeries is now looking for a person to take on the role as Operations Manager.  Your mission, as Operations Manager, will be to initiate and execute policies regarding the production locations in Sweden, to achieve the set objectives as successfully and as efficiently as possible in the field of production, quality, delivery as agreed, safety and environment within the applicable agreements and budgeting. You will be responsible for Continental Bakeries 2 production sites, located in Örkelljunga and Åsljunga. Great leadership is of utmost importance in this role, as you will drive a large team forward. This requires both clarity and mutually strong commitment. You will be a visible and present leader in close dialogue with the production teams and their daily work. You will work closely with Operation Managers from the other countries and with COO’s central managers team (Supply Chain, Engineering, Safety, Quality, Continuous Improvement, ESG).  In this position you report to the Managing Director Northern Europe, Mikael Carlsson.
  
   WHAT YOU WILL DO:
   As operations manager, you will be responsible for 4 significant areas with the following Key end results:
   1. Manufacturing Drawing up and implementing the country’s production and maintenance policy and budget for the production sites in Sweden, in consultation with the MD, to ensure the production organization is optimized within the framework of the company’s policy.
   
    Prepare annual budget and plan, and discuss this with/have it approved by the MD 
   Create a country’s Operation 3 years master plan and gain approval by MD’s office. Key dimensions of the master plan is; road map to achieve the KPI’s. Development of a culture of Operational Excellence (Safety/Quality/Cost/Service), the talent of the organization and people’s development, create attractive working environment. 
   Accountable for the Cost Savings results 
   Discuss policies with department heads reporting to the position and gain consensus for course correction 
   Follow up that the agreed policy, objectives, budget is achieved and escalate deviations offering alternate solutions in case of deviations 
   Fuel the Continuous Improvement program with local innovation and improvement projects. Adjust organization (fix and variable) when necessary. 
   Interact with internal stakeholders (eg sales, finance, purchasing, engineering, marketing and HR) 
   Coordinate with external parties, when necessary, independently or in collaboration with other departments (customers, government, suppliers, employee organizations)
  
  
   2. Production in accordance with safety and quality requirements, delivery conditions and costs Ensures that the production locations are produced in accordance with the agreed quality requirements, delivery conditions and costs as agreed. Ensure that Preventive Maintenance programs are executed to keep overall OEE and costs in target
   
    Responsible for meeting production and maintenance standards 
   Managing local management teams 
   Checking and monitoring the results, adjusting where necessary 
   Follow up on the agreed KPIs (e.g. OEE, waste, man-hour efficiency, absenteeism) 
   Fosters a culture of safety on the job, implementing and using the tools, programs, targets set forth by the COO office 
   Consults with the temporary employment agency regarding the policy regarding temporary work 
   Working on and improving quality systems (BRC/HACCP/IFS/GMP/Customer requirements)
  
  
   3. Innovation Is responsible for developing plans to strengthen the production organization.
   
    Formulate proposals in the field of cost control and technological improvements 
   Initiate and monitor the process of continuous improvement (eg improvement teams) 
   Develop, plan, and enable investment projects for the production sites 
   Responsible for CAPEX proposals concerning facilities improvements, safety conditions, quality, and productivity improvements 
   In sync with the central teams, champions new product launches in his/her factories
  
  
   4. Leadership Such an organisation, development and staffing of the department that it is possible to work effectively and efficiently within the guidelines set for this
   
    Formulate and implement an adequate organizational and personnel policy in line with the organizational objectives 
   Create a good and safe working environment for the employees in the production organization 
   Chairman HACCP team 
   Participation in or chairing of employee organization consultations, depending on local laws and regulations.  
  
  CONTINENTAL BAKERIES OFFERS:
   As the Operations Manager, you will be a part of a smaller organisation that operates within an international solid Group. This generates and enables a fast-moving business which promote quick decisions and a great opportunity to influence their way of working. Continental Bakeries also make great efforts to contribute to a sustainable future and is in fact the leader in its field within the European market. You will be a part of a company that is growing fast and operates in an international environment. 
  The culture within Continental Bakeries can be described as result-oriented, “down to earth”, open with a no-nonsense mentality. Their approach enables employees to do business and to accept challenges in a friendly working atmosphere.
   WHO YOU ARE:
   We believe you have a relevant engineering and/or manufacturing education. You have at least five years of proven successful managerial experience in an industrial environment, comparable to this position. We find it beneficial to have a background within the food or bakery segment. You have a clear structure and method for working as efficiently and optimal as possible within production, which LEAN and 5S is an essential part of. Due to the international context and continuous dialogues, good communication skills in English are required. In addition, your personal suitability, and personal skills, will be essential parts to this process. We therefore believe you can identify yourself with the skills below:
   
    Analytic and Strategic – You have the ability to proactively identify opportunities to develop processes and the way of working. 
   Cooperative – When things need to be done, you’re great at driving it with others. How do we solve this? 
   Brings clarity to the table – You’re a leader of clarity, both in terms of communication and in your consistent actions, which generates predictability. 
   Communication and listening skills – you know the importance of “two-way communication” and attaches equal importance to both outgoing and incoming information 
   The ability to inspirate and create engagement – Your clarity, positive approach and result oriented way of working creates a team that strives for the same goal, together with you.
  
  
   We hope we caught your interest and look forward to your application!
   ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
   Start: Per agreement
   Location: Örkelljunga and Åsljunga
   This recruitment process is handled by A-hub and on Continental Bakeries request, all enquiries regarding this position will be handled by A-hub and Therese Stenson, therese@a-hub.se.

Vårt Växjökontor har haft en stark och stabil tillväxt från start och huserar idag en bred palett av kompetenser i form av ett gäng härliga människor som dagligen levererar uppskattade innovativa digitala lösningar med kvalitet och transformation i fokus.
   Hos oss kommer du att trivas som fisken i vattnet om du uppskattar att arbeta i en entreprenörsdriven verksamhet med högt i tak där såväl kreativitet som nya idéer kring arbetssätt och verksamheten i stort välkomnas med öppna armar.
   Till vårt affärsområde Digitala Affärer söker vi en erfaren utvecklare som vill vara med och utveckla moderna lösningar som hjälper våra kunder att göra digitala affärer.
   Vem är du?
   Vi tror att du, precis som vi, är sugen på att få vara med och bygga riktigt coola och framtidssäkra lösningar till våra kunder. Du är lösningsfokuserad och vill tillsammans med lika dedikerade kollegor bidra under hela projekt från krav till förvaltning med din tekniska kunskap och stora engagemang. Kanske har du fastnat lite i din utveckling och är sugen på att bli utmanad igen i en varierad vardag där inget uppdrag är det andra likt och där slutmålet styr snarare än plattformen i fråga?
   En vanlig dag på jobbet
   Under en vanlig dag kommer du att få förmånen att hänga med trevliga, kompetenta och drivna kollegor, men också våra härliga kunder som vi har ett nära och långsiktigt samarbete med. Utöver detta kommer du också att pyssla med:
   
    Utveckling i t.ex. PHP, Laravel, Node och MySQL 
   Snyggt skriven kod utifrån god praxis inom webbstandarder, responsiv design samt utveckling för mobila enheter 
   Optimering av lösningar för maximal tillgänglighet och prestanda 
   Spaning efter ny teknik i syfte att utveckla både din kompetens och våra leveranser 
   Vue, React eller Angular är ett stort plus 
  
  Det praktiska
   
   Heltid 
   Tillsvidareanställning 
   Konkurrenskraftig lön och bra förmåner 
   Arbetsort: Vi har kontor i Växjö, Kalmar, Jönköping så bra om du kan ta dig hit ett par dagar i veckan. 
  
  Nyfiken?
   Vi stirrar oss inte blinda på ditt CV utan tycker att det är minst lika viktigt att du är en trevlig prick. Checkar du av boxar som social, lösningsorienterad, kreativ, nyfiken, engagerad, inkännande och snäll samt tycker att ovan beskrivning låter som rätt nästa steg?
   Tveka inte att skicka iväg en ansökan så snackar vi lite mer om rollen!

At Epidemic Sound we are reinventing the music industry. Our carefully curated catalog, with over 35,000 tracks, is tailored for storytellers, streaming services, and in-store soundtracks. Countless clients around the world, from broadcasters, production companies, DSPs, and YouTubers rely on our tracks to help them tell their stories. Epidemic Sound’s music is heard in hundreds of millions of online videos daily, across millions of playlist streams, and in thousands of in-store locations. Headquartered in Stockholm, we’re spread across offices in New York City, Los Angeles, Seoul, Hamburg, and Amsterdam. We’re growing fast, have lots of fun, and are taking the music industry with us.
We are now looking for a Platform Lead with experience of how to design and build robust, scalable and maintainable applications and services to help us take our product to the next level.
How you will make an impact
As a Platform Lead you will act as a leader and one of the main contributors of the long term vision of our technology platform. This means developing strategies, policies and efficient processes for the platform in collaboration with the rest of the organisation. You will get to promote solutions of good quality, sustainable methodologies and good habits while also identifying and addressing problems and challenges in the platform and encouraging continuous improvement.
As part of your role, you would also join one of our cross-functional product teams dedicated to solving a problem and delivering outcomes within one of our product areas. You would get to support and mentor more junior team members in finding the right solutions and system designs. You would also contribute to, and lead, cross-team initiatives to evolve shared components and platform architecture.
You can expect to:
Help create a positive environment where engineers can thrive. This might include holding discussions, collecting and consolidating ideas, and help facilitating strategies to reach our shared technical vision.
Contribute to all stages of the product life-cycle: Design, implementation, testing, releasing and maintenance.
Work in a lightweight agile process where we regularly evaluate how we work and try to improve.
Collaborate constantly: We’re big believers in teamwork and the value of practices like careful code reviews, pair (or mob) programming etc
Learn a ton of new things: Be it through hack-days, courses, conferences or tech-talks, we emphasize learning and we also expect you to share your knowledge with your colleagues.
Have fun and take a lot of pride in what you and all of Epidemic Sound is doing.
Who you are
In order for you to thrive in this role, we believe that you:
Have previously contributed to the long term vision of a platform and the strategies behind it.
Have a great understanding of modern web architectures, system design, data structures and software engineering principles, and understand how to apply them to design scalable and robust solutions.
Have been mentoring and supporting less experienced colleagues and engineering teams, particularly in reducing technical debt and complexity in applications.
Love teamwork.
Are passionate about building great products that people love, and you always make technology choices with this end-goal in mind.
Are principled but also pragmatic: You value best-practices but realize that all rules have exceptions.
Experience working closely with business and product stakeholders, and thus a strong understanding of business and user requirements.
Speak English with professional working proficiency (Swedish is not a requirement).
It would also be music to our ears if you have:
Experience of one or more of the following: Python, Django, React & Redux, ElasticSearch, Docker, Kubernetes, GCP ecosystem, Kotlin.
Worked with audio streaming and/or music library management.
Experience from e-commerce, online subscription and/or payment solutions.

Curious about our music? Find our music on Spotify here https://open.spotify.com/user/...
We have lots of fun soundtracking the world and our annual Spring Bash is an event that captures this perfectly. Take a look at our most recent one, a virtual celebration!
Application
Do you want to be a part of our fantastic team? Please apply by clicking the link below.
We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business and a better world. We value diversity and encourage everyone to come and soundtrack the world with us.

column1: Ports Group söker Senior Software Developer
column4:
Vill du vara med att trygga ensamrätten för några av Nordens starkaste varumärken?
Ports Group är marknadsledande i Norden med en vision om att bli Europas främsta bolag inom Brand Protection. Ports Group erbjuder tjänster och mjukvara som ger ett heltäckande skydd för hela varumärket världen över. Totalt är vi 80 medarbetare med kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö, Barcelona och Malta
Om tjänsten
Som senior utvecklare har du en central roll I utvecklingsteamet. Du hjälper till med att prioritera utvecklingsarbetet baserat på affärsutvecklingsplaner, kundbehov och andra stakeholders input. Du arbetar med helheten, både operativt och strategiskt. Du tar fram tekniska systemlösningar, och ser till att dessa blir implementerade. Du stötar och supporterar de andra utvecklarna. Företaget växer, och det finns troligen möjligheter att ta ett större ansvar framöver.
Kompetens- & erfarenhetskrav
Vi söker dig som har flera års erfarenhet från liknande uppdrag. Det är meriterande om du har en relevant högskoleutbildning
Mycket goda kunskaper i Java EE
Goda kunskaper i HTML, JavaScript, React, databaser, JPA, JAX-RS
Det är bra om du dessutom har kunskap om Micro Services
Flytande engelska i tal och skrift
Som person har du lätt för att kommunicera, har en god förmåga att hitta lösningar och ta till dig ny teknologi. Du trivs att jobba i team, och tycker om att hjälpa till att utveckla juniora utvecklare.
Du erbjuds
Ports Group AB är ett innovativt bolag där varje medarbetare är oerhört viktiga för oss. En spännande tjänst i en snabbfotad organisation som hela tiden fortsätter växa och utvecklas i en högaktuell bransch. På Ports Group tror man på att ge sina anställda stor frihet under ansvar och uppmuntrar en dynamisk och tillåtande kultur med mycket samarbete och stora möjligheter för personlig utveckling. Vi månar om våra anställda och erbjuder en flexibel arbetstidslösning, allt för att bibehålla den innovativa företagskulturen. Det finns goda utvecklingsmöjligheter, då vi växer både organiskt och genom förvärv.

Välkommen med din ansökan
I denna rekrytering samarbetar vi med XLNT Search. kom in med din ansökan snarast. Urval sker löpande. Har du frågor angående tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta Ulf Magnusson på telefon 070-569 09 28 eller Ulf@xlnt.se
Om oss
Ports Group är ett snabbväxande och lönsamt SaaS-bolag i segmentet Brand Tech. Ports Group har en unik position på marknaden med 25 års erfarenhet av digitalisering som ICANN-ackrediterad registrar och med ett heltäckande erbjudande inom Brand Protection med mjukvara och tjänster inom Domain Management, Trademark Management samt Cyber Security.
Centralt i erbjudandet är mjukvaruplattformen Ports Management som knyter samman portföljen av innehav för optimal överblick och automatiserad hantering av kundernas varumärkessäkerhet. I plattformen hanteras domäner, varumärkesinnehav och cybersäkerhetsprodukter. Genom ett proaktivt skydd med hjälp av Ports Groups monitoreringstjänster säkras kundens immateriella rättigheter och ensamrätt.

 Location:Contract:Travel:Our values:

The job
   Challengermode is a design-driven company that puts user experience and visual design front and center, making this role a crucial contributor to the overall product development process.
   As a product designer at Challengermode, you'll be joining a cross-functional team of engineers, designers, and product managers. Working in the product team you'll take part in the end-to-end process of creating and iterating on new features and products, maintaining what's already being used, and optimizing every step in the process. Moreover, you'll be heavily involved in the overall design and specification process of new projects together with other designers and product managers. In the future, you'll be able to drive and lead your own design projects and feature implementations.
   Who you are
   Generally speaking, we think that your knowledge in the design process is very good and that you have high attention to detail. Most important is that you're passionate about excellence - just like us!
   What you will do
   
   Design elegant flows & interactions across devices 
   Design pixel-perfect UI and components 
   Work with the product team to define problems and goals 
   Develop and maintain the Challengermode design system together with the design team 
  
  You should have
   
   At least 2+ years experience in tech-driven product design 
   Lo-fi & hi-fi prototyping skills 
   Experience with Sketch, Figma or other product design platforms 
   Experience with Adobe software programs 
   Cross-platform design experience for typical everyday devices 
   Excellent communication skills in both written and spoken English 
  
  These qualifications will help you stand out
   
   Experience creating and designing animations and illustrations 
   Frontend/UI development skills (HTML, CSS, React e.g) 
   Ability to architect efficient and reusable front-end components and abstractions 
  
  How to apply 
  To apply, we'd like to see some of your previous work - a portfolio or a link to your personal website, Dribbble, Behance, or similar. Applicants who do not supply a link or PDF with samples of their work can unfortunately not be considered.
   Why work at Challengermode?
   Challengermode offers you a chance to work on a quickly growing esports platform reaching millions of gamers and tournament organizers globally. At Challengermode, you’ll be a part of a highly ambitious and supportive team on a mission to make esports easily accessible for everyone.
   We believe that it’s important to work hard and reach for the sky but we also believe it’s more fun to do so with friends and people whose skills you can rely on. Everyone on the team is equally adept at working in a team setting as they are working individually. Prestige is nowhere to be found in our company, everyone can talk to everyone - we’re happy to listen. If you think you have what it takes, we want to hear from you!
   What we offer
   
   High performance, skilled and goal-oriented colleagues 
   A fun, friendly, and inclusive work environment 
   Hands-on, freedom-with-responsibility environment 
   Opportunities for personal growth with varied responsibilities and tasks 
   Competitive salary 
   Possibility to acquire stock options (after 6 months employment) 
   Newly refurbished office located in central Stockholm 
   Did we mention that playing computer games is part of the job?
  
   
  
   
  Location: Head office, Stockholm - you should be located in Europe or willing to move to Stockholm
   Employment: Permanent
   Start: ASAP

War On Cancer is a Stockholm-based impact tech start-up that aims to radically improve the mental health of everyone affected by cancer. The first step towards achieving that has been to create the social media app; War On Cancer. As our member community is growing, we’re in search of a digital product designer to play a fundamental role in developing a new web application to make the experience more accessible to a wider audience.
What you love to do:
You have a passion for technology and how it can empower people to improve their lives and the world. You thrive on solving complex problems in simple, intuitive ways. You enjoy working on a new project from start to finish. You have a strong vision and are able to execute it. You value working with a diverse team and can leverage the entire team throughout your design process to develop the best ideas as a group. You are constantly learning and adapting to the ever-changing digital landscape.
In short:
Develop the design and information architecture of our new web platform built on React.
Take an existing concept and adapt it appropriately to leverage a new audience, creating something useful and valuable that fits into our overall War On Cancer ecosystem.
Apply web design best practices and design patterns to maintain a strong level of quality and consistency.
Use human-centered design methodologies and practices to elevate the importance of user-centered design. For example, working with personas and user journeys.
Utilise the power of growth loops and hooks, experimenting with growth hacking.
Work with data and user testing to support design decisions.
Design flows and experiences that are incredibly simple and elegant.
Give and solicit feedback from other designers in order to continually raise our bar for quality.
Help shape the culture of the growing design team at War On Cancer
We are looking for someone who has:
4+ years experience as a digital designer working on responsive web applications.
Experience developing information architecture for complex web applications.
Strategic and purposeful in making design decisions and you do that by integrating user, business, and technical considerations into your design process.
Strong communication skills when collaborating with other members in your team.
Self-motivated and autonomous. Successfully prioritise and execute projects with quality outcomes.
Knowledge of technical constraints and guidelines as they apply to digital platforms across different devices and browsers.
Ability to identify when to optimise for speed and when to seek quality and hone into the details.
Awareness of inclusive design principles, best practices and accessibility standards.
Experience designing for diverse groups of people (international audiences, multi-language localisation, accessibility for people with disabilities, etc.).
Experience with Figma, or other well-known design tools.
Experience contributing to and working with design systems.
Experience working on products built using React is a big plus but not required.
Experience working on social media products is a plus but not required.
You will also:

About Humly
Humly is a digital marketplace for teachers to match exciting job opportunities within schools and nurseries. Humly’s teachers have delivered more than two hundred thousand teaching days to date. But we haven’t finished yet. We are continuously improving and developing our marketplace and expanding our offer into new international markets.
Humly has 60 employees working at our offices in Gothenburg in Sweden and Fareham, Milton Keynes, Manchester and Birmingham in the UK. We have over 3,000 registered teachers and agreements with over 4,000 schools in Sweden and the UK.
Humly has financially strong and active owners, Viking Ventures, and have raised 10 MEUR. We see great potential for the company and have a high ambition.
The Humly platform consists of multiple web clients written in React.js and mobile apps for iOS and Android written in React Native that connect to Ruby on Rails API. Data is permanently stored in the MongoDB database and temporarily cached in Redis.
The infrastructure is run on Amazon Web Services with Infrastructure As Code approach (Terraform).
About the role
Our business is growing quickly in multiple markets. Our marketplace is becoming more and more demanding to maintain and develop. With the extensive need for our platform and exciting opportunities, we need well-working and scalable internal tools to manage all bookings and users.
We are looking for someone that can own all internal tools within our product management organisation. You will be responsible for forming a globally scalable internal platform where our support, teacher success, customer success team and finance team can work in an efficient way.
The tasks included in this role are for example:Communication with all operational teams
Migration of the Humly platform into new businesses that we acquireDocumentationForming and owning a globally scalable internal platform
Service and process design
Defining and prioritizing the internal needs
Communication with the development team
Within the product management organisation, you will work close to the company CPO and our UX and UI designers. The current development organisation works data-driven and agile. We don’t follow any exact agile process model but have designed our own with similar principles. You must prefer being outcome-driven, running small sprints and deploying often to like working here.
What Humly can offer you
At Humly, we help and motivate each other. The team always comes first, and we like to work together. Seeing and working for the whole is essential, as is having fun, setting high goals, and constantly working for improvement. We have high ambitions for both the individual and the company’s development, but at the same time care about being a friendly workplace where everyone has a place.
In addition to a competitive basic salary, Humly also offers:Bonus
Pension scheme
Flexible and modern workstyle
A Viking Venture community of 20+ other companies to learn and share knowledge with
A globally important and exciting solution that creates a lot of good values for our users and all the children and students they meet every day
Qualifications3+ years of product management experience.
Experience in service design is a plus.Experience in managing a recruitment platform, digital marketplace or administration tool is a plus.Speaking Swedish is a plus but not required. The product management team communicates in English.
We also value your personality highly and think it’s important that it aligns with our values and culture at Humly. We believe that you will like working with us if you are communicative, have high integrity, like to laugh and are willing to walk the extra mile to achieve our goals together.
Location
Humly is a hybrid organisation with a team spread over many locations in Sweden, England and Poland. We harness the power of remote work and have a structure to build a solid collaborative culture through physical meetings. For this role, it will be preferable if the candidate is situated in Sweden or the UK as meeting and working with the operational teams there will be crucial. The job includes some travelling between Sweden and the UK. It is not a must that you are located in a city where we have an office.

We are looking for a
Product Manager – Subscription capabilities (m/f/d)
Work from Berlin, Verl, Münster, Amsterdam, Oslo, Stockholm, Tallinn
We are Arvato Financial Solutions
Within the Order To Cash (O2C) business unit at Arvato Financial Solutions (AFS) we are out to build ‘the next’! The next truly revolutionary product that will reshape the subscription economy. Together with industry leaders we have set out to deliver our ambitious product vision that provides consumers with absolute flexibility using and paying for their subscriptions whilst guaranteeing a steady and predictable cashflow for merchants to enable growth.
To set ourselves up for success we are building up a new tech & product organisation that can leverage the knowledge and experience of AFS as a proven market player with the speed and agility of a startup. At the heart of this all sits our unique company culture. Colleagues listen to understand, challenge each other to refine ideas and support one another to achieve personal growth and company success. We fiercely believe in a human-centric approach when it comes to building products. Only this type of focus delivers a truly unique customer journey that people will love.
So what are we looking for?
As the subscription economy is booming so are the different different use cases. Some subscriptions are accompanied with a piece of hardware that needs to be paid for in instalments, other subscriptions require a way for the consumer to add single-use consumptions into their monthly plan. To be effective in today's marketplace you require a high level of flexibility to match your consumers expectations. We want to provide this level of flexibility for our clients. As the Product Manager you'll translate the various subscription challenges into clear product requirements and guide the product team during the various iterations until the right solution is launched. By looking at the subscriptions landscape, following market trends and applying deep listening skills when interacting with clients you drive your roadmap with the objective to allow clients flexibility in making most use of their subscriptions and grow their business.
What will you need?
3+ years experience as a Product Manager, preferably within the subscriptions economy
General understanding of the various types of subscriptions
Understanding of the e-commerce landscape and how merchants, platforms and solution providers interact
Ability to identify and analyse issues, problems or opportunities to achieve desired outcomes, to apply structured thinking and to break down issues to form a logical train of thought that can be followed and understood by others.
Excellent degree of analytical skills, ability to interpret data and trends, diagnose problems, and recommend effective action plans to resolve issues.
Strong teamwork and collaboration skills with the ability to achieve mutually agreeable solutions by staying adaptable, communicating ideas in clear coherent language, and practising active listening.
Creativity and curiosity, a creative problem solver with a deep curiosity about our customers, business and product.
Excellent degree of communication skills, being able to effectively communicate both the strategic vision and specific details to various stakeholders - from senior leadership to individual product team members. Being able to write clear and concise product requirements, status updates, and product results.
Ability to react quickly to new insights always driven by delivering the best possible functionality to our clients and customers.
What do we offer?

So what are we looking for?
As the subscription economy is booming, so are the different use cases and needs. Let’s illustrate that with two examples. Some subscriptions, like car subscriptions, deal in high risks and open up room for different add-ons or pricing options, recurring or usage-based. Not to forget ad hoc costs like parking fines. In other cases, complexity comes from a B2B set-up with intricate billing based on complex tiered rate plans.
To be effective in today's marketplace, you require a high level of flexibility to match your consumers’ expectations. At the same time you need the capability to reliably deal with complex set-ups and growing markets. We want to provide a backbone for our clients that provides this combination of flexibility and reliability. It allows them to focus on their products and services and leave the admin to us.
As the Product Owner, you’ll work closely with all the subscription stakeholders to align the diverse needs towards a satisfying subscription experience for our clients and their customers. You'll translate the various needs into clear business stories and user stories, and guide the involved product teams in developing a seamless E2E solution.
In this volatile and uncertain market, you are geared towards an agile approach. This means iteratively developing new capabilities and then taking the time to listen to the clients and use their feedback to adapt and improve I the next iteration. Comfortably working with tech teams and translating back and forth between tech and business will be as much part of your day as E2E business process design.
To you pre-sales talks are not just about explaining about the benefits your product can offer.
They are very much an opportunity to keep learning about market requirements. They also present a chance to understand the individual needs of the potential client so that you can continually validate that your product really is offering answers to those needs.

3+ years experience in a role bridging the gap between business and IT, preferably as Agile Product Owner.
Outstanding ability to consider the big picture, think E2E and ensure optimization does not have negative impacts in the process somewhere down the line.
Ideally, experience as business process manager with BPMN skills.
Understanding of the e-commerce landscape and how merchants, platforms and solution providers interact.
Ideally 1+ year of experience in the subscription economy — minimum a sound basic understanding of the various types of subscriptions.
Excellent degree of communication skills, being able to effectively communicate both the strategic vision and specific details to various stakeholders — from senior leadership to individual product team members.
Responsible, communicative, assertive and open to intercultural and cross-functional issues.
Desire to constantly gain new insights on client and customer needs paired with the ability to react quickly to feedback, problems and even flops in order to deliver the best possible product to our clients and customers.
Excellent degree of analytical skills, ability to interpret data and trends, diagnose problems, and recommend effective action plans to resolve issues.
Ability to write clear and concise requirements focussing on needs, encouraging the team and leaving room to develop processes and features. At the same time, making use of a high IT affinity to understand tech challenges and ways of working.
Creativity and curiosity. #Listen and #CreateTheNext

We believe that diversity is what makes a good team great, and that diversity of experience and thought create inclusive and successful products. As a global company with colleagues around the world we work in English, even in the Stockholm office where the TriOptima technology department is located.

You are good in designing, developing and executing manual and automated test plans and test cases, and you speak and write unhindered in English.  Nice to haves:

   What's in it for you?  
  As an employee at Winningtemp, you will be part of our purple family 
  With 120+ colleagues in Sweden, Norway, Denmark and England, you will find energetic and loyal colleagues who help each other succeed together. With us, everyone is equally valuable, regardless of gender, ethnicity and background. Diversity is also something we work actively with and something we value. We share happiness every day, not only for our product and the work we do, but also for each other. The commitment of each employee is what really makes us stand out from other companies. You can expect a supportive workplace where everyone works together towards our vision; to forever change how people succeed together!

column1: Rädda liv som junior frontend utvecklare hos CSAM
column4:
Om uppdraget:
En ambulans med påslagna blåljus och sirener navigerar snabbt genom trafiken. Känslan av att du bidragit till ambulansens snabba utryckning är oerhört berikande. Bidraget till samhället genom teknisk utveckling är tydligt när man arbetar med teknik som räddar liv. Vill du arbeta på ett företag som levererar en viktig produkt? Vill du arbeta med utveckling i ett team där laget före jaget är ett tydligt motto? Då har vi rollen för dig!
CSAM är en av Nordens ledande leverantörer av nischade e-hälsolösningar. Företaget fortsätter att utöka sitt team och söker en utvecklare som brinner för innovation, programmering och som vill bidra med nya idéer. Du kommer att arbeta med att implementera ny teknik, ny funktionalitet och vara en del av resan att flytta över företagets arkitektur för att köras på containrar och flytta till cloudet. Din roll blir att arbeta i utvecklingsteamet tillsammans med övriga utvecklare, produktägare och solution arkitekter för att säkerställa att detta implementeras på bästa sätt. Du kommer initialt att arbeta främst med front-end (användargränssnitt) baserat på input från UX-design. Eftersom CSAM har en komplett mjukvarustack är det möjligt att även arbeta med back-end över tid. CSAM ser också till att ha roligt på jobbet – företaget tror att om du har roligt tillsammans med dina kollegor så gör du också ett bra jobb! Kontoret ligger i Göteborg men är öppna för flexibilitet och ”hemmakontor”.
Vi söker dig som:
CSAM söker dig som har en passion för programmering och en vilja att ständigt utveckla din kompetens. Du tror på att samarbete och att dela kunskap mellan kollegor är rätt sätt till välfungerande arbete. Förutom en högskoleexamen inom IT och mjukvara är du en lagspelare med en positiv attityd. Du är lösningsorienterad, ser detaljer och har en ”doer”-mentalitet. CSAM ser gärna att du har erfarenhet av .Net, C och Git. Det är även meriterande om du har erfarenhet av webbteknologier och utvecklingsverktyg i en windowsmiljö. Nya utvecklingsteknologier som WinUI, MAUI, Blazor etc. är meriterande men inget krav. Svenskt medborgarskap krävs samt fulla kunskaper i engelska och svenska i både tal och skrift.
Om företaget:
Cirka 100 personer arbetar på CSAM Public Safety. Majoriteten finns i Göteborg, men företaget har även kontor i Oslo, Karlstad, Stockholm, Valencia (Spanien), Reading (Storbritannien) och Auckland (NZ). CSAM har en komplett mjukvarustack med både back-end och front-end (User Interface) produkter som är integrerade tillsammans i systemlösningen. Produkternas målegenskaper är användarvänlighet, automatisering och enkelhet. CSAMs mjukvarulösningar gör det möjligt för vårdgivare att ta fram den högsta kvalitén och säkerhet mot sina patienter och i sin vård. Hos CSAM får du arbeta i en inspirerande miljö där du får bidra till samhället.
Om anställningen:
Anställningen är på heltid 100 %, det är en direktrekrytering som hanteras av Xamera AB där du blir anställd hos CSAM.
Xamera är karriärföretaget som ger dig möjlighet att ta ställning till de mest intressanta karriärmöjligheterna inom IT/Teknik & Ekonomi. Vårt mål är att hjälpa till att kickstarta karriären för dig som är ingenjör, ekonom eller teknisk profil till spännande möjligheter hos företag inom primärt IT- och tekniksektor.
Startdatum:
Enligt överenskommelse
Allmän information:
Ansök genom länken nedan! Om du har några frågor gällande tjänsten kan du kontakta andrea.zanders@xamera.se Detta uppdrag tillsätts löpande, så skicka iväg din ansökan idag.
Ort: Göteborg
Publiceringsdatum: 1/12 2021
Sista ansökningsdatum: 1/2 2022

Grebban söker nu fler medlemmar till vårt utvecklingsteam, och letar efter dig som vill arbeta med de tekniska detaljerna inom frontendutveckling med fokus på React.js. Du kommer jobba med våra frontendlösningar för e-handel, med både serversiderenderad React och statiska siter genererade med GatsbyJS.
   Vi söker dig som vill jobba med saker såsom t.ex. att:
   
    Optimera JavaScript-kod och React-komponenter för en blixtsnabb användarupplevelse 
   Bygga generella och återanvändbara komponentbibliotek i React 
   Sätta upp och optimera byggsystem i Webpack eller liknande bundlingsystem 
   Implementera både snygg och funktionell design 
  
   Som React / Gatsby-utvecklare krävs det att du har goda kunskaper i:
   
    Grundläggande webbteknologier (HTML/CSS/JavaScript) 
   React.js 
   TypeScript 
  
   Meriterande kunskaper:
   
    Automatiserad testning 
   CSS-in-JS (t.ex. styled-components, styletron, emotion) 
   Redux.js 
   GraphQL 
   Webpack 
   Babel 
   GatsbyJS (och liknande ramverk såsom Next.js) 
   NodeJS 
   Express 
   PHP / Laravel 
   CMS (Storyblok, Wordpress, Prismic, Contentful) 
  
   Egenskaper vi gillar:
   
    Du är stolt över din kunskap och förnyar den dagligen genom att lära av omvärlden. 
   Du är trevlig, flexibel och pragmatisk problemlösare. 
   Du tycker företagskultur är viktigt och uppskattar en social arbetsplats. 
   Extra meriterande är om du har arbetat med e-handelslösningar tidigare, eller på webbyråer som arbetar med konsumentinriktade webbupplevelser. 
   Hellre rätt drivkraft och talang än formella meriter eller utbildningar. 
  
   Vad vi erbjuder:
   
    Att vara med och utveckla i utmanande och roliga projekt, med varumärken du är stolt över att arbeta med. 
   Bra förmåner som t.ex. lönejustering två gånger per år, tjänstepension, friskvårdsbidrag, brusreducerande hörlurar, modern arbetsstation (valfritt pc/mac), upp till halvtid remote och mer än välfyllda kylskåp/snackshyllor- och maxade AWs. 
   Ett snabbfotat, socialt och roligt team att arbeta med, med både höga ambitioner och många att lära sig av 
   Modernt arbetssätt med tribe-upplägg, där man arbetar i ett autonomt team på 5-10 personer och 2-veckorssprintar, vilket skapar både förutsägbarhet och gör det enkelt att trivas 
   Både projekt och löpande vidareutveckling i kombination, dvs dels nyprojekt med spännande nya utmaningar, dels vidareutveckling i ett produkt-tänk för optimering 
   Kompetensutveckling både internt och externt via t.ex. konferenser, även t.ex. fokusgrupper internt inom områden som pagespeed, tracking, design mfl 
   Högt i tak och stor möjlighet till att både utvecklas och göra karriär, både som specialist och som ledare 
  
   Vem ska söka och ansökningsprocess:
   
    Grebban söker både juniora, mid-level och seniora utvecklare. Minimum 1 års erfarenhet efter utbildning (är du väldigt talangfull och duktig kan vi göra exceptions). 
   Vi rekryterar löpande både till Göteborg och Stockholm (generell remote policy på Grebban är upp till halvtid remote, så sökande i närliggande städer eller ytterområden välkomnas) 
   Observera att vi tillämpar kodtest på sökande (kodtestet är ej under tidspress). 
   För seniora (5+) sökande är full-time remote också ett alternativ. 
  
   Varmt välkommen med din ansökan!
   Om Grebban:
   Grebban är en av Sveriges ledande och mest snabbväxande e-handelsbyråer, som bara sedan coronapandemin startade mer än dubblat personalstyrkan. Vi arbetar med några av Skandinaviens hetaste varumärken och hjälper de affärsutveckla med hjälp av strategi, kod och design. Som e-handelsspecialister hjälper vi våra kunder med en av deras absolut viktigaste försäljningskanaler med t.ex. varumärkesidentitet, tillväxtstrategier, grafisk design, UX och digital design, systemarkitektur och att bygga deras e-handelslösningar. Vi är headless-experter och arbetar främst med plattformar som Centra Commerce, Storm Commerce och Shopify Plus. Några av Grebbans kunder är Björn Borg, iDeal of Sweden, Craft Sportswear, Hestra, NN07, RoyalDesign, Orrefors, Kosta Boda och Sandqvist.

About Mindler
Mindler was founded in 2018 by two psychologists and one doctor, who had a vision to enable a world with better mental health. Thanks to our hard-working tech team, who have developed our app and iCBT programs; Mindler has become known as the science driven mind leading industry changer.
We are now looking for a React Native Developer to join our expanding tech function. Our team is currently split into five sub-teams - all with different core responsibilities relating to the app, infrastructure, data, integration and features of our product.
The role:

As a React Native Developer you will be part of our Stockholm-based tech team. You will be a part of developing a world-class product, and our product makes a real difference in people’s lives. You will be making sure that people who would like to meet a psychologist via our app can do so fast and easy.
Stack:

Our stack is near-exclusively JavaScript/TypeScript, with React (both Native and Web) with a Redux architecture. Backend is mainly written in Node.js running on a mix of AWS Lambda, DynamoDB and MySQL. Our infrastructure runs completely on AWS.
What would you be working with?
Build the frontend of our App as we grow our user base and continue to add new features.
You will help us find solutions to make iCBT (cognitive behavioral therapy) more effective and accessible for everyone.
Ensuring quality and stability during implementation and being responsible for releases of our app.
Ensure creating value and lasting impressions for all our patients.
Be at the forefront of our international expansion.
Who are you?
Preferably 1-2 years of experience working with React Native.
Highly proficient in Javascript with an interest in mobile development.
Strong interest in UX-design and frontend development.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English.
It’s a plus if you have experience in iOS/Android development.
What can we offer?
If we are a good match for each other - we will offer you a role that gives you a lot of freedom (we highly value a hybrid remote-friendly setup), and the chance to join a well-funded company with the ambition to play an important role in the global market of digital mental health care. Since we are just in the beginning of our growth journey, you will play an important part in influencing how we work together and how we make the most impact to help our customers and further improve mental health in the society.

We are looking forward to hearing from you!
–-
Mindler is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will be considered for employment without regard to gender, gender identity or expression, national origin, religion or other beliefs, disability, sexual orientation or age.

You would get the chance to develop great software in a fast-moving environment in close connection to our global clients and their needs. Together we'll improve our product to meet increasing demands while focusing on scalability and quality. You will also get a chance to experiment with new technology and explore what solutions are most suitable for solving real-world problems. You would join a dynamic team eager to take on new challenges and are passionate about what they do.

We are looking to hire great people, who are passionate about using their talents to generate success. We are growing and looking for a skilled react native developer who has a passion for games.
You will be part of the development team and work together with other developers to build and maintain our platform. You will be part of the whole development life-cycle; Design, Develop, Test, Release and Maintain.

Develop new app features

Mentor and collaborate with other team members and stakeholders

column1: React Native developer for self-driving EV
column4:
About the opportunity:
Are you a functional JavaScript nerd and would like to work with the future of transport?
Does working with self-driving electric vehicles excite you?
We all know that we need more environmentally friendly, reliable and comfortable ways to move around. Improved public transport services, sharing platforms and self-driving car services from the biggest tech companies shape the future of transport.
You will be part of a cross-functional team that develops an app and a fleet management system. Your focus will be the app development but there is a separate UX team that will specify the UI.
Your profile should include the following:

Passionate about functional programming in JavaScript
If someone is talking about first-class functions, recursion, pipelines, currying, functors, and monads your first instinct should not be to run away...
Worked with functional programming and TypeScript
React Native both iOS and Android productions (please provide links to App Store and Google Play
Work experience in using AWS back-end
M.Sc or B.Sc. Computer Science or equivalent
You should have excellent communication skills even if the topic is not FP
We believe that you like technical writing; maybe you have a blog about stuff you find interesting
It would help if you liked to work in agile teams
We believe that you have at least three years of work experience
Location:
Multiple locations in Sweden.
Relocation/moving to Sweden:
We welcome applicants both from Sweden and outside of Sweden. If you are applying from outside of Sweden or from another city in Sweden, we will help you with the relocation.
About Insert Talent
At Insert Talent, we put your interest and career first. We have a transparent set-up where you are first permanently employed by Insert Talent as a consultant, usually 6-12 months. After that period you will have the option to join our client company as a permanent employee.
Please note that it is an option, meaning it's up to you and the client to find an agreement after the initial consultancy period. We are always transparent regarding salary expectations and benefits, which simplifies reaching an agreement with the client company.
If you decide not to join the client company for some reason, it is our responsibility to find you a new assignment that is a better match. Our success rate at finding a great match is very high, and it is our goal that you become permanently employed by our client company.
The model is appreciated both by our candidates and our clients.
http://www.inserttalent.com/

column1: React Native Developer to Digital Sales Channels
column4: Do you have a passion for development and want to be a part of a creative journey together with us?This might be the perfect next step in your career!About usATG has some of Sweden’s biggest- and fastest-growing digital products, with hundreds of thousands of users every week. Together, we are working to achieve our goal of creating the world’s best gaming experience.ATG believes strongly in sustainable and fun gaming!We value Drive, Respect and Ownership in everything we do. We believe that with ambition, the right mindset, and eagerness to help achieve common goals that we will succeed in becoming the long-term partner for our customers.We develop premium Horse games, Sports games and Casino. We continuously improve to deliver a great user experience in terms of accessibility, intuitive usage of the digital platforms/webpages and friction-free services overall.AND we certainly believe in having fun together, voicing our ideas and collaboration to work towards the bigger values.Want to join the team?About me - Håkan Sandström, hiring managerI have been working at ATG for about 2 years as a manager for the Digital Sales Channel section. I see myself more as a coach than a manager and want to create the best conditions for you as a developer to grow here at ATG. If you want to work at a company where innovation and exploring new techniques are highly valued, then you should come and be a part of ATG and my team.During my spare time I’m engaged in Swedish Sea Rescue Society where I’m a volunteer helping those in need with towing and medical care if needed.Looking forward to meeting you on an interview!Skills & RequirementsWho are you?We are looking for a senior React Native app developer who has several years’ experience in app development and has a customer centric perspective. You like to build smart and engaging functionalities in your apps and are always looking for lifting the quality in everything you do. Our current apps at ATG for iOS and Android are built using React Native, so relevant experience in javascript and/or typescript programming languages are a must to succeed in this role! We also use redux and redux-saga for managing state in our app. Future development can also include usage of GraphQL, together with apollo-client.Furthermore, you are also a developer who is passionate about front-end design and you are keeping up with current and future trends in your field of work.We believe that you are a driven person who appreciates collaboration in- and cross-team to achieve common goals. Sharing knowledge is a no-brainer for you, and you thrive in a mentoring position.You are likely to have a university degree in computer science or similar, however you may also have enough talent to challenge experience.We speak many languages, but mainly use Swedish.About recruitment process: Please note that all applications should go through our recruitment portal, so please apply accordingly. Personality and code tests and background checks are a part of the recruitment process. We apply 6 months probation period on all roles at ATG.We have made our media choice for recruitment and therefore avoid contact with advertisers or sellers of other recruitment services.Visa sponsorship and support with relocationOccupational pensionWork -life balance30 days of paid vacation per yearPersonal trainer and gym facilities at the officeJoin the game!Help us create the world’s best gaming experience We are the gaming company looking to create the best gaming experience there is. Games, sport, excitement and experiences are our passion. Our many well-known products see us inviting customers worldwide to a world-class gaming experience.We want to be the creative hub that takes the industry into the future, which is why we are always encouraging each other to think on new lines and try out new things. We are engaged in a digital transformation, working with modern solutions in tech.Fired by a combination of curiosity, a clear forward-looking direction, and with the well-being of colleagues, customers and all of Sweden’s trotting and thoroughbred horses close to our hearts, we are building on what will soon be 50 years of history and driving the industry on into the future. Our different backgrounds, experiences and personalities mean we are growing together. At ATG, everyone is expected to work actively to take the company to new levels, drawing on their role.We take gaming seriously. And we take our customers’ expectations and well-being seriously too, as well as your personal development and health.Job Type: Full-time

column1: React Native Developer to Digital Sales Channels
column4: About recruitment process:

Refunder letar just nu efter en ny apputvecklare som kan stärka upp deras utvecklingsteam.
Vi söker dig som:

gärna jobbar brett med både app och webb.
har utvecklat några appar i React Native.
har jobbat med JS-ramverk som t. ex Vue JS.
har erfarenhet av ett eller flera MVC-ramverk. Vi jobbar t. ex med Laravel och Codeigniter.
har ett öga för snygg design och jobbar gärna med UX/UI.
gärna är med och driver projekt från idé till slutprodukt.
Du kommer in som en nyckelspelare i ett mindre team och får ta lead på deras app och driva den framåt. Tillsammans ansvarar ni för den övergripande arkitekturen för alla deras webbapplikationer. De testar gärna nya features och strävar efter att fatta beslut snabbt för att minimera tiden från idé till lansering.
Om Refunder
De är störst i Sverige och näst störst i Polen. De hjälper över 700.000 shoppingglada medlemmar att handla smartare genom att erbjuda cashback i över 1000 butiker. De har över 14.000 recensioner på Trustpilot med ett mycket bra betyg på 9/10. Välkommen in i Refunder-familjen!

What's in it for you?
Be part of building a Swedish neobank aiming to improve everyone’s financial life, by offering relevant and personalized banking services built on intelligence.
We use the latest technology to develop safe, smart, and user-friendly products for our customers. They are the sole reason why we do what we do. We are a product company where technology is the driver to create smarter banking products. On a daily basis, we solve advanced challenges using cloud-based solutions, which we know have a real impact on the products and end-users. Over 50% of our people are working within tech.
The scope of your role
Challenging an entire industry and building a great company requires a lot of things. Guts, dedication, big visions, a mentality to get things done. Yet, there’s one thing that is more important than all of this – brilliant people. Just like yourself.
As our React Native Engineer, you will take part in the process of overseeing the development of modern financial applications. You will develop modern banking applications for web, Android and iOS.
You will have a great impact on our products by working closely together with the business and our customers. We offer you an amazing workplace with a great work environment of brilliant and humble colleagues. You will learn tons of stuff, get inspired, and most likely feel challenged. We are a flat organization looking for people who are better than ourselves (and we're damn brilliant). Northmill is a long-term player with organic growth and profitability since day one.
Who are you?
You are a creative and curious person with a genuine interest in software development. Like us, you also love to write high-quality code and do not hesitate to share your thoughts on various solutions. Or inform about any kind of problem that might occur. As you might have understood by now, we're looking for a team player, because there's no I in Team. Since we are a multicultural neobank, English is the required language (except React Native).
You bring:
Experience in creating web/desktop applications
Experience in developing applications using React Native
Experience in React.js
Experience in JavaScript and TypeScript
Willingness and interest to collaborate and work in a team
Experience with software engineering best practices (code reviews, continuous integration, continuous deployment, testing)
Familiar with Web services/web API
It would be amazing if you have:
Experience in developing Android and/or iOS applications
Exposure to Agile development methodologies
A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or a related field
What we offer you:
You will get a bunch of friendly, driven and nerdy colleagues! It's a big part of our success story. In addition to endless interest in innovative technologies, consumer credits, IT security, and data, we are experts in everything from football, dogs, Nintendo, interior design, technology and more. You will also enjoy fun stuff like daily breakfasts, education forums and social events in our brand new office with an astonishing view over Stockholm city.
Have we caught your interest?
We encourage you to apply as soon as possible, as we go through the applications continuously.

Are you an experienced React Native Developer with a strong passion for tech? Do you want to contribute to the cryptocurrency revolution? Then join Safello, Sweden’s leading crypto brokerage on it’s exciting journey to transform the financial infrastructure!
The mission of your role
Safello is on a journey to transform the financial infrastructure for good. In an ambitious pursuit like this, we need ambitious talent to help us get there. As React Native Lead Developer you will, with your communicative approach, play an important role in our organization while working in a leading position in the development team, taking the lead on app development at Safello.
With an innovative and self-starter mindset you will write code, tests and monitor the performance of the application on old and new phones.
You will report to the CPO and be based in Stockholm, our office is located centrally at WeWork. However, we are flexible remote workers and there is no mandatory office time.
About you
In order to succeed in the role we believe that you have..

React Native experience, understanding of the complete development process.
Passion for tech, an eye for detail and a love for new and exciting technologies.
Developed multiple mobile apps and worked in a team with UI/UX designers and backend specialists.

As we are a Crypto company, any experience or interest in blockchain technology and cryptocurrency infrastructures is highly appreciated.
What we offer
We offer flexibility, a competitive salary and a benefit package. Our office is located centrally in Stockholm, but we are all flexible remote workers. Being part of Safello means being on a growth journey which offers great career opportunities and the possibility to influence the future of financial systems.
About Safello
Founded in 2013 and regulated by Finansinspektionen, Safello is the safe and simple Cryptocurrency exchange for Swedish customers. Safello offers instant buying and selling and integrates several advanced features to deliver the full benefits of banking and blockchain technology to a mass of users. Read more on https://safello.com/.
To apply
Send in your application as soon as possible, but no later than 15th of April. The recruitment process is ongoing and we will review applications and conduct interviews continuously. Observe that the position may be filled before last application date.

About Challengermode
   Challengermode was founded in 2014 with the mission to make esports truly accessible. Today, we're running a platform that provides the fundamental online esports infrastructure to all the key stakeholders in the industry including players, organizers, and game developers. It's becoming the place for regular gamers to congregate, practice, or compete in esports. Our best-in-class tech automates complex competition infrastructure through game integrations and allows gamers to easily play in competitions on any device or console while enabling community building and monetization at scale for organizers of all kinds.
  
   About the team
   The mobile gaming market is ever-growing and Challengermode is putting competitive gaming into the hands of mobile gamers. The mobile app team is rethinking the Challengermode experience to provide the most intuitive and smooth experience for our mobile audience across the globe.
   As part of this team, you'll be designing, building, releasing, and iterating on an app that lets you compete in your favorite mobile games on your daily commute and serves as the perfect companion app to have Challengermode at your fingertips - anytime and anywhere.
  
   What you'll do
   
   Design, build and maintain high-performance, reusable, and reliable React Native code. 
   Work in close collaboration with the design team to create an extremely intuitive and engaging UI. 
   Create excellent user experiences in all parts of the app - always. 
   Set up and continuously improve the build pipeline and release processes. 
   Publish and maintain the app on the App Store and Play Store. 
   Track, discuss, and implement user feedback from the app stores and reviews. 
   In collaboration with the mobile, product, and leadership teams, define, track, and push towards success metrics that contribute directly to the company's overall goals and strategy.
  
  
   Who you are
   You have worked with React Native apps in the past and have the scars and experiences to show for it (i.e. a proven track record). You’ll receive a lot of responsibility but also a lot of freedom. You should be someone who enjoys having a lot of autonomy and ownership as you will be wholly trusted to do your job - just like you can rely on all your teammates to do theirs.
   
   3+ years of experience building mobile apps, preferably with React Native or similar cross-platform frameworks. 
   You have experience in publishing and maintaining apps on the App Store and Play Store. 
   You have a strong product sense and a habit to use this to inform technical decisions. 
   You have a Computer Science (or equivalent) degree - or the experience to make up for that. 
   You're an excellent communicator in both spoken and written language. 
   You're passionate about esports and gaming.
  
  
   These qualifications will help you stand out
   
   Experience with native mobile app development for iOS and/or Android. 
   Experience building responsive and Progressive Web Apps (PWA).
  
  
   Why work at Challengermode?
   Challengermode offers you a chance to work on a quickly growing esports platform reaching millions of gamers and tournament organizers globally. At Challengermode, you’ll be a part of a highly ambitious and supportive team on a mission to make esports easily accessible for everyone.
   We believe that it’s important to work hard and reach for the sky but we also believe it’s more fun to do so with friends and people whose skills you can rely on. Everyone on the team is equally adept at working in a team setting as they are working individually. Prestige is nowhere to be found in our company, everyone can talk to everyone - we’re happy to listen. If you think you have what it takes, we want to hear from you!
  
   What we offer
   
   High performance, skilled and goal-oriented colleagues 
   A fun, friendly, and inclusive work environment 
   Hands-on, freedom-with-responsibility environment 
   Opportunities for personal growth with varied responsibilities and tasks 
   Competitive salary 
   Possibility to acquire stock options (after 6 months employment) 
   Newly refurbished office located in central Stockholm 
   Did we mention that playing video games is part of the job?
  
  
   Location: Head office, Stockholm. You should be located in or willing to move to Stockholm.
   Employment: Permanent
   Start: ASAP

Vi på techlove söker utvecklare till vår familj!
Vi är ett Stockholmsbaserat konsultföretag med en stark entreprenörsanda som söker en utvecklare med erfarenhet av React, React Native och node.js till uppdrag hos våra kunder.
Som utvecklare hos techlove erbjuds du ett varierande arbete med olika typer av uppdrag som omfattar allt från enklare webbplatser till avancerade system och applikationer ute på plats hos våra olika kunder.
En förutsättning för vår framgång är vår förmåga att bygga, utveckla och leda konsulter och utvecklingsgrupper. Vi är ett fokuserat team som delar ambitionen att utvecklas tillsammans, både individuellt och som företag.
Vad kommer du att få göra?

Jobba med utveckling av tjänster och applikationer, i både back- och frontend.
Vara med att ta fram nya produkter och tjänster.
Säkerställa att kod, test och dokumentation håller hög kvalitet.
Ständigt leta efter nya lösningar om du stöter på patrull.
Ha kul på jobbet.

Person före papper
För att bli en del i vår familj ser vi att du är driven, vågar säga vad du tycker och inte är rädd för att ta egna initiativ. Vi har högt i tak och allas åsikter tas på allvar.
I dessa pandemitider bedrivs mycket av arbetet på distans men enstaka kundbesök kan krävas. Det går också bra att sitta i våra lokaler om man så önskar.
Uppdragen är olika men ofta är det fria arbetstider vilket innebär att du i stor mån kan bestämma själv när och var du vill arbeta - så länge du klarar av dina arbetsuppgifter. Vi tror därför att du är ansvarstagande, strukturerad och trivs med att planera din egen tid. Då våra projekt ofta har hög teknisk grad krävs tidigare erfarenhet från utveckling samt en kunskap att förstå webb från ett användarperspektiv. Därför ser vi gärna att du:

Har 3+ år erfarenhet av
React, React Native
Node.js
Pratar flytande svenska eller engelska
Har erfarenhet av att bygga kundrelationer
Har god kommunikation, både i skrift och tal på svenska eller engelska
Är en social kameleont och van vid många kontaktytor
Tycker om att arbeta i team

Vårt nätverk sträcker sig från spännande uppstickare och startups till svenska stoltheter som Klarna, Tele 2 och Spotify.
Kompetens, öppenhet, lekfullhet
Vi står för våra ledord och tror att både anställd och kund mår bäst om vi följer dessa.
Gemenskap
För oss är det viktigt att alla våra medarbetare trivs på jobbet och mår bra. Vi vill att alla ska känna den gemenskap vi har byggt upp.
Därför kan du förvänta dig:
Flexibla och schyssta anställningsvillkor
Roliga events och happenings med techlove-familjen
Utveckling både som individ, team och företag
TV-spel med kollegorna
Att få vara med på en spännande expansions-resa

Tror du att du skulle passa i techlovefamiljen? Skicka in en ansökan till jobb@techlove.se så hör vi av oss inom kort.
Vi ser fram emot din ansökan!

With more than 800 employees, $200M ARR in 2021, 1,300+ clients, and rapid year-over-year growth, Recorded Future is the world's largest intelligence company!
React Specialist (Göteborg, Sweden)

Recorded Future's Security Intelligence Solutions are used by our clients to stay on top of threats to their business. In our tools they can create alerts or search, analyze and process the cyber security information we are providing. Rest Services and Web Sockets

Delorean är en digital byrå med stark teamkänsla där du får vara med och påverka både din egen arbetssituation och företaget. Vi tror på att lära oss tillsammans och utvecklas med nya tekniker som kommer. Vi jobbar bland annat med kunder som Svenska Institutet, 7-Eleven, Pressbyrån och Nationalmuseum.
Om tjänsten
Vi söker nu frontend-utvecklare med erfarenhet av React.

Arbetsuppgifterna varierar mycket. Vi jobbar med flera lite större utvecklingsprojekt som ofta har en digital affär. Men vi skapar även kundspecifika verktyg, andra CMS-baserade lösningar, datadrivna prestandaförbättringar med mer.
Vi värdesätter en glad personlighet och ett stort intresse för webbutveckling. Ägnar du dessutom en del av din fritid till att förbättra din kompetens och undersöka nya ramverk och tekniker har vi mycket gemensamt.
Vår teknikfilosofi är att använda rätt verktyg till det utmaningen kräver. Därför är vi inte rädda att både testa och utvärdera nya tekniker, samt att implementera dessa i skarpa projekt. Vi undviker att välja verktyg enbart på popularitet eller gammal vana.
De flesta av våra projekt är headless i React där det finns en eller flera backends i Node, PHP eller .Net
Det som är viktigt för oss är inte att du är fullärd, utan att du har en positiv attityd och ett intresse för att lära dig nya saker.
(Under coronatider så arbetar vi majoriteten av tiden hemifrån - med tillgång till kontoret så mycket man vill)


Din roll i teamet
Programmera frontend-lösningar i våra webbprojekt.
Ansvara för och driva olika webbprojekt.
Ta fram tekniska strategier och koncept med vårt team av utvecklare, UX:are och projektledare.
Ha kundkontakt och svara på frågor relaterade till projekten.
Ha code reviews med utvecklingsteamet.
Kommunicera i tal och skrift på både svenska och engelska.
Vi tror du har erfarenhet av
JavaScript-frameworks så som React, Angular, Vue
HTML, CSS och JavaScript.
Versionshantering i GIT.
Att utveckla integrationer och kopplingar till andra system via API:er.

Vi är kollektivanslutna

Du får tjänstepension
En vacker dag går du i pension. Som kollektivanslutet företag betalar vi in till din tjänstepension från att du fyllt 25 år.
Du får friskvårdsbidrag
Alla som jobbar hos oss ska få de bästa förutsättningarna för att hålla sig friska och krya. Vi erbjuder bidrag på 3000 kr per år som du kan använda till din personliga träning.
Kompetensutveckling och delaktighet
Vi har regelbundna medarbetarsamtal samt tar fram individuella utvecklingsplaner. Och vi vill att våra medarbetare är med och påverkar både arbetsplats och hur vi arbetar.
Välkommen att skicka in din ansökan!

About Insert Talent
At Insert Talent, we put your interest and career first. We have a transparent set-up where you are first permanently employed by Insert Talent as a consultant, usually 6-12 months. After that period you will have the option to join our client company as a permanent employee.
Please note that it is an option, meaning it's up to you and the client to find an agreement after the initial consultancy period. We are always transparent regarding salary expectations and benefits, which simplifies reaching an agreement with the client company.

Är du webbutvecklare med minst tre års erfarenhet, älskar Javascript, har full koll på React och vill jobba med headless CMS? Då har vi ett utmärkt jobb för dig.

Vad vi gör
På Triggerfish får du möjlighet att jobba med kunder som gör världen lite bättre, exempelvis Naturskyddsföreningen, Diakonia eller Scouterna. Idag består mer än 20% av vår totala omsättning från den typen av organisationer. Vi jobbar i kundteam med alla kompetenser du behöver och nära och engagerat med ett mindre antal kunder. Vi växer i takt med våra kunder och medarbetares vilja att utvecklar och erbjuder även appar, intranät, webbshoppar och mängder av flera digitala lösningar.
Vem är du?
På Triggerfish blir du en del i en grupp med otroligt duktiga och mångfacetterade kollegor. Vi vill att du är nyfiken och lika mycket självgående som du är en lagspelare. Du är en skicklig och noggrann utvecklare som gillar Javascript och har erfarenhet av React. Vi vill gärna att du delar vår idé om att hög kvalité samt långsiktiga och bra lösningar som faktiskt gör nytta för våra kunder är bland det viktigaste som finns.

Vi vill att du har minst tre års erfarenhet av webbutveckling och Javascript och att du kan WordPress. Dessutom önskar vi att du har erfarenhet av att arbeta med headless-projekt, gärna med WordPress som CMS. I de flesta av våra headless-projekt jobbar vi med Next.js som frontend-framework för den publika webben. Är du van att jobba med olika typer av API:er så är det ett garanterat plus i kanten.

Vi gillar att du är med och bidrar till vårt tighta team. Vi lägger mycket tid på att förbättra vår setup, testa nya grejer och hitta nya verktyg som utmanar och utvecklar oss.

Vi lägger stor vikt vid personlighet och egenskaper utöver kompetens. Du behöver inte kunna allt vi nämner här men vi hoppas du vill lära dig mycket av det (och annat också).
Förmåner som gör skillnad
Vi har en go och omtänksam stämning på Triggerfish. Vi gillar att jobba ihop på kontoret men det går givetvis bra att köra hemifrån. Dessutom får du:

5 000:- i friskvårdsbidrag
30 dagars semester
Minst en resa varje år till en spännande plats
Seniort projektledarteam
Kreativa och prestigelösa medarbetare
Utbildningar som breddar kunskaper och personlig utveckling
Ofta frukost, fika och firande
Roliga aktiviteter efter arbetstid
Gemensamma träningspass
Alltid ett JA på ledighetsansökan
Schyssta och bra ersättningsnivåer, tjänstepension m.m

Det går finfint att jobba på distans eller från vårt kontor, du bestämmer.

The role

As Regulatory Compliance Counsel you will be part of the Global Kambi Legal Team and together ensure that the company meets all the applicable regulatory requirements, improves internal compliance procedures, and maintains a robust internal audit function. You will work closely with Technical, Product, Sportsbook Operations and Business Development teams to identify areas of the business where there is a risk of non-compliance and help develop processes, policies, and procedures to reduce the risk.

You will be based in our Stockholm office and will be working in a vibrant environment interacting with people from different nationalities and diverse background.

Key Responsibilities:

Review and understand Kambi’s gaming license requirements in multiple jurisdictions to ensure they are being met in full.
Provide expert advice on specific and complex gaming matters in countries of interest.
Examine and identify the risk areas across the business and mitigate risks ensuring full compliance with all applicable regulations, legislation, company policies and best practice.
Support teams in reviewing and creating processes as well as drafting and updating relevant documents and policies in the area of AML/CFT as well other compliance areas.
Contribute to robust and effective compliance controls within the organization, and develop a culture of compliance through the business.
Assist in the gathering of internal information and requirements in response to regulatory requests.
Prepare, produce, write, review, keep track of, and ensure consistency of regular reporting submitted by/to gaming authorities.
Support internal investigation of compliance issues, including internal audits of an ISMS that conforms to ISO 27001.

Your skills and experience:

Qualified Lawyer with at least 1 years of post-qualification of relevant experience in a compliance/legal environment (preferably working in highly regulated sectors and/or with AML compliance topics).
Experience in the i-Gaming industry and international environment would be considered an asset.
Literate and fluent in English, other European languages also useful.
High levels of initiative, pragmatism, organization, interpersonal skills and common sense.
Curiosity with a keenness to innovate, improve processes and drive efficiencies.
You should thrive in a dynamic work environment, be flexible and adaptable to change.
You have the ability to work of own initiative, manage your own tasks, take ownership and support colleagues when needed.
Inspire respect and confidence with internal and external stakeholders.

 You'll Like Kambi If You

Thrive in a relaxed but high-paced work environment
Like taking active ownership and initiative
Have high expectations of yourself and your peers

What’s in it for you?

Opportunity to work in a successful and fast-growing company
A fun and flexible working culture
Ability to directly influence your and your teams’ work environment and processes
International work environment

If you want to be part of the Global Kambi Legal Team, please apply with a cover letter and your CV.
