About Kambi

Kambi Group plc is a leading B2B provider of premium sports betting services to licensed gaming operators. Our services provide an end-to-end solution for operators wanting to launch a standalone Sportsbook or bolster their existing offering with an innovative sports betting product. From front-end user interface to customer intelligence, risk management and odds compiling, all built on our in-house developed software, we strive to deliver the ultimate service and solution to our partners.

Our vision is to create the world’s leading sports betting experiences, together with our partners.

With offices in Malta (HQ), Bucharest, London, Manila, Sydney, Uppsala and Stockholm and together with over 1000 passionate and highly skilled people; Kambi live and breathe sports betting. It is in everything we do. From delivering a premium service to our operators, to creating an entertaining experience for the end user; we are unwavering in our mission to create the worlds’ leading sports betting experience.

column1: Remote Javascript developer - React Native developer
column4:
About DigitalTolk
DigitalTolk is an organisation and company that works to make an impact. Our purpose is to give a voice to those who don’t speak the local language; we arrange translators so that patients can get medical treatments in their new country and communicate with doctors. We arrange translators for crime victims so that they can get justice. Our job is to arrange interpreters through our platform for our customers.
Our end customers are hospitals, courts/lawyers, and municipalities who communicate with refugees and other people in need.
Our company purpose is to use technology to make the world a better place. And we’re currently hiring developers to join us on this journey!
We are a company based in Sweden with developers in all parts of the planet!
Job Description
We are looking for a highly skilled ReactNative/mobile Developer/reactjs to collaborate with a team of designers and developers to create mobile and responsive web applications, platforms and SPA for our own products (some of which are customer facing, others which are for internal use). You will be responsible for developing the user and admin side of the web application and enhancing user experience through high level transitions and animations. The ideal candidate has strong communication skills and ability to create testable, reusable, and scalable code.
Responsibilities
Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create an innovative website that draws the user’s attention and interest.
Create reusable, effective, and scalable JavaScript code
Implement front-end components with ReactNative/react framework
Translate the client’s technical requirements into code
Test and update web application so that it can be used on all web browsers
Develop websites which are able to update in realtime
Skills and Qualifications required
English language proficiency
4+ years of professional experience in Vue.js and object orientated programming
Highly proficient in JavaScript, modern JavaScript, HTML, CSS
Highly proficient in Vue.js framework
Proficient in using Git as a control system
Using stack for updating sites in real time such as pusher, socket.io, or firebase
Having experience with other javascript frameworks such as React, and ReactNative is necessary for the role
Having experience writing APIs with Laravel would be beneficial (but absolutely not mandatory for this role)

Tipser is joining forces with Bolt, the company behind the best online checkout experience in the world and our team couldn’t be more excited about the journey we’re about to embark on together!
Bolt is fundamentally reimagining e-commerce identity by building a global identity layer that allows shoppers to have seamless, personalised, and rewarding experiences across any retailer with one account. We’re starting with one-click checkout but plan to expand what our accounts products can do for both shoppers and retailers.
The Bolt commerce solution expands into places where commerce has never been seen as native before. At Bolt, we believe e-commerce should not be tied to any specific place, app, or website. We make any product in the world buyable on any digital surface, with the most streamlined user experience possible. Bolt believes that anyone should be able to buy anything from anywhere with one click - Commerce Everywhere.
About Bolt:
Bolt is on a mission to democratize commerce by setting a new standard for buying and selling online. Bolt-powered experiences level the commerce playing field to help retailers of all sizes sell more, grow faster, and be in control of their own destiny.
We are driven by the challenge of creating something utterly unique, and by the thrill of delivering meaningful impact to the world. Come join the adventure today!
The Role:
Bolt is entering a phase of scale where the rate of incoming customers is expected to increase significantly. In order to ensure that we can deliver on this incoming volume, the process of onboarding new customers needs to be optimized for speed and simplicity while ensuring an appropriate level of service.
The Sales Engineer’s primary responsibility is to optimize the technical onboarding lifecycle, from sales to maintenance. Bolt foresees that in the future, 90%+ of incoming customers must be technically self-serviced. The Sales Engineer team is the organ that will drive Bolt towards that goal.
This is a full-time role based in our Stockholm office.
As a Sales Engineer, you will:

Lead in all technical aspects of the sales process and answer technical questions from prospects and clients regarding Bolt technology, features, solutions, and applications
Make technical implementation as smooth as possible for the client. This involves meeting the client to set the expectations ahead of implementation, advising and recommending them around any uncertainties they may have and acting as a technical point of contact towards that client until the scope has been achieved
Become a trusted advisor for the client and help define their integration strategy
Work together with Bolt's Client Success team to plan and ensure that clients' maintenance needs are met in an orderly fashion which does not sacrifice the quality of service towards new clients
Understand the needs of incoming publishers, and feed the relevant product owners with recommendations/requirements on how to improve the technology.
Partner directly with global product management teams to prioritize solutions impacting client adoption
Become a technical and functional internal expert of our technology, developing a deep understanding of our solution.
Be responsible for completion of technical requirements within RFI/RFPs
Create documentation and other material such as FAQ’s or technical decks for incoming clients.
Improving existing documentation, such as the developer documentation and the Bolt Knowledge Base.
We think that you have:

A university degree in Computer Science or other relevant field
1 - 2 years of professional experience solutions engineering or in a technical customer facing role
Proven ability to present in depth technical knowledge in a commercial and sales-driven setting
A service oriented mindset, are customer driven, and able to deliver high quality work without a lot of oversight
An analytical mind. You know how to collect data and how to visualize it
Proven knowledge of and working experience in HTML, CSS, and Javascript
Knowledge of React and its ecosystem
Experience working within a CMS
An understanding of web standards, best practices, browser features, limitations and quirks
Experience with APIs - how they work and how they talk

A big plus if you have:

Basic UI knowledge
An understanding of media and marketplaces and preferably e-commerce
Experience working in a scale up environment
A problem solving mindset
An entrepreneurial, self-driven way of working

We offer:

An international career at a scale-up tech-company with a flexible working environment
An opportunity to grow in a company where innovation, boldness and self-leadership are valued
A culture that values the idea of hypergrowth with a heart
100+ awesome colleagues around the world; offices in Wrocław, Poland; Barcelona, Spain; Stockholm, Sweden (HQ); and New York City, USA
Regular all team retreats, meet-ups, and continued learning opportunities
Weekly yoga, and bootcamp classes!
Extensive benefits package to include continued learning and development opportunities, generous vacation, and health benefits
An office by the water at Blasieholmen, Stockholm
Join the journey of a Swedish tech company that is changing the face of e-commerce!
Bolt is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability or age.

To help us place the right people in the right role, we believe in science-based and fair assessment methods. column1: Salesforce Junior Developer/Consultant (graduate level) - IBM CIC
column4:
Introduction
Are you passionate about tech and looking to kick-start your career after graduation in a fast-paced and friendly working environment? Then look no further!

IBM Consulting Sweden is growing, and we now have a range of opportunities for early professionals/recent graduates. So, if you are looking for an extraordinary opportunity to build a rewarding career in Salesforce consulting, we would love to hear from you.

After an initial training and certification that will give you a solid foundation to build from, you will become part of our growing team, at one of our major clients working side by side with IBMers and our clients enabling them to implement and adopt the next generation solutions.

Your Role and Responsibilities
You are:
Most likely available to start after your graduation in June-September, but if you prefer an earlier start date, please don’t hesitate to apply, and discuss options with your Talent Acquisition Partner during the selection process.
Located in/near or happy to relocate to Stockholm. Our priority is the well-being of IBMers, candidates and the communities we operate in and many IBMers are working remotely during these times. However, on-site presence will be expected once circumstances permit.
The Techy bit:
Salesforce is recognized as #1 CRM platform in various analyst reports for past many years and IBM is the longest standing strategic partner in Salesforce services. For large clients with extensive, global, Salesforce-implementation plans we are currently looking to hire a first team of newly gradated forward thinking, tech-savvy Salesforce developers to be.
After an initial training and Salesforce certification phase, that will give you a solid foundation to build from, you will become part of our growing Salesforce Practice, working side by side with our clients enabling them to implement and adopt the next generation CRM-solutions.
We help our clients work smarter with the help of the latest technology to lead in their industry and stay ahead of competition. IBM's client engagements in Salesforce span across the full project life cycle – from early design and architecture to implementation projects and maintenances services. There are also shorter “proof of concept” projects related to sales development.
Together with your project team you will configure, develop, integrate, test, enhance, and maintain solutions for critical business processes for large international clients with base in Sweden.
Starting as a graduate in IBM will give you a great platform to grow and thrive in one of the world's largest IT consulting companies where continuous development and learning is seen as a key component.

The selection is continuous and the role will be filled as soon as possible.
This is a job of IBM Client Innovation Center Sweden AB.

Required Technical and Professional Expertise
For these roles we look for team workers with general business awareness, a professional & innovative mindset, passion for tech and appetite for large enterprise solutions who have:
Minimum Bachelor’s degree in the Information Technology area
Strong communication skills in both Swedish and English
Most likely you also:
Quickly understand existing business processes/solutions to translate this into end user needs and technical requirements for new ways of working
Are proficient in at least one of the following languages and frameworks: Java, JavaScript, Node.js, React.js, Vue.js, Angular, C++, C, C#, Ruby, Python
Thrive in ever changing, technology-based service environments – motivated by learning new technologies and solving client problems together
Easily connect with new stakeholders and build professional relationships with other IBMers, clients and business partners, over Webex and in real life
Quickly understand existing business processes/solutions in order to translate this into end user needs and technical requirements for new ways of working
Don’t worry if you don’t meet all the required technical criteria. If you have a passion for problem-solving, are a quick learner and logical thinker, we would still like to hear from you and find out how you can become part of the IBM Client Innovation Center.

Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

Previous experience of CRM applications
Previous experience of agile ways of working and agile delivery models
Master's degree (technical)

Eligibility Requirements:
You must be eligible to work in Sweden when applying.

About Business Unit
IBM Consulting is IBM’s consulting and global professional services business, with market leading capabilities in business and technology transformation. With deep expertise in many industries, we offer strategy, experience, technology, and operations services to many of the most innovative and valuable companies in the world. Our people are focused on accelerating our clients’ businesses through the power of collaboration. We believe in the power of technology responsibly used to help people, partners and the planet.

Your Life @ IBM
Are you craving to learn more? Prepared to solve some of the world's most unique challenges? And ready to shape the future for millions of people? If so, then it's time to join us, express your individuality, unleash your curiosity and discover new possibilities.

Every IBMer, and potential ones like yourself, has a voice, carves their own path, and uses their expertise to help co-create and add to our story. Together, we have the power to make meaningful change – to alter the fabric of our clients, of society and IBM itself, to create a truly positive impact and make the world work better for everyone.

It's time to define your career.

About IBM
IBM’s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that through the application of intelligence, reason and science, we can improve business, society and the human condition, bringing the power of an open hybrid cloud and AI strategy to life for our clients and partners around the world.

Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are not only one of the largest corporate organizations in the world, we’re also one of the biggest technology and consulting employers, with many of the Fortune 50 companies relying on the IBM Cloud to run their business.


At IBM, we pride ourselves on being an early adopter of artificial intelligence, quantum computing and blockchain. Now it’s time for you to join us on our journey to being a responsible technology innovator and a force for good in the world.

Location Statement
IBM wants you to bring your whole self to work and for you this might mean the ability to work flexibly. If you are interested in a flexible working pattern, please talk to our recruitment team to find out if this is possible in the current working environment.

Being You @ IBM
IBM is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, pregnancy, disability, age, veteran status, or other characteristics. IBM is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status.

column1: SAP Analytics Manager to Swedish Technology practice
column4:
Do you have a passion for transforming businesses with the newest technologies and making them data-driven companies? Are you looking for a place where you could combine your business consulting skills with technology strategy know-how? Then our roles as SAP consultants in the Strategy & Consulting and Technology practices are a perfect find for you!
  
  
    Bring your talent and passion to Accenture and help us deliver on the promise of technology and human ingenuity. Take this opportunity to develop your skills and build an extraordinary career. You will play a key role in transforming organizations and communities around the world. Let there be change!
  
  
  
    About Accenture Accenture is a leading global professional services company, providing a broad range of services and solutions in strategy, consulting, digital, technology and operations. Combining unmatched experience and specialized skills across more than 40 industries and all business functions — underpinned by the world’s largest delivery network — Accenture works at the intersection of business and technology to help clients improve their performance and create sustainable value for their stakeholders. With more than 620,000 people serving clients in more than 120 countries, Accenture drives innovation to improve the way the world works and lives. Visit us at www.accenture.com
  
  
  
    About Technology
  
  
    Accenture Technology leverages design thinking, industry insights and the latest digital and security methodologies to help clients innovate, grow and improve their businesses. Our expertise, capabilities and experience mean that our clients (including some of the biggest brands in the world) trust us to find the right solutions for their needs.
  
  
    Together with our talented international colleagues, we focus on connecting the needs of businesses with the new possibilities that come with technological progress. Because that's where the real challenges are inventing and testing things that have never been tried before, getting new applications ready for roll-out, and ultimately guiding clients to select and implement the right technologies – including state of the art Security solutions - to transform their businesses. Read more about our SAP Technology practice here.
  
  
  
   
     About the Nordic SAP360° Value approach
   
   
     At SAP within Accenture, we embrace our 360° Value approach in order to play a leading role in our new go-to-market approach. This includes:
   
   
    
      Innovation & Storytelling: Focus on infusing innovation into our delivery and bringing inspirational storytelling and purpose-led vision into the overall delivery experience for our clients
      360° Value Focused: A 360° value approach throughout the transformation journey, focused on unlocking multidimensional value across e.g. financial value, sustainability and experience
      Compassionately Collaborative: Bringing the best team on the planet to every client moment, with ONE Accenture mindset and go-to-market approach
    
   
  
  
   
    
      World-class Tools: Leveraging our key global intelligent tools
      Industry-specific Content: Deep industry content and leading practices used to accelerate our clients’ value realization
    
   
   
   
     SAP Analytics Manager
   
   
     In your role as an SAP Analytics Manager at Accenture, you will (for example):
   
   
    
      Be an integral part of innovative SAP transformation projects
    
   
  
  
   
    
      Utilize your functional and technical expertise in Analytics by analyzing, designing and implementing business processes and reports supported by SAP best practice solutions
      Help clients transform to a modern SAP platform and IT landscape
      Work with several of the biggest SAP clients in the Nordics
      Take a central role in our SAP Analytics value tower by leading teams, build competence and drive sales initiatives
    
   
   
   
     What’s in it for you:
   
  
  
   
    
      Great development opportunities and support for progressing in your professional career
      Great opportunity to develop your business acumen, consulting toolbox, technical and professional skills
      Access to comprehensive tools and frameworks supported by our global organization - including methodology, knowledge databases, expert networks and benchmarks
      A dedicated mentor to guide you during your work with continuous feedback
      Being part of our culture and core values in a truly human work environment
    
   
  
  
   
    
      Inspiring colleagues to support and work with
      Competitive compensations and benefits
      Early leadership roles with an overview of engagements and sub streams
      Work side-by-side with clients in their organization and drive comprehensive, meaningful, and transformative projects
      Help clients’ sustainability agenda through SAP transformations
    
   
  
 
  
   Who we are looking for:
  
  
    In order to be successful as an SAP Analytics Manager, it is recommended that you have:
  
  
    Required Qualifications
  
  
   
    
      5+ years of experience with data modelling with SAP Business Warehouse, SAP HANA Modeling or SAP Data Warehouse Cloud
      Additional experience in S/4HANA or ECC, Front-end tools (SAC, Lumira or Power BI) or cloud solutions such as GCP, Azure or AWS is an advantage
      Business understanding of at least one functional area, such as Finance, Sales, Logistics, Manufacturing or Marketing.
      Eagerness to shape and work in a team-oriented environment
      Motivated, persistent, eager to optimize, drive for excellence
    
   
  
  
   
    
      Passionate about SAP, innovation, and delivery the latest technologies to your clients.
      You are an analytical problem-solver with strong business acumen
      A Bachelor or master’s degree
    
   
   
   
     Preferred Qualifications
   
  
  
   
    
      Experience in at least one S/4HANA implementation
      An SAP certification in your area
      A full life-cycle implementation experience: Experience of the full lifecycle including estimating, planning, and delivering a solution end-to-end
      Stakeholder management within complex SAP programs
      You shine with your deep business & industry experience in one or more of the industries, such as: Retail & consumer goods, media, manufacturing, energy & utilities, banking products or communications, media and technology
    
   
  
  
  
   
     Location
   
   
    
      Stockholm, Gothenburg or Malmö
    
   
   
   
     About Accenture Sweden
   
   
     At Accenture Sweden we have a range of communities and engagement opportunities.
   
  
  
  
    Accenture IF
  
  
    Accenture IF is a community hosted by our colleagues – for our colleagues, to meet and practice sports and physical activities. We offer a wide range of activities like football, racket sports, running, sailing, golf, yoga and much more.
  
  
    To exercise sports you enjoy in the company of others, to help you stay motivated and healthy. Join our yearly events such as a cross-country skiing bootcamp, Accenture European Championship in football or an upcoming hiking trip in the mountains. We strongly believe in work-life balance and to have fun together!
  
  
  
    Parental leave
  
  
    We want our employees to grow and achieve value in life, both in their profession and personal life. Accenture offer a market leading compensation for parental leave – we pay for 270 days and compensate 90% of the difference between Social Insurance Agency’s (Försäkringskassan) maximum coverage and a base pay up to 80 000 SEK/month.
  
  
  
    Sick leave/Well-being
  
  
    In need of medical treatment, we want our employees to get well supported. All Accenture employees are covered by a health insurance by Skandia - Skandia Lifeline Access. The insurance offer healthcare of physical and mental treatments, including rehabilitation. During sick leave you will get well covered, Accenture pay 80% of your salary day 2-14 and 90% day 15-90.
  
  
    Our “Truly Human” network aim to bring us all together – as truly human individuals. We commit to care for ourselves and others, to foster an open-minded and supporting environment. Together we can help each other to achieve our aspirations and become the best version of ourselves. One of many initiatives are “Truly Human Health Academy”, a 100-day journey filled with classes held by health- and dietician experts, workshops, and buddy challenges – to learn and reflect on well-being and daily habits.
  
  
  
    Networks
  
  
    At Accenture we offer network opportunities, for our employees to meet and share common interests. Our aim is to foster a company culture that stands for inclusion and diversity – a place for everyone in terms of cross-cultural diversity, ethnicity, gender, disability, mental health, and LGBT.
  
  
   
    Our set goal is to achieve 50/50 in percentage of gender equality by 2025.
   
  
  
   
    We have a LGBT community and ally program to support and raise awareness
   
  
  
   
    With a multi-cultural calendar, we take account to all the days our employees/clients observe and celebrate
   
  
  
   
    On a yearly basis, we acknowledge Equality Champions – colleagues with a passion for accelerating equality and drive lasting change

Company Description
   Evolution is a leading international B2B provider of games and services in online casino. Operating in the forefront of our industry, we offer a turn-key solution for casino operators. Our licensees’ players can move flawlessly between mobile, tablet and desktop to play slots or live casino, which feature real tables with real dealers in real time. Our innovative and high-quality offer includes brands like Evolution Live, Red Tiger and NetEnt, and multiple award-winning international player product favorites, such as Crazy Time, Lightning Roulette and Gonzo’s Quest. Evolution is listed on Nasdaq Nordic with a MCAP of EUR 20+BN.  Across our 20+ sites, we have 10 000+ people working in the fields of Product Innovation, Software Development, Game Presenters & Hosts, IT-support, Facility & Studio build as well as support services.Evolution provides a dynamic and creative work environment with a unique opportunity for the right people to enhance their skills and drive their passion. Our culture is rooted in Evolution’s core values ALIVE, do RIGHT and work TOGETHER and we operate guided by our vision to become the leading supplier of online casino in the world.
 
  Job Description
   We are searching for passionate Scala Engineers. We thrive in well-designed, scalable, systems which use modern functional programming based design approaches. We believe that the functional programming approach in Scala results in systems which are easier to build and maintain - we use modern, pragmatic approaches such as Tagless Final and libraries such as Cats and Cats Effect to achieve this.
   You will need to:
  
    Be proactive, pragmatic and professional, deliver results;
    Write code that make our games and related functionality run
    Write unit and other automated tests;
    Work and communicate efficiently with the rest of the development team, including PO, front-end developers and design
    Actively participate in code reviews so that code delivered by you and your team is of great quality;
    Own your applications, ensure they deploy and run 24/7 on our Kubernetes platform with great performance;
    Be ready to invest the effort to become an even better developer.
  
 
  Qualifications
   
  
    Passion for our profession, in particular Scala and Functional Programming, and improving yourself technically.
    Have a Full Stack mindset, meaning that you are able and willing to move outside your comfort zone and learn and work with new technologies.
    Proven experience in delivering production software using Scala or comparable experience, such as extensive JVM or Haskell experience
    Interest in the latest programming trends such as functional and reactive programming
    Excellent communication skills and a pragmatic approach to problem solving
    Highly proficient in spoken and written English
    Bachelor’s Degree in IT or equivalent.
  
   We will appreciate experience with or wiliness to learn about:
  
    Building high performance clustered systems, modular FP-based architecture, as well as actor systems, where they are necessary;
    Cats / Scalaz, Cats Effect, ZIO, Monix, Akka Actors, Persistence, Cluster & HTTP, http4s, Tagless Final and/or Scala.js
    Event Sourcing & CQRS;
    Docker, Kubernetes, Kafka, Cassandra.
  
   Additional Information
   We Offer A healthy mix of startup-like culture of the company, which will enable you to try new approaches and technologies and remain on the edge of technological development and enterprise, with stability and supporting functions to help you focus on your job.
   At the office in central Gothenburg, we start every week with a breakfast together. We are a driven, multi-cultural game studio at the forefront of the gambling industry, having created some of the most popular games, several years in a row.  You will be part of a big international family where cultural diversity is present. We all have the same thing in common: a passion for delivering the very best in gaming. Innovation is a big part of who we are since there is no other way to be a driver in the industry!
   Have a look at some of the games we have created in our studio!
   Gonzo's Gold
   Divine Fortune
   Starburst XXXtreme
   Does this sound appealing? Then look no further, send us your application and we promise you a fun workplace where you will grow technically and personally!
   Please note that we are primarily looking for candidates who have a work visa for the EU, and are based in Sweden or planning to move there in the near future.

column1: SEI HQ: Internship on Global Subnational Agricultural Production Platform
column4:
The Global Subnational Agricultural Production Platform (GSAP) intern will support a team of four researchers to acquire and prepare agricultural data from several countries, geolocate the regions of production to match those of the GADM initiative, upload the data to a simple database, create a global map to serve the data and participate in scoping analyses of the final data set and scientific publications. 
    Location: Stockholm, Sweden Type of contract: Full-time internship, four months Internship period: September–December 2022 Deadline: 9 May 2022 
  
  
  
   
    
     Apply now 
     
      Use the Apply now button below to submit your application. Applications sent via email will not be accepted. 
     Apply now 
    
   
  
  
   
    
     Background and role 
      SEI is developing a comprehensive database of agricultural crop production for all countries, providing the production, yield and area of the most important crops. This database focuses on providing this information at the finest subnational scale possible (provincial or municipal). To date, the lack of this information for most countries is a major gap hampering policymaking and research in fields as diverse as food security, international aid, climate and hydrological modeling, econometrics, geopolitical studies, supply chain analysis and the assessment of the drivers of land use change and deforestation. 
      The GSAP intern will support a team of four SEI researchers in: 
      
      acquiring and preparing agricultural data from several countries 
      geolocating the regions of production to match those of the GADM initiative 
      uploading the data to a simple database. 
      
     The selected intern will also have the opportunity to work on the creation of a simple front-end to serve the data (a global map) and scoping analyses of the final dataset leading, eventually to participation in scientific publications. 
      Essential skills 
     
      Keen interest in supporting open data efforts to help other researchers and practitioners in variety of fields 
      Interest and tenacity to handle multiple files (formatting, digitizing, scraping and editing) as well as performing quality assessment following predetermined rules 
      Basic knowledge of data handling and editing using Excel, EmEditor, R or similar 
      Curiosity and perseverance for understanding agricultural data of various countries, including interpreting data and translate the crop names to English, conducting internet searches to better understand the context and/or engaging with country experts by email or phone 
      High attention to detail and the ability to work independently and as part of a team. 
     
     Desirable skills 
     
      Basic understanding of one or more key global languages (Spanish, French, Arabic and/or Portuguese) 
      Previous experience with formatting and digitizing data 
      Basic GIS command using QGIS, ArcMap and/or Google Maps Platform.
     
    
   
  
  
  
   
    
      
     
      Use the Apply now button below to submit your application. Applications sent via email will not be accepted. 
     Apply now 
    
   
  
  
   
    
     Questions? 
      For questions regarding the research aims of the internship, please contact Senior Research Fellow Javier Godar (javier.godar@sei.org). For questions regarding the recruitment process, please contact HR Specialist Filippa Klintberg (filippa.klintberg@sei.org).

We are now working with a market leading product development company who work within the freelance industry. They help both companies and consultants to manage time sheets, payroll and consultant assignment matching. They make the process of freelancing easier for both client and consultant by developing efficient and easy to use SaaS platforms which are all entirely based on Cloud and integrated into multiple different environments.

Each service has its own SaaS platform which does something different. One service is time sheet services to help consultants to efficiently log their time sheets to their clients. This platform logs all time and evaluates how much a consultant is invoicing and then allowed the company to view and monitor these time sheets in an easy way.

Another service is payroll and helping companies and consultants to correctly manage their payments. From a freelance perspective it means the consultant knows exactly what they are being paid and allows the companies to easily figure out how much they are paying their consultants.

Lastly their is a service aimed at helping match consultants to assignments. Companies can log their requirements on the platform from tech to the aim of a project and this will then match with available consultants who are able and skilled to work on that assignment making the entire process much more efficient and beneficial to both parties.

With growing demand for their services the company are now in a phase of growth and looking expand their development teams over the next 6 months. As such we are looking for developers to join this in house role and help not only expand the team but expand the services they can provide and create new platforms for new customers and services.

The environment is entirely based around Microsoft technologies with a primary focus on .NET Core and Azure for development with added use of .NET and C#. There is also a small element of front end development ensuring that the back end not only works to an extremely high standard but also that customers can view their information in an eye friendly and easy manor.

The experience we are looking for is:

Strong background in back end development with 3 years' experience.

A core focus on Microsoft development tools (.NET/C#) with .NET Core being a huge benefit.

Cloud exposure with Microsoft Azure being high priority.

REST API development experience OR experience integrating systems.

Any Front end experience with React OR Angular would be beneficial.



For your work you will receive:

Huge impact on the direction of projects and use of technology.

Working in a team orientated environment where everyone is in it together.

Regular team events and social events.

Fantastic management and technical leadership from extremely well experienced leaders.

Wellness allowance

Pension contributions

Great salaries

Remote working with 1 day in office per week (Get the best of both worlds!)

We are actively looking to recruit for these positions as soon as possible and anticipate a high volume of applications for this role. If you are interested it is strongly advised to apply ASAP on the email below to ensure this role isn't filled before. Get in touch at h.roke@nigelfrank.com to find out more!

I rollen som utvecklare kommer du att arbeta som konsult ute hos våra kunder på långa, intressanta och utvecklande uppdrag. Du kommer att hjälpa våra kunder med nyutveckling, vidareutveckling och förvaltning.
   Vi levererar till många olika kunder, vilket ger oss möjlighet att erbjuda varierande och spännande uppdrag i skilda branscher. Hos oss arbetar du med andra utvecklare och arkitekter i ett stort nätverk inom kompetensområdet Java.
   Erfarenhet
   Som .NET-utvecklare hos oss arbetar du både med att vidareutveckla vår egna tjänster och att vara med i kundprojekt som teknisk expert samt för bistå utvecklingen av deras verksamhet
   Primärt söker vi dig som är fullstack-utvecklare eller back-end-utvecklare med några års arbetslivserfarenhet. Du ska prata C flytande och ha intresse av att vara med och utveckla en plattform som ska vara driftsäker och skalbar. Kunskap inom webbutveckling, Azure och distribuerade system är meriterande. Vi använder agila värderingar i hur vi organiserar och planerar vårt arbete.
   Följande nyckelord beskriver de teknologier och verktyg vi arbetar med:
   .NET Framework, C, Git, GitHub, Visual Studio, ASP.NET MVC, ASP.NET Web API, Microsoft Azure SQL, SQL Server, Entity Framework, Azure, NUnit, React, .NET Core, Agile, CI, Web services, REST
   Eftersom vi är ett tillväxtbolag, blir du en central del i det vi gör och möjligheten att aktivt delta i att bygga vår verksamhet och påverka är mycket stora.
   Varför ska du välja oss?
   Vi erbjuder en arbetsplats där du har frihet att själv styra över din tid, ersättning och utveckling utefter dina prioriteringar i livet.
   På Castra finns inga begränsningar vad gäller kompetens- eller karriärutveckling. Vi erbjuder dig valmöjligheter och intressanta uppdrag, så att du kan jobba med det du tycker är roligast, på det sätt som passar dig.
   På Castra har du som medarbetare stora möjligheter att påverka bolaget och genomföra dina idéer genom bl.a. delägarskap, advisory board och projektgrupper.
   Om Castra
   Castra är ett medarbetarägt & entreprenörsdrivet konsultföretag inom IT, Systemutveckling, Agile-Management och IT-infrastruktur. Bolaget ägs gemensamt av medarbetarna och tillsammans bygger vi det företag vi själva vill jobba på.
   Här tror vi på frihet, möjligheter och gemenskap. Att du som medarbetare ska ha möjlighet att utvecklas och forma ditt arbete utefter dina prioriteringar i livet. Att våra medarbetare har stora möjligheter att påverka bolaget genom delägarskap, advisory board och projektgrupper. Att det är viktigt att ha ett sammanhang, känna tillhörighet och att man har kollegor som stöttar, utvecklar och tror på en.
   Vår vision är att vi ska vara Sveriges bästa arbetsgivare för konsulter. Att vi blivit certifierade av Great Place to Work fyra år i rad är ett bevis på att våra höga mål kring företagskultur och våra tankar om delaktighet, påverkansmöjligheter och respekt för individens egna val och möjligheter fungerar.
   Företaget har kontor i Göteborg, Stockholm, Helsingborg, Malmö, Linköping, Norrköping, Örebro och Jönköping. Mer information om Castra-koncernen hittar du på vår hemsida www.castra.se.
   Har vi lyckats väcka din nyfikenhet? Sök direkt via länken eller kontakta Rebecca Kågemyr på 0760222542 rebecca.kagemyr@castra.se

Uppdragsspecifikation
Sektion Externa tjänster
Varje dag reser närmare en miljon människor med buss, tåg, båt eller färdtjänst i Region Stockholms kollektivtrafik. Under en dag har busslinje 4 lika många resenärer som SJ, och Hötorgets station lika många som hela Göteborgs central. Det är vi på inom Region Stockholm som ser till att hela det här komplexa systemet fungerar.
Verksamhet kräver mer och fler komplexa IT-lösningar som är en förutsättning för kollektivtrafiken med system och IT-utrustning för exempelvis trafikinformation, försäljning, trygghet, radio och trafikledning.
Sedan 2018 har vi stärkt upp vår förmåga inom digitalisering och egen utveckling och inom sektion Externa tjänster ansvarar vi för alla digitala tjänster mot resenärer, trafikutövare och samarbetspartners. Vi initierar och driver nya initiativ samt vidareutvecklar våra tjänster i enlighet med de digitala utvecklingsplanerna för att säkerställa att vi når övergripande digitaliseringsmål och de långsiktiga målen för Region Stockholms kollektivtrafik. Tillsammans med övriga inom IT ansvarar vi också för att implementera nya arbetssätt och processer för vår agila transformation inom områden som trafikinformation, nytt biljettsystem, våra digitala kanaler, Big Data och digitala stödsystem till moderna fordon.
Som anställd eller konsult förväntas man att efterleva värderingar vilket är:
Öppenhet: Ett enkelt hej kan leda till så mycket. Genom att bjuda in och dela med oss skapar vi en offentlig verksamhet med ett öppet klimat. Vi jobbar för hela regionens invånare. Alla räknas.
Kompetens: Hos oss vågar vi välja en riktning, men vi har också modet att tänka om. Vi tar tillvara på varandras kunskap och vill hela tiden lära mer. Här finns möjligheter att växa och utvecklas.
Pålitlighet: Tillsammans levererar vi kollektivtrafik och utvecklar den för framtiden. Vi är tydliga med både förväntningar och utmaningar. Om något inte fungerar förklarar vi varför och tar ansvar.
Samverkan: Hos oss är alla en del av helheten, det ger energi. Vi inkluderar alla som behövs för att vi ska kunna nå de gemensamma målen.
IT-avdelningen (IT) ansvarar för design, utveckling och förvaltning av digitala tjänster för att bidra till en attraktiv och hållbar kollektivtrafik.
Beskrivning av uppdraget
I uppdraget ingår att utveckla webbaserade lösningar främst riktade mot SLs nya biljettsystem. Arbetet med att bygga det nya biljettsystemet har pågått under några år och närmar en kritisk fas under det närmaste året då många de sista delarna byts ut. Projektet vann 2021 priset Årets digitala projekt vid CIO awards. Som medlem i webbteamet kommer du arbeta som en del i detta projekt.
Webbutveckling hos bedrivs idag av tre agila team. Tillsammans ansvarar vi för samtliga webbsajter, som bl a sl.se, waxholmsbolaget,se och fardtjanst. regionstockholm.se. Teknikstacken är modern och förnyas kontinuerligt vid behov, den är huvudsakligen byggd kring en mikroarkitektur bade i frontend och backend. Huvudsakligen arbetar vi med React i frontend och .Net i backend, strävan är att arbeta i en cloudbaserad miljö i Azure så långt som möjligt. Inom frontend används ett eget komponentsystem underbyggt av ett designsystem baserat i Figma. Vi fokuserar vår utveckling på att skapa fristående, test och releasbara komponenter med hög kvalitet och prestanda och har en strävan att automatisera så stor del av arbetet som möjligt. Utvecklingsarbetet bedrivs av sammansvetsade team som strävar mot snabba releaser och en miljö där varje teammedlem känner sig delaktig i den gemensamma produktutvecklingen.
Din roll blir att stärka upp i det webbteam som arbetar med tjänster som e-handel, biljetthantering och kundprofil-sidor. De användare vi vänder oss mot är allt från resenärer i kollektivtrafiken som vill hantera sina biljetter till större företag som gör stora inköp för sina anställda. Utvecklingen är huvudsakligen feature-baserad då det mestadels sker nyutveckling i detta skede.
Uppdraget möjliggör för närvarande både arbete på distans och på plats på kontoret på Kungsholmen i Stockholm. På sikt kommer vi ses inne på kontoret oftare. Dagar och tider för detta styrs efter behov av i organisationen och i de agila team man arbetar.
Konsulten kommer ingå i ett team där arbetsspråket i såväl tal som skrift sker på svenska.

Vi söker en backend-utvecklare med stor passion för tech. Är du driven, initiativtagande och har en positiv problemlösande attityd? Hos oss på Interactive Solutions kommer du jobba med ett fantastiskt team, och tillsammans kommer vi bygga många roliga och utmanande projekt.
Vilka vi är
Interactive Solutions är ett produktionsbolag som bland annat utvecklar mobilappar, system och webbtjänster. Vi är idag ca 25 anställda med ett kontor vid Vaksala torg i Uppsala, cirka 500 meter från tågstationen/Resecentrum.

Vi tror på frihet och flexibilitet för våra anställda och uppmuntrar därför till att jobba från den plats där man mår bäst - oavsett om det är på kontoret, hemifrån eller stugan på landet.
Vår kundstock består av alltifrån mindre startup-bolag till större starka internationella varumärken. Vi växer snabbt och har stora ambitioner för bolagets utveckling de kommande åren. Nu söker vi efter duktiga blivande kollegor som vill vara med på resan och påverka utformningen av vår verksamhet, vår kultur och vår framtid!
Om tjänsten
Som utvecklare hos oss på Interactive kommer du få stora möjligheter att bidra med egna idéer och det är viktigt att du vill vara med och påverka och förstå slutanvändaren av produkterna för att på så sätt kunna skapa lösningar med hög användbarhet och god tillgänglighet. I rollen kommer du få ta ett stort ansvar och vara med och bygga långsiktiga och nyskapande lösningar.
Du kommer spela en viktig roll i produktionsteamet och kommer att jobba tillsammans med andra utvecklare, designers, produktägare, säljare och affärsutvecklare för att hitta nya vägar att stärka kundens digitala närvaro och öka kvalitén i de produkter vi tar fram.
Vi tror att du:

Har goda kunskaper inom SQL (MySQL/PostgresSQL)
Har god kunskap inom Golang och/eller PHP.
Är strukturerad och gillar problemlösning.
Är genuint intresserad av ny teknik och håller dig uppdaterad om de senaste trenderna.

Utöver detta tror vi att du är en positiv, framåtsträvande person som gillar att ta ansvar för de projekt du sitter i. Du har flera års erfarenhet i webbutveckling och har arbetat med agila kundprojekt tidigare.

Du uppskattar även att ta en ledande roll för tekniken inom projekt. För oss är det viktigt att du är en hjälpsam person som kan stötta teamet och utvecklas tillsammans med dina kollegor!

Vi jobbar med kunder och kollegor från runt om i världen och arbetar dagligen med lika delar svenska och engelska, så det är viktigt att du behärskar båda väl i tal och skrift.
Ett extra plus är om du har erfarenhet inom:

React
.Net
Kubernetes / Nomad
CI/CD Pipelines
TDD/BDD
AWS / GCP
Högskoleutbildning eller relevant utbildning är meriterande men inget krav.
Vi kommer lägga stort vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper och ditt intresse att utvecklas som både utvecklare och kollega.
Låter det som något för dig?
Vad roligt! Rollen är tillgänglig så länge annonsen finns ute och rekrytering sker löpande. Tveka inte att höra av dig!
Inte mitt i prick?
Vi är alltid nyfikna på nya sätt att skapa affärsnytta för våra kunder och tar löpande in ansökningar till roller inom allt från produktdesign och utveckling till sälj, marknad och backoffice.
Har du en passion för morgondagens innovationer och en idé om hur vi kan skapa magi tillsammans, men hittar inte helt rätt roll för dig? Tveka inte att höra av dig med en öppen ansökan istället!

column1: Senior Backend-utvecklare till RevolutionRace i Borås
column4:
Vi söker dig som älskar IT och vill hjälpa oss att ta vår verksamhet till nästa nivå. Vi söker en senior .Netutvecklare som älskar e-handel och gillar att ta ansvar i utvecklingsprocesser. Idag är vi ett team på sju personer som behöver förstärkning för att fortsätta utveckla vår affär, växa och anpassa oss gentemot kunders förväntningar och behov. Är du vår nästa kollega?

DIN VARDAG

RevolutionRace är ett av Sveriges snabbast växande e-handelsbolag och har sitt fokus på outdoorkläder. Målet är att leverera högkvalitativa kläder till rimliga priser direkt till sina kunder. Tillväxtresan fortsätter och de vill nu utöka sitt team med en senior Backend-utvecklare inom .Net.

I rollen kommer du att ha en central del i utvecklandet av deras e-handel.

Du kommer exempelvis:

Utveckla nya funktioner för e-handeln
Förbättra, underhålla och utvärdera befintliga funktioner

Då RevolutionRace är i en tillväxtfas kommer du få en varierande vardag med många olika arbetsuppgifter samt goda möjligheter att röra sig inom bolaget.
VEM ÄR DU?

Som Backend-utvecklare ser vi att du har ett par års professionell erfarenhet inom backend-utveckling inom .Net och har jobbat med webutveckling.

Vi ser gärna att du har erfarenhet inom Azure och Microservices.
Det är meriterande om du tidigare har jobbat med e-handel och front-end utveckling i Javascript eller andra ramverk.
I den här rekryteringen samarbetar vi med Wise IT. Vill du veta mer, kontakta ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Jacob Elmeljung på mobilnummer +46 76-000 1840.

PASSAR VI DIG?

Vi på RevolutionRace är ett familjärt bolag som låter varje individ ta stort ansvar för sitt arbete. Vi ser till att fira våra framgångar och ha en trevlig stämning på vägen. Vi värdesätter att ha kul på jobbet. Stundtals är det högt tempo och det är viktigt att du känner dig bekväm i en organisation under stark tillväxt och ständig utveckling.
Vi har bra förmåner med bland annat friskvårdsbidrag, tjänstepension, trevliga resor med kollegorna och bra rabatt på egna sortimentet. Vi är ett bolag med mycket driv och hjärta där du verkligen blir en viktig del i vår häftiga tillväxtresa!

column1: Senior Compiler Developer for Compilation & Computation Team
column4:
About Modelon
Modelon offers systems modeling and simulation software that accelerates product innovation, development, and operations in a range of industries. Modelon’s flagship product, Modelon Impact, is a cloud-native system simulation software platform featuring a collaborative browser-based interface and thousands of proven models and components spanning a broad range of applications. Headquartered in Lund, Sweden, and with global reach, Modelon is an expert industry leader in model-based systems engineering with a focus on leveraging open standard technologies.
About the Role
Modelon’s OPTIMICA Compiler Toolkit is an advanced Modelica-based mathematical engine which offers users a powerful solution for automation, simulation and optimization of system behaviors throughout the model-based design cycle. The toolkit is the engine powering the newly released Modelon Impact. Additionally, the toolkit is in production in customized workflows as well as in OEM partner toolchains.
As a developer you will be part of a highly skilled team of software engineers developing OPTIMICA Compiler Toolkit. You will interact frequently with other branches of Modelon, including application engineering to provide customer support as well as export users of the tool. You will also be part a broader team with a wide range of areas that are required to build a capable modeling and simulation/optimization platform.
You are an experienced software developer with high ambition to contribute to the success of the compiler in a growing market of advanced industrial users.
Required skills and experiences
5-10 years of experience developing high performing software, including:

Highly experienced in front-end development, symbolic processing, and code optimization
Ability to deliver efficient and reusable code that can be understood by others
Good communication skills, including English
Track record of building production quality software
Desired skills, experiences, and interests

Experienced with the Modelica language
Experienced with LLVM
Experienced with build systems (Ant, Make, CMake) and continuous integration infrastructures (Jenkins)
Experienced with Docker
Experienced with development in Java, Python, C/C++ and Javascript/Typescript
Ability to teach/mentor junior team member
Contributed to software system architecture development
Comfortable with agile practices like pair programming and code reviews
PhD degree in Computer Science or equivalent
Application and Contact Details
This position is based in one of our Swedish offices; Lund, Stockholm or Gothenburg. We are handling applications as they come in, so apply as soon as possible. For more information and questions about this position, please contact Christian Winther at christian.winther@modelon.com.

Big fan of tech and developing cool solutions? Are you looking for your next step within tech - in an environment where everyone strives to grow and have fun doing it? Want to specialize yourself or broaden your skills? Then the role as IT-consultant, with us at Axakon might be just the right thing for you..
We are looking for you!
You are a person that keeps track of the latest tech-trends, tech is part of your passion just like our colleagues here at Axakon. You are comfortable with learning new things and spreading that knowledge. A team-player, through and through.
Humble, and always striving to improve yourself, and the people around you, with an ability to challenge and implement practices from earlier experience to create the best possible solution for your client.
Technical skills we look for
At least 3 years of experience within one or more of these areas:

JavaScript/TypeScript (React, Node, Vue, Angular)
.NET
Java
IOS (Swift) or Android (Kotlin)
React Native
We offer you
The opportunity to improve yourself within tech together with other people with the same passion.A chance to try out new solutions with clients in the front end of technologyThe possibility to make a difference in your workplace and influence both your colleagues and the future of Axakon.
If you have any questions, contact our Talent Manager, Tobias Carlsson at: +46 (0)73 844 07 11.
Looking forward to hearing from you!

You are experienced in agile development methods and practices, i.e. Scrum, SAFe, TDD Experience with unit and e2e testing as well as accessibility and visual testing. Nasdaq is continuously revolutionizing markets and transforming while we adopt new technologies to develop innovative solutions, constantly aiming to rewrite tomorrow. To be able to continue and excel in our exciting journey we need to continue bringing people with different experiences and backgrounds together.
   The Nasdaq Pre Trade Risk (Nasdaq PTR) team is now looking for a Senior Developer Specialist to join our team. NPTR gives Exchange members the ability to define, monitor, and enforce risk limits on the trading activity of their trading participants. Exchange members can control the trading risk exposure at the level of a single trading participant, or for a group of trading participants. PTR will enforce the risk limits, reject orders that exceed the limits, and also notify PTR users when pre-set limit thresholds are crossed.
  
   With this position we offer:
   Stepping into this role, you and the team will work with PTR focusing on programming large, distributed systems with low latency and high availability. Our mission-critical software runs in customer data centers all around the world. You will be part of a brand new and growing team of passionate Java and React developers, and also be involved in building up the team with the right people. You will guide and coach your team members to become better developers and ensure a delivery of great quality software.
   If you have a strong Object-Oriented and core Java foundation, are detail-oriented, methodical, take pride in your work, and enjoy investigating new technologies, this job is right for you. Come join our team at Nasdaq, and help us expand our innovative solutions in fin-tech!
  
   What you will be doing?
  
    Work with the team to build new features & functionality in an agile way.
    Responsible for the architecture and code quality for the product area that the team is responsible for.
    Perform code and design reviews with the team to improve the quality
    Work together with architects and delivery leads for other product teams to make sure all components work together in a great way.
    Build automated tests to ensure great quality in the product.
    Ensure the performance and reliability of the system.
    Ensure service operability by implementing proper security, monitoring, and alerting based on the Nasdaq Operating Environment.
    We have the mentality that if you build it, you own it. This means that you will participate in problem-solving if incidents occur.
    Stay up to date with technology trends and decide which frameworks/technologies should be part of the technical solutions.
  
  
   What you would bring to the team:
  
    Bachelors degree in Computer Science or another related field
    Solid and extensive technical background with an emphasis on Java development
    Excellent communication skills together paired with a strong client service mindset
    With a strong inner drive, you should thrive in supporting high demanding users in a fast-paced environment
    Experience using CI/CD
    Experience working in agile teams either using Scrum or Kanban
  
  
   It would be nice if you also have:
  
    Experience with web development and modern frontend technologies, particularly React and/or React/Typescript.
    Experience in the Financial Field.
    Experience in developing low latency applications.
    Experience in deploying systems both in the cloud and on-prem.
    Experience with the Scrum Master role.
  
  
   Does this sound like you?
   This is a full-time permanent position located in Stockholm. As the selection and interview process is ongoing, please submit your application in English as soon as possible.
  
   About Nasdaq Stockholm:
   Nasdaqs Stockholm office is located in the harbor area of Frihamnen, we have a private commuter shuttle running in the morning and evening hours between the office and Karlaplan metro stop. Our office offers free parking, secure bike storage, and bike/e-bike lending. The office also features a gym and recreational sports room, as well as a restaurant and snack shop. Nasdaq Sweden provides its employees with 32 annual vacation days, we offer a competitive compensation package that includes annual bonus and equity plans as well as an employee stock purchase program.
  
   Come as You Are
  
   Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
  
   We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

column1: Senior developer who loves to make magic with code
column4:
Prisjakt helps thousands of consumers safely navigate and make better decisions in the e-commerce world every single day. We want to help them so they never have to feel that they regret buying something, or discovering they could have gotten it cheaper or faster from some other shop. To make this even more of a reality for our users we are looking for curious and skilled developers to join our journey for better decisions!
Teams
When working as a developer at Prisjakt you will find yourself in one of our domain teams. That means that you are part of an agile cross-functional team that is dedicated to a specific area of Prisjakt. The team will consist of the skills needed for the current mission, and that can mean that you can find yourself in a team with other skilled frontends, backend, and native developers, UX designers, and architects, DevOps, or marketing specialists. The teams are the experts of their domain and with common sense and great cooperation, you’ll be able to find the paths you want to take towards our goals.
Where will you find yourself in this setup? Well, it depends on you! Based on what areas you prefer whether it’s the backend, frontend, or a bit of both - we’ll find the team you fit in and where you can grow even more.
Experimenting/data
With lots of data and many people that use our product, we have both challenges and opportunities. We navigate through these by constantly trying new things and seeing what sticks through experimentation and A/B testing. Together with your peers you’ll learn from what didn’t succeed and try again, and celebrate when you do succeed. What we’ll end up with is epic functionality that our users love.
Your vibe and tribe

You’re a developer with experience and expertise, who understands that the playing field around you is constantly changing and evolving. You are curious and don’t sit around and wait for work to come to you - you are a doer and drive initiatives like it’s all you’ve ever done. And if you run into any obstacles along the way you adapt, find a solution and keep going. This combined with the fact that you’re very results driven and love to learn things, which makes you pop new ideas like microwave popcorn.
What you bring

Proven experience of JavaScript / React / TypeScript / Node.js
No stranger to continuous releases
An agile mindset and a big amount of curiosity
Bonus points

ElasticSearch
GraphQL
Python
MySQL
Microservice thinking
Cloud services, like GCP, AWS etc

Where: You will be located at our beautiful Malmö or Ängelholm studio but great news, we are a hybrid working company which means that you have the flexibility to sometimes work from home as well.
When: We would like you to start tomorrow but we understand that you have obligations today and those need to be handed over first.
We want you to start loving Mondays
At Prisjakt, you don’t need a work persona. Our dearest principle is that you’re welcome just as you are. We’ve made it our mission to make you feel excited about Mondays and also make it easier for you to manage the hassle of everyday life. We are proud of our relaxed and familiar atmosphere. In addition to working, you will also be able to fix your torn jeans in our creative workshop or learn how to make a proper espresso. With our epic printer Printz Charming, we dress our walls with whatever art we like, and our scooter swiftly gets you to your lunch date. Kids are always welcome, and you are free to borrow tools from the workshop for your home improvement projects. You can read more about us in the Prisjakt Culture book. If you like it - you’ll definitely like us.

column1: Senior Front End Developer - 100%remote @Swedish E-com NA-KD
column4:
As a Front End Developer at NA-KD you will be responsible for building and extending an international e-commerce platform with millions of users. There will also be opportunities to create new e-commerce platforms & tooling to improve new and existing workflows and to further innovate within the Episerver Commerce platform. Your goals are set high and you plan to eventually become the best in your field. You have a genuine interest in technology and are keeping up with the latest developments.
   We have redesigned the engineering team structure and you will be part of an autonomous product team with a customer centric approach to product development.
   The successful candidate is curious, flexible and thrives in a scale-up organization. You have experience within Front End Development and we are looking for Senior Profiles.
   NA-KD is one of the fastest growing fashion e-commerce companies in the world. This past year we have doubled the team in the tech organization - and we are really scaling up - and to join now would be quite a journey!
  
   Your Future
   
   Work in a small cross-functional product squad focusing on a certain area of the NA-KD platform. 
   Create innovative solutions at global scale, consumed by fashion lovers, crafted with care. 
   Be part of the Front End community, where we all work together and help each other to create the best experience for our customers. 
   Design, prototype, develop, organize and maintain both new and existing applications, integrations and services on our current platform+ brand new platforms. 
   Day-to-day communicating and collaborating with designers, testers and other engineers. 
   Work in a modern stack, React-based, with unique challenges and an always evolving environment, full of development opportunities from the very beginning 
   You are an important asset for the growing team and will be part of an exciting journey 
   At NA-KD we value everyone's opinion so believe it is important that you like a flat organization 
  
  
  Your Past & Skills
   
   Minimum 5 years proven work experience as a Frontend Developer 
   Experienced in different JavaScript such as ReactJS or similar frameworks, including concepts like asynchronous programming, closures and ES6/7. 
   Experience with sub-systems and renders across a mixture of CSR and SSR 
   Experience in writing the appropriate automation tests 
   Experience and genuine interest for “You build it, you run it!” 
   Experience in mentoring junior developers 
   We value your experience developing applications with micro-frontends architecture 
   You are familiar with Agile methodologies such as scrum 
   We put high value to personal attributes
  
   
  
   
  Location:
   Possibility to be 100% remote within Europe(+/-2 hours CET) or work from one of our offices in either Gothenburg/ Stockholm.
   How To Apply: Send us your CV, LinkedIn link and a link to your Github or similar.
   Other: Running applications  
  TECHNOLOGY
   We're on a mission to build the technology that powers the NA-KD global platform. We operate a modular end-to-end technology platform purpose-built to connect to our customers worldwide, addressing complex challenges and enjoying them. We're empowered to break traditions and revolutionize, with the freedom and autonomy to make a difference for our customers all over the world.
   THE DREAM TEAM 
  Working at NA-KD is unlike any other fashion gig. We’re a young company with a start-up mentality and (a borderline insane) hunger to be the best. In less than 5 years NA-KD has become one of the fastest growing fashion e-com brand in the world. And we have a 4 million strong community to prove it. How? We see no limitations, only possibilities. No failures, only learning opportunities. We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters. We’re doers. And if you dream of going to work every day to build the next big thing – then welcome home.

column1: Senior front end Developer to Lending Transformation
column4:

Senior front-end developer to revolutionize the packaging industry
   The world is on fire. We need the very best and brightest to work on the largest challenges of our time. To disrupt industries and fundamentally reinvent how we do things, building the companies of tomorrow.
   Because if we don’t fix this, whatever else you chose to do won’t matter. So if you are one of these best and brightest, you owe this to us, to the world.
   We are Circulate, an intelligent purchasing tool and B2B marketplace that simplifies buying sustainable packaging for European small and medium-sized companies. Our mission is to speed up the world's transition to more sustainable consumption and a circular economy.
   Is now the time to apply your skills, ambition and drive on solving real tangible issues that matter? Join us now on this exciting journey and let’s shape the future together!
   Part-time. Remote possible or at office in Stockholm. Start date as soon as possible.
   What you will do: 
  
   Lead the development of the UI and front-end experience of our marketplace 
   Work closely with UX-designers to shape the look and feel 
   Work in an agile, cross-functional and customer-focused team 
  
   Qualifications: 
  
   At least 5 years of front-end development with HTML, CSS, javascript and with front-end data modelling/templating 
   A strong feel for easy-to-use UI and a trained eye for aesthetic layouts and graphics 
   A strong understanding in cross-browser compatibility 
   At least 3 years of experience with jQuery, React and/or Angular 
   Highly proficient in integrating third party UI-components 
   Experience with marketplace development and marketplace frameworks is a significant advantage 
   Experience with payment providers e.g. Stripe or MangoPay is a significant advantage 
   Experience with PHP is an advantage 
   A strong track record of execution and delivering results 
   Very proactive and able to get things across the finish line 
   Ability to work fluently in English – skills in Swedish and/or other European languages is an advantage 
   We encourage female applicants 
  
   What you get: 
  
   Join a diverse, passionate & driven team of all backgrounds 
   Accelerated growth potential — we rapidly advance team members who have an outsized impact 
   Competitive salary 
   Be part of shaping an impactful start-up from scratch 
   Great benefits 
   Flexible working hours 
   Possibility to work remote 
  
   We hope to hear more about you and how you can help us achieve our vision of a world where we consume only what the planet can regenerate and an environment free from packaging waste.

Do you want revolutionize the security industry using ethical AI?
At Irisity you will be given the opportunity to change the world to the better through real-time video analytics powered by machine learning. Irisity is a public software company situated at Lindholmen, Göteborg where the innovation spirit is flourishing. Our focus is to detect and predict suspicious activities while preserving people’s integrity. We believe that enhanced AI performance, ethics and integrity go hand in hand, creating a positive mark within the camera security industry.
About this role
We are now looking for a front-end developer to keep improving our products. Your work will cover web-based user interface development for all aspects of our systems, including real-time video display for alarm central operators and portals for configuration and health monitoring of thousands of cameras across the world. You will work closely together with both UX designers, back-end developers and machine learning researchers, making sure that our entire system is coherent, stable and easy to use.
Our R&D department consists of tight agile teams, where most people contribute to several aspects of the system. You will be located at our main office in Göteborg, as part of a team with a lot of energy and a strong community. In our company culture, we give a lot of individual freedom to each team member, as long as everyone takes responsibility and the teams function as a whole. For example, during the ongoing pandemic, we have full flexibility regarding working from home or from the office, depending on what each staff members feels is the right trade-off between safety, convenience and efficiency.
Who we think you are
To be qualified for this role, we expect you to have extensive experience in developing the front-end parts of complex web applications. We also expect great insight into how a complete web stack application works, including the interplay with back-end parts, APIs and databases.
As personal qualities, we expect good communication skills and initiative, with the ability to work closely together with product owners and UX designers, making sure that our user interfaces match the expectations of our customers.
To be qualified for this role, we have the following minimum requirements:

MSc or BSc in software engineering, web design or similar
At least 3 years of experience in developing the front-end parts of large-scale complex web applications (multi-locale systems with thousands of users and complex business logic)
Excellent knowledge in HTML/CSS, JavaScript and TypeScript
Professional experience from modern web framework such as React

Experience from front-end testing (cross-browser, multiple languages etc), back-end development or other related software development work is strongly meriting.
Great skills in the English language is a requirement and good Swedish skills is an advantage.
About Irisity
At Irisity, we develop video analytics software for the security industry with great respect for personal integrity and privacy, focusing on detecting suspicious activity rather than exposing personal identity. Our system excels at the automatic detection of unwanted activity, such as intruders at construction sites at night, or people climbing roofs or breaking windows. We focus on detecting and preventing criminal activity, and never do things like registering the identity and whereabouts of regular citizens. At sensitive installations such as schools, our system even white-masks all individuals to hide their identity, to make sure that the invasion of privacy is kept at a zero level. This way, our system can detect what happens and alert, leading to reduce crime rates and increase safety without any negative effects on personal integrity.
Irisity AB (publ) is a public company listed at OMX Nasdaq First North, with main office in Goteborg. We currently employ a staff of 40+ people within development, sales, support and finance. Our R&D department consists of a computer vision / machine learning team with a high number of PhDs, together with and excellent group of system architects, designers and software developers. Our software is packaged into a complete cloud-based SaaS platform marketed towards large global customers and with thousands of cameras connected.
Read more at www.irisity.com

We are a customer-obsessed team with the ambition to change the world. We are a driven team with big goals and seek individuals who are genuinely passionate about their work
    About Us
    Gelato has built the world's largest and most global network for on-demand production of customized items e.g. t-shirts, wall art, mugs, books, hoodies, and cards. We support a new wave of e-commerce entrepreneurs and the global shift towards local and more sustainable production.

Just imagine what will happen when we add 3D printing capabilities to this global service. We are already empowering thousands of e-commerce entrepreneurs to grow and scale their businesses.
    Gelato Engineering
    We own no physical production assets, nor servers, instead our asset is a cloud-based connectivity platform that enables world-class on-demand production for e-commerce platforms and applications. This engineered platform needs to provide our customers access to more than 100 production partners in 33 countries and includes production plate design, routing to an appropriate partner, finally linking to logistics’ systems for delivery to the consumer. All this in 72 hours and reaching more than 5 billion people and potential consumers in a smarter, faster, and greener way.
    We have a multicultural Engineering team of over 50 people working in 5 countries who build, grow and maintain our applications and platform. Our engineering landscape provides the technology to extend our capabilities and features across 3 customer-facing applications: Optimalprint, Globe, and Gelato API plus the digital connectivity platform. The employed technologies range from backends using PHP and GoLang to mobile apps built natively or with hybrid technology, running on cloud services and with a modern CI/CD pipeline.
    We are flexible on location and building our teams in Norway, Estonia, Sweden, Russia, Ukraine, India, Spain, and Brazil.

    Use the latest technologies to improve and streamline user interfaces across our products. 
    Collaborate closely with other engineers, architects, and QAs as a valuable member of a cross-functional team 
    Share your knowledge and build creative solutions while helping the team evolve best practices

     A minimum of B.S. degree in Information Technology or Computer Science or 5+ years in a similar position. 
    Ability to adapt, change and grow quickly as we scale the organization 
    Passionate about engineering practices like agile, continuous delivery, test-driven development, traceability and observability 
    Minimum 5 years of experience in writing excellent Javascript; all standards-compliant, cross-browser and cross-device. 
    Strong experience with React and/or Angular and willingness and interest in learning more about both Angular and React. 
    Good understanding of building shared UI components and test-driven development. plus a sharp eye for design and UX details. 
    You share your ideas and continuously improve yourself and the team around you 
    Strong communication skills, high integrity and great attention to detail 
   
   You’ll get to work with:
    
    React / Angular / WebComponents / Vue.js TypeScript 
    ELK, Jaeger, Prometheus & Grafana 
    Microservices architecture 
    Cypress / Jest / Cucumber.js 
    CircleCI

    We offer you a chance to be part of a truly amazing journey in a company that sets very high targets and works hard to achieve them. You will be able to work with smart, motivated and engaged co-workers from all over the world, in an intense and very energetic environment. This leads to you having a tangible impact on the way that we operate and expand our business.
