G-loot platform becoming more popular by the day, so now we’re looking for someone with talent and passion for frontend development in JavaScript.
By joining our team, you will become a part of the world’s first cross-platform company to shape the esports industry. Working at G-Loot is working in a fast-paced and creative environment where AW´s and esports tournaments are a part of our everyday life.
Who you are?
You are a positive person with a curious mindset, passion for programming, and interest in tech innovation. You are willing to contribute to the development of the G-loot and enjoy working in a changing environment. You highly value writing quality code, have excellent communication skills, and are open to learning & sharing knowledge.
What will you do?
As a Fronted JavaScript developer at G-Loot you will have a chance to make a great impact in shaping the E-sports industry. You will work in close collaboration with amazing colleagues in a startup culture that lives and breathe esports. Working in our team of Developers, you will be involved in the whole development cycle, namely bug fixing, improving, and adding new features to our platform. You will be involved in the whole development cycle, working tight with other developers, product owners, and designers.
Technologies you'll be exposed to during your time at G-loot?
React, Javascript, CSS, Typescript.
We believe you have:

5+ years of professional software development experience
Mastery of JavaScript and a modern JavaScript application
Hands-on experience in modern frontend framework
Thorough knowledge of React
A University Engineering or Computer Science degree or experience makes up for that.
We offer:
Competitive salary
Flexible holidays & working hours
HQ in central Stockholm
Great colleagues and work culture based around empowerment and impact
About G-Loot
G-Loot is the world’s first cross-platform company in esports. Our mission is to make esports available for all! G-loot enables gamers across the world to compete in skill-based games they already love and play. Through our unique online platform, we host fun and exciting esports tournaments in some of the world’s biggest game titles. Our philosophy is an inclusion that’s why we are focusing on hiring a diverse team, always encouraging applicants from all demographics, backgrounds, and cultures! Today, G-Loot is made up of more than 100 employees where 23 nationalities represented and 24 languages spoken, with $98M in funding and a goal to democratize esports while adding an extra layer of excitement for gamers across the world.
Don’t miss a unique opportunity to join Sweden’s largest E-sport company and make an impact on the future of esports!

Senior Frontend Developer
What are we as a business?
Krea helps companies find the best possible financing for their business. Our platform makes it easy to apply, compare and select financing offers from multiple lenders.
We have already helped over 20 000 companies and are growing rapidly. Our aim now is to become the largest financing platform in northern Europe and to achieve our goal we need exceptional talents who want to be part of building something exceptional.

What you’ll do
You will be a part of taking Krea’s stable platform to the next level by contributing with your developer skills, but also with your ability to think creatively, engage in the transparent process of solving technical challenges, contribute to future roadmaps and solving pain points. You will take on ownership and responsibility for bigger parts of our frontend code bases and have a leading role in innovation and scalability in those areas.
Who we think you are
We think a good fit for this role is someone who is motivated by striving towards a common goal together with your colleagues. Someone who wants to innovate, collaborate and be involved in both the technical journey and the journey of an evolving company. Someone who enjoys the work of finding a good level of abstraction in your technical solutions when it comes to the balance between value and effort.
Qualified applicants will have experience with:

4+ years of experience with frontend/full stack development.

Great knowledge of React and modern frontend ecosystems

A great communicator and team player.
Our stack
Our technical philosophy since launch has been to use the most suitable tool for the job. If we already know the tool, great! If we need to learn a new tool, great!
For our backends we use:

Python (Django)

GraphQL

REST (Django Rest Framework)

Typescript

Kotlin

Machine learning
For our frontends we use:

React
NextJS
For devops, binding it all together:

Docker

Github actions

Deployment on AWS, including using ECS Fargate
And for testing:

Unit testing in their respective languages

Puppeteer for integration tests
Am I right for this role?
If you think you might not have enough experience for this role, please still reach out to us, because who knows, you might be wrong! And even if not, we might have another role for you at Krea.

Company Description
   As one of the world’s largest fashion companies with more than 171,000 employees worldwide, H&M is an exciting and dynamic place to pursue a career within the fashion industry. H&M group comprises of nine independent brands: H&M, COS, Weekday, Monki, H&M Home, & Other Stories, ARKET and Afound. We have over 5,000 stores across more than 73 markets worldwide.
   Our values reflect the heart and soul of H&M. They define what it takes to work here and how we do things. When we interact with colleagues and customers around the world, our values help us develop and grow. We want to be at the forefront of both fashion and sustainability.
   Our employees play a key role and can contribute to more sustainable fashion, today and in the future.
   The H&M group is on an exciting journey to meet and exceed our customers' expectations today, tomorrow and in the future. During 2022, we will continue our agile transformation to further advance our ability to continuously surprise and delight our customers and accelerate our business – by releasing the power of people, data and technology. With focus on the customer and our strong values, we explore new ways to innovate and develop products that make a meaningful and sustainable impact all over the world, and we want you to take a leading role in the transformation.
   We explore new ways of working, have a customer-focused mindset, embrace our strong values and release the power of our people to innovate and develop products that make a meaningful impact to customers all over the world.
 
  Job Description
   Are you passionate about modern tech? Do you want to be working in a new team to build the next generation customer experience? Great! We are looking for Frontend Developers to join one of our completely new teams in Customer domain.
   What you will do
   You will join in on our journey creating the next generation customer experience by blending fashion and tech as a core. You will be in the center of a business area that are responsible for the digital-capabilities customers interact with across their shopping journey, both online and in-store. Impacting everything from how we attract our customers, through ensuring a seamless shopping experience across channels, to building loyalty and a positive customer service experience.
   Responsibilities
  
    Work with best practices for the full software development life cycle
    Translate product strategy and requirement into suitable, maintainable, and scalable solutions
    Collaborate closely with product owner and other cross-functional teams, share best practice as well as discuss and motivate design solutions
  
   As a team we are fully responsible for the whole development cycle, design, build, test, deploy, evaluate, and repeat. The mindset “You build it – you run it “is key for us. We are measured on business outcome, not code merge or defects.
   Your mindset & skills
   Our journey will lead to something new and exciting - we will test, fail and learn. You are an important player in this transformation; therefore, we believe you are flexible and able to work in an environment that is not yet formalized. As a Frontend Developer, you have an entrepreneurial mindset, are excited about creating something new and challenge the status quo. Other important skills needed in this role is to keep it simple, to be humble, open to new ideas and contribute in discussions in the forefront of undisrupted loyalty!
 
  Qualifications
   Required:
  
    5+ Javascript and on of the frameworks (React, Vue)
    SCSS/CSS
    HTML/HTML 5
    Code testing (unit, integration, smoke, regression, E2E, test coverage)
    TypeScript
  
   Nice to have:
  
    Webpack
    Azure DevOps
    Accessibility
    Next.js
    AB tests
  
   Additional Information
   We are a global value driven company and believe in creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where different perspectives meet, and great ideas evolve. Our colleagues around the world from Shanghai to New York, from Stockholm to Bangalore, all share our entrepreneurial spirit and open mind. Utilizing each individual’s unique competences and perspectives, we build empowered teams where innovation and meaningful impact all over the world is achieved.
   We welcome your application regardless of gender, age, gender expressions, sexual orientation, disabilities, religious beliefs, origin, or background.
   Practical info
   This is a fulltime position with placement in Stockholm. Please apply with your CV and Personal letter as soon as possible.If you have any questions about the recruitment, please contact Talent Acquisition Partner Wojciech Dziadura (wojciech.dziadura@hm.com).We are looking forward to your application!

Ansök nu 
     
    
    
     
      Är du en duktig problemlösare med stort intresse för frontendutveckling? Vill du jobba i en dynamisk miljö där du har möjlighet att jobba med de senaste teknikerna och bredda dina kunskaper mot arkitektur och ledarskap? 
      ATG har några av Sveriges största och snabbast växande digitala produkter, med hundratusentals användare varje vecka. Tillsammans arbetar vi för att uppnå vårt mål att skapa världens bästa spelupplevelse! 
      Häng med oss och bli en del av vår kreativa resa på ATG. Hos oss finns alla möjligheter att växa i din roll och karriär med hjälp av vårt interna karriärprogram för utvecklare. 
      Om oss – Horse Digital och teamet Horse Digital utvecklar och förvaltar hästspelsprodukterna, från startlistor till kvitton, produktsidor och speltyper som V75, Dagens Dubbel och Spela Reducerat, till livevisningen som gör att våra kunder kan följa loppen på mobila enheter. Kort sagt allt som händer före, under och efter tävlingarna. 
      Vi är ett innovativt och framåtblickande team som jobbar med den senaste tekniken och säkerställer ständig förbättring i allt vi gör. Vi driver vår lärandeprocess genom aktiva kompetensnätverk, innovationssprintar, mob-programmeringssessioner och forum för ständiga förbättringar, både vad gäller teknikval, arbetssätt och verktyg. 
      Teamkulturen är dynamisk, engagerad, inkluderande och framåtblickande. Vi gillar att ha roligt på jobbet, leverera värde till våra kunder och utmana oss själva att växa till nästa nivå. 
      Vi utvecklar MicroFrontends i Typescript, React, Redux/Redux Saga, Node JS, GraphQL och AWS. Vi jobbar korsfunktionellt och några i teamet är, eller strävar efter att bli, fullstack vilket ATG uppmuntrar. Vi strävar efter att bredda kunskaperna i teamen och säkerställer en hög kvalitetsnivå genom mobprogrammering varvat med parprogrammering och individuellt arbete. För oss innebär det en stabil inlärningskurva och bra flow i arbetet. 
      Hos oss kommer du att ha kul samtidigt som du växer din karriär! 
      Om mig- Thérèse Stackelberg – rekryterande chef För mig som chef är det viktigt att teamet har rätt förutsättningar och mandat att fatta egna beslut inom givna ramar. Teamhälsa och teamutveckling är ett stort fokus för mig och vi lägger kraft på att ständigt bli bättre tillsammans, ha kul på jobbet och växa i senioritet utifrån våra egna förutsättningar och önskemål. Jag strävar efter att du som medarbetare ska ha rätt förutsättningar att utvecklas professionellt och skapa värde för dig själv och ATG. Jag värdesätter en kraftfull utvecklar-/teamkultur där medarbetare känner engagemang och stolthet över det vi åstadkommer tillsammans och gärna delar med sig av våra lärdomar och resultat för att inspirera andra. 
      Vi erbjuder dig  Vår kultur är öppen och transparent med en platt struktur. 
      Våra värderingar: Offensiv, Respektfull och Ägarskap är en del av allt vi gör på ATG. När vi rekryterar till ATG söker vi personer som har genuint intresse för sitt yrkesområde, som aktivt bidrar till resultat, trivs i en mångsidig miljö och tar ägarskap för leveranser. 
      Utöver våra förmåner erbjuder vi dig en modern tech stack och en dynamisk arbetsmiljö där du har möjlighet att vässa dina kunskaper, lära dig nya saker, samarbeta med många duktiga och nyfikna kollegor samtidigt som du kommer ha möjlighet att påverka spelupplevelsen för drygt en miljon engagerade kunder.  Hos oss är du en viktig del i ett företag som värderar både sina kunder och sina anställda mycket högt! 
      Den här tjänsten är på heltid och utgår från vårat fräscha kontor vid Solvalla. Vill du hellre arbeta hemifrån, eller från någon annan del inom Sverige? Inga problem, ATG är en flexibel arbetsplats där du beroende på din roll har möjlighet att kombinera ditt hemarbete med arbete på kontoret.
     
    
   
  
 
  
   
    
     
      Kvalifikationer 
      Vem är du? Vi söker två seniora utvecklare med lång erfarenhet av front-end utveckling från större företag i transaktionsintensiv miljö. Det är meriterande om du drivit arkitekturfrågor eller deltagit i lösningsarkitektur på ett strukturerat sätt. Du har dokumenterad erfarenhet av att bygga mikrofrontends och förstår vilka överväganden som måste tas för att bygga en högpresterande funktion eller tjänst. 
      Vi ser det som en stor fördel att du har ett travintresse men det är inte ett krav, däremot behöver du vara öppen och intresserad av att lära dig hästspelsprodukterna. 
      Vi tror att du har naturligt självledarskap, är ambitiös, kunnig och älskar att inspirera och inspireras av kamrater i vårt team. Vi värdesätter tidigare erfarenhet av mentorskap för juniorer och att arbeta agilt. 
      Du talar engelska obehindrat i tal och skrift och har lätt för att uttrycka dina idéer och perspektiv så att andra förstår. 
     
    
   
  
  
  
   
    
     
      
       
        
         Tjänstepension
         
       
       
        
         Work -life balance
         
       
       
        
         30 dagars betald semester per år
         
       
       
        
         Personlig tränare och gym på kontoret
         
      
     
    
   
  
  
  
   
    
     
      
       Så här har vi det 
        Hos oss är du del av en innovativ miljö och med hjälp av den senaste tekniken utvecklar du den bästa spelupplevelsen. Vi gillar att samarbeta och hos oss får du stort utrymme att påverka ditt arbetssätt. Här hittar du nyfikna, nytänkande medarbetare och ledare – viktiga egenskaper för att kunna utveckla och utvecklas. Liksom energi , mod och motivation. 
       För att må bra är skrattmuskeln lika viktig att träna som alla andra muskler. Både den fysiska och den mentala hälsan skapar balans i livet. Hur vi har det på jobbet påverkar privatlivet- och vice versa. Vi ser det som en självklarhet att ge det stöd och de verktyg som behövs. Ditt val av arbetsplats och arbetssätt är flexibelt och vi lägger stor vikt på självledarskap. 
       Vi bryr oss om varandra och respekterar varandras olikheter på ATG. Och vi vill att våra kunder ska må bra och ha roligt när de spelar. Vi bryr oss också om sportens välmående, dvs. idrottarna och hästarna - och samhället runt omkring oss. Vi drivs inte av privata vinstintressen utan allt överskott går tillbaka till våra ägare, svensk trav- och galoppsport, något som både känns och gör gott.

Our offer

We are looking for talented Senior software developers that understand self leadership, and are nice people. You are likely a startup minded person with a genuine interest to build something new. We usually set up a remote office somewhere warm and sunny when things are dark and cold in the north (January - March). In 2018 we went to Phuket, Thailand and in 2019 Mauritius. It was canceled last year due to covid and if we travel next year will be decided in the coming months.

We are currently looking for a Senior Frontend Developer to join the polestar.com web development team.
If you are reading this, you probably already know that Polestar is an electric performance car brand. We work hard to create a unique experience for the customer, owner, and driver. The thrill of driving the car, the digital experience of buying, owning, and controlling a Polestar require us to push the limits of technology and software development. Sustainability has been there from the beginning, and we have set a moonshot goal for climate-neutral cars in 2030. There is an ocean of opportunities in this for talented IT professionals who want to dive in and make a difference.

Acquisition Tools
Acquisition Tools is a product area responsible for delivering and maintaining Digital Products to support sales activities and customer acquisitions. The products making up the Acquisition Tools product area include polestar.com, our CRM platforms and content management system (CMS), as well as parts of the car remarketing journey. Acquisition Tools is part of the Customer Acquisition and Services domain, through which we deliver a wide range of digital solutions serving both our existing and future customers. Our primary goal is to provide our customers with a first-class experience in both the physical and digital touchpoints. The domain leverages a best-of-breed of technology, combining bespoke solutions with commercial technologies. The domain is a key enabler of Polestar's overall strategy as a Direct-to-consumer brand and the increasingly important aftermarket business.
About the role
As a Senior Frontend Developer at Polestar, you will be a creator, transforming Polestar's digital vision into working solutions by building digital products, platforms & services. Thereby, Frontend Developers directly influence the digital functionality and how users will interact with it. You also stay on top of the ever-changing technological landscape and invest significant energy in evolving their skills. You are not only up to date on industry trends regarding the Digital Product's technology stack but also know what the near future will bring.
What you will do
Work closely with the Digital Lead, Business Analyst and other developers leading the digital product team and their vision
Build applications, often in close collaboration with designers, to optimize trade-offs between technical functionality and end-user experience
Design and develop the business logic and front-end systems of the Digital product
Ensure the code follows latest coding practices and industry standards
Write both unit and integration tests, and develop automation tools for daily tasks
Challenge ideas and opinions to avoid pitfalls and inefficient solutions
Maintain a close relation to Competence Group Leads and Architecture & Standards team (under Deputy CDO) to ensure latest guidelines and guardrails are followed when developing digital products/services/platforms
Who you are
You have solid problem-solving skills with the ability to quickly process and analyze information
You master both Typescript & React.js,
You should ideally be able to work through the "full stack”, i.e., back-end and front-end. But with a passion and natural focus for frontend
Experience/interest in developing serverless applications in a cloud environment, preferably AWS
Experience/interest working with event-driven microservices
Experience /interest with writing effective unit and integration tests
Preferably, you have experience with design principles and concepts like SOLID and Domain-Driven Design
Preferably, you already have strong experience from previous positions as a Developer on a cross-functional and/or agile team
An interest in data and analytics and data-driven development is a big plus
Personal Qualities
Great communicator, who is able to explain complex technical concepts and align organization on decisions
Team player and collaborator with an innovative mindset
Passionate about technology and excited about the impact of emerging technologies
Wants to unleash inner self-starter and work in an environment that fosters entrepreneurship
Believes in culture of complete transparency and trust
Open to learning new ideas outside scope or knowledge skillset
Ready to coach junior software engineers on the team
Polestar - the guiding star
Polestar is an electric performance brand, determined to improve the society we live in by catalyzing the change to sustainable mobility. We are a global team of highly talented individuals who share a passion to change the world. We challenge conventions and we challenge ourselves for the purpose of innovation. We believe innovation is a team effort and that just like each component is critical to the performance of our cars each person working at Polestar is as important to the team and its performance. We work in close collaboration across empowered global teams that don’t settle for anything less than excellence.
At Polestar, the sky is the limit.
Is this you? If you are interested in joining the Polestar family, don't wait with submitting your application. We apply a continuous selection process and the job post will be open until the position is filled.
