How to apply:
If this could be you take this quick 15-minute test to show us what you got.
That’s it, all there is to it. Pass the test and go straight to the interview. No need for complicated bureaucracy and CVs.
About our engineering culture:

We follow the lean startup methodology
Development by agile iterations
Continuous integrations and deployments (daily releases)
Test-driven development and 80%+ code coverage
Pair programming on complex tasks

What we offer:

Continuous learning environment
Trust and freedom to work on the product
Supportive and highly skilled coworkers
Great culture of transparency and openness
A workplace where initiatives are highly appreciated

About us
Producement is a team of ex-Wise engineers who fell in love with the process of building great products. After leaving Wise, they created their own sweat equity-based product engineering team. Producement’s mission is to help early-stage startup founders build and deliver scalable MVPs.

WELCOME TO UTOPIA
Music is incredible. It can excite hundreds, and unite thousands. But as an industry, it has been slow, complicated, and disparate. While the tech world has moved into the future, the music industry continues to be shaped by inefficient systems of the past. At Utopia we believe there is a better way. Which is why today we are setting out to transform the entire industry; creating new revenue streams, consolidating the data and decluttering the admin. Unlocking the industry’s full potential by unifying it all in one truly holistic space. Some might call that a Utopia.
Funnily enough, so do we. Welcome to Utopia. Where music lives.
WHAT UTOPIANS DO
The open secret is that the music industry is struggling with the very basics of music accounting: What was played, when and where? Who should get paid and how much?
Utopia Music is bridging the data gap by connecting global consumption, accurate metadata, and fast payments to an industry-wide trust platform. Our goal is to unlock creative value and enable Fair Pay For Every Play to make a better world for Music. The solutions we offer do not threaten to usurp the role of industry incumbents - it is about bringing transparency in the industry and supporting efficient royalty collection for all.
THE ROLE
We work in cross-functional (product, engineering, data, design) product teams that owns the end to end outcome, objective and metrics of the product. You’ll be working on Utopia products built on the Utopia big data platform. We work full-stack including the product infrastructure and user experience. We take a holistic approach to product creation from data to robust backend and customer experience.
Depending on your experience and strengths, we will find the right role for you in the new team.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Implement, test and support the backend and frontend technical modules
Support the technical leader in designing and building the global architecture, and in picking the rights tools, libraries and frameworks
Provide technical solutions to business requirements
Collaborate and work closely with other developers, product and design team to understand better the end-user requirements
Ensure the availability of the system.
Be part of the overall application lifecycle with particular focus on improving its technical architecture and user experience
Follow agile development methodologies
REQUIREMENTS
Proficiency working with Node.js. Experience with Golang is a plus
High quality code is even more important to you than the Force
You love to learn and you love to share your knowledge
Preferably you’ve worked with MongoDB and/or SQL
Experience with with TypeScript and React. Knowing ES6, redux, Next.js and Nest.js is a plus
Familiarity with Google Cloud and CI/CD skills are highly valued.
Good communications skills, fluency in English.
Good self organisation skills and strong personal integrity.
Passionate and skilled developer that already has a minimum 5 years of experience
WHAT WE OFFER
Great atmosphere - we live, love & breathe music & tech!
Working in an impact oriented team and inclusive company culture.
An experienced team to learn from, with proven track records in multiple startups and big tech companies.
Our flexible remote policy provides Utopians the freedom to work either from one of our inspiring offices or from home.
We celebrate being an international and multicultural company.
Competitive benefits; packages depend on location. You’ll be given more details on this during the interview process.
We are supporting work permits for employees that have already moved to our locations from countries outside the EU. However, we do not support relocation at the moment.
THE HIRING PROCESS
You send us your CV in English.
We invite you for an introductory phone/video call to get to know you better and share more about us.
You get a programming exercise and unlimited time to send us your solution.
Our lead developers evaluate it and we provide you with the feedback.
You meet our lead developers for the technical interview.
You meet the hiring manager for the culture fit interview.
UTOPIANS
As we want to bring transparency, trust, and clarity to the music industry we serve, we know a change comes from within. Utopia is a transparent, trust-based organization striving to have clarity in thinking and doing what we set out to do.
We execute urgently and innovate to grow faster. We ship things that make a difference today, so we can make them better tomorrow. We embrace fairness and are all accountable.
Strictly diverse and inclusive. We are an equal opportunity employer.
We celebrate our diverse backgrounds and we welcome everyone who identifies with the above to apply. Welcome to Utopia - Where Music Lives!
We’re eager to meet You! :)

column1: Senior Full Stack Engineer, User Platform
column4:
Engineering
User Platform (UP) is a part of Spotify’s Platform mission. The Platform mission is responsible for building the tooling and support platforms for the engineering teams at Spotify. UP owns the platforms for authentication, authorization, user account data, and user experience configuration at Spotify. UP was formed with the mission to provide a secure platform that helps users establish their identities and manage their account data on different surfaces. UP also enables teams around Spotify to experiment on and customize the user experience in new and more refined ways. User Platform is responsible for many of the core services needed for Spotify to function and provide 380M+ users across the world access to the audio experience they desire.
Location
Stockholm or Remote EMEA
Job type
Permanent
We are looking for talented, engaged full-stack software engineers to join our teams who are passionate about working services and experiences that allow the users to manage their digital identity with Spotify and form the backbone of our product experience for hundreds of millions of users across the globe. You will build highly-available and high throughput solutions to enable the world access to music. At peak, we serve >2m requests per second to power tens of teams @ Spotify and handle serving >3TB of user account data to live services. You will also be able to innovate to create better, more seamless user experiences to help users access Spotify.
What you'll do
Work across the Web and Backend stack to plan and deliver end-to-end solutions. As a Full-stack (or ‘T-shaped’) engineer you have the ability to work fluidly across different programming languages and technologies
Deliver testable, maintainable, and high-quality code
Continuously optimize the software you create
Share knowledge, evangelize best practices, and collaborate with a team of equally passionate peers.
Take operational responsibility for the services that are owned by your team, including taking part in an on-call rotation
Work in an environment that supports your individual growth by providing you with challenging work, the freedom to acquire new skills on hack days, reading groups, and a variety of internal training courses
Who you are
You are an inclusive colleague and a true great teammate
Have at least 5 years of experience in the working backend (Java) and front-end languages and relevant frameworks (JavaScript/TypeScript, React/Vue.js).
You are interested in keeping up with current best practices in your areas of expertise, as well as exploring other areas of computer science and continually learning and growing as an engineer.
You work with designers to iterate upon and deliver compelling user experiences.
You are experienced working with modern, cloud-native infrastructure and tools (such as Kubernetes)
You are comfortable running your software in Linux environments
You know and care about sound engineering practices like continuous delivery, defensive programming, and automated testing
You have a good understanding of data structures and algorithms, and understand how to apply them to design pragmatic solutions
You're passionate about your work, striving towards the goals of the team and, ultimately, the Spotify mission - “giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the opportunity to enjoy and be inspired by it".
Where you'll be
We are a distributed workforce enabling our band members to find a work mode that is best for them!
Where in the world? For this role, it can be within the EMEA region in which we have a work location and is within working hours.
Working hours? We operate within the Central European and GMT time zones for collaboration and ask that all be located in that time zone.
Prefer an office to work from home instead? Not a problem! We have plenty of options for your working preferences. Find more information about our Work From Anywhere options here.
Our global benefits
Extensive learning opportunities, through our dedicated team, GreenHouse.
Flexible share incentives letting you choose how you share in our success.
Global parental leave, six months off - fully paid - for all new parents.
All The Feels, our employee assistance program and self-care hub.
Flexible public holidays, swap days off according to your values and beliefs.
Spotify On Tour, join your colleagues on trips to industry festivals and events.
Learn about life at Spotify
Spotify is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome at Spotify for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what’s playing in your headphones. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all thrive, contribute, and be forward-thinking! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our differences that we will find the power to keep revolutionizing the way the world listens.
Spotify transformed music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the chance to enjoy and be passionate about these creators. Everything we do is driven by our love for music and podcasting. Today, we are the world’s most popular audio streaming subscription service.
Global COVID and Vaccination Disclosure
Spotify is committed to safety and well-being of our employees, vendors and clients. We are following regional guidelines mandating vaccination and testing requirements, including those requiring vaccinations and testing for in-person roles and event attendance. For the US, we have mandated that all employees and contractors be fully vaccinated in order to work in our offices and externally with any third-parties. For all other locations, we strongly encourage our employees to get vaccinated and also follow local COVID and safety protocols.

Till vårt kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg och Malmö söker vi nu en senior full stack-utvecklare. Som kollega till oss får du vara med i vår fortsatta utveckling och framgång. Du har en stor möjlighet att påverka din arbetssitutation och vilken väg företaget tar.
   Är du den vi söker?
   Du kommer jobba med projekt som innefattar all typ av webbutveckling. Allt från avancerade e-handelslösningar med kopplingar till olika affärssystem till enklare webbplatser.
   Det finns även möjlighet att jobba med ex. mer avancerade system som ex. bygger på Laravel och Vue/React.
   Du bör ha mycket goda kunskaper inom:
  
   PHP
   HTML
   CSS
   JavaScript/ES6
  
   Du bör även ha erfarenhet av:
  
   Versionshantering, speciellt Git
   Arbete med lokala utvecklingsmiljöer, t ex. Docker
   Pre/post processors, t ex. SASS/PostCSS
   Arbete med och modifiering av byggprocess, ex. webpack/rollup/vite
   Pakethanterare, ex. NPM, Gulp och Composer
   Deploy-verktyg via continuous integration pipeline
  
   Meriterande är även:
  
   React
   Vue
   Laravel
   En känsla för tilltalande och funktionell design
  
  
   Du bör också vara självgående och en naturlig problemlösare. Vi ser gärna att du pratar svenska flytande och även att du har minst grundläggande kunskaper inom det engelska språket.
   Tjänsten är på heltid (andra varianter är också möjliga) på vårt kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg eller Malmö.
   Vi ser verkligen fram emot att du hör av dig och hoppas att du vill komma hit för att prata mer om tjänsten och vad vi kan erbjuda varandra.
   Varför jobba hos oss?
   Mild tror på att låta byrån växa med sina medarbetare. Lika mycket som Mild tar ansvar för sina medarbetare tar medarbetarna ansvar för Milds mål och utveckling. Våra kunder bjuder dig på spännande utmaningar och vi erbjuder även internutbildning och övriga företagsevents. 
  Vår ambition är att du inte ska känna någon söndagsångest. Hos oss ska du ha kul, växa, utvecklas och bidra, ta fullt ansvar för ditt jobb och samtidigt känna att du har hela teamet bakom dig. 
  Förutom en härlig arbetsplats med trevliga kollegor så erbjuder vi självklart även en bra lön, del i bolagets vinst, personligt anpassade utbildningar, flexibla arbetstider, tjänstepension och friskvårdsbidrag.

We’re looking for an experienced Full-stack Developer to join the Calqulate team.
Calqulate’s mission is to bring financial knowledge to CEOs and founders, empowering them to make better business decisions and to reach their next funding round. Our vision is to create a software that unifies and automates a startup's financial and growth analytics, helping them scale and grow faster.
Calqulate is a tool that simplifies our customers’ financial reporting and forecasting. We provide CFOs, CEOs and founders with the accurate, up to date data they need to generate Customer acquisition costs (CAC), Lifetime Value (LTV) and Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR), giving them a bird's-eye view of their company’s current and predicted growth path.
Our company—a diverse, multicultural and geographically dispersed organization—is one year old and growing fast. Our team members share some common traits, and we strive to create a culture of humility, reliability and approachability. We also like to remain factual.
About the role
As Senior Full-stack Developer, you will be responsible for managing and further developing our existing GraphQL/Node.js back-end and React.js front-end. You should have extensive experience in writing clean, functional code on the front- and back-end as well as testing and fixing bugs or other coding issues across the full stack.
You'll make a great match for the team if you have:

3+ years of experience in writing code hands-down across the full stack, specifically in Typescript.
At least 2 solid years of experience in writing React.js web applications.
Solid understanding and experience with Apollo Client, Material UI is required.
Knowledge of relational database design principles is required.
Previous experience in working with OAuth2 is required.
Knowledge of GraphQL principles is a must; previous experience with Hasura is a plus.
Experience collaborating with software engineers & teams to solve complex application problems.
Solid knowledge and familiarity with Git and Jira.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English.
You love challenges, you thrive to get better everyday and positively learn from your own mistakes.
Responsibilities

Actively drive continuous engineering excellence within the tech team and across the organization.
Engage with the team members to discuss and implement service improvements and new development.
Work closely with the CTO to actively drive the organization technical roadmap.
Ship incrementally and often, helping the team to maintain a constant flow of feedback on its work.
Work with the Product Owner to ensure the technical roadmap meets requirements.
Mentor other engineers on the team and feel passionate about improving not only the software but the team skillset as a whole.
Be responsible for your deliverables from inception to operation and maintenance, including participating in team on-call rotations and support activities.
This is a full-time position. We're located at Station F in Paris, and at Maria01 in Helsinki. We have a flexible remote policy.
Please submit your application and CV, as well as relevant samples of your work.
We are processing applications as we receive them. All communications will be confidential.
Calqulate celebrates diversity and equal opportunity. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and talents. The more inclusive we are, the better and more inclusive our work will be.

Job Description:
Tidler provides consumer-centric first and last mile logistics to the automotive industry. Our drivers pick up and deliver cars to and from workshops and dealerships all over Sweden whether it be for a Test Drive, New/Used car delivery or for a routine Workshop visit.
So far we've delivered over 60,000 cars and have over 100 drivers out in the field. We work with Sweden's largest car manufacturers and dealers and are a critical part of their offering as they transition to online sales and service channels. Our vision is simple - to make car ownership simpler, more convenient and sustainable.
As a senior full-stack engineer at Tidler you'll be joining at an exciting phase in our journey and be a critical part of the team as we build out our systems and processes. You'll be expected to get your hands dirty on multiple projects using the latest technology and practices while at the same time championing simplicity, quality and reusability.
What you will do:
Build internal and external applications from mobile apps and customer-facing order systems to scheduling algorithms and data analysis tools
Work with a React/React Native, Node, Typescript, GraphQL and Postgres stack
Be a key part of a dynamic, collaborative, non-hierarchical culture where your talent is valued over a role or title
Have an active role in defining our development processes and systems architecture
Work in cross-functional teams and be a part of product and business decision making
Research the latest tooling and technology and make recommendations on how we can benefit from their use
Your qualifications:
Minimum 5 years of professional software development experience
Excellent spoken and written English, all day-to-day communication will be in English
Have the right to live and work in Sweden, sponsorship is not available
Proven track-record of delivering high-quality work and showing a high level of responsibility for all tasks
Strong focus on code quality and long term maintenance
Ability to communicate and work well within a small team
Keen eye for detail
Preferred Skills & Qualifications:
Experience with logistical planning systems
Strong Javascript-specific experience and skills
Experience with Kubernetes and Google Cloud Platform
Experience of Continuous Delivery, TDD, BDD, Infrastructure as Code, etc
Benefits:
Remote working possibility 2-4 days a week
Private Health care insurance
Pension (ITP1)
30 days paid vacation
Wellness allowance of 3000 SEK/year
Office in central Stockholm
Salary Range:
55,000 to 65,000 SEK/month

Who we are
Since our start in 2017 we have provided smart tools that help put financial power back in the hands of the people – where we believe it belongs. Everything we do is based on one vision: to improve the world’s financial health.
So far, we’ve helped Swedes, Finns and Germans save millions by refinancing expensive consumer credits. But we aim higher. New markets, new tools, new products and new ways of improving people’s financial lives. This means we need more brains and hearts to fuel our growth. That is why we are currently searching for a senior Fullstack Developer.
As a senior Fullstack Developer at Anyfin you will have the opportunity to work in a startup company in constant movement, where no day is like the other. You will join a highly technical team where you will be a part of solving the financial issues of tomorrow. You will have the opportunity to grow alongside other developers of different seniority and provide guidance and technical mentorship to more junior developers. If you are a prestigeless person who’s in for a challenge and with a “can-do” mentality, you might be the one we’re looking for!
What you will be doing

You'll be using Node and React as your main tools along with Typescript, GraphQL and Postgres.
You will work on complex coding challenges, building new products and also features to our existing products.
You’ll be sharing knowledge, best practices and guidelines with the rest of the company, driving change and inspiring other's to do so as well.
You'll be working on a variety of components, from processing systems and communication gateways to our customer facing web and native apps.
Actively contribute to the system and product design - an open and curious mind is key.
You will be working in autonomous cross functional domains and be part of product and business decision making.

Who you are

You have great skills in JavaScript and have a clear preference for Node and React.
We believe you have at least 5 years of professional experience.
You can find the right balance between the perfect code and what is required at the time.
We’re building the foundations of something truly big, so it’s extra important that you write clean and readable code.
It is a plus if you have been working in the financial sector and have a degree in computer science.
You have an open mind and like people for what they are (yes, this belong in the formal requirements section)

We offer you the chance to be part of something truly amazing. With strong backers and a world class team there is no limit to what we can achieve together.
We promise that you will be challenged, pushed to develop your skill set and get the opportunity to work alongside amazing and smart colleagues.


While we've had a good run so far it is what lies ahead that excites everyone that works here, and we are just getting started. Then there is the compensation package, centrally located cozy office, extra time off on your birthday and a bunch of other benefits as well. But we will get to all that in due time.

For now begin your journey with us by clicking "Apply" below.

We cannot wait to meet you!

Join us as a senior fullstack developer, building the next generation grocery shopping experiences for our B2B customers, to do the best work of your career and make a profound impact.
If you want to shape the future of grocery shopping being part of a high-performance global team then please read on and apply.
Northfork is on the path to the company vision to make grocery shopping a hands off experience.
Northfork is a B2B SaaS company that works to accelerate our grocery retail customers online revenue by adding recipe shopping technology as a seamless experience independent of platforms; the retailer’s own or publisher partner’s.
The Northfork senior fullstack developer understands the customer needs and can translate them into World class technical solutions. You will be responsible for building a product that brings customer value. The role will be mainly programming but you will also lead application architecture and agile ceremonies. We’re entering an exciting phase where we will provide more of the end user, customer facing, experience. Hence we’re looking for someone with experience in both back- and front-end. Your innovative mindset will be key for us and so will your pragmatic approach be.
Working in the Tech team you will work closely with the teams within Sales, Marketing and with our customers. You will be involved in supporting our customers with implementing our product, as well as being a crucial part of our product development. We are passionate about making grocery shopping easy. Everyone at Northfork needs to obsess over how to make retailers build successful growth.
What you be responsible for
Developing the next generation grocery shopping products
Code reviews
Mob programming sessions
Mentorship for more inexperienced developers
Deliver features in sprints together with the rest of the Tech Team
Perform product demos to customers, prospects and internally
Work closely with Gastrofy.se, our R&D platform
Run beta and pilot programs with customers and prospects
Act as a leader within the company
Create, implement and improve product development processes

What you need to have in skills and requirements
+7 years of experience working as a developer
Demonstrated success developing and releasing world class products
Very experienced in Java
You also have experience in AWS, AWS Aurora, Git, PHP, SQL, javascript, MVC, Docker, React
Devops and very experienced in Linux
Good verbal and communication skills
Excellent teamwork skills
High levels of integrity, autonomy, and self-motivation
Creative, curious and take initiative
Team player and approach work with a can do attitude
Strong problem solving, communications and stakeholder management skills
Work efficiently in a fast-paced environment
You’re responsible for your work and you take accountability for it
Agile methodologies

What we bring to the table
A competitive salary in a central role of our organisation. You will be a crucial part of developing the Northfork product. You will be a part of a fast paced expansion and you will get to work, remote first, with a distributed tech team with highly skilled developers.
Reports to
The Northfork Fullstack developer will report to Jens Hansen, the Northfork VP of Tech.
Location
We value placement in Sweden where we have our development stronghold. The company however works with the principle remote first, however you should be in GMT+1 +-2h.

Engineering
We are looking for a collaborative Senior Fullstack Engineer to join our Backstage product teams focused on creating the best developer experience for Spotify, the open source and commercially.
Location
Stockholm or Remote EMEA
Job type
Permanent
The Backstage squads are functions within the Platform Developer Experience tribe aiming to a) deliver an open and thriving ecosystem trusted by millions of engineers, one where hundreds of companies collaborate to build the best developer experience in the world and b) lead Spotify into a new era of infrastructure based on an open foundation, bringing an industry leading developer experience. By joining us, you will help play an instrumental role in improving the experience of over 2000+ developers at Spotify as well as a growing open source community. Directly helping Spotify on our journey towards becoming one of the top tech companies in the world.
What you'll do
Work as part of a multi-functional team on Backstage across the whole development stack, solving problems at scale for both our internal and open source end users.
Build and operate infrastructure, toolset and deployment pipelines
Take operational responsibility for the services that are owned by your team, potentially including taking part in an on-call rotation
Work in an environment that supports your individual growth
Be a part of a multi-functional team, working closely with internal customers and our open-source community
Promote sound engineering practices, drive work on technical strategy and roadmaps
Advocate for unification of infrastructure, tools and languages where clients are similar in structure to lower the cost of ownership and increase the speed of the adopting teams
You’ll collaborate with other engineers, product managers, and designers to identify and solve challenging problems, creating an amazing engineering experience for our open-source community and internal Spotify engineering teams
Who you are
You enjoy working with React, TypeScript and Java and have a working knowledge of GraphQL and interacting with backend systems
You are experienced in building and implementing large-scale systems across various projects
You are interested in keeping up with current best practices in your areas of expertise
As a contributor, you have engaged with large scale open-source projects
You know and care about sound engineering practices like continuous delivery, defensive programming and automated testing
You’re familiar with designing and building distributed and scalable systems and enjoy seeing millions of users running your code
You have good understanding of data structures and algorithms, and understand how to apply them to design pragmatic solutions
Mentoring and supporting peers and engineering teams, fostering best engineering practices, is important to you
You have impact through your communication skills and love sharing your knowledge with others, helping them grow
Where you'll be
We are a distributed workforce enabling our band members to find a work mode that is best for them!
Where in the world? For this role, it can be within the EMEA region or East coast Americas in which we have a work locations and is within working hours. .
Prefer an office to work from home instead? Not a problem! We have plenty of options for your working preferences. Find more information about our Work From Anywhere options here
Our global benefits
Extensive learning opportunities, through our dedicated team, GreenHouse.
Flexible share incentives letting you choose how you share in our success.
Global parental leave, six months off - fully paid - for all new parents.
All The Feels, our employee assistance program and self-care hub.
Flexible public holidays, swap days off according to your values and beliefs.
Spotify On Tour, join your colleagues on trips to industry festivals and events.
Learn about life at Spotify
Spotify is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome at Spotify for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what’s playing in your headphones. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all thrive, contribute, and be forward-thinking! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our differences that we will find the power to keep revolutionising the way the world listens.
Spotify transformed music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the chance to enjoy and be passionate about these creators. Everything we do is driven by our love for music and podcasting. Today, we are the world’s most popular audio streaming subscription service with a community of more than 381 million users.

Vi söker en fullstack-utvecklare med stor passion för tech. Är du driven, initiativtagande och har en positiv problemlösande attityd? Hos oss på Interactive Solutions kommer du jobba med ett fantastiskt team, och tillsammans kommer vi bygga många roliga och utmanande projekt.
Vilka vi är
Interactive Solutions är ett produktionsbolag som bland annat utvecklar mobilappar, system och webbtjänster. Vi är idag ca 25 anställda med ett kontor vid Vaksala torg i Uppsala, cirka 500 meter från tågstationen/Resecentrum.


Vi tror på frihet och flexibilitet för våra anställda och uppmuntrar därför till att jobba från den plats där man mår bäst - oavsett om det är på kontoret, hemifrån eller stugan på landet.
Vår kundstock består av alltifrån mindre startup-bolag till större starka internationella varumärken. Detta innebär att du kan komma ha kontakt med partners och kunder i andra länder. Vi ser gärna att du är en problemlösare och orädd för att prata engelska.
Om tjänsten
Som utvecklare hos oss på Interactive kommer du få stora möjligheter att bidra med egna idéer och det är viktigt att du vill vara med och påverka och förstå slutanvändaren av produkterna för att på så sätt kunna skapa lösningar med hög användbarhet och god tillgänglighet. I rollen kommer du få ta ett stort ansvar och vara med och bygga långsiktiga och nyskapande lösningar.
Du kommer spela en viktig roll i produktionsteamet och kommer att jobba tillsammans med andra utvecklare, designers, produktägare, säljare och affärsutvecklare för att tillsammans hitta nya vägar att stärka kundens digitala närvaro och kvalitén i de produkter vi tar fram.
Vem är du?
Du är en positiv, framåtsträvande person som gillar att ta ansvar för de projekt du sitter i. Du har flera års erfarenhet i webbutveckling och har arbetat med agila kundprojekt tidigare.

Du uppskattar även att ta en ledande roll för tekniken inom projekt. För oss är det viktigt att du är en hjälpsam person som kan stötta teamet och utvecklas tillsammans med dina kollegor!
Vi tror att du:

Har goda kunskaper inom JavaScript, React, SCSS och REST.
Har goda kunskaper inom SQL (MySQL/PostgresSQL)
Har god kunskap inom Golang och/eller PHP.
Är strukturerad och gillar problemlösning.
Är genuint intresserad av ny teknik och håller dig uppdaterad om de senaste trenderna.

Vi jobbar med kunder och kollegor från runt om i världen och arbetar dagligen med lika delar svenska och engelska, så det är viktigt att du behärskar båda väl i tal och skrift.
Ett extra plus är om du har erfarenhet inom:

Cypress
GraphQL
React-native
TypeScript
CL/CI
.Net
Kubernetes / Nomad
CI/CD Pipelines
TDD/BDD
AWS / GCP
Pingis

Högskoleutbildning eller relevant utbildning är meriterande men inget krav.
Vårt team växer snabbt och vi söker därför hungriga medarbetare som med tiden kan ta sig an växande ansvar och vill vara med och forma vår verksamhet och företagskultur. Vi kommer därför lägga stort vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper och ditt intresse att utvecklas som både utvecklare och kollega.
Låter det som något för dig?
Vad roligt! Rollen är tillgänglig så länge annonsen finns ute och rekrytering sker löpande. Tveka inte att höra av dig!
Inte mitt i prick?
Vi är alltid nyfikna på nya sätt att skapa affärsnytta för våra kunder och tar löpande in ansökningar till roller inom allt från produktdesign och utveckling till sälj, marknad och backoffice.
Har du en passion för morgondagens innovationer och en idé om hur vi kan skapa magi tillsammans, men hittar inte helt rätt roll för dig? Tveka inte att höra av dig med en öppen ansökan istället!

Är du en senior utvecklare inom PHP och gillar IPA?
Ok, du måste inte gilla att dricka IPA, men om du har mångårig erfarenhet inom webbutveckling och skulle gilla att jobba i ett fullservice-team med utvecklare, kreatörer och marknadsförare mot flera olika kunder, så kan Dazy vara arbetsplatsen för dig.
Dazy är en fullservice digital kommunikationsbyrå som hjälper tillväxtbolag med sin digitala närvaro. Det innebär att vi arbetar med en bredd av lösningar och tillämpningar. Vi behöver nu ännu en erfaren utvecklare som trivs med variation i ett socialt gäng. I arbetet kan du tillhöra flera team med helt olika utmaningar och vi ser gärna att du är en person som kan tänka ut och presentera lösningar för olika tekniska behov.
Dina main skills:
PHP
Javascript & ramverk som Vue.js
Versionshantering med Git
Open source CMS inkl. WordPress
Serverhantering
Meriterande kunskaper:
Laravel
Symfony
Apputveckling med React Native
Docker & Kubernetes
Några personliga egenskaper:
Noggrann
Ansvarstagande
Pedagogisk
Du gillar IPA (ej krav)

På beanloop ser vi webb-/systemutveckling som ett hantverk vi är väldigt stolta över. Vi är ett litet nischat bolag som lägger stor vikt vid att tillsammans ha kul, utvecklas och utmanas i vår yrkesroll. För att lyckas med det lägger vi stor vikt vid välmående och en hälsosam balans mellan jobb och fritid. Förutom en god sammanhållning och schyssta kollegor får du en riktigt bra lön och ett fint förmånspaket samt möjlighet till delägarskap. Vi har långsiktiga kunder och en god ekonomi, och just nu är vi i en tillväxtresa där du kan vara med och påverka allt ifrån teknikval till bolagsstrategi.*På Beanloop har vi både produktutveckling och konsultverksamhet. Vi jobbar mycket med React.js, React Native, TypeScript, GraphQL, Node.js, Kubernetes, Serverless och AWS. Har du erfarenheter inom den stacken är det bra, men absolut inte det viktigaste. Vi ser likväl fördelar i att du kommer in med andra erfarenheter och en del annan kompetens.Vi söker utvecklare med mer än tre års erfarenhet till Stockholm, remote i hela Sverige samt till Kalmar.Hör av dig så tar vi en fika/lunch för att prata om ifall vi kan vara arbetsplatsen där du tar nästa steg i din karriär.***Jobbtyp: Heltid, TillsvidareLön: 60 000,00kr - 70 000,00kr per månadFörmåner:AktiesparprogramBostadExtra semesterdagarFlextidFriskvårdsbidragGratis massageGymkortHälsokontrollerJobba hemifrånLivförsäkringPrivat sjukvårdsförsäkringTjänstemobilTjänstepensionUtbildningVinstdelningSchema:Måndag till fredagCovid-19:Vi är nu tillbaka till kontoret om man vill. Går lika bra att jobba hemifrån om man trivs bättre med det.Sista ansökningsdatum: 2022-03-31

Welcome! This is Billogram and we’re into digital invoicing. Why? Because traditional invoicing is lame. It’s basically anxiety on a paper, filled with apprehension (did I pay my invoices? Did our customer get their invoice?) and when done wrong it can waste so much time and energy. Time and energy that both sender and recipient could spend doing something else.
   It’s not the easiest thing to solve – we want both sender and recipient to have the best experience possible but since their interests don’t always align it’s up to us to come up with smart solutions to satisfy both parties. And to do that we need you to join our team of integration developers.
   As a Senior Integration Developer, you will work closely with the Customer Delivery Manager and take our customers (the invoice senders) through the onboarding process; getting the customer from sign to live as efficiently as possible. This is where we match their processes and current information architecture to our service to ensure the best and most seamless fit within the customer’s workflow.
   This means that you need to be able to understand and contextualize the customer’s workflow, comprehend how we can provide the most value through our product and integration. It means being creative, communicative, and empathic as well as being a good programmer. As a Senior Integration Developer, we’d like you to be familiar with the entire stack from database to frontend but you’re most comfortable with backend. You have +5 years of professional experience in software development, and hopefully, you might have come across some of the techniques that we are using in the past. A few examples of our tech stack includes:
  
   Python
   React.js
   DynamoDB
   MySQL 
   AWS
  
   We’d like you to contribute to our technical and product development process by taking our integration solution to new heights. We also believe that you thrive in an environment where you can use your technical knowledge to help your teammates to grow through discussions and mentorship. 
  Billogram is currently a team close to 150, but aiming for quite some growth during the rest of this year and onwards. That means you’ll be joining at a time of change and your perspective will help shape what that change results in. You’ll join a team of truly dedicated and helpful co-workers at a super cozy office as central as you get in Stockholm. There will be lots of challenges and lots of laughs. 
  Billogram is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified individuals will receive consideration for employment regardless of gender, transgender identity or expression, ethnicity, religion or other beliefs, disability, sexual orientation or age.
   What are you waiting for? 
  Hit that button

Job ID: 4219
IAM, JAVA, BI, Software Architecture

Would you like to work with Nordea's Cyber-Security setup that is central to access related governance? We are now looking for an Senior Java Developer in Identity & Access Management (IAM) to join Nordea’s IAM Access Solutions Development team, where you will enter a team of other Developers and Engineers, focusing on delivering new functionality for the changing demands of the leading bank in the Nordics.

At Nordea, we know our customers’ needs are changing – and we’re deeply committed to meeting them with the financial solutions of tomorrow. We’re creating an agile environment where we’re harnessing the power of technology – one where you can make an impact. So bring your skills, ideas and unique background. With us, you’ll find plenty of opportunities to grow and make your mark on something bigger.

About this opportunity

Welcome to the IAM Access Solutions Development team. We add value by delivering functionality to support the increasing security demands of Nordea as well as underpin the operational and service delivery units of IAM. As an Expert Java Developer in Identity & Access Management, you will play a valuable role in maturing our IAM tools, both on the front-end and integrating with existing bank systems on the back-end. You will be consulted in architectural considerations and will be expected to contribute to the system design and development.

What you will be doing:

Identifying new possibilities and performing complex application programming activities to improve the IAM processes within own area
Proactively identifying any bridge gaps between IAM goals and technical capabilities
Collaborating with Stakeholder Management and IAM Architecture to drive the technical vision to ensure high quality deliverables

We're a company called Elk. A team of music lovers, ranging from violin makers and python magicians to computer PhDs and record label managers. We're based in Stockholm, but most of us work from wherever we are.
At the core of what we do is an OS for Audio called Elk Audio OS which is the fastest audio OS on the planet. On top of this, we've built an ecosystem for musicians called Elk LIVE. Elk LIVE enables musicians to play live and in sync together over the world wide web.
We're so happy for what it enables - more spontaneous musical moments, less need for traveling, and infinite studio space for the next generation of musicians. The Elk Audio OS is on the fast track to becoming the modern standard for how music hardware and software are put to use. And for that, we need your help.
About the role
Do you want to be part of the next big thing in the music industry? We're in need of a talented Senior Javascript / React developer who will play a fundamental role in upgrading a fantastic Web GUI for our upcoming music service Elk LIVE. As always, you need to be a team player that knows how to work independently. You need to be creative, knowledgeable and you absolutely need to love music.
What you'll be doing

Take the lead in moving Elk LIVE Web GUI to the next level
Work independently, but at the same time interact closely with other team members working on various aspects of the system (embedded, cloud, real-time networking, DSP)

Skill & Requirements

Strong programming skills
2+ years of industrial experience working in a team
Strong Javascript experience (ES6+)
Real-world experience with React frameworks
Basic Python knowledge

Good to have

Experience with some non-REST protocols, e.g. WebSockets, sockets.io, JSON-RPC, gRPC
Experience with video chat frameworks (Amazon Chimes, Twilio, etc.) and WebRTC
Domain knowledge of audio applications
Experience working with Embedded Linux devices
If you have played in a band, produced beats in your bedroom or anything related to music, that's a big plus.

Skills:
Java
What you can expect from us:
Utveckla din karriär hos oss.

Det är en extraordinär tid i vår bransch. Den digitala transformationen accelererar och CGI är i centrum för förändringarna – som hjälp för våra kunders digitala resor och med spännande karriärmöjligheter för våra medarbetare.

På CGI når vi framgång genom våra medarbetares talang och engagemang. Som ett team delar vi de utmaningar och belöningar som kommer genom att vi skapar ett växande företag, vilket stärker vår ägarskapskultur. Alla våra medarbetare drar nytta av det värde vi gemensamt skapar.

Var med och bygg ett av världens största oberoende tjänsteföretag inom IT och affärsprocesser.

Columbus och vårt affärsområde Data & Analytics står inför en mycket spännande tillväxtresa som vi hoppas att du vill vara en del av. Vi söker nu fler seniora BI-konsulter som kan ta lead i våra kundprojekt där många av våra projekt ligger i teknisk framkant. 
  Arbetsuppgifter
   Vi erbjuder en roll med stora möjligheter att växa med oss. Gillar du att ta initiativ och vara med och påverka? Bra! Då kommer du trivas som fisken i vattnet. 
  I rollen som senior BI-konsult kommer du förutom att arbeta med BI bekanta dig med en rad olika tekniker. Du kommer att vara delaktig i hela processen - från initial dialog med kunden och framtagning av kravspecifikationer och design, till implementering. 
  Här berättar Paul om sin roll som BI-konsult och varför han valt att jobba just hos oss: 
  "På Columbus finns en stor kundflora – vilket ger en bred och intressant inblick i olika typer av projekt och kunder från olika branscher. Det som skiljer oss från andra bolag, utöver att vi också har en egen ERP-leverans, är att vi levererar projekt och inte resurskonsulter. 
  Det finns möjlighet att påverka och förändra både i projekten och i teamet. Jag får ett stort förtroende hos våra kunder och inom organisationen och får under ett projekts gång vara involverad i flera olika processer och roller. 
  Jag har en stor möjlighet att påverka vart teamet ska och det finns en möjlighet för mig att utvecklas inom de områden jag tycker är intressanta! För den som vill finns möjligheten att kontinuerligt utmanas och utvecklas. 
  Idag jobbar jag mer på en konceptuell nivå än i tidigare roller och det är inte ovanligt att delta i strategi och arkitekturmöten på ledningsgruppsnivå med kundverksamheten. 
  Jag samarbetar mycket med våra ERP-konsulter i andra affärsområden och är inte sällan en deltagare i ERP-implementeringar som en representant för BI och data management. Jag jobbar även en hel del med kollegor i andra länder – på Columbus har vi ett internationellt nätverk med över 100 BI-konsulter som man kan söka inspiration från eller plocka kompetenser till ett projekt. 
  En vanlig vecka pratar jag med prospekts, jobbar med krav och arkitektur, scopar ett projekt och utvecklar lösningar. Vi har hela tiden löpande samtal och jobbar enligt Scrum." 
  Kravprofil 
  Vi värdesätter både tekniskt kunnande och god samarbetsförmåga. Ett intresse för att effektivisera och digitalisera verksamheter är något både vi och våra kunder uppskattar och har du andra intressanta erfarenheter hör vi gärna om dem! 
  
   Du har flera års erfarenhet av BI-lösningar, exempelvis från Microsoft, Google, Infor 
   Du har också erfarenhet av att leverera rapporter, analyser och dashboard med hjälp av olika front end-verktyg, exempelvis Power BI, Qlik, Birst, Tableau 
   Du har naturligtvis kunskap i SQL och vi ser även att du har erfarenhet av DB/DW-modellering och att implementera ETL-processer 
   Vi förutsätter att du behärskar svenska och engelska, i tal och skrift 
  
  Vad vi kan erbjuda 
  Columbus är ledande i Norden inom Dynamics 365, M3 samt E-Commerce lösningar och du kommer att arbeta med spännande projekt hos flera nya kunder, oftast med den senaste tekniken. Våra kunder är främst verksamma inom produktion, tillverkning och distribution vilket ofta ger oss komplexa och intressanta projekt som bidrar till vår utveckling. Vi har en skön teamkänsla på jobbet, en platt organisation och vi arbetar oftast i gemensamma projekt tillsammans. Vi tror på att hela tiden utveckla oss själva - och därigenom våra kunder. Rollen innebär en stor del frihet under ansvar och det finns möjlighet att arbeta på distans.
   Om Columbus 
  Columbus är ett IT-konsultbolag med fler än 2200 medarbetare runt om i världen. Det vi gör allra bäst är utveckling, implementering och underhåll av digitala affärslösningar. Vår uppgift är att guida kunder i deras digitala transformation så att deras företag kan fortsätta att vara framgångsrikt en lång tid framöver. De senaste dryga 30 åren har över 4000 kunder anlitat oss. Det går bra, helt enkelt. Om du frågar oss är hemligheten att vi sitter på ett stort utbud av tekniska lösningar, djup branschkunskap, omfattande teknisk expertis och en rejäl dos kundförståelse. Våra medarbetare är engagerade i sitt arbete och företaget präglas av en stark entreprenörsanda. Detta tack vare de möjligheter som faktiskt finns att vara med och påverka både vår egen och våra kunders verksamhet. Nu behöver vi bli fler och vill ha dig med på färden!
   Jobba på Columbus
   Spana in vårt Insta-flöde för att få en bild av hur det är att jobba hos oss genom våra kollegor. Klicka på bilden för att komma till Instagram-kontot.
   Helt ofiltrerat har vi samlat in omdömen från nuvarande och tidigare kollegor. Klicka nedan för att läsa mer.

column1: Senior mjukvaruutvecklare som vill göra skillnad för vårt...
column4:
Vi söker en senior mjukvaruutvecklare som trivs med allt från inbyggda system till appar och webb. Störst fokus för denna tjänst är mot webb och .net för våra webbaserade användargränssnitt. Är du fascinerad av IoT och drömmer om att göra något åt klimatproblematiken med smarta lösningar?
Vem är vi?
Vi är ett entreprenörsdrivet och familjeägt företag. Från vårt huvudkontor i Lund utvecklar vi med hjälp av den senaste tekniken intelligenta, klimatsmarta lösningar för energieffektiva byggnader. Vårt produktsortiment sträcker sig från hårdvara och mjukvara för inneklimat, belysning, solskydd till användargränssnitt i form av webb och appar. Allt för att skapa energieffektiva innemiljöer i kommersiella fastigheter, skolor, sjukhus och labb. Vi har över 2000 referensobjekt vi är väldigt stolta över t.ex. huvudkontoren för SEB, Telia och Swedbank.
Dessutom har vi belönats med Stora innekmatpriset, Stora energipriset och Årets företagare i Lund.
Våra produkter
Vi utvecklar världsledande produkter inom behovsstyrt inneklimat och fastighetsautomation. Detta med olika sensor, kommunikation med CAN, Modbus TCP, TCP/IP, DALI samt trådlösa teknologier som Enocean och Bluetooth. Utveckling av firmware för ARM-processorer, backend-applikationer i .net för optimering, detta med marknadsledande webbgränssnitt för fastigheter som spetsas med API:er, appar och mycket mer.
Teamet
Lindinvent består av allt från produktion till service med totalt 95 personer på fem orter varav 13 personer på utvecklingsavdelningen. Du kommer att ingå i ett starkt team bestående av engagerade och uppfinningsrika utvecklare som drivs av att paralellt lösa avancerade problem inom många olika teknikområden. Hos oss har du stor frihet och utrymme att testa nya kreativa idéer som kan leda till smarta lösningar på kort tid.
I utvecklingsteamet gör man ofta efterforskningar på ny teknologi inom helt andra områden som sedan kan appliceras i de egna lösningarna i syftet att erbjuda kunderna så intelligenta och effektiva system som möjligt. Teamet arbetar mycket självständigt med nya produkter och lösningar dvs. från systemdesign och prototyp till implementation. Detta ger oss en utvecklingsmiljö som präglas av korta beslutsvägar och stor personlig frihet.
Profil
För att passa in hos oss bör du vara en person som trivs med att ta mycket ansvar, ta egna initiativ, har stor kreativitet och får saker gjorda. Det kan vara en fördel om du arbetat i mindre bolag där man inte alltid har 100% klara specifikationer och det kan råda lite ”produktivt kaos”. Vi tror att du är en pragmatisk generalist som med lätthet navigerar ibland de senaste nyheterna inom mjukvaruutveckling och känner dig bekväm med att sätta dig in i nya ramverk och de språk som krävs för uppgiften. Har du erfarenhet av att arbeta med säkerhet i dessa frågor så ser vi det som positivt.
Man bör ha erfarenhet av följande begrepp:
.NET C (Core/6.0)
ASP.NET
React
Javascript
Typescript
IPC/RPC
Cloud
Containers
Relationsdatabaser
NoSQL
Xamarin
Enhetstestning
AI/ML
Låter detta som en spännande vardag för dig? Tveka då inte att skicka in din ansökan redan idag eftersom löpande urval sker. Har du fler frågor om rollen? Hör av dig så berättar vi gärna mer!

Omgående

Kambi's Engineering Operations team supports the infrastructure of the entire organization and ensures a stable environment, so that Kambi’s business can deliver twenty-four seven, year-round. We are dedicated to agile operations, believe dev-ops and automation is a great way of achieving that and use agile methodologies to support our efforts along the road.

As a part of the network team you will be responsible for Kambi’s network infrastructure on a global scale, there will be plenty of problem solving and room to learn. To fit our team, we believe you should thrive in a fast-paced environment where everyone is free to speak their mind and a good solution is prioritized over prestige.

This is what you will do:

Design, build and maintain on-prem infrastructure for our data centers and offices around the globe
Work to deliver reliable, scalable and highly available solutions and systems
Plan capacity together with the team and architects
Support other teams and our operators from network and traffic perspective
Create and improve the automation that our environment runs on (we mainly use Puppet)
Be operationally responsible for our infrastructure, including taking part in third line stand-by rotation

You'd like to work with these technologies:

Networking (dynamic routing, datacenter switching, site-to-site VPNs, and security)
Load balancers (nginx)
System monitoring and alerting
Network infrastructure on a global scale
Automation engines (Puppet, Ansible)

You can relate yourself to this if you:

Have an extensive background in Networking
Have experience with load balancing, routing, firewalls, VPNs
Have experience with infrastructure automation (including writing modules or playbooks)
Have experience working with transaction heavy systems
Enjoy working in a team while having a great sense of ownership
Are interested in open-source systems and open networking
Think code & automation is the right way to evolve infrastructure

If you want to be part of a dedicated Infrastructure team in central Stockholm, please apply with you CV and cover letter.

#wearekambi
About Kambi

Kambi Group plc is a leading B2B provider of premium sports betting services to licensed gaming operators. Our services provide an end-to-end solution for operators wanting to launch a standalone Sportsbook or bolster their existing offering with an innovative sports betting product. From front-end user interface to customer intelligence, risk management and odds compiling, all built on our in-house developed software, we strive to deliver the ultimate service and solution to our partners.

Proactive
A decision-maker – daring to make decisions together with the organization
Motivating others, and enable good cooperation

Goal-oriented
Lacking prestige

We are now working with a market leading product development company who work within the freelance industry. They help both companies and consultants to manage time sheets, payroll and consultant assignment matching. They make the process of freelancing easier for both client and consultant by developing efficient and easy to use SaaS platforms which are all entirely based on Cloud and integrated into multiple different environments.
Each service has its own SaaS platform which does something different. One service is time sheet services to help consultants to efficiently log their time sheets to their clients. This platform logs all time and evaluates how much a consultant is invoicing and then allowed the company to view and monitor these time sheets in an easy way.
Another service is payroll and helping companies and consultants to correctly manage their payments. From a freelance perspective it means the consultant knows exactly what they are being paid and allows the companies to easily figure out how much they are paying their consultants.
Lastly their is a service aimed at helping match consultants to assignments. Companies can log their requirements on the platform from tech to the aim of a project and this will then match with available consultants who are able and skilled to work on that assignment making the entire process much more efficient and beneficial to both parties.
With growing demand for their services the company are now in a phase of growth and looking expand their development teams over the next 6 months. AstraZeneca are looking for a Senior Software Engineer - Early Science to help build and enhance our next generation Drug Discovery platform!
AstraZeneca is investing heavily in our Augmented Drug Design-Make-Test and analyse platforms as we seek to deliver better, differentiated Candidate Drugs into trials, faster, for greater patient benefit. We have made great strides in creating the AI and ML toolsets that will pave the way for this transformation and platforms supporting new therapeutic modalities. The next part of this journey will involve firming up our existing toolsets and building the applications that will enable us to maximise the value of our new technologies in bringing small molecule and other therapeutic modalities (e.g. peptides, oligonucleotides and conjugates) through the pipeline.
In Early Science, we have highly skilled scientists generating ideas and performing experiments in the support of complex drug discovery projects. Our environment is driven by scientific and technical innovation with a high degree of diversity in workflows, data, vendor solutions and in-house builds.
What you'll do
Working alongside Software and Data Engineers, Architects, Analysts and other IT and science partners, you will devise technical solutions, estimate, and deliver high value returns in our DevOps teams to some of the most challenging issues slowing down innovation. You will use your technical acuity to troubleshoot and provide innovative solutions to ensure smooth experiences for our users, as well as make recommendations with peers on how we can move forward.
Your work will have a direct impact on the science we do, and you have an opportunity to enable our scientists to undertake science not possible today.
You will:
In this role you will join a globally distributed team of software engineers, support engineers and cheminformaticians in our A-DMTA platform. You will be responsible for designing and implementing software and data solutions to make our science easier to do, easier to learn from, and offer faster delivery and higher quality across all therapeutic areas.
Working with innovative technology stack in cloud environment
Design and build novel products and features to address long-standing problems in drug discovery with a focus on producing amazing user experiences that are more than the sum of their parts.
Collaborate with product, design, data science, and our scientific teams to build pioneering experiences and services
Propose and implement changes to our data models, core architecture, and codebase
Develop all levels of the technical stack even if you are more experienced in some layers
Advocate and advance modern, agile software development practices and help develop and evangelize a vibrant software engineering culture
Support more less experienced software engineers mentoring, feedback and hands-on career development
Collaborate in the transformation of an estate of siloed systems into an ecosystem that delivers great user experiences
Plan, implement and support core infrastructure with an overall objective to improve the scalability, reliability, performance, and availability
Advocate for rigorous engineering practices and discipline: code reviews, automated testing, logging, monitoring, alerting, etc.
Requirements
This role needs senior level technical skills. You are passionate to stay on top of tech trends, experiment with and learn modern technologies, participate in internal & external technology communities, and mentor other members of the engineering community.
We also see that you have:
Proficiency in JavaScript frameworks like React, Angular, Node.js developing single page application
Extensive experience in programming languages like Python or Java with the willingness and ability to quickly ramp up on new ones as the need arises
Extensive experience in at least one major web development framework like Express, Django, Spring, and beyond
Extensive experience in defining overall API architecture, API implementations, integration and deployment.
Experience in cloud services, preferably AWS
Experience in asynchronous messaging and microservice architecture
Experience in container and serverless architecture (Docker, Kubernetes etc.)
Experience in Linux environments
Experience with GitFlow and/or GitLab flow
Understanding and experience in backend Databases (RDBMS, NoSQL, GraphDB) and their AWS Cloud counterparts (RDS, Aurora, Neptune, etc.)
Understanding with DevOps, Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery (Jenkins, Argo etc.)
Experienced in Agile methodologies (Kanban and SCRUM)
Excellent verbal and written communication skills, interpersonal skills, collaborative skills, and cross-functional interface skills
