  Som systemutvecklare på Sileo Kapital kommer du att tillhöra teamet som har ansvar för affärssystem, applikationer och integrationer. Teamet består i dag av 7 personer med olika kompetenser inom IT och kredithanteringsbranschen. 
  I din roll kommer du att jobba med utveckling och förvaltning av applikationer och stödsystem som integrerar mot vårt affärssystem. Du kommer således vara en affärskritisk pusselbit i vår verksamhet.
   Det handlar bland annat om ”Mina Sidor”-lösningar där våra kunder själva kan hantera sin ärenden, monitoreringssystem som bevakar vår miljö, med mera.
   Helst bygger vi med:
   Python
   Django
   React
   SQL Server
   Alla applikationer är containeriserade med Docker och deployas genom vårt CI/CD-system.
   Tjänsten är en heltidstjänst med start enligt överenskommelse. 
  
   
  Vem är du?
   Du har Universitets-/högskoleutbildning eller YH-utbildning inom lämpligt område eller motsvarande arbetslivserfarenhet. Du har ett par års arbetslivserfarenhet inom systemutveckling. 
  För att trivas hos oss tror vi att du är en kreativ problemlösare som gärna samarbetar med dina kollegor för att hitta de bästa lösningarna. 
  Du är intresserad av ny teknik och har ett driv att lära dig det senaste inom ditt område. 
  Du behöver ha goda kunskaper i något programmeringsspråk och bra koll på hur relationsdatabaser fungerar. Extra meriterande är det om du behärskar något av de språk/ramverk som vi använder.
  
   Vad vi erbjuder
   Varierande arbetsuppgifter där du får arbeta med hela stacken, från databas till frontend.
   Agil arbetsmetodik, där du tillsammans med teamet kommer att planera, estimera och exekvera med korta feedbackloopar.
   Vi jobbar aktivt med kompetensutveckling, där vi tillsammans kartlägger dina styrkor och svagheter och skapar en plan för hur du ska nå din fulla potential.
   Flexibel arbetsplats, där vi kombinerar kontorsarbete med arbete hemifrån.
  
   Om oss
   Sileo Kapital, med kontor vid Lilla Bommen i centrala Göteborg, är ett kredithanteringsbolag som ingår i den norska börsnoterade koncernen B2Holding ASA. Vi startade 2012 och består idag av drygt sextio engagerade medarbetare som tillsammans arbetar för att hjälpa skuldsatta individer tillbaka till en bättre ekonomisk tillvaro. Vår kultur präglas av omtänksamhet, prestigelöshet och en experimentlusta där vi hela tiden söker efter nya sätt att arbeta och utveckla verksamheten. Vi tror stenhårt på devisen "laget för jaget" och söker efter kollegor som både vill utvecklas i sin yrkesroll och vara med och bygga ett fantastiskt företag.

On our path to becoming the world's favorite way to shop, we’re assembling an unparalleled global talent network, accelerating individual careers, and disrupting entire industries. We are on a mission to liberate humanity from all the meaningless time spent managing their purchases and finances, so they can do more of what they love. We’re in search of global talent eager to embrace a hypergrowth atmosphere and defy their own expectations.
Engineering at Klarna is an inspired, customer focused community, dedicated to crafting solutions that redefine our industry. Working in small, highly collaborative Agile teams, you and your team will have a clear mission and ownership of an important outcome that supports Klarna and our customers. At Klarna we optimise for quality, flow, fast feedback, focussing on end-to-end ownership, continuous improvement, testing, monitoring and experimentation. We aim for teams that are inclusive, helpful, and have a strong sense of ownership for the things they build.
Our engineers make some of the most significant decisions for the company and we are looking for bold, open and curious developers. As a Klarnaut, you’ll be inspired to contribute to the growth of Europe’s most highly valued fintech and your work will reach millions of users.
Want to be part of the change? We're expanding several of our engineering teams, including; teams working on our core checkout product, payment services, fraud prevention, or improving our billing service and shipping credentials to name a few.
What you’ll get to do;
As an engineer experienced in Site Reliability Engineering practices you will be the enabler and multiplier.
Working in a small, highly collaborative Agile team, you will build solutions and mechanisms that the development teams use to own their product end-to-end.
You will allow them to build, maintain and deprecate the products that they are responsible for smoothly and with minimum friction.
You will educate the development teams on the do’s and don’ts of building and make sure that they can easily maintain what they built.
Some of the technologies you’ll get to work with;
Docker
Jenkins
AWS
Javascript / Typescript
Node.js
React/React Native
Redux
Express.js
You should have;
Deep practical knowledge of SRE topics
Continuous drive for scaling both software and processes
High judgement to make the right trade-offs for the customers and the business
BS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience
Strong coding ability in Javascript and/or other high-level programming languages
Passion for system thinking and building clean, scalable and robust systems
Passion for writing clean and testable codePractical application of Agile/XP practices (Pairing, TDD/BDD, Continuous Integration, Continuous Delivery)Willingness to learn new technologies and move between different tech stacks
What we can offer you
Culture - You'll have an opportunity to work with talented people from 90+ different countries in our offices in Stockholm city center.
Learning - We have a learning and development focused environment with an emphasis on knowledge sharing, training, and regular internal technical talks.
Compensation - You’ll receive an attractive salary, pension, and insurance plans, plus we offer all of our employees an opportunity to invest in a RSU program and own a stake of the company. You’ll also receive 30 days annual leave and since we recognise that life is about more than work, we also offer benefits for gym memberships, marathons, and all sorts of activities that promote physical health. We also have generous parental leave (for men and women).
Relocation - We can offer relocation support to Stockholm.
We know diverse teams are strong teams, so we welcome those with alternative identities, backgrounds, and experiences. Our teams include women, men, mothers, fathers, the self-taught, the college-educated, and people from all over the world.
We also believe in contributing back to the open source community. You can find some of our work here https://github.com/klarna.
How to apply: please send us your CV or LinkedIn profile in English
What we offer:
Diversity & Community
With our diversity of skills, perspectives and backgrounds, we can create, innovate, and disrupt like no other. Diversity is part of who we are, and essential to our success.
Ownership & Impact
Here, every voice matters. We’re organized into hundreds of small teams, each run like a start-up, focused on their own problem-space.

Trust & Collaboration
Successes and failures are won together at Klarna in a melting pot of teams. Win, lose, and learn, we’re on this path together.
The Klarna Work Policy is designed to make sure we foster team collaboration while also ensuring a productive and flexible work environment. We work 2 days per week in the office on agreed days, and then 3 flexible days. We’re also providing each Klarnaut with an annual financial contribution to improve their flexible work life whether they use it to upgrade their work accessories, or their home office space!
Challenges & Rewards
We take a very Swedish approach to benefits. Support for parents, health and wellness perks—we’ve got you covered.

About Klarna
Since 2005 Klarna has been on a mission to revolutionize the retail banking industry. With over 90 million global active users and 2 million transactions per day, Klarna is meeting the changing demands of consumers by helping them save time and money while better managing their cashflow and making informed decisions. Over 250,000 global retail partners, including H&M, Saks, Sephora, Macys, IKEA, Expedia Group, and Nike have integrated Klarna's innovative technology to deliver a seamless shopping experience online and in-store. With over 5,000 employees, Klarna is active in 20 markets and is one of the most highly-valued private fintechs globally, with a valuation of $45.6 billion. For more information, visit Klarna.com
It is our commitment that every qualified person will be evaluated according to skills regardless of age, gender, identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability status or religion. Please refrain from including your picture and age with the application.

column1: Site Reliability Engineer Lead to PostNord
column4:
job description. 
  
   
    Do you want to be part of an exciting growth journey and collaborate with our product teams to identify and plan improvement opportunities to the system design from a reliability perspective? Would you like to identify required enablers in product and platforms to achieve improved reliability and work with the product team to agree on work activities needed? If yes - this position as a Site Reliability Engineer Lead at PostNord is something for you! 
   
  
  qualifications. 
  
   
    To fit in this position you have an academic degree in systems engineering, or equivalent knowledge and skills acquired through work experience and continuing professional education. We think that you have good analytical skills and good leadership qualities. In this position you need to be self motivated and capable of proactively identifying, planning and organizing work activities and also an ability in coaching developers and other technical competencies. 
     
     You have proven ability to independently capture and share information through formal written documentation in English and a local language. 
     
     We hope to see that you want to develop in the long term at PostNord where we can give you good development opportunities and a chance to influence PostNord`s IT-future! 
     
     
    Requirement: 
   
   
    Senior level expertise in: 
    Software development 
    Database management systems and SQL 
    Containerization with orchestration platforms e.g. OpenShift, Kubernetes, Docker swarm 
    Integrations though event streaming and integration platforms like: 
    KAFKA 
    Java 
    Cloud (Azure/AWS) 
   - Infrastructure automation, unix scripting, cloud scripting languages - Terraform or/and Ansibel 
    
   
    Observability platforms and technology layers e.g. Op5, ELK, etc. 
    Proven experience in developing production-grade, performant, scalable and durable applications 
    Experience at all levels of the technology stack, i.e. Infrastructure, Database, API, components and front-end 
    Hands on experience of managing complex, high-volume applications/components in production critical environments 
    Experience of performance tuning techniques, stability patterns and scalability approaches 
    Experience of fact-based, data-driven problem solving and communication. 
    Understanding of automated testing and tools 
    Experience with continuous integration and continuous delivery 
   
    
   Meritorious: 
    
    
   
    Previous work experience of Site Reliability Engineering 
   
  
  responsibilities. 
  
   
    In this position you will work closely with the product team and identify, establish, and uphold appropriate system Service Level Objectives (SLOs) together with the team and implement the use of error budgets along with policies/consequences for deviating from them. You will play an important role and ensure observability and monitoring of relevant systems. Provide guidelines and educate the product teams on observability practices/standards around metrics, logs and traces so that both proactive and reactive measurements are taken. You will also proactively seek out system weaknesses and find ways to fix them before they cause production issues using monitoring data, watching trends, and using Chaos Engineering. You have a big impact and will be responsible for adapting automated solutions and tools to help debug and resolve problems in production and prevent them from reoccurring. You will work in a broad role and move among different contact surfaces and lead blameless post-mortems for incidents together with different product teams and vendors. 
   
  
  application. 
  
   
    We offer you: 
     
     
    
     Work in a Nordic and dynamic environment. 
     Wellness allowance & access to the office´s gym and health center (Solna). 
     Employee benefits through PostNord’s own personnel foundation PostNord Plus. 
     Great occupational pension terms. 
     Great development opportunities and a continuous learning culture. 
     Employment in Solna. 
    
     
    Welcome with your application! 
     
     Selection is ongoing and we want your application as soon as possible. In this recruitment, we collaborate with Randstad Technologies, for questions about the role contact responsible recruitment consultant Julia Rhönnstad, 0729872754, julia.rhonnstad@randstad.se or Akim Kraft, 0707232565, akim.kraft@randstad.se 
   
  
  about PostNord Group AB. 
  
   We make everyday life easier! 
    
    PostNord is the leading supplier of communication and logistics solutions to, from, and within the Nordic region. We ensure the provision of a postal service to households and businesses in Sweden and Denmark. We aim to make everyday life easier and more sustainable for everyone who lives and works in the Nordic region. 
    
    We are accountable, brave and committed, effectively leading change regardless if we lead our self or others. We emphasize teamwork, sincerity and positive relationships in the workplace. We build on our success and learn from both colleagues and mistakes. People with different backgrounds work with us. You will therefore be part of a workplace with great diversity, which contributes to better results for the business. Visit us at www.postnord.com 
  
  https://www.postnord.com

column1: Site Reliability Engineer with experience of performance...
column4:
About the assignment:
Location: Stockholm
Duration: 5 months
Start: TBD
Apply: as soon as possible
Extent: 100%
Please note that the mandatory requirements have to be met in full in order for us to present your profile to our Customer.
Description
The client is now looking for a Site Reliability Engineer.
Main responsibilities, activities and duties:
Thoroughly analyse assigned systems and supported business to understand design and functionality in relation to stakeholder needs.
Identify, establish, and uphold appropriate system Service Level Objectives (SLOs) together with the team and implement the use of error budgets along with policies/consequences for deviating from them.
Ensure observability and monitoring of relevant systems. Provide guidelines and educate the product teams on observability practices/standards around metrics, logs and traces.
Proactively seek out system weaknesses and find ways to fix them before they cause production issues using monitoring data, watching trends, and using Chaos Engineering.
Build automated solutions and tools to help debug and resolve problems in production and prevent them from reoccurring.
Lead blameless post-mortems for incidents together with different product teams and vendors.
Be part of on-call rotations to ensure SLOs are met, with the goal of eliminating the need for support outside of office hours.

Mandatory competence and experience:
 Academic degree in systems development, or equivalent knowledge and skills acquired through work experience and continuing professional education.
Senior level expertise in:
Software development.
Database management systems and SQL.
Containerization with OpenShift/Kubernetes.
Integration though KAFKA and message queues.
Java
Cloud (Azure/AWS)
Proven experience in developing production-grade, performant, scalable and durable applications.
Experience at all levels of the technology stack, i.e. Infrastructure, Database, API, components and front-end.
Hands on experience of managing complex, high-volume applications/components in production critical environments.
Experience of performance tuning techniques, stability patterns and scalability approaches.
Experience of fact-based, data-driven problem solving and communication.
Fluent in English and Swedish, both spoken and written.

Preferred competence and experience:
Excellent analytical skills.
Good leadership qualities.
Excellent in planning and working in a very structured way.
Proven ability to independently capture and share information through formal written documentation in English and local language.
Previous work experience of Site Reliability Engineering is meritorious.
Other qualitications:
Process oriented mind-set and a strong ability to follow and apply and methods to secure cross functional efficiency and collaboration.
 _______________________
How to proceed with the process
Apply for the assignment through this ad.
State your preferred hourly rate in the application.
Upload your CV in word format.
We will revert to you if we need further information or clarification regarding your application.
The Customer usually reverts to us within 10 working days from the last application date. We aim to get back to you promptly with any new information regarding your application or the assignment. If you have not received any information from us within this time frame, please contact us through our platform.
You will be informed about the Customer should you be called to an interview.
About Shaya Solutions
Stockholm based consultancy and competence firm with focused on IT, Management and Technology.
We focus on customer / consultant satisfaction and quality in our services offered throughout Sweden.
Our core values are Humility, Perseverance and Flexibility.
Please do not hesitate to contact us if you have any questions.
We politely decline all contact from ad vendors. Many thanks!

Sveriges vackraste arbetsplats söker flera
   
   
  Systemutvecklare frontend
   
   
  med placering i Norrköping 
  Att arbeta som Systemutvecklare på Sjöfartsverket 
  Som systemutvecklare kommer du att tillhöra Sjöfartsverkets IT-avdelning som i dagsläget består av cirka 80 medarbetare. Vi är i en expansiv fas för att klara av det ökade förändringsbehovet från våra kunder och verksamhet. På IT-avdelningen sitter vi nära både varandra och stora delar av vår övriga verksamhet vilket ger möjligheter till snabba kontaktvägar och smidig samverkan mellan olika roller och avdelningar. Vår småskalighet gör att du kommer nära användaren av det du utvecklar och du kommer få stor möjlighet att påverka vad du gör och aktivt delta i att förbättra våra arbetssätt, rutiner och verktyg. Arbetssättet är agilt, med korta beslutsvägar, vilket gör att det finns utrymme att bidra med nya idéer som skapar värde. Förnyelseresan innebär en stor förflyttning i vilka tjänster vi levererar och på vilket sätt. Vi gör det tillsammans med övrig verksamhet men bjuder också in våra kunder i arbetet. Vi har många spännande initiativ på gång. Det Du gör påverkar och gör skillnad. 
  För att få en inblick i vad du kan vara med och bidra till, titta gärna på filmerna nedan: 
  Sjöfartsverkets verksamhet 
  Sea Traffic Management - services and their benefits 
  Safe, Secure and Efficient Shipping through e-Navigation 
  Arbetsuppgifter 
  Du kommer att arbeta med både nyutveckling och legacy med målet att lyfta vårt IT stöd till det bästa för våra användare. Du kommer att bli en del av ett agilt utvecklingsteam med blandade kompetenser för att kunna leverera värde till våra kunder och medarbetare. Teamet ansvarar för en delmängd av domänen Sjöfartsnära tjänster, området är centralt för Sjöfartsverket och spänner från interna till internationella system. IT-tjänsterna står inför modernisering med fokus på ytterligare digitalisering och automatisering. Arbetsuppgifterna kommer huvudsakligen fokusera på frontend-området, men kan vid behov även inkludera backend. Vår plattform för frontend består i dag mestadels av Angular, Javascript, CSS och C# för backend. 
  Vem är du? 
  Vi söker dig som uppfyller följande krav: 
  
   Akademisk utbildning inom IT alternativt erfarenheter som du byggt upp under många års arbete inom IT-området och som vi bedömer likvärdiga 
   Minst tre års aktuell erfarenhet (från de senaste fem åren) av systemutveckling med tyngd på frontend. 
   Erfarenhet av och goda kunskaper inom frontend relaterade ramverk såsom Angular, React eller Vue.js eller liknande 
   Erfarenhet av och goda kunskaper inom CSS-ramverk såsom Bootstrap, Material Design eller likvärdigt och HTML5 
   Kunskap om UX och UI-design 
   Goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska i såväl tal som skrift 
   
  Det är meriterande om du har: 
  
   Erfarenhet av mobil och app-utveckling exempelvis för IOS 
   Kunskap om micro-frontend 
   Erfarenhet inom UX och goda UX-seder för god användarupplevelse 
   Erfarenhet av CI/CD (continuous integration, continuous deployment) 
   Kunskap om mikrotjänster och container-plattformar
  
   
   
  Vi kommer att lägga stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper. Vi söker dig som har en utvecklad analytisk förmåga och är lösningsfokuserad. Du har lätt för att samarbeta och trivs med att jobba i team samtidigt som du kan genomföra arbetsuppgifter självständigt. Du är drivande, med inställningen att ständigt göra saker bättre samt har en flexibel och nyfiken inställning till nya arbetsuppgifter, tekniker och verktyg. Du är även hjälpsam, trivs i en rådgivande roll och ser positivt på kunskapsdelning och tekniska diskussioner kollegor emellan. Vi ställer höga krav på våra medarbetares säkerhets- och sekretessmedvetande. Befattningen är placerad i säkerhetsklass och en säkerhetsprövning med registerkontroll kommer att genomföras innan beslut om anställning fattas. Du måste vara svensk medborgare, men får gärna ha utländsk bakgrund. Befattningen kan innebära krigsplacering vid Sjöfartsverket. 
  Varför ska du välja Sjöfartsverket 
  Sjöfartsverket är ett tjänsteproducerande affärsverk inom transportsektorn. Vår arbetsmiljö är unik – Sveriges vackraste arbetsplats. Vårt uppdrag är att utveckla transport och sjöfart i linje med riksdagens och regeringens beslut. Vår affärsidé är att erbjuda effektiva sjövägar, moderna tjänster och maritimt partnerskap för tillväxt, konkurrenskraft och hållbar utveckling.  Sjöfartsverket erbjuder en trivsam arbetsmiljö med goda möjligheter att förena arbetsliv och privatliv, det kan till exempel finnas möjlighet till enskild överenskommelse om distansarbete några dagar i veckan. Vi har en tydlig identitet, ett starkt varumärke och många extremt engagerade medarbetare som brinner för det de gör. Vi är en utvecklingsinriktad organisation och arbetar ständigt för att utveckla våra medarbetare samt för att upprätthålla våra nöjda kunder. Är vi rätt organisation för dig är det en självklarhet för dig att agera på ett professionellt, öppet och engagerat sätt. Vårt arbete utgår från den statliga värdegrunden, vi arbetar också aktivt för jämställdhet, mångfald och inkludering och ser det som en självklarhet att du delar vår uppfattning.  Hur och när? 
  Den här rekryteringen gäller en tillsvidareanställning som beräknas tillsättas snarast. 
  Kontakt 
  I den här rekryteringen samarbetar Sjöfartsverket med Jefferson Wells, ManpowerGroup. Vid frågor angående tjänsten kontakta rekryteringskonsult Therese Fyhr på 011-19 18 98 eller therese.fyhr@jeffersonwells.se. Du kan också kontakta Enhetschef Henrik Manfred, 010-478 65 67 eller henrik.manfred@sjofartsverket.se. 
  Fackliga företrädare: 
  Saco-S Jesper Svensson, OFR/ST Tapani Hoffrén, Seko Bengt-Erik Johansson, samtliga kan nås via vår växel 0771-63 00 00. 
  Registrera din ansökan senast den 9 Maj 2022. 
  Diarienummer: 22-01293
   
   
  Sjöfartsverket gör kontinuerliga och aktiva val kring exponering och rekryteringsstöd i varje rekrytering. Vi undanber oss därför direktkontakt av annonsförsäljare, bemannings- och rekryteringsföretag.

column1: Skillad utvecklare, vill du ha en nystart?

column4:
We are so happy you found us! We hope to catch your interest and that we will get the opportunity to get to know each other a bit better.
Working at Ninetech
As a consultant at Ninetech, you will work with techniques like .net, C and Azure. You will also have the opportunity to work with frontend development like HTML, JavaScript, React, Vue if that is in your interest.
We value our long-term relationships with our customers, so it is important for us that we continue to build and deliver solutions with the highest quality - and this is where you come in! With your expertise and with close collaboration with your peers, you will share the responsibility to keep our high quality and high customer satisfaction. You should like getting in to the nitty gritty in a project while still keeping your eye on the big picture and you have extensive experience from working in cross-functional teams.
As a developer with focus on Azure, you will have an important part of implementing processes and workflows using Azure-components, elegant APIs and various architect patterns. Your expertise in Azure will be valuable when it comes to building sophisticated solutions, but also to support your colleagues in sales and analytics across projects.
You are a curios person that enjoys taking on new challenges. You have a great passion for technology but what really excites you is how technology can be used to create solutions that solves the challenges our customers face. This is of course not something you do completely on your own, but in a greater team with your colleagues (project management, UX-designers, frontend-developers etc).
Is this you?

I have experience with developing applications in Azure cloud
I’m familiar with the basic concepts of serverless, CI/CD and infrastructure-as-code
I have a good understanding of possibilities and challenges with different kinds of architect patterns and techniques (microservices and event driven architecture for example)
I value automation and believe DevOps is crucial to make solid solutions.
My background is in backend development, but I’m curious on how interfaces are created and formed
My primary language is C, but I am comfortable to use other technologies to solve a challenge ahead.

Two or three of these skills would be great if you had. Four or more would be magical! If you have other superpowers – you’re more than welcome to tell us!
What you get
We have a strong, value-driven culture here at Ninetech that is characterized by trust, teamwork and entrepreneurship. We will ensure that you get the support and help you need to develop as well as encourage you to find your own space and contribute with your unique expertise and knowledge. Some of the offers that our employees get:
Personalized development plan for your individual and technical growth
Mentorship program
Different kind of events for knowledge sharing
Ninetech have the ambition to be the best place to work – we value our positive work culture and strong team focus. You will work mainly with inhouse-projects in Ninetech-teams towards our customers. The team constellation is cross-functional and will consist of experts from different areas, such as project leaders, designers, architects and developers. You will also visit our customers from time to time - to work closely in workshops or around go-live.
To be honest, the most important thing we are looking for is your personality. We are looking for people who are curious, wants to be at the forefront of technology and love to deliver great digital solutions to our customers. Since we work in cross functional teams and projects, we also see that you have good collaboration and communication skills. We succeed together!
Swedish is still our main language at the office, though most of us speak English quite well. We will ensure that you will have the best prerequisites to succeed at Ninetech as an English speaker. However, it would be great if you have the ambition to learn the language even if you’re not there just yet.
Location? Karlstad. We provide a flexible “50/50” work model as part of our culture and way of working.
Ninetech is a full-range digital development agency. Our clients are well known brands in Scandinavia, who wants to create the best user experience and thereby develop their future business.

Would you like to enter the iGaming industry?
Hacksaw Studios is a company that builds online games for real money gaming. The games we build are enjoyed by millions of people every month by players all over the world.
We are currently looking to expand our game development team with 2-3 additional slot game developers and are looking for both junior and senior candidates. You will be working in a tight knit team involving both front-end developers, back-end developers and designers. Your task will be to bring our game ideas to life in co-operation with the designers and product owners.
We offer a nice office in central Stockholm, an opportunity to work with other experienced game developers as well as a co-ownership program for suitable candidates.
Your tasks will include:
Work with the development and design team to create new games and update old games, as required
Learn about the online gaming industry and stay up to date on current trends and what is popular with players
Participate in code reviews and merge requests
Work on our game development framework which modularizes functionality that gets re-used between games
Co-operate with colleagues with similar roles, both in-house and with our partners
Required skills and experience:
Experience with game development, or a solid development background and a strong desire to learn
Experience with a programming language suited for game development, such as Javascript, Typescript, C#, Java, Haxe or similar
Other things that would be a bonus (but not required):
Experience with some form of game development library, such as Unity, Unreal Engine, Pixi or similar
Shader programming experience
An interest in mathematics
3d programming experience, such as OpenGL
A working knowledge of how a browser communicates with a back-end server
Experience in debugging
Social gaming experience
A personal interest in real money gaming
To apply for this role, please submit your CV at https://hacksawstudios.bamboohr.com/jobs

At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.

Job description 
  
   Configura works with parametric configuration. We develop rules-based software to draw spaces in 2D and 3D for leading companies within the commercial furniture, kitchen and material handling industries. In the background, prices and configurations are automatically calculated. We are a global company with customers in 10 countries and users in more than 100. Configura is headquartered in Linköping (Sweden) with five wholly-owned subsidiaries in Grand Rapids (Michigan, USA), Kuala Lumpur (Malaysia), Shenzhen (China), Berlin (Germany) , and Japan (Tokyo). Our unique expertise places us at the forefront of Space Planning and Configuration solutions. With more than 250 professionals we are now ready to take on unique challenges anywhere in the world.
    
    At Configura we aim high, our vision is to become the leading solution provider for communities that design spaces. Our solutions are made for the design of buildings and everything within and around them. We provide an open ecosystem for companies that sell highly configurable products. To do this, we always engage with simplicity and deliver with power. 
   
   WHAT WE OFFER YOU 
   Configura is in an exciting growth phase where Cloud Services will play a central part. Our ambition is to develop new cloud-based products and to do so we need a new cloud-based application platform. We aim to create a new scalable cloud native infrastructure with a tightly integrated web application framework.
    
    We are creating a new cloud native platform for Configura to build our next-generation cloud-based products on. We have a clear development process and structured development methodology where it´s the project team that owns the project and makes the important decisions. 
   We offer a chance to be part of creating this, those who join now will have the opportunity to help guide the process and help shape the platform that we will work with over the next decade and beyond. We want our engineers to lead, take initiative, and push technology forward. 
   You will be one of the members of the Architects group that drives Configura’s technical product development. 
   You will build strong relationships across the company and understand multiple points of view and drive a process to conclusions in a timely and respectful manner. You create a supportive, cooperative fearless atmosphere where every team member can achieve their maximum potential and continuously grow their skill set. 
   
   WHO WE BELIEVE YOU ARE 
   You will be the talented Principal Developer with extensive experience and overall knowledge of the system. We believe you will excel at design and programming at all levels and specifically at user empathy, user-interface design, naming and conventions, program structure, performance, general quality and long-term consequences.
    
    As a software architect, you could lay out a path across many versions guided by long-term strategic goals and participate in and support initiatives outside the main area of responsibility. 
   To be successful as a Software Architect, you should be a communicative and mature person who takes pride in your work and is driven to deliver with quality. 
   We believe you are someone who: 
   
    Cares about performance/stability/scalability. 
    Has experience working with scalable cloud services and/or distributed systems with high performance. 
    Is communicative and have strong collaboration skill and can lead other developers to success.  
   
   WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING 
   
    Collaborate with project teams and other architects to design cloud-based services with a focus on high availability, low latency, and scalability. 
    Set product direction and has ownership over large components. An Architect thinks both strategically and tactically, keeping in mind quality, performance, technical, and company goals. 
    Provides technical leadership for the company. 
   
  
  Job requirements 
  
   WHO ARE WE LOOKING FOR  
   
    Bachelor degree and above in Computer Science or equivalent with a minimum of 10 years of relevant work experience 
    Document databases, preferably DynamoDB. 
    Distributed systems / eventual consistency. 
    Cloud environments, preferably AWS. 
    "Infrastructure as Code" tools, preferably Pulumi. 
    Typed programming languages, preferably Rust. 
    Modern JS frameworks, ex. React/Next.js 
    Core web technologies, ex. HTML, CSS 
     
      Good writing and verbal English communication skills 
      Collaborative and enjoys working in teams 
     
   
   Bonus skills/experience: 
   
    Modern JS build toolchains, ex. Webpack / Babel 
    Modern JS package managers, ex. NPM/Yarn 
    Observability tools, ex. honeycomb.io 
    CD/CI pipelines, ex. Gitlab CI. 
    Experience developing secure software

In joining our Tech Team as our new Software Developer, you will become a part of the mission to provide our customers with world-class applications, used to discover and read magazines through apps currently available on iOS, Android and the Web.
As Software developer, you will work with the development of new products, as well as ensuring our backend stack is an enabler for the future, so as to best manage the underlying business logic and integrations, such as content preparation, APIs, CRM tool integration, data warehouse integrations, etc. You will work in collaboration with your team in shaping the direction of our complete stack portfolio, and the corresponding development processes.

Ruby
MongoDB
AWS
Golang
Redshift
RabbitMQ
Linux
Docker

Since September 2020, Readly is listed at Nasdaq Stockholm.

About us!
   Vimla is not just another mobile carrier and never will be. Ever since the launch of Vimla in 2014, we've changed what people expect from a phone operator. By pushing boundaries, we have managed to become the fastest growing mobile carrier in Sweden. And more importantly, we have earned the trust and loyalty of our customers to an extent normally unheard of in our industry. This year we were even awarded Carrier of the Year (for the 3rd time!) based on our customer satisfaction. Things are good, but we're just getting started!
   In the team, we are excited to work on:
   
   Improving our internal tools so that everybody can work more efficiently 
   Improving our products to remove pain-points for our users 
   Migrating our systems to Kubernetes and other improvements to our code quality 
   Developing new types of services based on new telco capabilities 
   Building an efficient work environment for development with excellent ergonomics
  
   
  
   
  The role
   As a software engineer at Vimla, you'll join our small and ever-evolving team with some of the most humble and skilled technical nerds in the business, devoted to enabling all the fun stuff for our users!
   Focusing on the back-end, you’ll be part of building entirely new micro-service environments, reliable high availability services, and a new legacy free telco platform. We encourage each other to stepping up and taking ownership and you’ll have a hand in the whole process of designing, implementing, documenting and testing our software. 
  Our back-end is based on Kotlin, Node, AWS, and Kubernetes, while using Typescript and React in our front-end. We value investing in the best possible tools and environments to make development efficient and ergonomic. Some of our platform is open source, and part of your work will be to contribute to that and other open source projects. 
  We’re working in an agile environment without Scrum or Kanban, where your ideas and opinions will count, with the opportunity to make a big impact on both our future and the future of mobile carriers.
   Main responsibilities
   
   Planning, building, documenting and testing new services 
   Improving and maintaining our software development environment and tools 
   Planning long-term how Vimlas software should evolve 
  
  Some cool stuff in the pipeline
  
    Our vision is that Vimla should be the natural choice for any developer - by launching a developer portal where our users can get API:s to interact with the network.
    By switching telephone network type to cloud based, we will be able to manage and do new and interesting things in our telecom network
  
   We believe you already
   
   Know one or a few programming languages well 
   Have experience working in a medium or large project 
   Know our technology stack or are willing to learn on the job 
  
  It's also a plus if you
   
   Are familiar working with Java, Kotlin, AWS, Kubernetes, Node or Typescript 
   Have operations-knowledge using Kubernetes, Linux and AWS 
   Have experience in working with mobile apps 
   Experience with micro-service architecture 
   Have some domain knowledge in telco
  
   
  
   
  Why you want to work @Vimla
   As Vimla is currently on a really exciting growth journey, the possibilities to grow and develop with us are huge. We’re all intrigued by the opportunity of building the next generation telco, with the vision to disrupt the telecom industry from the inside!
   We believe in empowering our team to work the way they’re most efficient, therefore you’ll choose your own equipment and have the possibility to affect your own work environment. 
  We value each other’s progress and have a flexibel budget for competence-development, with room for important matters like learning new technologies and attending relevant conferences, ensuring we all keep á jour with all the needed knowledge to keep progressing.
   Vimla is a part of Telenor Sweden which means you get the best of two worlds - freedom to work independently as an online startup company but with employment benefits and development opportunities offered by a large company. We currently work completely remotely, but when we're back to the office, we will be in our completely new offices in Solna, Stockholm right next to T-Bana Solna C.
   Apply today!
   Is there a chance that you could be our new teammate? Make sure to press that application button. You might be glad that you did. Send your application in Swedish or English, whatever feels best.
   At Vimla we believe that a diverse work environment will improve both the quality of our work and our workplace. All qualified candidates will receive our consideration for employment without regard to religion, ethnicity, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, national origin, disability or age.
   At the moment, we are recruiting continuously.
   Employment type: Full-time

column1: Software Engineer - Developer Tools - Node.js / React
column4:
From our technology to our team members, Neo4j is built on relationships.
   
   
   
     As part of Neo4j product engineering, you will work together with a diverse team of talented colleagues from around the world. Our culture encourages engineers who want to become deep experts in a particular field – or to build broad expertise across several technologies. Our engineers regularly work with peers in field engineering and experience the full lifecycle of the systems they build.
   
   
   
     We build technology that helps cure cancers, addresses diabetes, and gets humans to Mars. We're proud to fight fraud, crush pandemics, and even help journalists uncover the truth. Neo4j’s engineering teams are located in Malmö, Sweden and London, UK.
   
   
   
     Please submit your CV and cover letter in English.
   
   
   
     What we are doing
   
   
     We are building a set of tools to provide for developing applications on the Neo4j Graph Platform. These tools are for:
   
   
    creating, running and operating Neo4j databases
    developing data models and graph queries
    building full-stack GraphQL-based applications using the GRAND stack
   
   
   
     We want the tools to provide world-class developer experience for our users, who are developers with a broad range of backgrounds.
   
   
     A majority of our users develop on Windows, and we are specifically looking to improve their developer experience in our next phase of improvement. We are looking to grow our Windows-specialist experience to meet this goal.
   
   
   
     The Role
   
   
     You'll be joining the existing "devtools" team that created the popular Neo4j Desktop and Neo4j Browser. We are now working on the next generation of these tools, and creating new complementary tools.
   
   
   
     You will collaborate with engineers from across the Neo4j organisation as well as with external developers who use our products. To be successful in this role you will need to develop empathy with those external developers. As a developer yourself, you will know what a difference good tools make in day-to-day work, and so understand the impact that you can have.
   
   
   
     We also have a large user base in the enterprise world and prior experience with working within an enterprise environment would be a big plus.
   
   
   
     The majority of the applications, tools and libraries this team creates are open source, and we encourage contributions to the upstream open source products that we use. You will have the opportunity to go into the depths of open source technologies such as Electron, Chromium, GraphQL, React, NestJS and participate in the open source community.
   
   
   
     You’ll be based in either our engineering HQ in Malmö, Sweden or our office in London, and will travel on occasion between the two. Expect to be pairing and joining design discussions using online collaboration software on a regular basis.
   
   
  
   
    We are looking for candidates who:
    
      use Windows as their main development platform are comfortable working in a team distributed across multiple sites - London and Malmö have experience following a development process that includes PR review and rigorous automated testing (unit, integration, e2e) have empathy with developers and a passion for product quality ideally, have experience of using Neo4j
    
   
   
  
   
    Candidates need to have at least 3 years of experience in:
    
      Nodejs React
    
   
   
  
   
    Nice to Have:
    
      Electron NestJS react-native-windows Windows internals Powershell
    
   
   
  
   
    Country
    
      SE
    
   
   
  
   
    Neo4j Values:
   
   
     Our work in Neo4j Engineering is guided by our company values:
   
   
   
     (we)-[:VALUE]->(relationships)
   
   
     (we)-[:FOCUS_ON]->(:UserSuccess)
   
   
     (we)-[:THRIVE_IN]->(:Culture {type: [‘Open’, ‘Inclusive’})
   
   
     (we)-[:ASSUME]->(:Intent {direction:’Positive’})
   
   
     (we)-[:WELCOME]->(:Discussions {nature: ‘IntellectuallyHonest’})
   
   
     (we)-[:DELIVER_ON]->(ourCommitments)
   
   
   
     Why Join Neo4j?
   
   
     Neo4j is one of the 20 most popular databases in the world, and the leader in the rapidly emerging Graph Database category. We’re building the technology that enables connected data to solve the world’s most pressing problems. You’ll work on unique engineering projects that challenge what’s possible.
   
   
   
     We have customers in every industry across the globe, and our products a proven product/market fit. Joining our team is an opportunity to shape the future of data and analytics.
   
   
   
     We pride ourselves on being a welcoming team. Most of us would agree that one of the best parts of working at Neo4j is the people we get to work with.
   
   
   
     We encourage you to apply even if you don’t 100% fit the qualifications above. Why? Because we are committed to building an environment that fosters belonging, which means valuing intellectually honest discussions and being receptive to new ideas and perspectives.
   
   
   
     One of our central objectives is to provide an inclusive, diverse, and equitable workplace for everyone to develop their potential and have a positive, career-defining experience.
   
   
   
     About Neo4j:
   
   
     Neo4j is the leader in graph database technology. As the world’s most widely deployed graph database, we help organizations – including NASA, UBS and Volvo Cars – to reveal and predict how people, processes and systems interrelate. Using this relationships-first approach, applications built using Neo4j tackle connected data challenges such as analytics and artificial intelligence, fraud detection, real-time recommendations and knowledge graphs.
   
   
   
     Neo4j is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. Please read the privacy notice regarding Neo4j's recruitment process to understand how we will handle the personal data that you provide.

Juni who? 
  We’re Juni. The fastest-growing fintech in Europe. We’re born remote, built for remote, and busy building the future of financial services for ecommerce entrepreneurs.
   What we do 
  Think of us as the world’s best financial companion for ecommerce entrepreneurs. We build products that help our customers sell smarter and understand their business better. We even finance their working capital so they can smash their goals and dream up new ones. See for yourself at https://demo.juni.co/demo. If you are curious about upcoming features and what you will help build, you can also find our public roadmap at https://www.juni.co/roadmap.
   How & why we do it 
  We give our people the same thing we’re building for our customers: freedom. Freedom to work wherever there’s good WiFi. Freedom to be 100% yourself. Freedom to explore your potential and what’s more – make the most of it. We truly believe we’re making the world a better place for small businesses, and we want you to be a part of that mission.
   Your role 
  Tackle convoluted problems and develop clean, stable solutions that scale. The ideal candidate would be someone who has a genuine passion for designing and implementing elegant software solutions. They would also be intimately familiar (and up to date) with their development ecosystem for making sound decisions when it comes to choosing the right tool or library for the job. We expect our engineers to be able to contribute across the entire product stack, as well as collectively oversee the integrity of the codebase.
   Your responsibilities 
  In this role you’ll:
  
    Play a focal role in the development of user interfaces for our web-based product.
    Help build our engineering culture as we're growing.
    Provide technical leadership around our frontend with exceptional knowledge around React and ideally some experience with server web infrastructure, such as Go, Python, Rails, CDNs or Node.js
    Overall we are looking for someone to aid Juni's code quality and architectural decisions as an Engineer in the team
  
  
   Within 1 month you'll:
  
    Introduce an important architectural improvement to our React codebase
    Fix two thorny unfixed bugs, which the team otherwise could not have done
  
  
   Within 3 months you'll:
  
    Other web frontend engineers say they’re learning a lot and are more productive because of you
    Have helped us to fully migrate core flows to React quicker than we otherwise would have - our velocity has increased significantly
  
  
   Within 6 months you'll:
  
    Help introduce significant new features which radically improve our product.
    Impact the quality of the product, getting to the point where we fix all bugs and are improving performance metrics
    Be proud of the product and the codebase
  
  
   Your qualifications 
  What we need to see:
  
    Strong knowledge of React, Typescript, Babel, Webpack or equivalents and building single page web applications. Ability to autonomously make good technical choices that solve business problems. Experience working with product managers and designers to produce high-quality user interfaces. Strong product focus and commitment to good design and user experience.
  
   Your tool stack 
  Mac. Chrome. Even… Windows. Choose the hardware that helps you work best. We’ll also support whatever software you need. From Miro to Slack and everything in between.
   Tech stack:
  
    React, Javascript/Typescript
    Go
    gRPC (Protocol buffers)
    PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Elasticsearch, Redis
    Kafka
    Kubernetes, AWS
  
   Your people 
  Forget office-based culture. This is people-first culture. We’re real. We never wait. We care deeply. About building better for our customers and each other. About doing something that’s never been done before. Here, you can work with people at the top of their game, who didn’t get there by playing games. You can help us change business, change banking, change the world – wherever in the world you may be.
   Your benefits 
  We’re born remote-first. Transparent. Caring. Empowering. So our benefits are too.
   The good stuff:
  
    Hello work. Meet freedom. Join us anywhere within 6 hours of Sweden.
    Swap 2D for 3D. Meet the team IRL at fun onsites every quarter.
    Work with the best people for the job. Not the best people within 1 hour’s commute.
    Diversity is at our core. We’re part Swedish. Part British. Part French. Part Italian. Part Hungarian. Part Canadian. Part Spanish. You get the idea.
    Great players can stay great players. Progress your career whether you choose to manage people or not.
    Get support to switch things up. People change. Careers can too.
  
   The really good stuff:
  
    Happiness stipend. The best things in life are free. But money can buy you a herd of puppies. Get €8,500 per year to spend on whatever makes you happy.
    Work al desko. Get €500 a month towards a co-working space.
    Stock options. We can’t promise you’ll make a fortune. But we’ll give it our very best shot.
    Vacation days. At least 30 per year as standard. Awesome.
    Global health insurance. You know. Just in case.
    Get sick? No stress. Feel better with unlimited sick leave.
  
   Free your nine to five 
  Hit apply and help us revolutionise financial services for ecommerce entrepreneurs.
   The process 
  CV screening > Get to know us call > Home Assignment (30min home code challenge) > Tech Interview > CTO > Values interview > Offer

What we do at Detectify 
   The fear of cyber threats should never stand in the way of digital greatness. That is why we are changing the fundamentals of how cyber security works. We collaborate with ethical hackers to build a powerful platform that automates and scales crowdsourced vulnerability research. 
   For us, security is not just about protecting what you have but more so a tool to achieve what you want. At Detectify, your opinion and ideas matter. You belong to a dedicated, driven and forever curious team that recognises the power of knowledge sharing and challenging the status quo. 
   We value diversity of minds, different backgrounds, and perspectives. We are all here because we want to make a positive impact in the world. If you are collaborative and passionate about what you do, then you too could be a Detectifyer. 
   The Predictive Assessment team 
   Our team is growing and we are looking for a Software Engineer to the Predictive Assessment team. This team is currently composed of four people that work hard in order to make sure that the members of Detectify Crowdsource - our network of white-hat hackers - are engaged and enjoying the best possible experience when collaborating with Detectify. 
   When a researcher submits a vulnerability through our Crowdsource platform, our team builds a module for it and adds it into the Detectify service. By reporting the vulnerability to us, it becomes a security test which is then made available to all our customers – this is how Detectify combines automation and crowdsourcing. 
   These tests come in various, unique flavors, and are driven by crowdsourced security knowledge. We in the Predictive Assessment team are responsible for validating, configuring and executing such tests on our customer's web applications. 
   We aim for the best possible scanning performance with comprehensive coverage of possible security issues optimizing for flow, fast feedback and quality. We follow lean and DevOps concepts, aiming to be innovative, helpful, and have a strong sense of ownership for all the things we build. 
   What you'll get to do 
   As a full stack software engineer in our team, you will help us provide a world class user experience for our customers by taking both our web application and security testing to the next level. As part of that, you will get to: 
   
   Use the latest technologies to solve real problems for our customers at a massive scale 
   Collaborate in a dynamic and empowered domain-driven environment to bridge software development and UX design 
   Experiment and learn fast to help us deliver cutting edge solutions for our customers 
   Share your knowledge and build creative solutions while helping the team make use of best practices 
   Be part of a great environment with awesome colleagues and world-class white hat hackers 
   
  Technologies you will get your hands on: 
   
   Modern development tools: React, GraphQL, Typescript, Golang and RabbitMQ 
   Event-based microservices architecture on AWS built using Kubernetes and Terraform 
   Various kinds of security testing: authentication bypass, cross-site scripting, DNS side channel attacks, etc. 
  
  Who you are 
   You come from a background where you are used to focusing on user behaviour as an important part of your delivery and you strive for simplicity and ease of use in your solutions. You love working in a collaborative environment bringing out the best of everyone within the team. 
   You like to set and achieve your own ambitious goals and solve complicated technical problems with a team full of creative problem solvers. You think it's meaningful to continuously evaluate and reflect on the team's solutions and think outside of the box to help the team solve hard problems with smart and simple solutions. 
   Typically you are used to working with SaaS products in a cloud first environment, running microservices at scale, having experience in building modern web applications relying on contemporary tools such as React and GraphQL. It is a bonus if you have an understanding of cyber security. 
   So, what do you think? 
   We are proud to foster an inclusive workplace free from discrimination. We strongly believe that diversity of experience, perspectives, and background will lead to a better environment for our employees and a better product. This is something we value deeply and we encourage everyone to be a part of changing the way the world thinks about security! Go hack yourself! 
   Remote work 
   This position is for the Stockholm office. We offer remote working, with access to our office in central Stockholm. We think you should be able to work from anywhere but for tax reasons we need you to be located in Sweden, and we are more than happy to help you relocate.
