Techquity is a legal technology start-up with exciting prospects in a fast-paced and highly international industry. At the heart of our company is our digital platform, which structures and automates the investment process in connection with the fundraising of private equity funds.
We are currently working on establishing a strong presence on the Swedish market, while planning to go international in the coming year. Our customers and users are mainly law firms, private equity firms and institutional investors.
This is a rare chance to join a uniqely well-positioned start-up in a highly intellectual and challenging field, in a thrilling phase of the company's journey.
Could this be you?
Job description
You will be key-player in developing and perfecting our private equity investment platform. You will form an essential component of our tech team, which is directed by our CTO Alexander. As our Tech Lead, you will have great possibility to form and shape the role based on your experience and preferences.
You will join a start-up with a proven, market-ready product. Having raised capital from respected investors, we are now ready to scale nationally and - quite soon - internationally.
Last but not least, you will work with exciting technologies such as AI, ML and NLP as we continuously develop our platform and features to become ever more advanced.
Who are you?
You probably have a few years of experience having worked as a developer. You may have held various developer roles before, but are now ready to take your career to the next level with a more managerial role.
As a person you are always ready to walk the extra mile to ensure you deliver the highest quality product possible. You are curious, driven and not afraid to take own initatives. You enjoy working closely with other team members and participate in mob and/or pair programming on a daily basis.
In addition, you are:

A true team player - you like to work closely with other team members.
Used to and appreciates working in an agile environment.
Happy to help and support others in the team.
Driven and eager to test new things, to be on the leading edge technically.
What skills do you have?
Strong background as a full-stack developer.
We work in a Docker-based environment both locally and in the cloud. Our primary cloud platform is AWS.
Techquity builds on a Node-based back-end built in TypeScript.
The interface is a GraphQL-based API which serves data to the front-end.
Business data is stored in a MySQL database and our application logs are managed in MongoDB.
Our front-end is based on React and communicates with the back-end through GraphQL.
What can Techquity offer?
Techquity combines the power of being an independent start-up, while also being part of the CIMON Group, a technology-focused investment firm. This means that although we are a start-up, we have 400+ wonderful colleagues working in different portfolio companies, always ready to help and support us.
At Techquity, you will work in a creative, energetic and innovative work environment. You will join a start-up with great potential and international ambitions, just as we are ready to scale up operations.
As part of a start-up, you will be of central importance to the company's continued growth and success, and a highly valuable player on our team. Your work will have great impact on our company and customers.
We have offices in Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö and Karlshamn.

column1: Tech Lead / Senior Fullstack Developer to Celemi in Malmö
column4:
job description.
Are you a Fullstack Developer or have experience as Backend and Frontend Developer who wants to advance to become a Tech Lead / Senior Fullstack Developer ? Then this new role at Celemi may be just right for you!


You will pro-actively drive technical direction and ensure we leverage the best technologies for our global business simulation solution.

Celemi is a leading, international provider of strategic communication and learning solutions who focuses on experiential learning and business simulations that deliver business results and are “serious fun”.


Celemi is on an exciting journey of growth and digitalization and is looking for a Tech Lead / Senior Fullstack Developer to join our team and help us accelerate our digital development and build and manage internal as well as external software development capacity.


You will be responsible for all business simulation software development. You will be directly involved with end clients for custom simulations. You will collaborate with our internal team of designers and concept developers, as well as third party software consulting companies.


We are looking for a skilled developer to join our international team and help us with hands on software and infrastructure development.


What we offer

Besides working with world known brands, you will be part of defining our future direction for digital business simulations and an eco-system to serve our customers and partners


Work in an environment where people value people, our core values are Customer committed, Open, Trusting and Creative. We value diversity and sustainability is high on our agenda and future direction.


We have an open-minded atmosphere at Celemi and we will shape the role to leverage your strengths, and to find your place in the organization. You will take full responsibility for your tasks, to help your team members when needed, and to drive initiatives within your area of responsibility.
qualifications.
At least five years of professional software development. Mainly backend, but also frontend

Solid skills in Node.js and React

Experienced in agile methods, way of working and development

Capable and enjoys leading and driving others

You know how to develop API;s (REST, WebSockets)

Database management and development (SQL, DynamoDB, MongoDB)

Experienced in Continuous Integration and Delivery (CI/CD)

Very good knowledge in AWS

You understand the concept of and how to use containers and container management (Docker, Kubernetes) as well as Infrastructure as Code (IaC)

Professional English in writing and oral. It is an advantage if you can communicate in Swedish. Fluency in additional languages is a big plus.

We are open to all types of full stack development leads - whether your experience leans more heavily towards the front end or the back end is not as important as your overall software expertise, open-mindedness and willingness to collaborate and learn.
responsibilities.
You will be responsible for the implementation of application designs, including ensuring the technical architecture, development, testing, and deployment and operations of software solutions. You will work collaboratively to solve challenges and build the best digital learning experiences in the market; you will be part of our Tech team and work with our team of designers and concept developers.


You will report to our CTO. You will also be in close collaboration with the CEO, to assist us in building this function for the future. Our ambition is to add more software development capacity, internally or externally. You will be instrumental in how we find the right balance between inhouse and offshore development. Working as a combined team will be fundamental. Your input will help manage project priorities, deadlines and deliverables. The solutions you will be developing will be used worldwide.


Additional areas of responsibility
You will be responsible for the technical approach to feature development, application architecture and problem solving, and will be accountable for the technical platform and delivery of the solution.

You will be very hands-on with projects, a lead in the initial architecture and scaffolding, and getting deep into code. You will be our senior authority in software development and delivery.

Part of your role will be to mentor members of the Celemi team assigned to projects you are working on. Collaboration with teams and great coordination capabilities are therefore important.

Over time you will be client facing, representing Celemi in both technical and non-technical discussions, and be able to engage directly with client teams and stakeholders.
application.
This recruitment is conducted in collaboration with Randstad Technologies in Malmö, Sweden. If you have any questions please contact Senior Recruitment Consultant Elin Bjursten at elin.bjursten@randstad.se or +46 73 856 74 56.


You are welcome to submit your application as soon as possible since we contact and interview candidates continuously during the process.
about Celemi.
Celemi is an award winning developer of business simulations with three international offices (Malmö, Chicago and Shanghai) and with a worldwide network of partners in more than 70 countries.


For almost 40 years, we have been developing and delivering standard and custom built solutions for learning. Historically this has mainly been done in the form of physical games but in the last few years, our digitalization of solutions have developed rapidly.


Until now, we have worked internally with authoring tools and for full stack applications; we have worked with off-shore coding expertise, now we want to internalize more of this knowledge and capability. We want you to lead the development and building of this capability with internal as well as external capacity.


At Celemi, we are passionate about making change happen. Our creative learning solutions engage people’s hearts, minds, and hands, so that they can - and want to - make a difference; leading to desired results for our clients. We have designed serious games, simulations, dialog programs and learning journeys since 1985, helping clients move their people and organizations towards higher levels of performance. We have offices in Sweden, the United States, and China. Through our partner network, we operate across the globe. Among our clients you can find leading companies like ABB, Amazon, Airbus Alibaba, BASF, Hilti, Skanska and Siemens just to mention a few.
https://www.celemi.com

Ansök nu
Hackberry söker sin nästa Flutter expert! Är du utvecklare med erfarenhet av appar och mobilitet? Har du byggt en del i Flutter och redo att bli den som tar lead hos oss? Vill du ha flexibilitet och ansvar, jobba med riktigt små kunder och stora etablerade företag?

Vi är ett litet konsultbolag som jobbar med apputveckling primärt. Vi har ganska nyligen tagit över bolaget själva och bygger vidare på det vi byggt upp senaste året. Ett bolag som vi själva vi jobba på kort och gott!
Idag är vi 10 personer och söker ytterligare några utvecklare som både vill vara med på resan framåt, och som vill påverka vart det hela tar vägen.
Vad vi gör

Vi bygger appar för våra kunder! Internt eller på plats hos kund, stora projekt och små, i team eller individuellt, stora etablerade företag eller nya startups. Allt går och allt gör vi. Vi är ett fullservice företag, och kan hantera alla delar av kedjan från idé till koncept, design, UX/UI, utveckling, integration, test, support och förvaltning.
Flertalet av våra internprojekt har vi byggt just i Flutter och fler kommer det att bli.
Vad du får

Vi bygger ett bolag som vi vill jobba på själva. Det innebär en massa saker, men i korthet en fast bra lön med alla förmåner på plats. Inget skitsnack, bara öppenhet och ett ställe som låter dig fokusera på vad du gör bäst utan att tumma på work-life-balance.Kvalifikationer
Rätt person är av absolut vikt för oss, dvs DU. Vi anställer människor, inte CV:s och är lika intresserad av vad du kan lära dig som av vad du faktiskt redan kan. Alla här skriver under på våra valda ledord: Care, Share, Learn, Laugh & Grow. Rimligen tycker du det spännande att vara med och bygga upp något, och troligen bor du norr om stan (som nästan alla vi gör, dock har det smugit sig in någon enstaka Stockholmsbo).

Du bör vara mångsidig och flexibel, bekväm i en platt och föränderlig verksamhet. Med det sagt, vi är konsulter så det är av största vikt att du gillar och hanterar kundkontakter och kan ta dig an nya projekt och miljöer snabbt.
Vi bygger både Native iOS & Android men också cross-plattform i Flutter samt React Native. För den här rollen ska man såklart ha god erfarenhet av Flutter.
Vi värdesätter att du har en bred teknisk bakgrund, erfarenhet från AWS, GCP eller Azure är starkt meriterande. Har du jobbat som konsult tidigare är det bra, men inte ett måste.
THE NEXT STEP

Vi söker dig som har minst fyra års erfarenhet av app-utveckling i någon miljö.

Nyfiken? Skicka in en intresseanmälan!
Förvirrad? Skicka mig ett mail!

Ser fram emot att höras!Vi har riktigt bra förmåner
Private health insurance
Pension with the possibility to salary exchange
Skills development during working hours
Startup culture
Fixed & competitive salary
Possibility to invoice via own company
Relocation assistance
A great team!
Flexible working hours

“The piano aint got no wrong notes” Thellonius Monk
Mr Monk is considered to be one of the most prominent and original jazz composers ever. He was an outstanding piano player who had a habit of, in the middle of a song, simply stop playing, stand up and start to dance, completely engulfed in what the other musicians were playing. After a while he would sit down back at the piano and continue to play and lead the band.
That is the type of leader that we are looking for right now in our front-end department. Someone who is known for eyebrow raising original creations and has the passion for development that makes you simply have to stop what you are doing from time to time to be engulfed in and enjoy what your team is doing. And someone who can recognize that the team “aint got no wrong players”.
Further traits that we are looking for, for this position:
You don't give up when faced with problems that seem impossible to untangle
You have spent most of your life working with software development and engineering and consider yourself fluent in multiple programing languages & platforms

You don't give up on your own ideas, even if others find them weird or too far out

You enjoy giving lectures and talks, both inside and outside the office

You are living in, or plan to relocate to, the greater copenhagen region
If the description above sounds somewhat like you, we urge you to send in your application.
What you will be doing
Playing for Skymill as a Tech Lead in Front End Development means that you will be involved in a few projects at the same time and have full responsibility and freedom when working with our clients, helping them create and maintain quality software. You will be doing this either by working at our clients location, adapting to the clients processes and requirements, or by creating your own requirements and processes working from our office in Malmö. You also need to have the ability to turn these requirements and processes into beautiful implementations. You also have to walk and support your team members and your customer through the entire development cycle, including presales and arranging workshops.
Most of all, you have to let the passion you have for producing quality software shine through in your everyday work. You will be working alongside some of the most brilliant developers on the scene at the moment, so you have to be able to let them shine as brightly as you do

Desired skills
To be able to fill the bill as Tech Lead for front end development, we believe that you have at least five years of real work life experience from the field, and you have to be at an expert level within one or many of the following areas or technologies:
JavaScript

Typescript

Node.js

React, Vue, Angular

UI/UX design

API Development

Test driven development

Cloud first development practices
In addition, we take for granted that you possess sufficient day-to-day knowledge of:
Relational and NoSQL databases

Version control in Git

CI/CD work flows

AWS and/or GCP

Open source methodologies
As tech lead, you also need the skills to guide, train and motivate your more junior team members and colleagues towards getting the same quality in their work as you get in yours. Occasionally, you are expected to attend software development events and host public sessions and workshops around your expertise. And of course, you have to be comfortable in the role of a consultant.
.
Our offer to you
Apart from working with one of the fastest growing, most flexible companies in the region, you will get a competitive salary and pension package, as well as 30 days paid vacation. Our different bonus systems is another perk that we think you will appreciate.
You will be working alongside lots of smart and talented developers, cloud architects and project managers with extensive experience from the industry, each being a master of their own instrument. Knowledge transfer and information sharing are some of our strongest bywords and we try to live up to this by making sure we get together at least once a week for cross reference groups, q&a´s and brainstorming sessions.
We also offer an extensive training and educational program to make sure that your competence and your skills are constantly kept at top level.
Outside the office we have recurring “jam-sessions” where having fun is the main objective. We often hang out at the office for a beer or two after work, keeping the fridge full at all times. So if you wanna give it a shot, send us your application!
Ps. If you are wondering about all the music references, please ask us at the interview.

Tycker du om att jobba i React, Angular eller Typescript? Är det dags att ta nästa kliv i karriären? Då borde du läsa vidare. 
   Vi söker nämligen vår nästa tech lead med tyngdpunkt i frontendutveckling till vårt härliga gäng! Är du en person som tycker det är viktigt med respektfull kommunikation, vågar utforska och pröva samt gillar att skapa värde tillsammans? Då delar du våra värderingar. På Decerno arbetar vi tillsammans för att skapa värde i allt vi gör, både för våra anställda och för våra kunder. Det är något som är med oss i hela processen från början till slut och är en självklarhet i vår vardag. 
   Våra uppdrag – bidra till samhällsnytta 
   Vår nisch är att bygga skräddarsydda digitala lösningar som skapar nya möjligheter, förenklar livet för människor och stärker våra kunders konkurrenskraft - allt utifrån vår kunds specifika behov. Vi riktar in oss på uppdrag där vi tar ett helhetsansvar över projektets framgång och kan bemanna med ett helt team av våra egna anställda. Vi söker nära och långa samarbeten med kund där vi bygger långsiktigt hållbara lösningar. 
   Det som driver Decerno är att göra skillnad. För oss är det viktigt att vi kan bidra till en bättre värld och ett bättre samhälle. Därför har vi en stark etisk policy som guidar oss i våra val av projekt. Vi väljer aktivt bort projekt inom vapenindustrin och med koppling till alkohol, tobak eller spel om pengar. Dessutom siktar vi på att kunna koppla fler av våra projekt till FN:s globala hållbarhetsmål. 
   Rollen 
   Rollen vi söker är en Tech lead till vårt Volvo cars-team. Teamet och leveransen är just nu i en etableringsfas, vilket öppnar upp för en varierande vardag som kan omfatta (men inte begränsas till): 
   
   Utveckling, främst i React, Vue och Typescript 
   Delta i workshops och möten med stakeholders 
   Initiera och implementera konkurrenskraftiga lösningar för produkten 
   
  Vi tror på att kunna erbjuda våra medarbetare en stor flexibilitet och anser därför att valmöjligheten att kunna sitta heltid på distans ska vara en självklarhet. Vårt Virtuella kontor är vårt sätt att erbjuda dig möjligheten att välja din arbetsplats själv. Om den är i sommarstugan vid sjön eller fjällstugan i skogen spelar oss ingen roll – du är en del av vårt team ändå, där du får ingå i ett befintligt team i något av våra pågående projekt. 
   Är det här du? 
   I rollen som tech lead ser vi gärna att du tar med dig en del tidigare erfarenheter. Därför önskar vi att du har ungefär 4 års tidigare erfarenhet av frontendutveckling, gärna i React/Vue.js eller Typescript. Det ses som meriterande (men inte absolut nödvändigt) om du tidigare har arbetat med Azure, azure devops, integrationer, .net web api eller CSS. En högskoleutbildning väger såklart också tungt, men tidigare erfarenhet som motsvarar utbildningen funkar också. 
   Som person tycker du om att kommunicera enkelt, rakt och ärligt med dina kollegor på såväl svenska som engelska i tal och skrift. Du trivs med att jobba i ett team med stark ”tillsammans” känsla och blir gärna en ”doer” under de tekniska diskussionerna tillsammans med ditt team. Under arbetets gång tar du dig tid och förstår vad kunden är ute efter och kan sedan översätta det till användarvänliga lösningar för slutanvändaren. 
   Varför du ska välja Decerno 
   I våra medarbetarundersökningar blir det gång på gång tydligt att det är de fantastiska kollegorna, de roliga och utmanande projekten och möjligheten att kunna bidra till samhällsnytta som gör att vi trivs så bra på Decerno. 
   Sedan finns det också några ytterligare aspekter som vi som arbetsgivare ser som självklarheter: 
   
   En flexibel arbetsplats med större frihet att planera vardagen för att få arbete och privatliv att gå ihop 
   Vi erbjuder extra föräldraförmåner för vi tycker att familjen är viktigast 
   Vi tycker att din kompetensutveckling är viktig! Därför anordnar vi interna utbildningar i vår egen Dec Academy och håller årliga konferenser 
   Vi vill att du ska må bra, trivas och ha roligt på arbetet och därför arrangerar vi regelbundet olika sociala aktiviteter, utmaningar och hälsotävlingar – såväl virtuellt som på plats (i vanliga fall) 
   
  Utöver detta erbjuder vi även ett brett förmånspaket som inkluderar bland annat friskvårdsbidrag och försäkringspaket. Vi berättar gärna mer om du vill veta vad mer vi på Decerno skulle kunna erbjuda dig. 
   Låter detta som ditt nästa steg i karriären? 
   Bra, då vill vi ha in din ansökan så snart som möjligt! 
   Vi välkomnar en mångfald av sökande med olika bakgrund och ser fram emot att få veta mer om dig och hur vi kan bli en del av ditt nästa steg i karriären. 
   På Decerno är vi ca 130 anställda fördelade på mellan vårt virtuella kontor och våra fysiska kontor i Stockholm, Uppsala, Göteborg, Malmö och Sevilla, Spanien. Vi är måna om vår familjära känsla av ett mindre bolag samtidigt som vi sedan 2010 har haft tryggheten av att vara en del av Addnode Group. 
   Vid frågor är du välkommen att kontakta HR-specialist Henny Forsberg på henny.forsberg@decerno.se

YOUR BEET

Looking: for a Tech Lead to join our engineering organization. Your work will impact our first cohorts of active users and several influencers/recipe creators either by working directly on product features or insight tools.

Think of BEET as Spotify meets Digital Personal Nutritionist.
Position:

You will:

Lead the development of our MVP, working closely with our CPO, and continue to build it into a stellar consumer app incorporating user input
Have ownership over the full tech stack
Ensure that our user experience is seamless and the very best it can be

Search
